(681, ' Prepare salad as directed on package except omit oil from dressing and mix in sour cream and red pepper. Stir in chicken. Line serving plate with tortilla chips. Mound salad onto chips; top with tomato and cheese. Garnish with guacamole and sliced ripe olives , if desired. Serves 4.', '1 pkg. Suddenly Salad Italian pasta', '1/4 c. dairy sour cream', '1/8 tsp. ground red pepper', '1 (6 3/4 oz.) can chunk chicken , drained or about 1 c. cut-up , cooked chicken', ' tortilla chips', '1 medium tomato , seeded and chopped', '1/2 c. shredded Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese', ' guacamole (for garnish)', ' sliced ripe olives (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(682, ' In saucepan , cook fresh cauliflower , covered , in boiling water just until crisp-tender. (Or cook the frozen cauliflower according to package directions.) Drain. In another saucepan combine soup , milk , onion , parsley , curry and paprika. Bring mixture to boiling , stirring occasionally. Stir in cream cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts. Remove from heat; stir in cauliflower. Serve over the hot cooked pasta. Sprinkle with almonds and additional parsley , if desired. Makes 6 side dish servings.', '2 c. fresh or frozen cauliflower flowerets', '1 (10 oz.) can condensed cream of celery soup', '1/2 c. milk', '2 Tbsp. chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. snipped parsley', '1 Tbsp. curry powder', '1/4 tsp. paprika', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , cut up', '6 oz. spaghetti , cooked and drained', '1/4 c. sliced almonds', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(683, ' Wash chicken; place in large pot with water and boil. Remove foam that forms. Add salt , pepper , onion , celery and carrots. Cook 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove chicken and shred. Add spinach and already cooked pasta. Add shredded chicken and tomatoes. Cook 1/2 hour longer. More water may be added if necessary. Add cheese , garnish with parsley and serve while hot.', '4 chicken breasts , skinned', '3 qt. water', ' salt to taste', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1 medium chopped onion', '1/2 c. celery , diced', '1 c. carrots , diced', '1 pkg. frozen spinach', '3/4 c. acini de pepe , cooked', '1 small can mashed tomatoes', ' grated Parmesan cheese', '1 Tbsp. parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(684, ' In large skillet heat oil. Saut&eacute; onion , green pepper and garlic until tender , but not brown. Blend in remaining ingredients except pasta. Bring to a boil , then reduce heat and simmer , stirring occasionally for 15 minutes. Meanwhile , cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Serve sauce over hot cooked pasta. Makes 6 servings.', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/3 c. finely chopped green pepper', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '1 2/3 c. crushed tomatoes (15 oz. can)', '1 c. tomato sauce (8 oz. can)', '5 tsp. molasses', '1 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 tsp. prepared mustard', '1/4 tsp. ground red pepper', '1/4 tsp. chili powder', '1/4 tsp. red hot sauce', '1 (12 oz.) pkg. Skinner spaghetti (uncooked) or 1 (12 oz.) pkg. Skinner Lone Star pasta (uncooked)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(685, ' ', '2 (20 oz.) cans Dole chunk pineapple', '16 oz. medium-sized box seashell pasta', '1 large can Mandarin orange slices', '1 red bell pepper , julienne cut', '2 c. thinly sliced carrots', '2 c. frozen peas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(689, ' ', '3 (4 oz.) boneless , skinless chicken breast halves', '3 1/2 c. cooked small macaroni shells (2 c. raw)', '1 c. sweet red pepper strips', '6 to 8 oz. green peas (frozen type , cooked approximately 5 minutes)', '1/4 c. sliced green onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(695, ' Melt butter in roasting pan and brown chicken lightly. Mix all ingredients together except spaghetti and pour over chicken. Roast at 350&deg; for 1 1/2 hours. Cook spaghetti and use the sauce on it. Recipe may be doubled or tripled. Serves two people.', '1 Tbsp. butter', '3 lb. chicken', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 can tomato soup', '1 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '1 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. mustard', '1 tsp. Tabasco sauce', '1 bay leaf', '1/2 tsp. oregano', '1/4 to 1/2 c. water', ' spaghetti', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(700, ' Mix Ricotta cheese , Mozzarella cheese , broccoli (thawed) , about 1/4 cup onion , Parmesan cheese and garlic salt and pepper to taste. Cook shells (about 24) as directed on the box. Put a layer of spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Drain shells and rinse in cold water. Stuff shells with cheese mixture and place on top of the spaghetti sauce (seam side upright). Then spread more sauce on top of shells. Bake at about 350&deg; for 45 minutes to 1 hour. This makes an excellent appetizer , too, Makes about 20 to 25 shells.', '1 c. Ricotta cheese', '1 c. Mozzarella cheese', '1 pkg. frozen chopped broccoli , thawed', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1/4 c. fresh grated Parmesan cheese', ' garlic salt and pepper to taste', ' large jar your favorite spaghetti sauce', '1 pkg. large pasta shells', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(701, ' In a skillet or wok , saut&eacute; onion , celery , pepper , zucchini , broccoli and asparagus in butter until tender-crisp. Do not overcook. Add mushrooms , tomatoes , cheese and spices. Stir until thoroughly heated. Do not overcook. Serve immediately on hot buttered pasta and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese , if desired.', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 stalk celery , chopped', '1 green pepper , chopped', '2 medium zucchini squash , sliced', '4 pieces broccoli', '4 stalks asparagus', ' butter', '6 mushrooms , sliced', '3 tomatoes , quartered', '1/2 c. freshly grated Parmesan cheese', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '10 oz. your favorite pasta (fusilli , angel hair or spaghetti) , cooked and drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(706, ' In large skillet saut&eacute; broccoli , zucchini , red pepper and snow peas in butter until crisp-tender. Add half and half , salt and pepper. Cook briefly until slightly reduced. Serve over pasta; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.', '1 c. small broccoli florets', '1 small zucchini , sliced', '1 small sweet red pepper , cut in strips', '1/2 c. Chinese snow peas', '1/4 c. butter', '1 c. half and half or cream , warmed', ' salt and pepper to taste', '1 lb. spaghetti or other pasta , cooked and drained', ' Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(707, ' Cook pasta. At the same time in large saucepan melt butter over medium heat. Add garlic and saut&eacute; 30 seconds. Add spinach , salt and pepper; saut&eacute; 2 minutes or until spinach is wilted. Transfer pasta to a warm serving bowl. Add spinach , tomatoes and goat cheese; toss well. Makes 4 servings , containing 645 calories each.', '8 oz. spinach pasta', '4 Tbsp. milk', '8 oz. Philadelphia cream cheese', '2 (2 3/4 oz.) pkg. Boursin cheese with garlic and herbs', '2 oz. chopped walnuts', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley or chives', '12 oz. radiatore , ruffles or rotelle pasta', '1/2 c. butter', '1 Tbsp. finely chopped garlic', '1 lb. fresh spinach , well rinsed , trimmed and torn into bite-size pieces', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. freshly ground pepper', '4 plum tomatoes or 2 medium tomatoes , seedless and chopped (about 1 1/2 c.)', '4 oz. goat cheese , crumbled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(709, ' In large pan , cook onion and garlic in oil. Add pasta sauce; simmer 15 minutes. In bowl , mix Ricotta , spinach , 1 cup Mozzarella , Parmesan cheese and eggs. In 15 x 19-inch baking dish , layer 2 cups sauce , half the lasagna , half the remaining sauce , all of the spinach mixture , half the Mozzarella , remaining lasagna and sauce. Cover; bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes or until hot. Uncover and top with remaining Mozzarella. Bake for 15 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes; top with parsley , if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.', '3/4 c. chopped onion', '2 cloves garlic , finely chopped', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '2 (26 oz.) jars Classico pasta sauce (any flavor)', '1 (15 or 16 oz.) container Ricotta cheese', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped spinach , thawed and well drained', '1 lb. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', '1/2 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '2 eggs', '1 (1 lb.) pkg. Creamettes lasagna , cooked and drained', ' parsley (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(710, ' Brown hamburger , sausage , pepper and onion (drain grease). Put 1/2 sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in 1/2 pasta. Add pepperoni. Add mushrooms and 1/2 cheese. Add rest of pasta , then rest of sauce. Add remaining cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.', '1/2 lb. ground beef', '1/2 lb. ground hot sausage', '1 green pepper , diced', '1 onion , diced', '1 1/2 qt. spaghetti sauce', '1 lb. wheels and corkscrews , cooked , or other pasta', '1/2 lb. pepperoni', '1 small can mushroom pieces , drained', '8 oz. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(711, ' In a large skillet or Dutch oven , combine ground beef , onion and garlic. Cook until ground beef is no longer pink; drain if necessary. Stir in next 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes , stirring occasionally. Prepare rigatoni according to package directions; drain. Serve with meat sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 to 6. Refrigerate leftovers.', '1 lb. lean ground beef', '1 medium onion , chopped', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '1 (28 oz.) can whole tomatoes , cut up (undrained)', '1 (16 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 1/2 tsp. Durkee Best Italian seasoning', '1 tsp. sugar', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. (scant) crushed red pepper', '1/2 (1 lb.) pkg. Creamettes rigatoni (uncooked)', ' grated Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(712, ' Drain spinach , squeezing out as much liquid as possible. Combine with beef , egg , bread crumbs , onions and oregano in medium bowl. Mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls. Place in single layer on jelly roll pan. Bake at 425&deg; for 5 minutes. Turn and bake another 5 minutes. Reduce oven to 350&deg;. Remove meatballs and place in shallow 1 quart casserole. Pour sauce over meatballs , cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until meatballs are cooked through and sauce is hot. Serve over pasta , sprinkled with Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 servings.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped spinach , thawed', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 egg , lightly beaten', '1/2 c. Italian style bread crumbs', '1/2 c. finely chopped onions', '1/2 tsp. oregano leaves , crushed', '1 (15 1/2 oz.) jar marinara spaghetti sauce', ' cooked pasta', ' grated Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(713, ' Combine beef , bread , half of onions , salt and pepper. Shape into 1-inch balls. In Dutch oven or large pot , combine remaining onions , sugar , raisins , sauerkraut , gingersnaps and tomato sauce. Add meatballs and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Serve over cooked and drained noodles. Serves 4.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 slice white bread , cubed', '2 medium onions , grated', '1 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '1/2 c. firmly packed brown sugar', '3/4 c. raisins', '3 1/2 c. undrained sauerkraut', '8 gingersnaps', '2 (8 oz. each) cans tomato sauce', '8 oz. egg noodles (rigatoni) , cooked and drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(714, ' Let eggs , cream and butter stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours. In skillet , cook bacon until brown. Remove and drain on paper towel. Beat together eggs and cream just until blended. Toss hot pasta with butter. Pour egg mixture over and toss until pasta is well coated. Add bacon , cheese and parsley. Toss to mix. Season to taste with pepper. Serve at once. Serves 4. The heat from the pasta cooks the eggs.', '4 eggs', '1/4 c. whipped cream', '1/4 c. butter', '1/2 lb. bacon , cut up', '12 oz. hot cooked linguine or other pasta', '1 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '1/4 c. parsley', ' pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(715, ' In Dutch oven heat oil and garlic. Salt and pepper lamb shanks. Brown shanks in oil and garlic; drain excess oil and remove garlic. Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce to lamb shanks. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours , depending on how well cooked you like your veggies. Add strips of onion and green pepper to pot 1/2 hour to 45 minutes before end of cooking time. Also cook pasta at this time. Serve lamb shanks and pour the sauce and veggies over pasta.', '3 or 4 lamb shanks', '2 Tbsp. oil', '1 garlic clove , sliced', '1 (16 oz.) can stewed tomatoes', '1 (8 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 (16 oz.) box pasta (spaghetti of your choice)', '1 large green pepper', '1 large white onion', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(716, ' In large saucepan , brown sausage; pour off fat. Add onion and green pepper; cook and stir until tender. Add pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes , stirring occasionally. Toss hot cooked mostaccioli with oil to coat. Serve with sauce. Garnish as desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.', '1 1/2 lb. link Italian sausage , sliced', '1 c. chopped onion', '3/4 c. chopped green pepper', '2 (26 oz.) jars Classico pasta sauce , any flavor', '1/2 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '1 (1 lb.) pkg. mostaccioli , cooked and drained', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(717, ' In a large heavy pan , brown ground beef in oil with onion , garlic and parsley. Add tomato paste , 2 cups water , salt and pepper; simmer 1 hour. Meanwhile cook lasagna as directed on package. Mix together eggs and Ricotta or cottage cheese. In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan , spread about 1/2 cup sauce , then alternate layers of lasagna , sauce , Ricotta and egg mixture and Mozzarella until baking pan is filled. Top with sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in moderate 375&deg; oven about 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '1 medium onion , minced', '4 cloves garlic , chopped', '1 tsp. chopped parsley', '2 (6 oz.) cans tomato paste', '2 c. water', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '8 oz. lasagna', '2 eggs', '3/4 lb. Ricotta or creamed cottage cheese', '3/4 lb. Mozzarella cheese , sliced', ' Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `ingredients` (`recid`, `method`, `ing1`, `ing2`, `ing3`, `ing4`, `ing5`, `ing6`, `ing7`, `ing8`, `ing9`, `ing10`, `ing11`, `ing12`, `ing13`, `ing14`, `ing15`, `ing16`, `ing17`, `ing18`, `ing19`, `ing20`, `ing21`, `ing22`, `ing23`, `ing24`) VALUES
(718, ' In large skillet , brown beef; drain. Add canned tomatoes and taco seasoning; simmer , uncovered , 5 minutes. Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions. In bowl , combine cottage cheese , 1 cup Cheddar cheese and eggs. Place 3 tortillas on the bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Overlap 6 tortillas around sides of baking dish. Spoon meat mixture evenly in dish. Top with 3 tortillas , then with cheese mixture. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Place remaining onions in center of casserole; bake , uncovered , 5 minutes longer. Before serving , arrange tomato and lettuce around edge of casserole. Makes 6 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 (16 oz.) can whole tomatoes , cut up', '1 (1 1/8 oz.) pkg. Durkee taco seasoning', '1 (2.8 oz.) can Durkee French fried onions', '1 (12 oz.) carton cottage cheese', '1 1/2 c. (6 oz.) shredded Cheddar cheese', '2 eggs , slightly beaten', '12 (6-inch) flour or corn tortillas*', '1 tomato , chopped', ' shredded lettuce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(720, ' In large skillet break up the ground beef. Let beef get brown. Add tomato juice , then add tomato paste. Add chili powder , garlic salt , sugar , oregano and minced onions. Cover and bring to a boil. Cook spaghetti noodles. Serve noodles with sauce. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 (18 oz.) can tomato juice', '1 (6 oz.) can tomato paste', '1 1/2 to 2 tsp. chili powder', '1 tsp. garlic salt', '1 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. sugar', '1 tsp. dried oregano leaves', '2 Tbsp. instant minced onions', '7 oz. spaghetti noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(724, ' Cook noodles according to package directions. Melt butter and stir in flour. Add milk. Cook quickly , stirring constantly , until mixture bubbles and thickens. Stir in horseradish , salt , mustard and pepper. Add thawed peas and the noodles. Turn into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Slice corned beef into 6 slices and arrange over mixture. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes. Serves 5.', '4 oz. medium noodles', '3 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '3 Tbsp. all-purpose flour', '2 1/4 c. milk', '1 Tbsp. prepared horseradish', '2 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. prepared mustard', ' dash of pepper', '10 oz. pkg. frozen peas , thawed', '12 oz. can Libby''s corned beef', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(725, ' saut&eacute; onion and garlic in butter over medium heat. Stir in meat and brown. Add flour , salt , pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes. Combine diluted soup with sour cream. Stir in meat mixture; add parsley and sherry (optional) and simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot , drained egg noodles that have been cooked according to directions on the package. Serves 4 to 6.', '1/2 c. minced onion', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1/4 c. butter', '1 lb. ground beef', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '8 oz. can sliced mushrooms with liquid', '10 1/2 oz. can cream of mushroom soup , diluted with 1 can water', '1 c. sour cream', '2 Tbsp. minced parsley', '1/4 c. sherry (optional)', '12 oz. pkg. egg noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(727, ' Bring water to boil for pasta. In a small bowl , mix pork , 1/2 the salt , pepper flakes and wine and marinate for 5 minutes. Cook pasta al dente. Heat large saut&eacute; pan over high heat. Add oil and pork mixture and stir-fry for 1 minute. Lower heat to medium high; add shallots and saut&eacute; for 1 minute. Add tomatoes and remaining salt and saut&eacute; for 1 minute. Stir in chicken stock and cream and simmer for 1 more minute. Add drained pasta to sauce along with the cheese. Toss and continue to cook until sauce is creamy and cheese is melted. Add parsley and serve directly from the pan.', '1/2 lb. lean pork , cut in 1/4-inch pieces', '2 tsp. sea salt', '1 tsp. hot red pepper flakes', '1/4 c. red wine', '1 pkg. red penne pasta', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 c. thinly sliced shallots', '2 c. crushed tomatoes', '1 c. chicken stock or bouillon', '1 c. heavy cream', '1 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '1/2 c. freshly chopped parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(729, ' Wash and pat shrimp dry. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Saut&eacute; green onions and garlic in oil in a large skillet until tender , about 3 minutes. Stir in chopped tomatoes , wine , salt , pepper , basil and 1 tablespoon parsley. Lower heat; simmer , uncovered , for 15 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly; stir in shrimp and lemon juice; cook over medium heat just until shrimp turn pink and feel firm , about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add cheese and sprinkle with remaining parsley.', '1 1/2 lb. medium shrimp , peeled and deveined', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '6 green onions , chopped', '1 clove garlic , peeled and chopped', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '4 small ripe tomatoes , peeled and chopped', '1/2 c. dry white wine', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. each: pepper and basil', '2 Tbsp. fresh parsley , chopped', '3/4 c. cubed Feta cheese', '1 (16 oz.) pkg. mostaccioli or other short pasta', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(731, ' In large skillet heat corn oil over medium high heat. Add shrimp and garlic; saut&eacute; 2 minutes or until pink. Remove from heat. Stir in wine , vinegar , mustard , salt and pepper. In large bowl , combine shrimp , pasta , artichokes , peppers , olives and green onions. Toss gently to coat. Cover; chill at least 1 hour.', '1/3 c. corn oil', '1 lb. shrimp , shelled and deveined', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '1/4 c. dry white wine or vermouth', '2 Tbsp. vinegar', '2 Tbsp. Dijon mustard', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '6 oz. pasta , cooked and drained', '1 (14 oz.) can artichoke hearts , drained and cut in eighths', '1/2 c. thinly sliced roasted red peppers', '1/2 c. sliced pitted ripe olives', '1/2 c. sliced green onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(732, ' Cook pasta until just tender; drain and rinse with cold water. Stir together egg , crabmeat , shrimp , Cheddar cheese , tomato , chives and pepper. Fill shells with mixture. Mix egg with water. Dip each filled shell into egg mixture , then in crumbs. Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Fry , a few at a time , in deep hot 365&deg; oil until golden. Serve with tartar sauce. Makes 16.', '1 box jumbo pasta shells', '1 beaten egg', '1 (6 oz.) can crabmeat , drained and flaked', '1 small can tiny shrimp', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 chopped tomato , peeled and seeded', '2 Tbsp. chopped chives', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 beaten egg', '1 Tbsp. water', '2/3 c. fine dry bread crumbs', ' oil for deep frying', ' tartar sauce (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(733, ' Cook noodles according to package directions. In frying pan over medium heat , place margarine and oil. When margarine is melted , add green onions , garlic and tomatoes. Cook , stirring until mixture boils. Adjust heat so mixture boils gently and cook for 2 minutes. Mix in lemon juice , crab and parsley. Cook just until crab is heated. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon sauce over pasta. Lift and mix pasta gently. Makes 4 servings.', '8 oz. angel hair pasta', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '1/4 c. oil', '1/2 c. sliced green onions', '1 clove garlic , minced', '2 medium-sized tomatoes , peeled and chopped', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/2 lb. cooked crab', '1 Tbsp. parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(734, ' Boil fettucini as per instructions on box. Melt butter in skillet. Lightly saut&eacute; scallops and shrimp in skillet and add Old Bay to taste. Divide fettucini onto 2 platters and top with grated Mozzarella , shrimp and scallops; use pimento pieces for garnish. Hurry into preheated oven until cheese is melted. Bon appetit,,', '3/4 lb. fettucini pasta', '2 Tbsp. butter', '3/4 lb. scallops (sea or bay)', '3/4 lb. shrimp , shelled and deveined', ' Old Bay seasoning to taste', '1 c. grated Mozzarella cheese', ' several pieces diced pimento', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(735, ' Prepare rotini according to instructions and drain. In medium skillet , melt butter. Add mixed vegetables and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender and garlic is golden.', '1/2 lb. rotini (uncooked)', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen mixed vegetables , thawed', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can Campbell''s cream of mushroom soup', '3/4 c. milk', '1 1/2 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1/8 tsp. pepper', ' dash of ground nutmeg', '1 (7 oz.) can tuna or salmon , drained and flaked', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(737, ' Chop 5 vegetables. Melt oleo in skillet and add vegetables; saut&eacute;. Add cheese until it melts. Blend flour into mixture. Add half and half. Stir in crawfish tails; stir well. Add parsley and Tony Chachere seasoning. Cook pasta according to directions and drain. Add to crawfish mixture. Put in large casserole. Top with Parmesan cheese. This may be made the day before serving , or frozen a week before. Serves 12.', '2 medium onions', '3 green shallots', '1 bell pepper', '2 ribs celery', '3 cloves garlic', '1 stick oleo', '2 rolls jalapeno cheese', '3 Tbsp. flour', '1 pt. half and half', '2 lb. crawfish tails', '2 Tbsp. parsley', '1 tsp. Tony Chachere Cajun seasoning', '1 lb. angel hair pasta', '3 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
