(809, ' Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan and heat until blended and smooth. Pour on chicken and baste.', '1 (8 oz.) can jellied cranberry sauce', '1 (8 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(814, ' ', '4 Rock Cornish hens', ' salt and pepper to taste', '4 Tbsp. tarragon leaves', ' garlic salt to taste', '1 stalk celery , diced', '1 medium onion , diced', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can chicken broth', '2 Tbsp. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(820, ' Season squab with salt. Brown squab , skin side down , in butter in skillet. Turn , cover and simmer about 35 minutes or until tender. Remove to warm platter. Combine broth , apricot nectar and cornstarch. Add to pan drippings. Simmer and stir until sauce thickens slightly and bubbles. Pour over birds. Serves 4.', '4 (12 to 14 oz.) ready to cook squab , split in halves lengthwise', ' salt to taste', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '1/2 c. chicken broth', '1/2 c. apricot nectar', '2 tsp. cornstarch', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(822, ' Combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt in paper or plastic bag. Add 2 or 3 pieces partridge at a time and shake to coat. Brown partridge pieces in butter in Dutch oven. Add onion and beef broth. Cook , covered , over low heat 50 to 60 minutes or until tender. Remove birds to warm serving dish. Add wine to Dutch oven and simmer 5 minutes , stirring and scraping brown bits from bottom of pan. Pour sauce over partridge. Makes 2 or 3 servings.', '1/2 c. all-purpose flour', '1 tsp. salt', '2 (1 lb.) ready to cook partridges , cut up', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '2 Tbsp. finely chopped onion', '1 (10 1/2 oz.) can condensed beef broth', '3/4 c. Claret or red Burgundy', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(823, ' Line 6 to 8-quart baking dish with pastry. Season hens with salt and pepper. Put 1 tablespoon butter in each cavity and fit into dish. Surround with pieces of steak and a combination of two of the artichokes , bamboo shoots , mushrooms or chestnut pieces. Sprinkle with egg yolks. Add water or broth. Seal top with pastry. Cut slits in pastry. Bake at 350&deg; for 1 1/2 hours.', ' pastry for 2-crust pie , unbaked', '2 Rock Cornish hens', ' salt and pepper to taste', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 1/2 lb. steak , cut in 1 to 3-inch strips', ' two of the following: artichoke pieces , mushrooms , bamboo shoots or water chestnuts', '2 hard-boiled egg yolks', '2 c. water or chicken broth', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(825, ' About 45 minutes before serving , preheat oven to 350&deg;. In Dutch oven over medium heat , in hot butter or margarine , cook quail until browned on both sides. Remove quail to platter. To drippings in the Dutch oven , add onion and mushrooms; cook , stirring occasionally , until onion is tender , about 5 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and salt. Add quail to mixture , cover and bake 20 minutes or until quail is tender.', '1/3 c. butter or margarine', '4 ready to cook quail', '1 small onion , chopped', '1/2 lb. mushrooms , sliced', '1 c. chicken broth', '1 1/4 tsp. salt', ' toast points', '2 Tbsp. all-purpose flour', '3 Tbsp. Sauterne (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(826, ' Simmer for 45 minutes and debone (leave quail whole). Place meat in baking dish; salt and pepper to taste. Stuff quail with favorite dressing if desired. (I use sausage and bread crumbs moistened with chicken stock.) Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream and spread over meat. Melt butter and drizzle over sauce. Crush Ritz crackers; sprinkle over sauce. Add poppy or sesame seed over all. If desired , white wine or sherry may be added to sauce initially. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes.', '2 pheasants or 1 chicken or 8 quail', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' dressing', '2 cans cream of chicken soup', '6 oz. sour cream', '1/2 stick butter', '24 Ritz crackers', ' poppy or sesame seed', ' sherry or white wine to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(827, ' Combine butter and boiling water. Stir until butter melts , then pour over stuffing crumbs and toss lightly. Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions. Spoon mixture into 9-inch shallow buttered baking dish (1 1/2-quart). Press stuffing in bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell. Combine soup , milk , turkey and peas. Pour into stuffing shell. Bake , covered , at 350&deg; for 30 minutes. Uncover and top with remaining onions. Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1/2 c. (1 stick) butter or margarine', '1 1/4 c. boiling water', '3 1/2 c. seasoned stuffing crumbs', '1 (2.8 oz.) can French fried onions', '1 can cream of celery soup', '3/4 c. milk', '1 1/2 c. cubed , cooked turkey', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen peas , thawed , rinsed in cold water and drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(829, ' Combine chicken broth , tomato sauce and dried whole oregano in a small bowl. Stir well and set aside. Combine turkey , parsley , poultry seasoning , pepper and garlic in a medium bowl. Stir until well blended. Divide mixture into 4 equal portions shaping each into a 1/2 inch thick oval patty. Sprinkle breadcrumbs on a sheet of wax paper. Press patties in breadcrumbs , lightly coating each side. Place patties in a shallow baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 450&deg; for 8 minutes; drain. Turn patties over and spoon tomato mixture evenly over patties. Bake an additional 8 minutes or until sauce is bubbly. Sprinkle patties with cheese and bake 1 additional minute or until cheese is melted. Garnish with parsley.', '1/4 c. no-salt-added chicken broth', '1 (8 oz.) can no salt added tomato sauce', '1/2 tsp. dried whole oregano', '1 (1 lb.) pkg. frozen raw ground turkey , thawed', '1/4 c. minced fresh parsley', '1/4 tsp. poultry seasoning', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1/3 c. Italian seasoned breadcrumbs', '1/2 c. (2 oz.) shredded part-skim Mozzarella cheese', ' parsley sprigs (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(830, ' Preheat oven to 375&deg;. Spray two 1 3/4-cup casseroles with nonstick cooking spray; set aside. In 1-quart saucepan , heat margarine until bubbly and hot. Add vegetables , stirring to coat with margarine. Cover pan and cook over medium heat , until veggies are tender. Sprinkle veggies with flour and broth mixture and stir quickly to combine. Cook uncovered for 1 minute. Gradually stir in water and , stirring constantly , bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook , stirring until mixture thickens. Add turkey and seasoning mix and stir to combine. Pour half of mixture into each sprayed casserole. Top each portion with 6 biscuit wedges and bake until thoroughly heated and &quot;dumplings&quot; are browned , 10 to 15 minutes.', '1 Tbsp. margarine (diet)', '1/2 c. each: diced onion and celery', '1 c. each: thinly sliced carrots and mushrooms', '1 Tbsp. plus 1 tsp. all-purpose flour', '2 packets instant chicken broth and seasoning mix', '1 1/3 c. water', '8 oz. skinned and boned cooked turkey , diced', '1/8 tsp. each: poultry seasoning and pepper', '2 ready to bake refrigerated buttermilk flaky biscuits , cut into 6 wedges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(832, ' Saut&eacute; onion and green pepper in melted oleo. Stir in mushrooms , pimento , soup , milk and basil. Heat. Arrange 1/2 of noodles in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Layer 1/2 sauce , cottage cheese , turkey and Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes.', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '3 Tbsp. oleo', '4 oz. can mushrooms', '1/4 c. pimento (optional)', '10 oz. can cream of mushroom soup', '1/3 c. milk', '1/2 tsp. basil', '8 oz. lasagna noodles , cooked', '1 1/2 c. small curd cottage cheese', '3 c. cooked turkey', '2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(835, ' Prepare grill or heat broiler , if directed by manufacturer. Cut turkey into 1-inch cubes. In glass bowl combine juice , oil , molasses and herbs and other seasonings; add turkey. Stir to completely coat turkey; let stand about 15 minutes. Prepare bell pepper and fruit as directed. Arrange turkey , bell pepper and fruit alternately on 8 separate skewers. Grill or broil kabobs about 5-inches from heat source for about 15 to 20 minutes , turning once and basting with marinade left in bowl. Serve warm. Makes 4 servings; contains 216 calories per serving.', '12 oz. fresh , uncooked turkey breasts', '1/4 c. lime or lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 Tbsp. molasses or honey', '1 tsp. fresh thyme or rosemary leaves', '1/4 tsp. salt (optional)', '1/8 tsp. cayenne or white pepper', '1/8 tsp. garlic powder', '1 green bell pepper , seeded and cut into 8 chunks', '2 small plums , halved', '2 (1-inch) thick slices fresh pineapple with rind , cut into 4 wedges', '1 orange , cut into 4 wedges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(836, ' Saut&eacute; onion in margarine. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook , stirring constantly , until thickened. Add turkey , broccoli and 1/2 cup of the cheese. Mix well. Spoon into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Separate crescent dough into one large and two small rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal. Cut large rectangle lengthwise into fourths , forming four 12-inch strips. Cut remaining rectangles lengthwise into thirds , forming six 8-inch strips. Place dough strips over turkey mixture in lattice design. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350&deg; for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Makes 8 to 10 servings.', '1/3 c. chopped onion', '1/4 c. margarine', '1/3 c. flour', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '2 c. milk', '4 c. chopped , cooked turkey or chicken', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped broccoli , partially thawed', '3/4 c. (3 oz.) grated Parmesan cheese', '1 (8 oz.) can refrigerated quick crescent dinner rolls', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(837, ' Combine salad dressing mix , flour , salt , lemon juice and butter into a paste and coat chicken evenly. Stack pieces in a bowl; cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. About 1 hour before serving , heat about 1 1/2 pints cooking oil in heavy 9-inch saucepan. Put 2 cups milk or club soda in bowl and dip each piece of chicken in the liquid. Combine pancake mix , paprika , sage and pepper. Dust chicken with pancake mix. Dry pieces a few minutes without letting them touch. Fry a few pieces at a time 5 to 6 minutes. Place fried chicken on cookie sheet or shallow pan. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 30 minutes.', '3 lb. chicken parts , cut into small pieces', '2 (0.6 oz.) pkg. Italian salad dressing mix', '3 Tbsp. flour', '2 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. butter (at room temperature)', '3 c. (24 oz.) vegetable oil (for frying)', '2 c. milk or club soda', '1 1/2 c. pancake mix', '1 tsp. paprika', '1/2 tsp. sage', '1/4 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
