(838, ' In medium bowl , combine chicken , soy sauce and sherry; set aside. In a 12-inch skillet or wok , stir-fry cashews in hot oil over high heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until browned. Lift out with a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the chicken mixture to the skillet. Stir-fry over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until just done. Stir in hoisin sauce and cashews. If desired , sprinkle with sliced green onion. Serve at once with hot cooked rice. Makes 4 or 5 servings.', '2 whole medium chicken breasts , skinned , boned and cut in 1/2-inch cubes', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1 Tbsp. plus 1/2 tsp. dry sherry', '1 c. raw cashew nuts', '2 Tbsp. cooking oil', '1 Tbsp. hoisin sauce', ' sliced green onion (optional)', ' hot cooked rice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(839, ' Wash and dry chicken parts. Place crumbs in large bowl. Add cheese and parsley and combine well. Melt butter. Add garlic after melting and simmer a few minutes to absorb flavor. Remove from heat. Add Worcestershire sauce , mustard and white pepper. Mix well. When cool enough to handle , dip chicken pieces in butter mixture , then roll in bread crumb mixture. Place in single layer on cookie sheet. Pour any remaining butter mixture over chicken. Bake in 350&deg; oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overbake.', '8 chicken breast halves', '3 c. bread crumbs', '1 c. Parmesan cheese', '1/4 c. chopped fresh parsley', '1 c. melted butter', '2 large cloves garlic , minced', '2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '2 Tbsp. Dijon mustard', '1/8 tsp. white pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(840, ' Place chicken parts in a large deep skillet. Add m.s.g. , garlic , onion , green pepper , tomato sauce , bay leaves , cumin , oregano , raisins , olives and vinegar. Cover and bring to a boil. Turn heat down and simmer 1 hour , turning chicken occasionally. Remove chicken to a platter and serve the sauce over rice or noodles.', '4 to 5 lb. skinned fryer chicken parts', '1 tsp. m.s.g.', '5 cloves minced garlic', '1 onion , chopped', '1/2 chopped green bell pepper', '2 (15 oz.) cans tomato sauce', '4 bay leaves', '1 tsp. cumin seed', '1 1/2 tsp. dried leaf oregano', '1 c. raisins', '1 c. stuffed green olives', '1 tsp. cider vinegar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(841, ' Mix all ingredients in roasting pan. (You can mix all the liquid ingredients and spices and then pour over chicken , mushrooms , artichoke hearts and onion.) Bake at 325&deg; , uncovered , at least 1 1/2 hours , stirring a couple of times. Serve over rice.', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '1/2 cube butter , melted', '1 (8 oz.) sour cream', ' salt and pepper to taste', '6 chicken breasts , skinned and deboned', '1 lb. mushrooms', '1 can artichoke hearts (plain) , drained', '1 white onion , diced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(842, ' Make cream sauce with margarine , flour and milk. Add cheese , soy sauce , salt and pepper; stir until cheese melts. Combine rice , chicken , water chestnuts , mushrooms and celery. Place alternate layers of chicken-rice mixture and sauce mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange noodles around edge of casserole and bake in 350&deg; oven for 25 to 30 minutes.', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 1/2 c. milk', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. Cheddar cheese', '1 tsp. soy sauce', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '2 c. cooked rice', '3 c. diced cooked chicken', '1 small can water chestnuts , sliced', '1 (3 oz.) can sliced mushrooms', '1 c. sliced celery', '1 (3 oz.) can chow mein noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(843, ' Heat 4 tablespoons oil; add onion , celery and bread crumbs. Cook until celery is glazed and crumbs brown. Add seasonings; remove from heat. Add egg. Place 2 tablespoons of filling on flattened chicken. Roll up from wide end , folding in to hold filling. Put in greased pan; add wine. Use 2 tablespoons oil with wine to bake. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 45 to 60 minutes.', '6 Tbsp. butter or oil , divided', '1 medium onion , chopped', '2 Tbsp. chopped celery', '1 3/4 c. coarse bread crumbs', '1/8 tsp. nutmeg', '1/2 c. parsley', '1/2 tsp. lemon peel', '1/2 tsp. salt (optional)', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1/2 tsp. paprika', '1 egg , beaten', '4 whole chicken legs , boned and pounded', '1/2 c. sherry wine', '2 Tbsp. oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(844, ' Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece. Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper. Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden picks. Dip each chicken breast in egg; coat well with bread crumbs. Melt butter in a heavy skillet; brown chicken on all sides. Remove chicken to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish , reserving drippings in skillet. Add remaining ingredients to reserved drippings and stir well. Pour sauce over chicken. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 40 to 45 minutes.', '8 (1 oz.) slices cooked ham', '8 (1 oz.) slices Swiss cheese', '8 boneless chicken breasts', '3 Tbsp. minced parsley', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 egg , beaten', '1/2 c. Italian bread crumbs', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '1 can cream of celery soup', '8 oz. sour cream', '1/3 c. dry sherry', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(845, ' Saut&eacute; onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender. Stir in chicken , 1 can cream of chicken soup , sour cream , mushrooms , green chilies , almonds , oregano , salt and pepper , mixing well. Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over tortillas. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 35 minutes.', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '3 c. chopped , cooked chicken', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of chicken soup', '1 (8 oz.) carton sour cream', '1 (4.5 oz.) jar sliced , drained mushrooms', '1 (4 oz.) can chopped green chilies', '1/2 c. toasted , sliced almonds', '1/2 tsp. dried whole oregano', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '10 (7-inch) flour tortillas', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of chicken soup', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1/2 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(846, ' Cook broccoli in boiling salted water; drain. Melt butter; blend in flour. Add chicken broth , stirring until thick. Stir in cream , sherry , salt and pepper. Place broccoli crosswise in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour 1/2 the sauce over broccoli; top with chicken slices. Add Parmesan cheese to remaining sauce; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes or until heated through. Broil until sauce is golden.', '2 bunches fresh broccoli or 2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen broccoli', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '1/4 c. flour', '2 c. chicken broth', '1/2 c. light cream', '3 Tbsp. sherry wine', '1/2 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '3 whole chicken breasts , cooked , boned and thinly sliced', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(847, ' ', '1 chicken', '1 can peas and carrots', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '4 boiled eggs', '1/2 c. diced celery', '1/2 c. canned milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(848, ' On the day before the casserole is to be served , mix all items together except the cashews. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and refrigerate. Before baking , cover top with cashews. Bake 45 minutes at 350&deg;.', '3 large chicken breasts , cooked and cut up', '2 cans condensed cream of chicken soup', '1 (15 oz.) can fancy Oriental vegetables , drained', '1 Tbsp. chopped onion', '1/2 lb. sliced mushrooms', '1 c. chopped celery', '1/2 c. mayonnaise', '1 (5 or 6 oz.) can water chestnuts , sliced and drained', '1 tsp. lemon juice', '1 (3 oz.) can chow mein noodles', '2 to 3 c. cashews', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(850, ' With meat mallet or dull edge of French knife , pound each chicken breast half to 1/4-inch thickness. Place bread crumbs in pie plate. Moisten chicken pieces with water , then dip into bread crumbs to coat evenly. In a 12-inch skillet , over medium-high heat , add 3 tablespoons hot oil. Cook chicken a few pieces at a time until golden brown on both sides , about 2 minutes. Add more oil if necessary. Slice Mozzarella cheese lengthwise into 8 slices. Alternate chicken and cheese , overlapping slightly in baking dish. Spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes.', '4 whole large chicken breasts , boned and skinned , each cut in half', '1 1/2 c. dried bread crumbs', ' olive oil or salad oil', '1 (18 oz.) pkg. Mozzarella cheese', '1 (15 to 15 1/2 oz.) jar spaghetti sauce', ' Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(851, ' Preheat oven to 375&deg;. Pound chicken breasts; add seasonings to taste. Cut bottoms off the asparagus , leaving them about 6 inches long (most tender part). Lay breasts flat , then put 3 or 4 spears side by side in the center of each breast. Spread 1/2 tablespoon margarine across the spears in each breast. Fold chicken over like a jacket (overlap).', '6 whole chicken breasts (boneless)', ' chicken seasonings', '1 lb. fresh asparagus', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 large can Campbell''s chunky cream of mushroom soup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(852, ' Fry 6 strips of bacon in 3 tablespoons oil until crisp in large Dutch oven. Remove bacon and crumble; set aside. Meanwhile , cut up uncooked chicken into bite-size pieces or leave as breasts , legs , etc. , but remove skin. Combine flour , garlic salt , salt and pepper in bag. Add chicken to bag and shake. In bacon grease , cook onion , then add chicken and flour. Stir and let chicken brown for about 10 minutes. Add carrots , water , bouillon , wine and crumbled bacon , stirring frequently. Bring to boil , then simmer , covered , until carrots are tender , 30 to 45 minutes. Stir frequently. It should thicken on its own. Serve over rice.', '6 strips bacon', '3 Tbsp. oil', '1 whole fryer chicken , cut up or 4 boneless breasts , cut into bite size pieces', '1 c. flour', ' garlic salt to taste', ' salt to taste', ' pepper to taste', '1/2 medium onion , diced', '6 to 8 carrots , cut into sticks', '3 c. hot water', '2 Tbsp. chicken bouillon crystals', '2 c. wine (white , red or Rose)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(853, ' Rinse chickens with water and dry. Sprinkle with salt , pepper and enough flour to stick lightly. In large skillet or electric frying pan , brown half the chicken at a time in hot oil. Remove from skillet. Add onions and curry to oil left in skillet and cook only until tender , not brown. Add chopped apples , tomato juice plus water , raisins , 1/2 teaspoon salt , sugar and soup. Return chicken to skillet. Cook , covered , on low heat for about 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to serving platter. Serve sauce left in pan over chicken and rice. Serves 8. May be served with condiments such as chopped peanuts , coconut , crumbled cooked bacon , sieved hard-cooked egg , finely chopped onion or chives.', '2 (2 1/2 to 3 lb.) broiler-fryers , cut up', ' salt and pepper', ' flour (for light dredging)', '1/4 c. cooking oil', '1/2 c. onions , chopped', '2 Tbsp. curry powder', '3 medium sized apples , peeled and chopped into small pieces', '3/4 c. tomato juice plus 1/4 c. water', '1/4 c. raisins', '1/2 tsp. salt', '3/4 c. sugar', '1 can condensed cream of celery soup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(854, ' Soak chicken in buttermilk for 1 1/2 hours; remove and drain. Mix flour , salt , pepper and garlic. Thoroughly coat chicken with mixture and allow to sit for 20 minutes. Heat vegetable oil to 375&deg; and fry chicken.', '8 chicken breasts (skinless; 4 oz. raw weight)', '40 oz. buttermilk', '1 c. flour (self-rising)', '1 Tbsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. cayenne pepper', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '3/4 c. butter', '1/2 c. honey', '2 Tbsp. dark brown sugar', '1/2 c. pecans (10% halves , 90% pieces)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(855, ' In a 9 or 10-inch skillet , heat oil. Add onion and garlic and saut&eacute; until onion is translucent , about 5 minutes. Add tomato , tomato sauce and seasonings. Cook , stirring occasionally , for about 5 minutes. Add chicken and cook until heated through. Divide chicken mixture into taco shells , then top with cheese and lettuce.', '2 tsp. vegetable oil', '1/2 c. sliced onion', '2 garlic cloves , minced', '1 medium tomato , chopped', '1/2 c. tomato sauce', ' dash of hot sauce', ' dash of oregano leaves', ' dash of salt', ' dash of pepper', '4 oz. skinned , boned and cooked chicken , diced', '2 taco shells', '1 oz. Cheddar cheese , shredded', ' lettuce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(856, ' Remove skin from chicken pieces. Lightly salt chicken. Preheat oven to 400&deg;. In oven , melt 2 tablespoons butter and shortening in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. In 2-quart plastic bag , combine flour , salt , pepper and paprika. Shake chicken pieces to coat them well. In medium bowl , beat together eggs with milk. Dip flour coated chicken in egg mixture. In another 2-quart plastic bag , combine cheese and bread crumbs. Shake chicken pieces in cheese mixture to coat well. Place chicken bone side down in melted butter and shortening in jelly roll pan. Drizzle 1/4 cup butter over chicken pieces and bake in preheated oven at 400&deg; for 1 hour. Serve hot or cold. Serves 8 to 10.', '5 lb. meaty broiler-fryer chicken pieces', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '2 Tbsp. vegetable shortening', '1 c. flour', '2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '2 tsp. paprika', '2 eggs , slightly beaten', '3 Tbsp. milk', '1 1/3 c. Parmesan cheese , grated', '2/3 c. dry bread crumbs', '1/4 c. butter or margarine , melted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
