(973, ' Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat. Add onion and leek; saut&eacute; , stirring often , until soft , about 8 minutes. Stir in pumpkin , chicken broth and spices. Bring to a boil , stirring; reduce the heat and simmer , uncovered , for 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf. Process in blender or food processor in batches. (May be refrigerated for 2 days or frozen , puree only.)', '4 Tbsp. unsalted butter', '1 large (8 oz.) onion , chopped', '1 medium leek (white part only) , cleaned and chopped', '1 lb. pumpkin puree (canned or fresh)', '4 c. chicken broth', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. curry powder', '1/4 tsp. nutmeg', '1/4 tsp. white pepper', '1/4 tsp. ginger', '1 bay leaf', '1 c. half and half', ' chopped chives (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(975, ' Melt butter in pot and add onion. Saut&eacute; for five minutes. Add carrots and curry powder. Cover and cook 20 minutes more. Remove skin on tomatoes by dipping in boiling water for 30 seconds , then chop coarsely; add tomatoes and chicken broth to saucepan with vegetables. Bring to boil , lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Add 2 tablespoons basil , salt and pepper; simmer 1 minute. Transfer soup to blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Stir in remaining basil. Serve cold or hot topped with a dollop of sour cream. Makes 2 to 4 servings.', '2 Tbsp. unsalted butter', '1 yellow onion , peeled and chopped', '1/2 lb. carrots , peeled and chopped', '1 tsp. curry powder', '7 large ripe plum tomatoes', '3 1/2 c. chicken broth', '6 Tbsp. slivered basil leaves', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' sour cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(976, ' Brown rice lightly in lard. Add onions , garlic and tomatoes. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add 3 cups of broth. Cover and simmer on top of range 25 to 30 minutes or bake in covered casserole in 350&deg; oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Garnish with chiles , parsley and olives. Use leftover broth , if you want a more moist rice.', '2 c. uncooked rice', '6 Tbsp. lard', '2 small onions , finely chopped', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '4 medium sized tomatoes , peeled and chopped or 1 c. tomato puree', '4 c. regular strength beef or chicken broth', '2 or 3 canned green chile slices , chopped', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley', '1 c. pimiento-stuffed green olives', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(981, ' Melt butter; add onion and celery and cook over low heat until tender. Add flour , seasonings and condiment sauce; blend. Stir in milk and cook over low heat until smooth and thickened. Add bouillon cubes and stir to dissolve. Stir in blanched almonds. Turn into hot soup bowls and sprinkle with almonds. Serves 6.', '3 Tbsp. butter', '1/2 c. finely diced onion', '1 c. finely diced celery', '4 Tbsp. flour', '2 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1/2 tsp. condiment sauce', '4 c. milk', '2 chicken bouillon cubes', '1/2 c. blanched chopped almonds', ' slivered , toasted almonds (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(982, ' Saut&eacute; onion , celery or green pepper and cumin seed in oil until tender. Stir in flour and saut&eacute; briefly. Add vegetable stock and cook , stirring , until it thickens slightly. Add milk.', '1 medium onion , finely chopped', '1/2 c. chopped celery or green pepper', '1/2 tsp. ground cumin seed', '1 Tbsp. oil', '1 Tbsp. whole wheat flour', '2 c. vegetable stock', '1 c. skim milk', '1 c. lightly toasted cashews', ' dash of hot sauce (optional)', '1 tsp. salt', ' generous grind of fresh black pepper', '1/2 c. fresh or frozen peas', '1/4 c. thinly sliced scallions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(983, ' Cook onions in 3 tablespoons butter until wilted , 5 to 10 minutes. Add broth , rice and broccoli and cover. Simmer over low heat until tender , 10 to 20 minutes. Puree soup; add cream and reheat. May serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top or chopped dill and butter.', '1 c. chopped white onions', '3 Tbsp. butter', '4 c. chicken broth', '1/2 c. rice , uncooked', '3/4 lb. broccoli (1 1/2 bunches)', '1 c. lite cream*', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(984, ' In a medium saucepan cook onion , carrots and celery in butter or margarine until tender. Stir in flour , paprika , dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce until blended. Add chicken broth and milk. Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir in liquid smoke. Reduce heat to very low , then stir in cheese. Simmer 10 minutes. Ladle soup in bowls; top soup with chopped chilies and 4 or 5 tortilla chips. Makes 4 servings.', '1/2 c. finely chopped onion', '1/2 c. shredded carrots', '1/2 c. thinly sliced celery', '1/3 c. butter or margarine', '1/3 c. flour', '1 tsp. paprika', '1 tsp. dry mustard', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 (14 1/2 oz.) can chicken broth', '1 c. milk', '1/2 tsp. liquid smoke', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', ' canned chopped green chilies', ' tortilla chips (nacho cheese)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(985, ' In hot butter in 3-quart saucepan cook carrots , onion and potatoes , covered and stirring occasionally , about 25 minutes or until tender. (Put carrots in first). Add peas and remove from heat; stir in flour and mix well. Cook 1 minute , stirring occasionally. Add chicken broth. Bring to boil , stirring constantly. Gradually stir in cheese; cook over medium heat until cheese has melted. Gradually add milk. Season. Bring to boil , but do not boil. Serve with croutons.', '8 Tbsp. butter', '1 c. pared , diced carrots', '1/4 c. finely chopped onion', '1 c. diced potatoes', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen peas', '5 Tbsp. flour', '1 (10 oz.) can chicken broth', '4 c. grated Cheddar cheese', '2 c. milk', '1/4 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', ' croutons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(986, ' In 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add onion , celery and carrot and saut&eacute; until vegetables are tender. Sprinkle vegetables with flour and stir quickly to combine; gradually stir in water. Add broth mix and , stirring constantly , bring to a boil. Add asparagus and cook , stirring , for about 3 minutes; add milk and cheese and continue stirring and cooking until cheese melts. Reduce heat to low , add remaining ingredients , and cook until thoroughly heated.', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/2 c. chopped celery', '1/2 c. chopped carrot', '2 tsp. all purpose flour', '1 c. water', '1 pkg. instant chicken broth and seasoning mix', '1/2 c. frozen asparagus cuts and tips', '1/2 c. skim milk', '2 oz. Cheddar cheese , shredded', '4 oz. skinned and boned cooked chicken , diced', '1 c. cooked small macaroni (shells , tubetti or elbows)', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', ' dashes of salt and white pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(989, ' Peel , seed and coarsely chop apples and squash. Coarsely chop onion. Combine first 10 ingredients in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered 45 minutes. Cool soup a bit , then puree in blender. Return soup to saucepan and bring to a boil. Add cream and , if desired , sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serves 6.', '1 small butternut squash (2 lb.)', '3 tart apples', '1 medium onion', '1/4 tsp. rosemary', '1/4 tsp. marjoram', '3 cans chicken broth', '2 cans water', '2 slices white bread', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1/4 c. heavy cream', ' chopped parsley (optional garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(991, ' Saut&eacute; onion in oleo. Add celery , chicken broth and sliced carrots. Cook until carrots are tender. Put all in blender. Blend until pureed. Add milk and nutmeg. Heat and serve.', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. oleo', '1/2 c. chopped celery', '2 c. chicken broth', '2 c. sliced carrots', '1 c. milk', '1/4 tsp. nutmeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(992, ' Saut&eacute; celery and onions in margarine. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add broth and milk. Cook , stirring constantly until thickened. Add cauliflower and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted.', '2 c. chopped celery', '3/4 c. onion slices', '6 Tbsp. margarine', '1/3 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '4 1/2 c. chicken broth', '3 c. milk', '3 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen cauliflower , cooked , drained and chopped', '2 c. shredded Monterey Jack cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `ingredients` (`recid`, `method`, `ing1`, `ing2`, `ing3`, `ing4`, `ing5`, `ing6`, `ing7`, `ing8`, `ing9`, `ing10`, `ing11`, `ing12`, `ing13`, `ing14`, `ing15`, `ing16`, `ing17`, `ing18`, `ing19`, `ing20`, `ing21`, `ing22`, `ing23`, `ing24`) VALUES
(993, ' In saucepan , cook apple , coconut and onion with curry in butter until tender. Add soup; pour into blender and blend until smooth. Return mixture to saucepan; gradually stir in milk and yogurt. Heat and stir occasionally. Garnish with sliced apple. Makes about 3 cups or 4 servings.', '1 1/2 c. diced apple', '2 Tbsp. flaked coconut', '2 Tbsp. chopped onion', '1 1/2 tsp. curry powder (or less)', '2 Tbsp. butter or oleo', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '1/2 soup can milk', '1/4 c. plain yogurt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(994, ' Peel and seed avocados and cucumbers. Blend avocados with 1 cup of broth until smooth in food processor or blender. Stir in lime juice. Set aside. Blend cucumbers , remaining 1 cup of broth and chilies until smooth. Combine with avocado mixture. Stir in cream and salt to taste. Serve very cold. Garnish with chives , if desired. Serves 4.', '2 large ripe avocados', '2 large cucumbers', '2 c. chicken broth', ' juice of 2 limes', '1/4 c. diced green chilies', '1 c. (1/2 pt.) heavy cream', ' salt to taste', ' chopped chives (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(995, ' In large saucepan , melt butter; add onions , bay leaf and thyme. Cook until onions are translucent. Add potatoes , broth and pepper. Boil until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf. With slotted spoon , remove about 2 cups of the potatoes and onions to a bowl. Puree remaining soup in a blender and return to saucepan. Stir in milk and the reserved potatoes and onions. Season with salt and heat just to boiling. Garnish with green onions , if desired.', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 bay leaf', '1/2 tsp. dried thyme', '4 c. cubed potatoes', '2 cans chicken broth', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 c. milk', '1/2 tsp. salt', ' sliced green onions (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(997, ' In a 4-quart electric crock-pot , stir together first 13 ingredients. Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours. If necessary , skim off fat before serving. Sprinkle each serving with bacon and eggs. Makes 6 to 8 servings.', '4 c. chicken broth', '3/4 lb. Polish sausage , cubed', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of mushroom soup', '1 (16 oz.) can sauerkraut , rinsed and drained', '8 oz. fresh mushrooms', '1 onion , chopped', '1 medium potato , cubed', '2 carrots , chopped', '2 stalks celery , chopped', '1/2 c. cubed , cooked chicken', '2 Tbsp. vinegar', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '2 tsp. dill weed', '2 slices bacon , cooked crisp and crumbled', '2 boiled eggs , cubed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(998, ' Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly. Garnish with chives or parsley. Serves a large group.', '1 can Boston or New England clam chowder', '2 cans shrimp soup', '1 can cream of celery soup', '1 can shrimp or 1/4 lb. fresh shrimp', '1 can crab or 1/4 lb. fresh picked crab', '1 can minced clams', '2 soup cans milk', '1 to 2 dashes of Tabasco sauce', '2 to 3 dashes of Worcestershire sauce', ' pepper to taste', ' sherry to taste', ' chives or parsley (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(999, ' Combine butter and flour , cooking over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Saut&eacute; celery , carrots and onions. Heat milk and chicken broth together. Add butter , flour , seasoning , vegetables and crab meat. Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes. Then add sherry and half and half. Simmer for another five minutes.', '1/4 lb. butter', '1/2 c. flour', '1/2 c. finely chopped celery', '1/2 c. finely chopped carrots', '1/2 c. finely chopped onions', '1 pt. milk', '1 c. chicken broth', '1 Tbsp. Old Bay seasoning', '1 lb. crab meat', '1/3 c. dry sherry', '1 pt. half and half', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1000, ' Saut&eacute; scallops in butter with garlic. While saut&eacute;ing scallops , dice celery , carrots and onions. Heat chicken broth. Add seasonings , vegetables and scallops. Bring to a boil. Lower heat to simmer and cook for about 45 minutes (until vegetables are tender enough to be pierced with a fork). Add half and half. Cook approximately another 15 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch to desired thickness.', '1 lb. scallops', '1/2 stick butter', '1 clove garlic', '2 stalks celery', '3 to 4 medium carrots', '2 to 3 medium onions', '2 cans chicken broth', ' salt to taste', ' white pepper to taste', '1 tsp. thyme', '1/2 to 3/4 c. half and half', ' cornstarch', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1001, ' Make a roux of butter and flour; add milk and make a thick white sauce. If cheese is used , add here and whisk to melt. Mix in leftover cooked vegetables or meat; stir until smooth. Add broth to desired consistency. Season to taste.', '1/2 c. butter or margarine', '1/2 c. flour', '2 (14 1/2 oz.) cans evaporated milk', ' cheese (optional)', '1 to 2 c. chopped meat or vegetables', '2 to 3 c. broth', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1002, ' *Use more chicken broth , if desired , and less evaporated milk.', '2 avocados , peeled , seeded and cubed', '1 (13 oz.) can evaporated milk*', '2 c. milk', '1 c. chicken broth*', '1/2 tsp. celery salt', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. white pepper', ' watercress or parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1003, ' Saut&eacute; onions and carrots in 3 tablespoons butter. Stir in chicken broth , seasonings and potatoes; simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove the bay leaf. In skillet saut&eacute; mushrooms in remaining butter 5 minutes. Stir in flour and cream. Add to soup and bring to boil.', '2 leeks or onions , chopped', '2 large carrots , chopped', '5 Tbsp. butter or oleo , divided', '6 c. chicken broth', '2 tsp. dill weed', '2 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '1 bay leaf', '5 c. potatoes , diced', '1 lb. fresh mushrooms , sliced', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 c. half and half or cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1004, ' Saut&eacute; onions in butter until tender. Blend in flour , salt and pepper. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Gradually stir in chicken base or water. Bring to a boil , stirring constantly. Stir in cream just before serving. Put in ovenproof bowls. Add 1 slice toasted French bread. Top with Swiss cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.', '6 medium onions , sliced', '1/4 lb. butter', '1/2 c. flour', '1 to 1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '8 c. chicken stock or 8 c. water', '1 2/3 c. cream', ' French bread', ' Swiss cheese , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1005, ' Cook onions in butter until soft. Add nondairy creamer all at once to boiling chicken broth and stir to blend. Add potatoes , carrots and rice to cooked onions; stir. Cover and cook 15 minutes; add to broth. Add frozen spinach and continue boiling for 15 minutes more , stirring often to prevent sticking. Salt and pepper to taste. Can be frozen and reheated.', '1 c. green onions , firmly chopped', '6 Tbsp. margarine or butter', '2 c. dry nondairy creamer', '5 c. chicken broth', '2 medium potatoes , thinly sliced', '2 medium carrots , sliced', '1/4 c. uncooked regular rice', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen spinach', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1006, ' In a Dutch oven , saut&eacute; onion 5 minutes in hot butter. Add broth and heat to boiling; add vegetables , potato , celery and beans. Then cover and cook until potatoes are tender. Add pumpkin and seasoning; over high heat , heat to boiling. Cover and reduce to low; cook 5 minutes. Stir in cream and heat through. Serve in hollowed out pumpkin. Can add small amount of raw pumpkin , put in with vegetables , if desired. Makes 8 servings.', '1 large onion , chopped', '2 Tbsp. butter', '3 c. chicken or beef broth', '1/2 bag frozen mixed vegetables', '1 large potato', '1 stalk celery , sliced', '1 (16 oz.) can garbanzos or white kidney beans', '1 (16 oz.) can pumpkin puree', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. ground nutmeg', '1/8 tsp. white pepper', '1/2 pt. heavy or whipping cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1007, ' Pare and slice 2 cucumbers (about 3 cups). Cook with onions in butter until soft. Stir in flour; add broth slowly. Cover; simmer until cucumbers are tender , about 10 minutes. Cool slightly; add seasoned salt. Whirl smooth in blender or processor. Chill well. Pare remaining cucumber and scoop out seeds. Grate the cucumber medium coarse. Add to chilled soup base along with sour cream. Blend in lemon juice and dill.', '3 medium cucumbers', '1/2 c. chopped onions', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 Tbsp. flour', '2 c. rich chicken broth', '1 tsp. seasoned salt', '1 1/2 c. dairy sour cream', '3/4 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/8 tsp. dried dill', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1008, ' Melt butter and stir in flour. Add milk , bouillon or soup stock and corn. Season with salt and pepper. Boil 5 minutes and serve in bouillon cups with popcorn floating on top. Croutons can be used in place of popcorn. Serves 4.', '2 Tbsp. butter', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 pt. milk', '1 pt. bouillon or soup stock', '1 can creamed corn (strain through a colander)', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' popcorn or croutons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1009, ' Saut&eacute; zucchini and onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender. Combine zucchini and onion with sour cream , cream of chicken soup , shredded carrots and 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs tossed with 2 tablespoons margarine. Bake for 30 minutes at 350&deg;.', '4 medium zucchini , sliced 1/2 inch thick', '1/3 c. onion , chopped', '6 Tbsp. margarine , melted', '1 c. sour cream', '1 can condensed cream of chicken soup', '1 c. shredded carrots', '2 c. seasoned bread crumbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1012, ' Heat the oil and cubed stew meat and brown. Add tomato sauce , chili powder , paprika , sugar , vinegar , molasses and salt plus 1 cup water , and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add more water , if needed. Add the carrots , onions and green pepper and cook another 30 minutes.', '2 Tbsp. oil', '2 lb. beef stew meat', '2 (8 oz.) cans tomato sauce', '2 tsp. chili powder', '2 tsp. paprika', '1/4 c. sugar', '1/4 c. vinegar', '1/2 c. molasses', '1 tsp. salt', '2 c. carrots , sliced', '2 c. onions , diced', '1 green pepper , diced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1013, ' Cut meat in cubes. In a Dutch oven cook onion , celery and pepper in oil until tender. Add water , potatoes , tomatoes , catsup , Worcestershire sauce and bouillon granules and bring to boil. Reduce heat , cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in corned beef and cook 2 minutes more.', '1 (12 oz.) can corned beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/4 c. chopped celery', '1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1 Tbsp. oil', '2 c. water', '4 potatoes , cubed', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes', '1 Tbsp. catsup', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. instant beef bouillon granules', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1014, ' In skillet brown meat in oil; drain off fat. Place onion rings , green pepper and garlic in slow cooker. Place meat on top and sprinkle with salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add beef broth , undrained tomatoes , mushrooms and barbecue sauce; stir to mix. Cover and cook on low heat setting for 8 hours. Turn cooker on high heat setting. Blend 1/4 cup cold water slowly into cornstarch; stir into stew. Cover and cook until thickened and bubbly , stirring occasionally. Serve over hot rice. Makes 8 servings.', '2 lb. beef stew meat (cut in 1-inch cubes)', '2 Tbsp. oil', '1 c. thinly sliced onions , separated in rings', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '1 large clove garlic , minced', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '2 c. beef broth', '1 (8 oz.) can tomatoes , cut up', '1 (4 oz.) can mushroom pieces , drained', '1/3 c. barbecue sauce', '1/4 c. cold water', '3 Tbsp. cornstarch', ' hot cooked rice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1015, ' Saut&eacute; sausage and beef until almost done. Add meats to stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Cool enough to remove bones. Return meat to broth. Return to boil; add all ingredients , except corn. Simmer 45 minutes , stirring frequently. Add corn and simmer 15 minutes. Season to taste. Serves 8.', '3/4 lb. beef , cubed', '3/4 lb. Italian sausage , skinned and cut in chunks', '1 stewing chicken , cut up', '3 1/2 qt. stock', '2 1/2 c. quartered , skinned tomatoes', '1 c. fresh lima beans', '1 can okra (optional)', '2 c. diced peppers', '3/4 c. diced onions', '1 c. diced carrots', '1/2 c. diced celery', '1 c. sliced mushrooms', '1 bay leaf', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '2 c. fresh corn or Niblets', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1016, ' Cut chicken breasts into quarters; heat oil in frying pan and brown chicken well. Add onion , green pepper , garlic , chili powder and cumin. Saut&eacute; 2 minutes until onion is soft; stir in rice , water and salt and bring to boiling. Transfer to stew pot , cover , reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in shrimp and tomatoes. Return to simmering , cover and cook 15 minutes. Add crab and okra and cook 5 minutes longer. Stir in chopped parsley just before serving.', '3 chicken breasts , quartered', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1/2 onion , diced', '1/4 c. green pepper , diced', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1 Tbsp. chili powder', '1/4 tsp. ground cumin', '1/2 c. uncooked rice', '3/4 c. water', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 lb. shelled , deveined shrimp (medium)', '1 (1 lb.) can whole tomatoes', '1 c. flaked crab meat or 1 doz. crab claws', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen okra', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1017, ' Cut meat into 1 1/2 inch cubes; season with flour. Heat olive oil in deep iron skillet or Dutch oven. Brown meat slowly; add other ingredients. Cover tightly , turn meat often and simmer for 10 minutes.', '2 lb. tenderloin tips', ' salt , pepper and flour to coat meat', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 c. beef stock', '1 bay leaf', '1 clove garlic , chopped', '1 pinch of rosemary', '1 bell pepper', '1/2 c. butter', '6 small onions', '2 tomatoes', '2 potatoes', '1 tsp. parsley', '2 c. red wine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1018, ' Combine flour , paprika , salt and the one teaspoon chili powder. Dredge beef cubes in the flour mixture and brown in hot lard in Dutch oven. Add onions and garlic; cook until soft. Add tomatoes , 3 tablespoons chili powder , cinnamon , cloves and red pepper. Cover and simmer 2 hours. Add potatoes and carrots; cook until vegetables are tender , about 45 minutes. Makes 8 servings.', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 Tbsp. paprika', '2 Tbsp. salt', '1 tsp. chili powder', '5 c. beef cubes', '3 Tbsp. lard', '2 onions , sliced', '1 clove garlic , minced', '28 oz. can tomatoes', '3 Tbsp. chili powder', '1 Tbsp. cinnamon', '1 tsp. ground cloves', '1 tsp. dry crushed red pepper', '2 c. chopped potatoes', '2 c. chopped carrots', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1019, ' Slice meat thin and sprinkle with pepper. Brown meat in oil. Add golden mushroom soup , water , onion and soy sauce. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add cabbage , cut into 1-inch pieces and bamboo shoots or Chinese vegetables. Simmer , covered , for 8 minutes or until cabbage is done. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6. Cooking time is 1 hour and 45 minutes.', '1 lb. beef or more , sliced thin', ' pepper to taste', ' oil for frying', '1 can golden mushroom soup', '1 1/4 c. water', '1 onion , sliced thin', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1 small head cabbage', '1 can bamboo shoots or Chinese vegetables', ' rice or Chinese noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1020, ' Combine flour , salt and pepper. Dredge beef cubes in flour mixture , reserving remaining flour. In Dutch oven , brown meat in hot oil , turning often. Add onion , water and garlic; cook until tender. Stir tomatoes with liquid into reserved flour; add to meat with mushroom steak sauce , basil , celery salt and cayenne. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer , covered , for 1 hour. Add potatoes; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Stir occasionally; add more water as needed. Stir in mixed vegetables.', '3 Tbsp. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 to 1 1/2 lb. round steak , cut into cubes', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 medium onion , peeled and sliced into rings', '2 c. water', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1 (16 oz.) can whole tomatoes , cut up', '1 (6 oz.) can mushroom steak sauce', '1/2 tsp. dried basil', '1/4 tsp. celery salt', ' dash of cayenne pepper', '2 medium potatoes , diced and pared', '2 (16 oz.) cans mixed vegetables', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1021, ' Measure Corn Flakes into large bowl. Crush slightly. Stir into egg , 1/4 cup beef broth , salt and pepper. Beat well and add ground beef. Mix well. Make into balls and brown meat balls in oil in frying pan over medium heat. Pour off excess fat. Stir in the remaining beef broth , tomato soup , water , thyme , carrots , onion rings and potatoes. Cover and cook over medium heat about 25 minutes or until meat balls are thoroughly cooked. Pour into individual bowls. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.', '2 c. Kellogg''s Corn Flakes cereal', '1 egg', '1 (10 1/2 oz.) can condensed beef broth , divided', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 lb. ground beef', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can condensed tomato soup', '1/2 c. water', '1/4 tsp. thyme', '2 c. frozen sliced carrots', '1 medium onion , sliced into rings', '1 (1 lb.) can whole white potatoes , drained', ' dried parsley flakes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
