(1103, ' Lightly pound the cutlets to make them into thin fillets. Melt half the butter and saut&eacute; the onion , parsley , and celery over gentle heat. Add the seasonings. Remove from the heat and place in a bowl. Add the bread crumbs , dampened with a bit of water and mix gently. Divide into 8 equal portions and place each on a pork fillet. Roll and secure with a skewer or tie with string. Dredge in flour sprinkled on waxed paper. Brown in a frying pan , using the rest of the butter. Add the chicken stock , lower the heat , cover and cook very slowly , about 1 1/2 hours.', '8 lean pork chops , very thinly sliced and flattened into cutlets (1 lb.)', '1 chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. chopped celery', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley', '8 tsp. butter', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. poultry seasoning', ' pepper to taste', '2 c. fresh bread crumbs', '1/2 c. chicken bouillon , defatted', '2 Tbsp. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1105, ' Melt margarine in saucepan. Add salt and pepper. Split hens; place skin side up in shallow baking pan. Baste with margarine. Roast hens for 1 1/2 hours uncovered. When done , pour pan drippings into small saucepan. Add chicken broth and grape juice. Simmer 15 minutes until reduced to 1 cup. Add grapes; cook 2 minutes. Calories: 206.', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '2 Rock Cornish game hens', '1 c. chicken broth', '1/2 c. grape juice (unsweetened)', '1/2 to 1 c. seedless grapes , halved', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1107, ' Combine milk , onion , eggs and salt. Add bread crumbs and let stand for 5 minutes. Add meat and mix thoroughly. Shape into 4 dozen small balls. Bake at 375&deg; for 25 minutes.', '1/2 c. skim milk', '1/4 c. chopped onion', '2 eggs', '1 tsp. salt', '3 slices bread , crumbled', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1108, ' Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper , garlic and basil. Combine remaining ingredients except lemon and lime slices. Pour over chicken. Bake uncovered 30 minutes. Turn and baste. Bake 30 to 40 minutes more. Garnish with fruit slices. Bake at 400&deg;. Calories: 235.', '1 chicken , cut up', ' salt and pepper', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '1 tsp. basil', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '1/4 c. lime juice', '1/2 c. water', '2 tsp. lemon peel', '2 tsp. lime peel', '1 lemon , sliced up', '1 lime , sliced up', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1109, ' Saut&eacute; beef , onion and pepper. Drain fat and add salt. Place potato in bottom of baking dish. Alternate layers of carrots , rice and meat. Pour the tomatoes all over casserole. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350&deg;.', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '1 c. sliced onion', '1 c. chopped green pepper', '2 tsp. salt', '1 large potato , peeled and sliced', '1 c. sliced carrots', '1/3 c. rice , uncooked', '28 oz. can tomatoes , mashed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1110, ' Pour 2 tablespoons margarine in bottom of baking pan. Combine celery , carrots , olives , green pepper , onions , tomatoes and tomato sauce. Spread half of mixture in bottom of pan. Place fish on top. Cover with remaining mixture. Dot with margarine. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350&deg; oven. Calories: 280.', '2 lb. thick fish fillets', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '3/4 c. celery , diced', '3/4 c. diced carrots', '1/4 c. black olives', '1/2 c. green pepper , diced', '1 red onion , chopped', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes', '3/4 c. tomato sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1112, ' ', '1 small chicken (1 1/2 lb.)', '1 1/2 c. water', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 stalk celery (1/4 c.)', '1/4 c. onion', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1113, ' Combine soup , milk , chicken , vegetables , 1/4 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions until well blended. Spread mixture into 8 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake uncovered at 425&deg; for 10 minutes.', '1 (1 lb.) pkg. frozen mixed vegetables (broccoli , cauliflower and carrots) , thawed and drained', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '3/4 c. milk', '2 c. chopped , cooked chicken', '1 c. biscuit mix', '1 egg , slightly beaten', '1/4 c. milk', '1 c. Velveeta cheese , cubed', '1 can Durkee onion rings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
