(1114, ' Preheat oven to 450&deg;. Remove skin from fish , cut meat from bones. Cut 4 (10 x 12-inch) pieces of heavy-duty foil , use oil to grease center of each piece of foil. Place a steak on each piece of foil. Top each steak with slices of onion , potato and carrot. Salt and pepper. Using drugstore wrap , fold each piece separately. Put on cookie sheet and bake until fish flakes and is tender , approximately 20 minutes. Garnish with parsley.', '4 (3 oz.) fish steaks', '3 tsp. oil', '1 onion , sliced thin', '1 potato , sliced thin', '1/2 carrot , sliced thin', ' dash of salt and pepper', '1/2 tsp. parsley , snipped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1115, ' Cut off all fat from meat. Cut into strips 1/2 x 3-inches or so. Brown meat in oil; add ginger , garlic and broth. Bring to a boil. Lower heat , cover pan and cook 1 hour. Blend cornstarch with water and soy sauce; stir into pan. Add green pepper; cook until sauce is thickened and clear. Serves 6.', '2 lb. round steak', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 tsp. ginger', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '2 c. beef bouillon (broth)', '2 Tbsp. cornstarch', '2 Tbsp. water', '1 1/2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1 green pepper , cut in very thin strips (may be omitted)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1116, ' Fry meat in large skillet until meat changes color. Pour off excess fat. Add onions , celery and green pepper. Stir and cook 1 minute or 2. Combine all other ingredients; mix well and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.', '1 lb. lean ground beef', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. onions , chopped fine', '3/4 c. celery with greens , chopped fine', '1/4 c. green pepper , chopped fine', '1/2 tsp. grated lemon rind', '1/4 c. tomato catsup', '3/4 c. beef broth', '1/2 tsp. dry mustard', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1117, ' In 2 1/2-quart pot , Teflon or spray with Pam , place beef in pot. Sprinkle with salt. Cook until meat changes color. Add onions , celery and green pepper; mix well. Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomatoes and liquid and all seasonings , mixing well. Bring to a boil; cover and turn heat low and simmer gently for 25 minutes , stirring occasionally. Add kidney beans and beef broth. Continue cooking over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.', '1 lb. ground beef lean', '1 1/4 tsp. salt', '1 c. chopped onions', '1 c. finely cut celery', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes , cut up with liquid', '1/2 c. green pepper , cut fine', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 tsp. oregano', '1 Tbsp. chili powder', '1 (16 oz.) can kidney beans', '1/2 c. beef broth', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1119, ' Heat oil in deep heavy pot; add celery and onions. Stir-fry over moderate heat until onions are transparent but not brown. Add chicken broth; cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes.', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '3 c. slant-sliced celery', '1/2 c. slant-sliced green onions with tops', '2 1/2 c. hot chicken broth', '3 Tbsp. cornstarch', '1/8 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 tsp. ground ginger', '1/2 c. cold water', '1 Tbsp. soy sauce', '3 1/4 c. cooked chicken in small pieces', '1 (6 oz.) can mushrooms', '1 1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1 (8 oz.) can water chestnuts , drained and sliced', '1 (3 1/2 oz.) can chow mein noodles', '2 Tbsp. finely cut candied ginger', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1120, ' Cut eggplant in half lengthwise; scoop out center , leaving 1/2-inch walls. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place cut side up in a large baking dish , shallow. Chop scooped out eggplant centers and set aside. Brown meat and drain off fat; stir in eggplant , onions , parsley and oregano. Cook at medium about 10 minutes or until tender. Add tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Spoon 3/4 cup of mixture into each eggplant shell. Sprinkle with cheese; cover with foil and bake at 350&deg; for 45 to 50 minutes.', '2 eggplant (1 lb. each)', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 lb. 85% lean ground beef', '1 c. onion , chopped', '1 Tbsp. parsley , minced', '1/2 tsp. oregano', '1 (6 oz.) can tomato paste', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1125, ' Brown meat in skillet sprayed with vegetable pan spray. Add remaining ingredients; mix. Place in 2-quart casserole dish; cover. Bake at 325&deg; for 2 hours , adding water if necessary. Serve over rice , noodles or potatoes.', '1 3/4 lb. lean beef , cubed', '1 1/2 oz. pkg. dry onion soup mix', '2 1/2 c. tomato juice', '1/2 c. water', '1/2 c. catsup', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1127, ' Remove fat or gristle from chicken. Split each piece into 2 thin layers , then cut layers into strips about 2-inches long , 1/4-inch wide. Cook rice according to package directions (omit margarine). Heat oil in skillet or wok , add chicken. Stir constantly until chicken turns white and is slightly brown (approximately 2 minutes). Turn heat to medium and add peppers , celery , onion , bouillon cube , water chestnuts , salt , ginger and water. Make a smooth paste of arrowroot and soy sauce and stir in chicken mixture until smooth. Cook gently 6 to 7 minutes , tightly covered. Add bean sprouts to cooked vegetables; cover and cook gently another 2 minutes. Each serving consists of 1/2 cup cooked rice with 1 cup chicken mixture.', '2 lb. chicken breasts , boned and split', '1 c. long grain rice', '3 Tbsp. oil', '1 green pepper , chopped fine', '3 stalks celery , cut in 2-inch pieces', '1 small onion , chopped fine', '1 chicken bouillon cube', '1/2 c. water chestnuts , drained and sliced thick', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. fresh ginger , chopped fine', '3/4 c. water', '1 tsp. arrowroot powder', '1 tsp. soy sauce', '1 lb. can bean sprouts , drained thoroughly', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1128, ' Saut&eacute; onions and celery in margarine until celery is wilted. Remove and set aside. Add livers and turn heat high. Cook , turning once or twice , until done , approximately 3 to 5 minutes. Top with onions and celery. Season with salt and pepper.', '2 onions , sliced thin', '2 stalks celery , sliced thin', '1 Tbsp. diet margarine', '1 lb. chicken livers', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. fresh ground pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1129, ' Preheat oven to 300&deg;. Trim fat from meat and cook , using 1 tablespoon liquid fat. Combine salt , marjoram , thyme and sage. Sprinkle on meat and press with fingers. Brown meat on both sides (using cooked fat). Transfer to shallow dish. Combine chicken broth , orange rind and ginger. Pour over chops. Cover and bake 45 minutes. One chop contains 285 calories.', '4 loin chops', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. marjoram', '1/8 tsp. thyme', '1/8 tsp. sage', '3/4 c. chicken broth', '1/2 tsp. grated orange rind', '1/8 tsp. ground ginger', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1131, ' About 50 minutes before serving , let scallops stand in oil and garlic for 30 minutes. Preheat broiler 10 minutes. Meanwhile , sprinkle tomato halves with pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. In shallow roasting pan , arrange with scallops. Over scallops pour margarine , 1/2 teaspoon salt , lemon juice and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Broil about 10 minutes , turning once. Serve garnished with lemon twists and parsley.', '1 lb. scallops', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 garlic clove , minced', '2 medium tomatoes , halved', ' pepper', ' salt', '1 1/2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 Tbsp. melted margarine', ' lemon twists (for garnish)', ' chopped parsley (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1133, ' Combine flour , salt and pepper. Coat steak with seasoned flour. With wooden mallet , pound meat between wax paper until it is 1/2-inch thick. Cut into 6 serving pieces. Heat oil; brown steak well , all sides. Saut&eacute; onion until tender. Add tomatoes and broth. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots. Cover; simmer 1/2 hour or until meat and carrots are tender.', '1/4 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 lb. beef round steak (about 3/4-inch thick)', '1 Tbsp. oil', '1 large onion , sliced', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes', '1/2 c. beef broth', '2 c. peeled sliced carrots', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1134, ' Put chicken in glass or plastic bowl. Add hot sauce and stir lightly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Mix flour with salt and spices. Remove chicken from hot sauce; roll in flour mixture (using it up completely). Heat oil in small skillet until HOT. Fry the chicken chunks until they are cooked and crispy.', '5 oz. deboned and skinned chicken , cut in 1-inch squares', '1/4 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', ' dash of paprika', '1 tsp. hot sauce or Tabasco sauce', '1 Tbsp. plus 1 1/2 tsp. all-purpose flour', ' dash of garlic powder', '1 tsp. salad oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1135, ' ', '1/2 c. all-purpose flour', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. baking powder', '2 Tbsp. shortening', '1/2 c. sour cream or yogurt (add 2 Tbsp. flour if using yogurt)', '1 egg , beaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1136, ' Combine chicken , bean sprouts , water chestnuts and soy sauce and mix well. Set aside. Mix eggs , water , green pepper , onion , salt and pepper with a fork. Heat butter or margarine in a 10-inch skillet. Pour in egg mixture. With spatula , draw cooked portions of egg toward center so that uncooked portions flow to bottom. Cook until bottom is set and lightly browned and top is creamy. Arrange chicken mixture on half of omelet. With spatula , fold other half over and turn out on serving platter. Yields 2 servings. Each serving equals 3 ounces of meat and 1 vegetable.', '1/2 c. chopped-cooked chicken', '1/4 c. bean sprouts', '3 water chestnuts , thinly sliced', '1 tsp. soy sauce', '4 eggs', '1/4 c. water', '2 Tbsp. chopped green pepper', '1/2 tsp. minced onion', '1/2 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '1 Tbsp. butter or margarine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1137, ' Combine eggs , soup , onion , chicken , rice , celery , mayonnaise and lemon juice , stirring well. Spoon mixture into nonstick 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and butter substitute; sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350&deg; , uncovered , for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.', '2 hard-cooked eggs , chopped', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of mushroom soup', '1 small onion , chopped', '1 1/2 c. diced , cooked chicken (no skin)', '1 c. cooked rice', '1/2 c. chopped celery', '1/4 c. reduced calorie mayonnaise', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/4 c. soft bread crumbs', '1 Tbsp. dry butter substitute', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1138, ' Combine all ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to a boil; then cover. Let simmer one hour. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking , as nearly all the liquid will be absorbed by lentils and rice. Serves 4.', '4 1/2 c. chicken broth', '3/4 c. dry lentils', '1 c. chopped onions', '1/2 c. brown rice (raw)', '1/2 c. shredded Swiss cheese', '1/2 tsp. basil , salt and oregano', '1/8 tsp. thyme', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '1 tsp. black pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1140, ' Cover head of cabbage with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes. Peel off 12 nice leaves. Combine beef , salt , pepper , rice , onion , egg and poultry seasoning. Place equal portions in center of each leaf. Fold sides of leaf over meat and roll up. Place in small casserole. Combine water , lemon juice and tomato sauce and pour over rolls. Cover. Bake at 350&deg; for 1 hour.', '12 large cabbage leaves', '1 1/4 lb. ground beef', '2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1 c. cooked rice', '1 chopped onion', '1 egg', '1/2 tsp. poultry seasoning', '16 oz. tomato sauce', '1/4 c. water', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1148, ' Take your nonstick frying pan and spread the frozen beans over the bottom. Add broth and onions and simmer over low heat until liquid evaporates. Stir often so that beans cook evenly. Don''t cover the pan; beans cooked in a covered pan quickly lose their color and end up a sickly gray-green. Beans should be crisp and tender by the time the water disappears. If not cooked sufficiently , add a little more broth , but take care not to overcook. Don''t throw away the pan juices that remain; serve them over the beans. Serves 3.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen green beans , whole or cut into pieces', '1/2 c. chicken stock or broth', '1 Tbsp. onion , minced or 1 Tbsp. dried onion flakes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1149, ' Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Saut&eacute; onion and celery in margarine in nonstick skillet until clear. Mix broccoli , soup and cheese; add to celery and onion. Stir in rice , salt and pepper. Put into nonstick 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with breadcrumbs. Bake at 350&deg; for 35 minutes and serve.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen , chopped broccoli', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/2 c. chopped celery', '1 tsp. reduced calorie margarine', '1 1/2 c. cooked rice', '1 (10 1/4 oz.) can cream of chicken soup', '1 c. grated low-fat process American cheese', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 Tbsp. breadcrumbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1163, ' Beat together the oil , sugar , eggs and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Combine the flours , baking powder , soda , salt , cinnamon and raisins in bowl. Stir into the creamed mixture with the milk or orange juice. Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350&deg; for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 15.', '1/3 c. vegetable oil', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '2 eggs', '3/4 c. cooked or canned pumpkin', '1 c. flour', '1 c. whole-wheat flour', '1 Tbsp. baking powder', '1/2 tsp. baking soda', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 c. raisins', '1/4 c. low-fat milk or orange juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1164, ' Combine the flours , sugar , baking powder and orange rind in a mixing bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and stir until well blended. Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350&deg; oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool for 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan. Turn onto a wire rack and cool thoroughly. Store in a plastic bag or aluminum foil for at least 1 day before slicing. Serves 15.', '1 c. whole-wheat flour', '1 c. white flour', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 Tbsp. baking powder', '2 tsp. grated orange rind', '1 c. orange juice', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 egg', '1 c. chopped fresh or frozen cranberries', '1/3 c. raisins', '1/3 c. chopped walnuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1165, ' Place flour , cocoa , dry buttermilk , sugar , cinnamon , baking soda and baking powder in bowl and mix at low speed to blend well. Mix water , oil , egg , sweetener and vanilla with a fork to blend. Add to flour mixture and mix at medium speed only until flour is moistened. Add nuts to dough and spread evenly in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan which has been greased with margarine. Bake at 375&deg; for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean from the center and the bread pulls away from the sides of the pan. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out on wire rack to cool to room temperature.', '1 3/4 c. all-purpose flour', '1/3 c. cocoa', '1/4 c. dry buttermilk', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1 tsp. baking soda', '1 tsp. baking powder', '1 c. water', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '1/4 c. liquid egg substitute (at room temperature)', ' liquid sugar substitute to equal 1/3 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1/2 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1188, ' Beat egg yolks 5 minutes until thick. Combine water , sweetener , vanilla and lemon juice; add to yolks. Beat 10 minutes until thick and fluffy. Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form. Fold carefully into yolk mixture. Combine sifted flour and salt. Sift a little at a time over mixture , folding in gently. Pour into ungreased 9 or 10-inch tube pan. Bake in slow 325&deg; oven for 1 1/4 hours.', '7 eggs , separated (room temperature)', '1/2 c. cold water', '3 Tbsp. liquid sweetener', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '3/4 tsp. cream of tartar', '1 1/2 c. sifted cake flour', '1/4 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1189, ' Add cold water to soften gelatine. Add boiling juice or water , fruit and sweetener; place in refrigerator until it starts to jell (about 1 1/2 hours). Fold in 1 package whipped Dream Whip and angel food cake that has been broken in small pieces. Press down in large bowl; place in refrigerator until firm. Remove from mold and frost with other package of Dream Whip.', '1 large angel food cake or 2 small', '1 large can fruit cocktail or crushed pineapple , drained', '2 pkg. Knox gelatine', '2 pkg. Dream Whip', '2 Tbsp. cold water', '8 pkg. Sweet ''N Low or Equal', '1 c. juice from fruit or 1 c. boiling water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1190, ' Cream together shortening , eggs , bananas and dates. Sift together the dry ingredients , then mix all together. Bake one hour at 350&deg;.', '1 c. bananas , whipped', '1 c. dates , chopped', '1/2 c. nuts', '1 3/4 c. flour', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. soda', '1/3 c. vegetable shortening', '2 eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1191, ' Beat eggs; add vegetable oil. Sift together dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to eggs and oil. Add apple juice concentrate. Stir in carrots , raisins and 1/2 cup walnuts. Spray an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup walnuts over top. Bake in preheated oven at 325&deg; for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Yield: 32 slices. One slice equals 180 calories.', '4 eggs', '1 1/2 c. vegetable oil', '3 tsp. cinnamon', '2 tsp. baking soda', '1 tsp. salt', '2 Tbsp. vanilla', '2 c. flour', '3/4 c. frozen unsweetened apple juice concentrate , thawed', '3 c. raw carrots , grated', '1 c. raisins', '1 c. walnuts , chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1199, ' Add oil to applesauce and egg. Add sweetener. Sift flour , baking powder , baking soda , cocoa , salt , cinnamon , nutmeg and cloves. Add lemon rind , raisins , dates and nuts to dry ingredients. Then add to applesauce mixture. (It will be thick.) Pour mixture into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325&deg; for 1 hour.', '1/3 c. cooking oil', '1 1/2 c. unsweetened applesauce', '2 Tbsp. liquid sweetener', '1 large egg , beaten', '2 c. flour', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/2 tsp. baking soda', '2 Tbsp. cocoa', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 tsp. ground nutmeg', '1/2 tsp. ground cloves', '1/2 c. seedless raisins', '1/2 c. chopped dates', '1/4 c. chopped nuts', '1 tsp. lemon rind', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1201, ' Boil together the dates , raisins and water for 3 minutes. Cool and drain , saving the liquid.', '1/2 c. dates or apricots , chopped', '1 c. raisins', '1/2 c. chopped raw apples', '1 c. water', '2 eggs , beaten', '1/2 c. shortening or oleo', '2 envelopes Sweet ''N Low', '1 c. flour', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1/2 tsp. lemon flavoring', '1/2 tsp. black walnut extract', '1 tsp. soda', '3/4 c. nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
