(1411, ' Place fryer into a bowl with a tight fitting lid. Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken early in the day. Place in the refrigerator. Shake the bowl several times that day. Cook on an outdoor barbecue grill as you would any other chicken. Use the sauce to baste the chicken while cooking. The whole family should go for this one. Serves 4.', '1 large fryer , cut up', '1 c. Italian salad dressing', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 tsp. onion powder', '1/2 tsp. paprika', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1413, ' Place serving size portions of fish on well-greased grill. Spray grill well before putting on fish. Baste fish with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Cook about 5 inches from hot coals for 8 minutes. Baste with sauce , then turn and cook for 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes or turns shiny white. Serves 4.', '2 lb. fresh fish steaks , 3/4-inch thick', '1/2 c. melted margarine or butter', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '1 dash hot pepper sauce', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1414, ' Thaw frozen steaks. Cut into serving size portions and place in well-greased , hinged wire grill. Combine remaining ingredients except paprika. Baste fish with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Cook about 4 inches from moderately hot coals for 8 minutes. Baste with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Turn and cook for 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Serves 6.', '2 lb. red snapper steaks or other fish steaks (fresh or frozen)', '1/2 c. melted fat or oil', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 tsp. white pepper', ' dash of liquid hot pepper sauce', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1416, ' Make 4 or 5 shallow slits on each side of fish. Brush fish generously with a mixture of oil , lemon juice , salt , pepper , oregano and Accent. Cook over coals until golden brown , brushing with mixture. Turn fish gently to cook both sides. When fish is done , put on serving platter and pour remaining mixture over fish. Serves 3 to 4.', '2 1/2 or 3 lb. white fish (trout , snapper or mackerel may be used)', '1/4 c. olive oil', '1/2 c. fresh lemon juice', '3/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1 Tbsp. oregano', '1/2 tsp. Accent', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1419, ' Marinate roast in beefy onion soup mix all day and night (turn often). Preheat gas grill; sear roast on both sides. Turn grill to low setting and baste well. Cook until inside temperature is about 140&deg; to 150&deg;.', '3 lb. chuck roast', '1 pkg. Lipton beefy onion soup mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1420, ' Score fat edge of ham. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over ham in shallow baking dish. Refrigerate overnight or let stand at room temperature 1 hour , spooning marinade over ham several times. Place ham on grill over slow coals. Cook 15 minutes on each side , brushing frequently with marinade. Heat remaining marinade and serve with ham.', '1 1/2 lb. thick sliced cooked ham', '1 c. ginger ale', '1 c. orange juice', '1/2 c. firmly packed brown sugar', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 Tbsp. wine vinegar', '2 tsp. dry mustard', '3/4 tsp. ground ginger', '1/2 tsp. ground cloves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1422, ' Combine soy sauce , brown sugar , oil , ginger , mustard , pepper and garlic. Mix well. Add meat and let stand 2 hours. Drain and reserve marinade. Thread meat on skewers alternating with vegetables. Broil over hot coals 5 to 6 minutes , turning frequently and basting with marinade; or broil in oven 3 to 5 minutes from heat until crispy brown.', '1/2 c. soy sauce', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '1 tsp. ground ginger', '1 tsp. dry mustard', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '1 1/2 lb. top sirloin , cut into 1 inch cubes', ' cherry tomatoes', ' small whole onions', ' mushrooms', ' green pepper , cut into 1 inch squares', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1423, ' Place steak in a large shallow dish. Combine onions , vinegar , oil , brown sugar , garlic , salt , marjoram , rosemary and hot sauce; pour over steak. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours , turning occasionally. Remove steak from marinade. Press 2 teaspoons pepper onto each side of steak. Grill over hot coals 15 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness. Place steak on serving platter; garnish with tomato wedges and fresh parsley. To serve , cut into serving pieces. Yield: 3 to 4 servings.', '1 (1 1/2 to 2 lb.) sirloin steak , 1 1/2 to 2-inches thick', '2 large onions , thinly sliced', '1 c. red wine vinegar', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '1/3 c. firmly packed brown sugar', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. dried whole marjoram', '1/4 tsp. dried whole rosemary , crushed', '3 drops hot sauce', '1 Tbsp. plus 1 tsp. coarsely ground pepper , divided', ' tomato wedges', ' fresh parsley sprigs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1425, ' ', '1 well trimmed brisket', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1427, ' Remove the seeds from the chilies and lightly roast to develop the full flavor. Soak in the vinegar (add enough water to cover) for 15 minutes , then puree. Brown the onions , then add the garlic puree and cumin. Add the chili puree and stock. Let cook for about 20 minutes or until the flavors have all merged.', '12 ancho chilies', '1/2 c. vinegar', '2 onions', '1 Tbsp. garlic , pureed', '2 Tbsp. cumin', '4 c. chicken stock , canned or preferably homemade', '1/4 c. brown sugar', '1/4 c. orange juice', '1/8 c. lemon or lime juice', '1/4 to 1/2 c. tomato puree (no salt added)', '6 medium-sized chicken breasts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
