(1440, ' Combine wine and oil in large bowl. Season to taste with salt , pepper and thyme. Place chicken in mixture for at least one hour. Remove chicken from marinade , reserving marinade. Broil chicken on both sides in oven or on barbecue grill for 35 to 40 minutes. Meanwhile , combine 2 tablespoons of reserved marinade , dry mustard and honey. When chicken is just done , brush with honey-mustard sauce and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1 c. white wine', '1/2 c. olive oil', ' salt , pepper and thyme', '1 (3 lb.) chicken , cut in serving pieces', '2 Tbsp. dry mustard', '1 Tbsp. honey', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1448, ' Combine oil , soy sauce , honey or brown sugar , vinegar , ginger and garlic. Marinate 8 hours in this mixture for delicate flavor , overnight for more pronounced flavor. Poke meat with two prong fork while marinating. Use sauce to brush on while cooking. Cook 4 to 5 minutes on each side. (Better cooked on grill , but can use broiler.) Carve diagonally in 1/4 inch strips.', '1 flank steak', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '1/3 c. soy sauce', '1 Tbsp. red wine vinegar', '2 Tbsp. honey or firmly packed brown sugar', '1 tsp. freshly grated ginger', '1/2 clove garlic , crushed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
