(1835, ' Brown ground beef. Add the tomatoes and green chilies and the green chilies and stir. Then add the cheeses and melt. Serve hot with Tostitos , Fritos or bread cubes. Good with raw vegetables , too,', '1 lb. ground beef , browned', '1 c. tomatoes and green chilies', '1 c. green chilies , chopped', '8 oz. Velveeta cheese', '8 oz. shredded Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1836, ' Brown meat , onion and pepper. To this , add beef broth , tomatoes , corn , beans and seasonings. Simmer 1/2 hour; just before serving , put in cornstarch. Also , just before serving , cut tamales in 1-inch pieces. Heat and serve.', '1 lb. hamburger', '1 onion , chopped', '1 bell pepper , chopped', '1 can beef broth', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', ' salt to taste', '1 large can tamales , drained', '1 can stewed tomatoes', '1 (10 oz.) can cream-style corn', '2 cans beans with jalapeno (if you like it hot)', '1/2 tsp. cumin seed', '1 Tbsp. cornstarch', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1837, ' In 5-quart saucepan lightly brown chorizo. Remove with slotted spoon. To drippings in pan add stew meat. Just before it is finished browning , add onions; stir to brown lightly. Add chorizo , carrots , tomatoes and beef bouillon. Simmer covered until beef is tender and carrots done. Skim off some of the fat. Add peas and steamed yams plus their juices , salt and pepper. Reheat.', '1/2 lb. chorizo , sliced 1/4-inch', '1 1/2 lb. stew meat (in small cubes)', '1 large Spanish onion , coarsely chopped', '2 medium carrots , thinly sliced', '1 (1 lb.) can tomatoes', '2 Tbsp. instant beef granules in 4 to 5 c. water', '1 can chickpeas (I use frozen black-eyed peas)', '3/4 to 1 lb. yams (in small cubes) , steamed', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1838, ' Start the meat in cold water. Make a rich broth by cooking it slowly with garlic , onion , pepper and salt. When the meat is tender , strain off broth. Add the vegetables (corn last) and cook slowly until done. Add the meat , cut in cubes , to the soup. If extra piquancy is desired , you may serve this with jalapeno sauce. Pick the corn up with fingers.', '2 lb. beef shanks', '3 qt. water', '2 cloves garlic', '1 onion , sliced', '8 peppercorns', '3 carrots , sliced', '3 zucchini , sliced', '1/2 lb. green beans , cut up', ' salt to taste', '3 ears of corn (fresh or frozen) , cut into 1-inch pieces', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1839, ' Melt butter and oil; add onion and stir. Cover pan and cook on low heat 15 to 20 minutes until onions are tender. Uncover , raise heat to medium-high; stir in salt and sugar. Stir until sugar caramelizes. Cook 30 minutes until onions are a dark brown. Stir often. Lower heat and stir in flour to make paste with onions. Cook slowly for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Pour 1 cup hot broth , stirring with wire whip to blend flour. Add rest of broth and ingredients. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with French bread and Parmesan cheese.', '3 Tbsp. butter', '1 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 1/2 lb. or 5 to 6 c. thin sliced yellow onions', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. sugar', '3 Tbsp. flour', '2 qt. hot beef broth', '1 c. red wine', '1 bay leaf', '1/2 tsp. sage', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1840, ' In blender or food processor , combine tomatoes and their liquid , green chilies and onion. Whirl until smooth. Pour into a 4-quart kettle with the broth and salsa and bring to a boil. Add turkey , rice , corn , cumin , salt , garlic and chili powder. Heat through. Makes about 3 quarts.', '1 (1 lb.) can tomatoes', '1 (7 oz.) can green chilies', '1 small onion , chopped', '3 c. turkey broth (or 2 cans regular strength chicken broth)', '1 Tbsp. green chili salsa', '2 c. cooked brown rice', '3 c. cooked turkey , cut in bite size chunks', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen corn , thawed', '3/4 tsp. ground cumin', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 clove garlic , minced', '1/4 tsp. chili powder', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
