(2223, ' Add jello and marshmallows to boiling water. Stir until jello is dissolved. Drain juice from oranges and pineapple; add water to make 1 cup. Mix cream cheese , fruit juice , fruit and nuts together. Add to jello mixture. Let chill until thick , then fold in Cool Whip. (If this is to be molded , 1 envelope plain gelatin may be added with dry jello.)', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. orange/pineapple jello', '1 c. boiling water', '2 c. miniature marshmallows', '1 (8 oz.) Cool Whip', '3 oz. cream cheese , softened', '1 small can crushed pineapple', '1 can mandarin oranges', '1 c. nuts (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2224, ' Pour dry pudding over undrained pineapple , then mix. Add nuts and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. instant pistachio pudding', '1 (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple (undrained)', '1/2 c. miniature marshmallows', '1/2 c. nuts , chopped', '1 (4 oz.) Cool Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2240, ' After cooking your meat , pour off grease until just bottom of pan is covered. Add salt and pepper. Stir in 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of flour. Cook , stirring constantly , until nice brown roux (just before scorching). Have hot water in bowl ready. Pour about half of water into roux. Mixture will be thin. Cook over medium heat , constantly stirring , until desired consistency is reached. Tastes great with homemade biscuits and scrambled eggs.', ' pan drippings (chicken , beef or pork)', ' self-rising flour', ' hot water', ' salt to taste', ' pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2258, ' Sprinkle brisket with pepper and paprika. Slice onions on top to cover. Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over meat. Marinate overnight. Bake at 300&deg; to 325&deg; for about 3 to 4 hours , depending on oven and thickness of meat. When ready to serve , slice very thinly against the grain and serve with sauce.', '1 c. vinegar', '3 Tbsp. prepared mustard', '1 small can tomato sauce', '1 tsp. garlic salt', ' pepper and paprika', '4 lb. beef brisket', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire', ' dash of Tabasco', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '1 bay leaf', ' sliced onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2259, ' ', '4 chicken breasts', '2 cans mixed vegetables', '1 can chicken broth', '1 can cream of chicken soup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2260, ' Boil chicken in large deep pot in salted water until tender. Remove bones and skin; cut into bite sized pieces and place in a well-greased 3-quart casserole (Pyrex 9 x 13-inch dish is ideal).', '1 (3 lb.) chicken', '2 c. water', '1 Tbsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2261, ' Combine buttermilk , Old Bay , Tabasco sauce , onion , garlic , salt and pepper. Pour over chicken breasts and allow to marinate for 3 to 4 hours. Pour flour onto large plate. Remove chicken breasts from marinade and coat with flour. Place floured chicken on wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove chicken from refrigerator and allow to warm to room temperature (about 15 minutes). In a large frying pan or skillet , heat oil to 370&deg;. Cook chicken breasts one at a time for about 7 to 10 minutes each side until brown and cooked through. Drain chicken breasts on paper towels.', '8 boneless , skinless chicken breasts', '2 c. buttermilk', '2 Tbsp. Old Bay seasoning', '1 tsp. Tabasco sauce', '1 small onion , minced', '1 clove garlic , minced', ' salt and pepper', '1 c. flour', '1 c. vegetable oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2262, ' Heat 1/4 cup margarine in heavy saucepan. Add onion and saut&eacute; 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Add rice and stir until rice just begins to brown. Stir in boiling broth. Remove from heat and let stand , covered , for 10 minutes. Add a little more broth if mixture is too dry. Saut&eacute; livers in remaining margarine , after dusting them with flour , until done. Add seasoning. Stir gently into rice mixture.', '1/2 c. margarine', '1 medium onion , minced', '1/2 lb. mushrooms , sliced', ' salt and pepper to taste', '1 c. instant rice', '2 c. chicken broth , boiling', '1/2 lb. chicken livers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2263, ' In a 3-quart casserole dish , combine water , bouillon granules , thyme , rosemary and bay leaves. Rinse chicken; pat dry. Place chicken breast side down in casserole. Cook , covered , on 100% power (High) 10 minutes. Turn chicken over. If using new potatoes , peel a strip around the center; arrange potatoes , onions and carrots around chicken. Cook , covered , on 50% power (Medium) , 30 to 40 minutes or until done , drumsticks move easy in the sockets and vegetables are tender , giving dish a half turn and rearranging vegetables once. Transfer chicken and vegetables to a platter; keep warm. Skim fat from pan juices. Remove bay leaves. Measure 1 cup pan juices into a 4-cup glass. Combine the buttermilk and flour; stir into measure. Cook on High , uncovered , for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened and bubbly , stirring every minute. Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Spoon some of the gravy over meat and vegetables. Garnish with parsley if desired. Pass remaining gravy. Makes 6 servings.', '3/4 c. water', '1 Tbsp. instant chicken bouillon , grated', '1/2 tsp. dried thyme , crushed', '1/2 tsp. dried rosemary , crushed', '2 bay leaves', '3 to 3 1/2 lb. broiler/fryer chicken', '3 medium red potatoes , peeled and quartered', '1 lb. whole tiny new potatoes', '2 medium onions , sliced', '1 c. carrots , sliced 1/4-inch thick', '1/2 c. buttermilk', '1/4 c. all-purpose flour', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2264, ' ', '8 to 10 chicken breasts (boneless)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2265, ' Cook broccoli about 10 minutes , until almost tender. Drain and arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with chicken; set aside.', '1 1/2 to 2 lb. fresh broccoli or 2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen broccoli spears', '1 1/2 to 2 c. cooked chicken , cut into strips', '1/4 c. margarine', '1/4 c. flour', '1/4 tsp. salt', '2 chicken bouillon cubes , dissolved in 2 c. hot water', '1 1/2 c. shredded cheese', '1 tsp. Worcestershire', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2266, ' Melt butter in skillet over medium heat. Cut chicken in small strips and put in butter. Cut up green peppers and onions and put in skillet to simmer. Cook over medium-low heat until chicken is done , about 15 minutes. Warm tortillas in microwave and serve with chicken mixture , sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.', '4 chicken breasts', '2 green peppers', '2 onions', '3/4 stick butter', ' tortillas (soft)', ' shredded cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2267, ' Wash chicken and place in a large pot with enough water to cover well. Add salt , pepper , carrot and celery. Bring to a boil; lower heat and cook at a gentle boil for about 45 minutes to an hour. Be sure to add more water if it gets low.', '1 whole chicken (3 to 4 lb.)', '1 small carrot', '1 stalk celery', '3 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '3 c. flour', '1/2 c. shortening', '1/2 c. milk', '1/2 stick butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2268, ' Halve or quarter chickens and dry well. Place in shallow pan. Mix together the salad oil , minced garlic and paprika. Pour over chicken and marinate for 3 or 4 hours , turning the chickens every half hour. Remove from pan and season with salt and pepper. Place chickens in broiler pan with inside upwards and place broiler about 8-inches from broiler unit. Baste frequently with the basting sauce. Place oven control at 350&deg; and cook until tender. Turn chickens the last 15 minutes of cooking with skin side upwards for skin to brown.', '2 fryers (1 1/2 to 2 lb.)', '2 c. salad oil', ' salt and pepper to taste', '2 or 3 cloves garlic', '2 tsp. paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2269, ' Boil chicken for about 30 to 45 minutes; drain and cool. Tear chicken into thin pieces. Add cream cheese. Sprinkle salt over entire chicken. Add about 1 tablespoon pepper. Add almonds. Cut up onion and add. Stir in milk. Melt butter in microwave. Open crescent rolls and add mixture , everything except butter , onto crescent rolls , usually a teaspoon. Close rolls and put on baking pan. Pour melted butter over rolls and bake at 350&deg; for about 10 minutes or until brown.', '4 skinless chicken breasts', '1 onion', '1 pkg. almonds , slivered', '1 pkg. cream cheese', '1 c. milk', '1 Tbsp. butter', '4 cans crescent rolls', ' desired amounts of salt and pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2270, ' Heat oven to 400&deg;. In small plastic bag , combine flour and red pepper; coat chicken. Bake 20 minutes. Mix butter , hot pepper sauce and barbecue sauce with orange juice. Pour half of mixture over chicken. Broil 10 minutes. Turn chicken; pour rest of sauce on. Broil again until crisp.', '1 1/2 c. barbecue sauce', '1/2 tsp. red pepper', '1/2 c. orange juice', '1/4 c. butter , melted', '1/2 tsp. hot pepper sauce', '1/2 c. flour', '6 lb. chicken wings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2271, ' Rinse chicken under running cold water; drain and pat dry with paper towel. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Combine crumbs and herbs. Brush all sides of chicken with oil; then roll each piece in crumb mixture until coated on all sides. Spread honey mixture on each piece of chicken and roll into a ball. Make a cup of foil to hold each piece of chicken. Place in baking dish. Pour wine over each piece of chicken. Then generously cover top of chicken with more honey sauce , about 1 1/2 tablespoons for each piece. Place in 375&deg; oven and bake , uncovered , for 45 minutes or until golden brown.', '3 chicken breasts , skinned , split and boned', ' seasoned salt and pepper', '1 c. coarse bread crumbs', '1/2 tsp. thyme', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. oregano', '1/2 c. white wine', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2272, ' Brown chicken in butter. Put in large baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and salt. Add mushrooms , water , soup and wine to butter left in skillet. Cook about 5 minutes. Pour over chicken in baking dish. Bake at 325&deg; for 1 1/2 hours.', '12 chicken breast halves', '1 large can sliced mushrooms , drained', '1 stick butter or margarine', '1 c. white wine', '2 cans cream of chicken soup', '1/2 can water', ' salt and paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2273, ' Make 1 to 2 days ahead of time the honey mustard dip so it has time to let the flavors blend. You do this by mixing honey and mustard together well and store in airtight container. Refrigerate.', '1/2 c. honey', '1/4 c. Dijon mustard', '4 (4 oz.) skinless , boneless chicken breasts', '1 c. all-purpose flour', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '3/4 c. milk', '1 c. vegetable oil for frying', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2274, ' Thoroughly mix meat loaf ingredients. Pack into loaf pan. Bake at 350&deg; for one hour or until done. Drain excess grease from pan. Mix topping ingredients; spread on meat loaf. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer. Remove from oven. Let sit 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.', '2 lb. ground beef', ' fresh bread crumbs (about 4 slices)', '2 eggs', '1 small onion , finely chopped', '1/2 c. milk', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2275, ' Combine first two ingredients in a Dutch oven or a large saucepan. Brown meat; drain off fat. Add next 12 ingredients; stir to blend. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours , stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf. Serve with crackers. Makes 6 servings.', '1 1/2 lb. hamburger', '2 medium onions', '1 (28 oz.) can tomatoes', '1 (6 oz.) can tomato paste', '1 c. water', '1 beef bouillon cube', '1 can red kidney beans', '2 Tbsp. diced green peppers', '2 cloves garlic', '2 tsp. salt', '2 tsp. oregano', '2 tsp. chili powder', '1/2 tsp. crushed red pepper', '1 bay leaf', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2276, ' Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over meatballs and bake at 350&deg; for 1 hour.', '3 lb. ground beef', '1 can evaporated milk', '2 c. quick oatmeal', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '2 Tbsp. chili powder', '2 c. ketchup', '2 c. brown sugar', '2 Tbsp. liquid smoke', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '1/2 c. chopped onion', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2278, ' Make hamburger patties. Saut&eacute; onions and patties over medium heat. When patties are done , pour soup over them after draining grease off. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 medium onion', '2 cans cream of mushroom soup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `ingredients` (`recid`, `method`, `ing1`, `ing2`, `ing3`, `ing4`, `ing5`, `ing6`, `ing7`, `ing8`, `ing9`, `ing10`, `ing11`, `ing12`, `ing13`, `ing14`, `ing15`, `ing16`, `ing17`, `ing18`, `ing19`, `ing20`, `ing21`, `ing22`, `ing23`, `ing24`) VALUES
(2279, ' Mix all ingredients thoroughly. It''s easier to mix , then knead it , as you would bread , to spread the seasonings throughout the meat. Pack into a glass bowl , cover and refrigerate 24 hours. Remove from the refrigerator; mix well again and refrigerate for another 24 hours. Repeat for a total of 4 days.', '5 lb. ground beef (cheap brand , not lean ground)', '5 Tbsp. curing salt (Morton &quot;Tender Quick&quot;)', '2 Tbsp. garlic powder (do not use garlic salt)', '1 Tbsp. whole peppercorns', '2 Tbsp. mustard seed or more to taste', '1 Tbsp. cayenne pepper or more to taste', '1 Tbsp. coarsely ground pepper (may use 2 Tbsp. and no whole peppercorns , if desired)', '2 Tbsp. liquid smoke or more to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2282, ' In a Dutch oven over medium heat , cook beef , onion , celery and green pepper until the meat is no longer pink and the vegetables are tender; drain. Add the next 9 ingredients; mix well. Simmer , uncovered , for 35 to 40 minutes , stirring occasionally. Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto each bun.', '2 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '2 celery ribs with leaves , chopped', '1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1 2/3 c. canned , crushed tomatoes', '1/4 c. ketchup', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '1 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 Tbsp. steak sauce', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '1/4 tsp. ground mustard', '1/4 tsp. paprika', '8 to 10 hamburger buns', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2283, ' Press and flatten biscuits onto bottom and sides of a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside. In a skillet over medium heat , cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. In a bowl , beat eggs. Add spinach and mushrooms; mix well. Stir in cheese , garlic powder , salt , pepper and beef mixture; mix well. Spoon into prepared crust. Drizzle with butter. Bake , uncovered , at 375&deg; for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned. Yield: 6 servings.', '2 (7 1/2 oz.) tubes refrigerated buttermilk biscuits', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. finely chopped onion', '2 eggs', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped spinach , thawed and squeezed dry', '1 (4 oz.) can mushroom stems and pieces , drained', '4 oz. crumbled Feta or shredded Monterey Jack cheese', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', '1 1/2 tsp. garlic powder', ' salt and pepper to taste', '1 to 2 Tbsp. butter or margarine , melted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2284, ' Cook the macaroni and drain. Brown the ground beef and drain. Combine the macaroni , the cooked ground beef , mushroom pieces , sliced black olives and enough spaghetti sauce to make a Sloppy Joes consistency. Heat to simmering. Add the cubed cheese and continue heating only until the cheese starts to melt. Remove from heat and serve with garlic bread.', '1 1/2 c. elbow macaroni', '1 can sliced mushrooms', '1 large jar your favorite prepared spaghetti sauce', '1 loaf garlic bread', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 can pitted black olives', '1/4 lb. cubed mild Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2285, ' Place sliced onion in a medium nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until onion is limp and golden , stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low and add 1/4 cup chili sauce and grape jelly. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender and thoroughly heated. Combine beef and next 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well. Divide mixture into 4 equal portions , shaping each into a 1/2-inch thick patty. Prepare grill or broiler. Place patties on grill rack or broiler pan coated with cooking spray and cook 4 minutes on each side or until done. Line the bottom halves of each bun with a lettuce leaf; top with a patty , 1/4 cup onion mixture and top half of bun.', '2 c. thinly sliced onions , separated into rings', ' vegetable cooking spray', '1/4 c. chili sauce', '2 Tbsp. grape jelly', '1 lb. ground round', '1/4 c. dry bread crumbs', '1/4 c. chili sauce', '1 Tbsp. instant minced onion', '1/4 tsp. ground pepper', '1 garlic clove , minced', '4 (1 1/2 oz.) hamburger buns , split', '4 curly leaf lettuce leaves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2286, ' Mix well with hands and make patties. Have the grill nice and hot. Cook until done.', '1 1/2 lb. lean ground chuck', '1 pkg. Knorr''s dry beef/mushroom or onion soup mix', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 green pepper , chopped', ' Worcestershire sauce (about 1/4 c. , more or less)', ' garlic powder', ' seasonings to your taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2287, ' In a skillet , fry ground beef and onions. Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and corn chips. Bring to a boil; reduce heat , cover and simmer for 20 minutes , stirring occasionally. Serve over corn chips , then top with cheese.', '1 lb. ground beef', '3/4 c. chopped onion', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes , cut up and drained', '1 (15 oz.) can kidney beans (undrained)', '1/2 c. uncooked rice', '1/2 c. water', '3 Tbsp. chopped green pepper', '1 1/2 tsp. chili powder', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '3/4 c. shredded cheese', ' corn chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2292, ' Place turnip greens in a large pot; sprinkle sugar on greens. Lay turnip slices on top of greens. Lay pork chops on greens and turnips. Pour grease from fried white bacon over greens , chops and turnips. Add water to pot; cook on high until water starts to boil. Reduce to low heat; cook , covered , about 45 to 60 minutes , until greens are done.', '6 pork chops (center cut)', ' greens from 6 turnips , cleaned', '6 medium turnips , washed , peeled and sliced 1/4-inch thick', '1 tsp. sugar', ' grease from 10 pieces white bacon , fried (salt pork)', '2 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2293, ' Brown pork chops in skillet with oil. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside. Combine soup , milk , sour cream , pepper and salt. Stir in potatoes , 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onion rings. Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange pork chops over potatoes. Bake at 350&deg; for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onion rings. Bake , uncovered , 5 more minutes.', '6 pork chops', ' vegetable oil or Pam', ' seasoned salt', '1 can cream of celery soup', '1/2 c. milk', '1/2 c. sour cream', '1/4 tsp. black pepper', '1 (24 oz.) pkg. hash browns , thawed', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 c. Durkee French fried onion rings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2296, ' Mix all ingredients well. Cut about 1 or 1 1/2-inch holes all over in roast. Stuff ingredients in holes and bake in oven for about 1 1/2 or 2 hours at 350&deg;.', '5 or 6 lb. roast beef', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1/2 bell pepper', '4 cloves garlic', '1/2 c. celery', ' salt and pepper', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '2 jalapeno peppers (without seeds)', ' few drops of hot sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2297, ' In a 6-quart saucepot , in hot oil , brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat. Stir in mushroom soup , onion soup mix and 1 cup water. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 2 hours. Add vegetables. Cover and cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender. Remove roast and vegetables. Stir flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth. Gradually stir into soup mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens , stirring constantly.', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '3 1/2 to 4 lb. beef round or chuck roast', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of mushroom soup', '1 pouch Campbell''s dry onion quality soup and recipe mix', '1 1/4 c. water', '6 medium potatoes , quartered', '6 carrots , cut into 2-inch pieces', '2 Tbsp. all-purpose flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2298, ' Put all ingredients , except cornstarch and water , into slow cooker (crock-pot) for six hours or so. (I cook mine during work hours.) Bring to a boil just before serving. Mix cornstarch and water and add to meat mixture. Boil until thickened. Delicious served over rice or noodles.', '2 lb. sirloin steak (bite size pieces)', '1 large onion , chopped', '1 can beef bouillon', '1 c. non-alcoholic cooking sherry', '1 bay leaf', '2 Tbsp. grated lemon rind', ' salt and pepper to taste', '1/4 c. cornstarch', '3 Tbsp. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2300, ' In a large bowl , beat egg. Stir in 1/3 cup of soup , bread crumbs , salt and pepper. Add beef; mix gently. Shape into 6 oval patties. Brown in a skillet over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Remove and set aside; discard drippings. In the skillet , combine flour and water until smooth; add ketchup , Worcestershire sauce , mustard and remaining soup. Bring to a boil. Return patties to skillet. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Serve patties and gravy over noodles.', '1 egg', '1 (10 1/2 oz.) can French onion soup (undiluted)', '1/2 c. bread crumbs', '1/4 tsp. salt', ' pinch of pepper', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '1 Tbsp. all-purpose flour', '1/4 c. water', '1/4 c. ketchup', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 tsp. prepared mustard', '6 c. hot cooked egg noodles', ' chopped parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2301, ' Slice meat into 4 x 1/4-inch strips and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a shallow dish. Add steak , coating well. Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Remove steak from refrigerator and place on skewers. Add fresh vegetables if you like. Grill 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until desired level of doneness is reached. Baste frequently with marinade.', '1 1/2 lb. steak or chicken , partially frozen', '1/2 c. soy sauce', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '2 Tbsp. honey', '2 Tbsp. wine vinegar', '1 clove of garlic', '1/2 tsp. ground ginger', '1/8 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2302, ' Season meat with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Mix flour with 1 teaspoon pepper in shallow plate. Dredge each steak in flour. Dip in beaten egg , then dredge in flour again. Heat lard or oil in large , heavy skillet until hot. Fry steak 3 to 4 minutes on each side , until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the oil. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the dredging flour into oil. Cook over medium heat 1 minute , scraping up browned bits from bottom of skillet. Stir in milk , a little at a time , until gravy is smooth. Cook , stirring frequently , 3 to 4 minutes , until thickened and bubbly. Add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt; gravy should be quite peppery. Serve steaks smothered in gravy.', '4 (4 to 5 oz.) cube steaks', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 1/2 to 1 3/4 tsp. pepper', '1 c. all-purpose flour', '2 eggs , lightly beaten', '1/4 c. lard or vegetable oil', '1 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
