(2454, ' Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Mix cake mix , margarine , 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts. Press 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350&deg; for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chips over this crust; pour the caramel mix on and dab the remaining cake mixture on top. Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes at 350&deg;. Let cool. Cut in squares.', '1 box German chocolate cake mix', '3/4 c. melted margarine', '1 small can evaporated milk', '1 (14 oz.) pkg. vanilla caramels', '1 c. chopped nuts', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. chocolate chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2455, ' Beat egg. In a small mixing bowl , combine the milk , egg , sugar and melted margarine. Add orange juice , rind , chopped apples (skins may be left on) and vanilla. Sift together flour , salt and baking powder. Stir into milk mixture with a spoon until blended. Do not overbeat. Preheat oil in a skillet to 350&deg;. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown. Turn so they brown evenly. Allow to cool.', '1 c. milk', '1 egg , beaten', '4 Tbsp. margarine', '1/4 c. sugar', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 orange (rind and juice)', '1 c. apples , chopped , but not too fine', '3 c. cake flour', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1 tsp. vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2460, ' Melt margarine in a heavy pan. Add beaten eggs , sugar , dates , vanilla and nuts. Cook 10 minutes , stirring all the time. Add Rice Krispies. When cool , roll in small balls in coconut.', '1 stick margarine', '2 eggs', '1 c. Rice Krispies', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 c. sugar', '1 c. chopped dates', '1/2 c. nuts', '1 can coconut', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2464, ' Brush bread lightly with melted margarine. Sprinkle evenly with one-third of the sugar substitute and cinnamon. Cut bread slices into quarters. Layer bread and raisins in a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.', '6 slices white bread , crusts removed', '2 Tbsp. reduced-calorie margarine , melted', '3/4 c. sugar substitute , divided', '1 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1/2 c. raisins', ' vegetable cooking spray', '4 eggs , lightly beaten', '2 c. skim milk', '1 tsp. vanilla extract', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2480, ' Pour sprinkles into a bowl. Crush some graham crackers into another bowl. These are what you will use to decorate your candy. Combine one 6 ounce bag of chocolate morsels with 2 teaspoons vegetable oil in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 1 minute , until melted; stir. Poke a bamboo skewer or a fork into a marshmallow. Dip into chocolate , coating it well. Hold it over bowl to let excess chocolate drip off. Coat marshmallow with sprinkles or graham cracker crumbs. Slide marshmallow off skewer onto a waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Repeat. Let set at room temperature about 1 hour. Wrap candies in a pretty box for a special gift. Yield: About 20 marshmallow candies.', ' candy sprinkles', ' graham crackers , crushed', '1 bag chocolate morsels (6 oz.)', '1 bag large marshmallows', ' bamboo skewer', '2 tsp. vegetable oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2481, ' Place ample helping of ham , cheeses , lettuce , tomato , onion , pickles and peppers on bun. Add Salad Supreme , salt , pepper , olive oil , vinegar and mustard to taste.', ' chipped ham', ' Swiss cheese', ' American cheese', ' lettuce', ' tomato', ' onion', ' pickles', ' jalapeno peppers', ' Salad Supreme seasoning', ' sub buns', ' salt and pepper', ' olive oil', ' vinegar', ' mustard', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2488, ' Bring cheese to room temperature. Add remaining ingredients , except paprika , and mix thoroughly. Spread waxed paper heavily with paprika; roll cheese into ball. It will be soft. Cover with paprika; wrap in waxed paper. Place ball in refrigerator until firm. Serve with crackers.', '1/2 lb. spreadable Cheddar cheese', '1/4 c. chicken broth', ' garlic powder', ' dry mustard', ' pepper', ' parsley flakes', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2489, ' With electric mixer or rotary beater , gradually blend soup into cream cheese. Beat just until smooth. Mix in remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve as a dip with crackers or chips. Makes about 2 1/3 cups dip.', '1 can Campbell''s cream of shrimp soup', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1/4 c. finely chopped green pepper', '2 Tbsp. finely chopped onion', ' dash of hot pepper sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2491, ' Mix beef , bread crumbs , egg and salt; shape into 50 small meat balls (1/2 inch). Place in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2 inches). Broil until browned; turn once. Spoon off fat. Meanwhile , in saucepan , cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over meat balls. Cover; bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes. Makes 50 meat balls for appetizers.', '1 lb. ground beef*', '2 Tbsp. bread crumbs', '1 egg , slightly beaten', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. finely chopped onion', '1/3 c. finely chopped green pepper', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can Campbell''s tomato soup', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '1 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. prepared mustard', ' dash of hot pepper sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2493, ' Bring soup to boil. Add cream cheese. Cook until melted. Add gelatin and cool in refrigerator. Add other ingredients and pour into lightly oiled pan. Refrigerate until firm. Can double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.', '1 can tomato soup , diluted', '3 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '2 Tbsp. plain gelatin , dissolved in 1/2 c. water', '1 c. mayonnaise', '1 1/2 to 2 c. chopped celery', '1 c. chopped green pepper', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 (6 1/2 oz.) can shrimp', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2494, ' Place the party rye bread onto cookie sheet. Brush each little bread with the melted butter. Open artichoke can; drain and cut each artichoke into sixths.', '1 loaf party rye bread', '1/2 stick melted butter', '1 can artichokes (not in oil)', '2 c. shredded mild Cheddar cheese', '1 to 1 1/2 c. real mayonnaise', '1/2 tsp. dill weed', '1/4 tsp. garlic salt', '1/4 tsp. lemon pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2495, ' Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Put the soup , mayonnaise , cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce into saucepan over low heat. (Or use double boiler.) Stir constantly until cheese is melted. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Remove from heat. Add onion , celery and crab meat. Pour into a greased mold and chill overnight. Unmold onto a dish or tray. Serve with crackers.', '2 Tbsp. unflavored gelatin', '1/4 c. cold water', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', '1 c. mayonnaise', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '6 to 8 oz. cream cheese', '1 medium onion , chopped fine', '1 c. celery , chopped fine', '1 (7 3/4 oz.) can crab meat , drained or 5 to 6 sticks imitation crab legs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2496, ' With electric mixer or rotary beater , gradually blend soup , chili sauce and onion into cream cheese. Chill. Serve with crackers or chips. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.', '1 can Campbell''s New England clam chowder soup', '1/4 c. chili sauce', '2 Tbsp. finely chopped onion', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2497, ' Rub inside of fondue pot or saucepan with cut edge of garlic , then discard. In fondue pot , simmer apple juice. Blend in soup. Combine cheese and cornstarch; stir into soup mixture. Heat until cheese melts; stir now and then. Spear bread with fondue fork and dip into fondue. Makes about 4 cups.', '1 large clove garlic , cut in half', '1 c. apple juice', '1 can Campbell''s Cheddar cheese soup', '1 lb. natural Swiss cheese , cubed or shredded', '3 Tbsp. cornstarch', ' French or Italian bread cubes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2499, ' Saut&eacute; onion in butter. Cook broccoli. Put broccoli , onion , soup , cheese and mushrooms in large pan and heat until bubbly. Serve with dip-size corn chips.', '1/2 large onion , chopped', '1/2 stick butter', '3 (10 oz.) pkg. chopped broccoli', '2 cans cream of chicken soup', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. Rondelle semi-soft garlic cheese', '3 oz. mushrooms , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2500, ' Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled; drain excess grease. In crock-pot , melt cheeses. Add meat , soup , tomatoes , green chilies and onions; mix well. Makes a large amount and can be frozen. Serve with chips. Serves many.', '1 lb. sausage (hot)', '1 lb. hamburger (lean)', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1 lb. hot Velveeta', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes', '1 can chilies and green peppers', '1 onion , chopped fine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2506, ' Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.', '1 c. sour cream', '1 c. mayonnaise', '2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese', '1 pkg. Knorr vegetable soup mix', '1 Tbsp. finely chopped onion', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped spinach (uncooked) , thawed and liquid squeezed out', '1 (8 oz.) can water chestnuts , chopped coarsely', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2507, ' Brown ground beef , onion , garlic and salt; drain and add remaining ingredients. Heat in crock-pot. Dip chips , crackers , bread , etc.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. onion , chopped', '1 clove garlic , mashed', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 (8 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1/4 c. catsup', '1/2 tsp. oregano , crushed', '1 tsp. sugar', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '1/3 c. Parmesan cheese', '1 green chili pepper or 1 small jalapeno pepper (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `ingredients` (`recid`, `method`, `ing1`, `ing2`, `ing3`, `ing4`, `ing5`, `ing6`, `ing7`, `ing8`, `ing9`, `ing10`, `ing11`, `ing12`, `ing13`, `ing14`, `ing15`, `ing16`, `ing17`, `ing18`, `ing19`, `ing20`, `ing21`, `ing22`, `ing23`, `ing24`) VALUES
(2520, ' Place soup bone and beef in large pot (8 quart). Add water; bring to boil; skim. Add tomatoes , sauce , onions , parsley , garlic , salt , pepper and basil; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add carrots and celery; cover and simmer 1/2 hour. Remove meat and bones; trim fat off meat and discard. Cut meat into pieces and return to soup. Heat to boiling; add uncooked pasta , green beans and peas. Simmer 20 minutes. Stir in kidney beans; heat to boiling. Makes about 6 quarts.', '1 (2 lb.) beef soup bone', '2 lb. shin beef , cut up', '4 qt. water', '1 1/2 lb. tomatoes , peeled', '1 (15 oz.) can tomato sauce', '2 medium onions , cut up', '1/4 c. chopped parsley', '2 cloves crushed garlic', '2 Tbsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '2 tsp. basil leaves , crushed', '2 c. sliced carrots', '2 c. sliced celery', '4 c. uncooked shells or macaroni', '2 pkg. Italian green beans', '10 oz. peas', '1 lb. can red kidney beans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2521, ' Wash and peel 1 quart mushrooms and dice. Stir into them 1 1/2 quarts of good rich stock (veal or chicken). Thicken with 1 tablespoon flour creamed with 1 tablespoon butter , 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper. At the last moment , add a bit of whipped cream and croutons.', '1 qt. mushrooms', '1 1/2 qt. good rich stock (veal or chicken)', '1 Tbsp. flour', '1 Tbsp. butter', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', ' whipped cream', ' croutons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2522, ' Mix bouillon cubes , water , onion , celery and potatoes together. Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes. Add remaining vegetables and cook until tender. Add cream of chicken soup and 1 cup water. Add Velveeta cheese and cook slowly until all cheese is melted. Sprinkle in bacon crumbs.', '4 chicken bouillon cubes', '1 qt. water', '1 c. diced onion', '1 c. diced celery', '2 c. cubed raw potatoes', '1/2 c. diced carrots', '1 small pkg. frozen cauliflower', '1 small pkg. frozen broccoli', '2 cans cream of chicken soup', '1 to 2 lb. Velveeta cheese', '5 to 6 strips crisp bacon , crumbled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2524, ' Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Mix soup with milk; stir constantly while heating. Don''t boil. Add broccoli , pepper to taste , butter and herb. Heat to bubbly and serve.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen broccoli , chopped', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', '1 1/2 c. milk', ' black pepper to taste', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', ' tarragon (if desired)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2525, ' Peel and slice onions thinly. Saut&eacute; in butter in large saucepan. Add tomatoes , beef broth and spices. Cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Serve with toasted French bread.', '2 large sweet Spanish onions (about 6 c.) , sliced', '1/2 c. butter', '2 (14 1/2 oz.) cans stewed tomatoes', '3 (10 1/2 oz.) cans beef broth', '1/2 tsp. basil', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2527, ' Cook vegetables in enough water to keep from sticking until tender. Add chicken broth and seasonings. Add Accent while cooking.', '2 medium potatoes', ' bottoms of 3 large leeks', '1/2 c. celery , chopped', '1/2 c. carrots , grated', '1/2 c. onion , chopped', '1 pt. or more chicken broth', '1 small clove garlic', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' Accent', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2528, ' Slice onions. Melt butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven. Slowly cook onions in butter until lightly browned , about 20 minutes. Add bouillon cubes , water and chicken broth to onions. Cover and simmer 2 hours , stirring occasionally. Add Worcestershire sauce , salt and white and black peppers to soup. Stir. Shred cheese.', '2 lb. red onions , peeled and halved', '3/4 c. butter or margarine', '6 beef bouillon cubes', '2 qt. water', '1 c. chicken broth', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. salt', ' dash of white pepper', ' dash of black pepper', '8 oz. chilled Swiss or Gruyere cheese', '1/2 loaf French bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2529, ' Boil chicken and onions until tender meat can be removed from bones. While chicken cools , add beans , potatoes and okra to broth and cook for 45 minutes. Remove chicken from bones; remove skin and chop chicken into small pieces. Add to beans along with corn and tomato juice. (Amount of juice depends upon the amount of chicken broth you have.) Season and simmer for at least another hour , adding the soup during the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking time. Freezes well.', '1 (3 lb.) fryer', '4 medium onions', '1 1/2 qt. fresh or frozen butter beans', '3 or 4 medium potatoes', ' okra (optional)', '1 qt. corn', '1 qt. or more tomato juice', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' red pepper to taste', '2 cans alphabet soup , undiluted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2530, ' Combine apples , marshmallows , celery and walnuts. Add enough salad dressing to moisten. Toss lightly. Chill. Add additional salad dressing and garnish with apple slices before serving , if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.', '3 c. chopped apples', '2 c. miniature marshmallows', '1 c. thin celery slices', '1/2 c. chopped walnuts', ' Miracle Whip salad dressing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2533, ' Cook green beans until done , but still firm. Drain. Add onions , salt , pepper , Italian seasoning , oil and vinegar. Toss. Serve at room temperature or chilled.', '2 c. fresh green beans', '1/4 c. onions , sliced', ' salt', ' pepper', ' dash of Italian seasoning', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '3/4 Tbsp. wine vinegar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2534, ' Fold dry pudding mix into whipped topping. Add pineapple and juice , marshmallows and nuts. Refrigerate.', '1 (9 oz.) carton whipped topping', '1 box instant pistachio pudding', '1 (1 lb.) can crushed pineapple and juice', '1 c. miniature marshmallows', '1/2 c. nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2535, ' In small saucepan , cook garlic in olive oil; combine in a large bowl with soup , water and vinegar. Chill for 4 hours. Serve in chilled bowls. Pass chilled vegetables and croutons for garnish. Makes about 6 1/2 cups.', '2 medium cloves garlic , minced', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '3 (10 3/4 oz.) cans Campbell''s tomato soup', '3 c. cold water', '1/4 c. wine vinegar', '2 c. chopped cucumber', '1 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. chopped onion croutons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2536, ' In large saucepan , combine first 4 ingredients. Cook over low heat 10 minutes; stir now and then. Add whitefish; cook 5 minutes more. Remove bay leaf. Makes about 9 1/2 cups.', '3 cans Campbell''s chunky clam chowder soup', '1 lb. (15 to 20) large shrimp , shelled and deveined', '1 medium bay leaf', '1/4 tsp. hot pepper sauce', '1 lb. whitefish , cut in 2-inch pieces', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2537, ' Season beef with salt and pepper; shape into 18 meat balls. In saucepan , brown meat balls (use shortening if necessary); cook over low heat 5 minutes. Pour off fat. Stir in soup and water. Heat; stir now and then. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.', '1/2 lb. ground beef', ' dash of salt and pepper', '1 can Campbell''s bean with bacon , minestrone , tomato or vegetable soup', '1 soup can water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2538, ' In large saucepan , brown beef; cook with green pepper , onion and chili powder until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat , stirring occasionally. Makes about 6 1/2 cups.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 Tbsp. chili powder', '2 cans Campbell''s chili beef soup', '1 soup can water', '1 c. chopped canned tomatoes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2539, ' Bring sugar , vinegar and oil to a boil and , while hot , pour over cabbage mixture. Do not stir until cold. Cover and put in refrigerator. Will keep for days. Serves 10 to 12.', '1 large head cabbage , shredded', '1 medium green pepper , chopped', '1 large onion , chopped', '1/2 tsp. mustard seed', '1/2 tsp. celery seed', '1 c. sugar', '1 c. white vinegar', '2/3 c. salad oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2543, ' Cook bacon until crisp; drain. Heat drippings; blend in flour , sugar , salt , celery seed and pepper. Gradually blend in broth and vinegar. Cook , stirring constantly , until slightly thickened. Combine potatoes and bacon bits. Pour sauce over; toss gently and put in serving dish. Put in oven at 325&deg; to reheat for 1/2 hour.', '1/2 lb. cooked bacon , diced', '1/3 c. bacon drippings', '1 Tbsp. flour', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. celery seed', '1/4 tsp. ground pepper', '1/2 c. chicken broth', '1/2 c. white vinegar', '6 c. sliced and cooked potatoes (about 3 lb.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2544, ' ', '2 c. powdered sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '3 eggs', '2 sticks oleo', '2 to 3 bananas', '1 large can crushed pineapple , drained', '1 large carton Cool Whip', '1/2 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2550, ' Skin , halve and bone chicken breasts. Cut chicken into 1 inch pieces. In a small bowl stir soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in chicken broth , ginger root , sugar , salt and red pepper. Set aside. Preheat a wok over high heat; add cooking oil. Stir-fry green peppers and green onions in hot oil for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Remove from wok. Add walnuts to wok; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until just golden. Remove from wok. Add half of the chicken to the hot wok; stir-fry 2 minutes. Remove from wok. Stir-fry remaining chicken 2 minutes. Return all chicken to wok. Stir soy mixture into chicken. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in vegetables and walnuts; cover and cook 1 minute more. Serve chicken and vegetables at once with hot cooked rice. Garnish with whole red peppers and fresh cilantro , if desired.', '1 1/3 lb. whole chicken breasts', '3 Tbsp. soy sauce', '2 tsp. cornstarch', '2 Tbsp. chicken broth', '1 tsp. each grated ginger root and sugar', '1/2 tsp. each salt and crushed red pepper', '2 Tbsp. cooking oil', '2 medium green peppers , cut into 3/4 inch pieces', '4 green onions , bias-sliced into 1 inch lengths', '1 c. walnut halves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2551, ' Roast meat uncovered at 350&deg; until internal reading is 150&deg; , about 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Cool and slice. Add water and bouillon to pan drippings; stir in seasonings and green peppers. Simmer 15 minutes (do not allow to boil). Put sliced beef into marinade and refrigerate overnight. Reheat to serve. Can be frozen.', '3 to 5 lb. beef roast', '2 to 3 c. water', '2 to 3 pkg. beef bouillon', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', ' garlic powder to taste', '1 tsp. marjoram', '1 tsp. thyme', '1 tsp. oregano', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', ' hot pepper sauce to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2552, ' Skin fat from chicken pieces. In a 5-quart pot , heat 4 tablespoonfuls oil and fry onions until browned. Remove and set aside. In the same oil , fry coconut. Now add the chicken , onions , ginger and garlic and fry until the chicken is slightly brown. Do all this on moderate heat , adding a little more oil if necessary. Now add the yogurt , tomatoes , chili powder , cloves , cardamon , cumin , coriander and peppercorn powder. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Now add the nutmeg , cinnamon and paprika. Stir thoroughly , reduce heat to low and simmer until chicken is tender. Sprinkle fresh chopped coriander leaves on top before serving. Serve with white rice. Serves 6 to 8.', '3 1/2 lb. chicken pieces', '5 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '2 c. finely sliced onions', '2 Tbsp. grated coconut', '3/4 tsp. ginger powder', '3/4 tsp. garlic powder', '5 Tbsp. yogurt', '1 1/2 c. chopped tomatoes', '1/2 tsp. chili powder', '1/4 tsp. cloves', '1/4 tsp. cardamon powder', '1 tsp. ground cumin seed', '1 Tbsp. ground coriander seed', '12 black peppercorns (powdered)', ' pinches of nutmeg and cinnamon powder', '1 1/2 tsp. paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2553, ' Remove bone and fat from steak. Cut meat into thin , narrow strips. Dredge in flour; using large skillet , quickly brown meat on all sides in hot oil. Add onions , broth , thyme , mushrooms and liquid from mushrooms. Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in sour cream. Heat through; do not boil. Serve over hot rice.', '1 lb. lean round steak', '1/4 c. flour , seasoned with salt , pepper and garlic powder', ' flour', '2 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '3/4 c. chopped onion', '1 c. beef broth', '1/2 tsp. thyme', '1 (4 oz.) can sliced mushrooms with liquid', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen peas', '1/2 c. sour cream', '3 to 4 c. hot cooked rice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2554, ' In a saucepan , saut&eacute; onions in butter. Add carrots , potatoes , 1/2 can of soup , parsley and 1/4 teaspoon dill. Cook until partially tender. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper. If using round steak , cut into 4 or 5 pieces and flatten. Place stuffing in center of meat. Roll up , tuck in ends and skewer with toothpicks. Using a skillet , brown roll-ups on all sides in shortening. Remove excess fat. Pour in soup , dill , tomatoes and remaining stuffing. Simmer about an hour , but stir frequently. Add apple juice and simmer for 15 minutes more.', '1/2 c. chopped onions', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '1 c. finely diced carrots', '1 c. finely diced potatoes', '1 can mushroom soup', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley', '1/2 tsp. dill (optional)', '4 cube steaks or 1 1/2 lb. round steak , 1/8-inch thick', ' salt and pepper to taste', '2 Tbsp. shortening', '1 medium size can tomatoes , cut up', '1/2 glass apple juice (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
