(2729, ' Mix milk and cream cheese until blended. Add confectioners sugar and mix until blended. Add maple flavor to taste and nuts , coconut or cocoa cherry flavor. Refrigerate until solid and then dip in chocolate.', '1 can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese', '1/2 lb. confectioners sugar', ' maple flavor to taste', '2 c. peanut butter', ' nuts , coconut or cocoa cherry flavor', ' melted chocolate chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2731, ' Mix gelatin , nuts and shredded coconut with the Eagle Brand milk. Shape into strawberries. Refrigerate until cold (much easier to handle). Dip the top into green sugar. Roll the berry in the red sugar. If desired you can soak slivered almonds in green food coloring and use for stems.', '1 c. ground nuts', '1 can Eagle Brand milk', '1 (7 oz.) pkg. shredded coconut', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry gelatin', '1 box red tinted sugar', '1 box green tinted sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2735, ' For each color desired for dyeing , measure food color , water and vinegar into a small bowl; mix well with a spoon. Leave the spoon in the bowl , so the colors don''t get mixed together from one bowl to another.', '1/4 tsp. of each food color', '3/4 c. boiling water (for each color)', '1 Tbsp. vinegar (for each color)', ' hard-boiled eggs', ' vegetable oil (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2737, ' Mix all these together. Eggs dipped in this mixture will have a pretty marbled coloring.', '1 c. hot water', '1 Tbsp. salad oil', '1 Tbsp. white vinegar', '1 food coloring of your choice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2739, ' ', '1 c. cornstarch', '1/4 c. milk', '2 eggs', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. Accent or monosodium glutamate', ' dash of garlic salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2740, ' Melt butter; add to melted butter the salts , sauces and onion powder. Mix dry ingredients in large containers and place in cake pans or roasters. Pour some of the liquid mixture over it , just enough to slightly dampen. Bake at 250&deg; for 15 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes , adding more liquid if desired.', '1 box Corn Chex', '1 box Wheat Thins', '1 box Twigs', '1 box Rice Chex', '1 box Cheerios', '1 box Cheese Nips', '1 box pretzels', '1 large can mixed nuts', '1 large can Spanish peanuts', '1 large can dry roasted nuts', '4 sticks butter', '2 1/2 tsp. seasoned salt', '4 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1 tsp. onion powder', '2 tsp. garlic salt', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2746, ' Precook ribs in salt , pepper and water for 2 hours. Barbecue over slow coals 15 to 20 minutes. Baste in sauce and serve with remaining sauce.', '3 lb. beef short ribs', '1/2 c. water', '1/3 c. vinegar', '1 tsp. salt', '1 c. chili sauce', '1 (12 oz.) jar pineapple preserves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2749, ' Brown ground beef , bacon and onion. Drain excess fat. Combine and add all other ingredients except the beans. Stir well. Add beans and combine thoroughly. Bake for 1 hour at 350&deg;. Makes 20 to 24 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef (chuck)', '1 lb. bacon , chopped', '1 large onion , chopped', '1/2 c. catsup', '1/2 c. barbecue sauce', '1 tsp. salt', '4 Tbsp. prepared mustard', '4 Tbsp. molasses', '1 tsp. chili powder', '3/4 tsp. pepper', '2 (16 oz.) cans red kidney beans', '2 (16 oz.) cans pork and beans', '2 (16 oz.) cans butter beans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2758, ' Prepare cake mix according to package in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Remove from pan; cool completely. Place cake on wire rack over sheet of waxed paper. Poke cake using fork or end of wooden spoon at 1-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; slowly drizzle over cake. Chill 1 hour.', '1 box yellow or white cake mix', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry gelatin', '1/2 c. boiling water', '1 1/2 c. milk', '3 c. whipped topping', '1 (3 3/8 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding and pie filling', '1 c. blueberries', '1 1/2 c. strawberries , sliced', '1/2 c. miniature marshmallows', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2760, ' Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside at room temperature. Prepare and bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool cake in pan on rack for 25 minutes. Poke deep holes through top of cake with fork. Space holes 1 inch apart. Slowly pour gelatin mixture over cooled cake. Set in refrigerator while preparing frosting.', '1 pkg. Duncan Hines Deluxe fudge marble cake mix', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry flavored gelatin', '3/4 c. boiling water', '1/2 c. cold water', '1 tub Duncan Hines creamy vanilla frosting', '3 oz. cream cheese , softened', '2 tsp. lemon juice', '20 fresh strawberries', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2763, ' At high speed , mix whipping cream until peaks. Add sugar until stiff. Spread cream over top and sides of cake (removed from pan and placed on serving board). Mark 7 1/2 x 5-inch top corner of cake. Place berries in even rows for stars. Alternate rows of strawberries and bananas for stripes , overlapping fruit. Chill until serving , up to 2 hours. Great for 4th of July.', ' any flavor cake mix , prepared as directed and baked in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan', '3 (8 oz.) cartons heavy whipping cream', '1/3 c. powdered sugar', '50 blueberries', '2 pt. strawberries , halved', '3 thinly sliced bananas , tossed in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2767, ' Prepare cake mix and bake in two 8-inch pans , following package directions. When cakes have been removed from pans , let stand on cooling racks at least 2 hours to firm up for easier frosting. Empty container of frosting into medium-sized bowl. Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Gradually beat in black food color , 1/4 teaspoon at a time , until icing is almost black (color darkens upon standing). Place cake on serving plate. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake , smoothing out the sharp edge and rounding top slightly.', '1 pkg. chocolate cake mix', '16 oz. ready-to-spread chocolate frosting', ' black paste food color', '8 (12-inch) black bump chenille (thick and thin) pipe cleaners', '1/2 pair vampire''s teeth', '2 plastic cat''s eyes', ' red ready-to-pipe gel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2768, ' Heat oven to 425&deg;. Divide thawed dough in half; roll and stretch each half into 10 to 12-inch circle on round pizza pan. Turn up edges 1/2 inch and pinch. Brush circles with oil. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Mix tomato sauce , onion , salt , oregano and garlic powder. Pour on circles. Top with Cheddar cheese. Decorate with overlapping pepperoni slices , green pepper strips and olive slices for face. Bake until crust is brown , 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2 pizzas.', '1 (1 lb.) loaf frozen bread dough , thawed', '2 tsp. vegetable oil', '1 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1 (15 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 Tbsp. chopped onion', '1 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. dried oregano leaves', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '4 oz. sliced pepperoni', ' green pepper strips (eyebrows , nose , mouth)', ' olive slices (eyes)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2770, ' Combine and mix well the sugar , brown sugar , pumpkin , salad oil and eggs. Sift together and add flour , soda , salt , nutmeg , cinnamon and ginger. Stir in water. Add pecans and raisins. Mix well and spoon into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350&deg; oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. When done , turn out on a rack to cool. Yields 1 loaf.', '1 c. sugar', '1/2 c. brown sugar', '1 c. cooked pumpkin', '1/2 c. salad oil', '2 eggs , unbeaten', '2 c. flour', '1 tsp. soda', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. nutmeg', '1/2 tsp. cinnamon', '1/4 tsp. ginger', '1/4 c. water', '1/2 c. pecans , chopped', '1 c. raisins (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2776, ' Sift dry ingredients on wax paper. In mixing bowl , combine remaining ingredients and mix well with dry ingredients. Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts. Pour into two greased 8-inch baking pans. Bake 30 minutes in 350&deg; oven. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. Use Brown Sugar Icing and decorate with Halloween candy.', '2 c. cake flour', '3 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. baking soda', '4 Tbsp. melted shortening', '2/3 c. sugar', '2/3 c. brown sugar', '2 beaten eggs', '2/3 c. pumpkin', '1 tsp. maple flavoring', '1/2 tsp. allspice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2784, ' *Tint 1 cup icing green and the remainder tint orange.', '2 boxes favorite cake mix', '1 flat-bottom ice cream cone shell', ' White Icing , made by favorite recipe (or 2 cans icing may be used)*', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2786, ' Mix and spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.', '1 pkg. German chocolate cake mix', '2 beaten eggs', '1 stick margarine , softened', '1 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2795, ' Drain beans and corn. Mix in casserole dish. In separate bowl , mix sour cream , Cheddar cheese and cream of celery soup. Pour on top of beans and corn. Crumble Ritz crackers and cover with melted margarine. Put on top of mixture. Bake , uncovered , for 40 minutes at 350&deg;.', '1 can Shoe Peg corn', '1 can French-style green beans', '1 1/2 containers sour cream', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. sharp Cheddar cheese', '1 can cream of celery soup', '1 stick margarine , melted', '2 rolls Ritz crackers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2797, ' Combine beans , milk , soup , pepper and 1/2 can of French fried onions; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.', '2 (1 lb.) cans cut green beans , drained', '3/4 c. milk', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can condensed cream of mushroom soup', '1/8 tsp. Durkee ground black pepper', '1 (2.8 oz.) can Durkee French fried onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2800, ' Sprinkle chicken with parsley and pepper. Dip in eggs; coat well with bread crumbs. Melt margarine in skillet; brown chicken on all sides. Remove chicken to a large baking dish. Reserve drippings in skillet. Add remaining ingredients to drippings and stir well. Pour sauce over chicken. Bake uncovered at 350&deg; for 40 minutes.', '4 whole chicken breasts , split and skinned', '3 Tbsp. minced parsley', '1/4 tsp. black pepper', '1/4 tsp. red pepper', '2 eggs , beaten', '2/3 c. Italian bread crumbs', '1/2 c. margarine', '2 cans golden mushroom soup , undiluted', '8 oz. sour cream', '1/3 c. dry sherry', '1 (4 oz.) can mushrooms , drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2801, ' Simmer in pan just before serving dinner. Excellent for turkey dressing.', '1 can cream of chicken soup (use broth off giblets instead of water if possible)', '1 boiled egg , sliced or chopped', '1 large helping giblets , cooked and chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2809, ' Mix flour and sugar together; add Karo syrup and eggs. Add melted butter and vanilla. Stir in nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425&deg; for 15 minutes , then at 375&deg; for 30 minutes.', '3/4 c. Karo syrup (light)', '3 eggs , well beaten', '1/2 c. sugar', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1/2 stick butter , melted', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 c. nuts', ' pinch of salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2812, ' Beat 2 minutes the cake mix , cream cheese and milk. Mix in the eggs. Combine. Fold into batter the cranberries , walnuts , sugar and mace. Pour into greased 10 x 4-inch tube or 12-cup Bundt pan. Bake in 350&deg; oven for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 20 minutes; remove from pan. Dust with confectioners sugar. Yield: one 10-inch cake.', '1 (19 oz.) pkg. lemon cake mix', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. softened cream cheese', '3/4 c. milk', '4 eggs', '1 1/4 c. ground , fresh cranberries , drained', '1/2 c. ground walnuts', '1/4 c. granulated sugar', '1 tsp. mace', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2813, ' ', '3 eggs', '1 1/2 c. salad oil', '2 c. sugar', '3 c. flour', '1/4 c. milk', '1 Tbsp. cinnamon', '1 tsp. soda', '1 tsp. salt', '2 tsp. vanilla', '3 c. chopped McIntosh apples', '1 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2814, ' Drain pineapple and oranges. Combine pineapple , oranges , grapes , marshmallows , coconut and nuts. Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture. Chill. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1 (20 oz.) can chunk pineapple in juice or syrup', '1 (11 oz.) can Mandarin orange segments', '1 1/2 c. seedless grapes', '1 c. miniature marshmallows', '1 c. flaked coconut', '1/2 c. nuts', '3/4 c. dairy sour cream', '1 tsp. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2815, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Combine all ingredients , except pecans. Beat at medium speed 5 minutes. Add nuts and mix well. Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Let cool in pan 10 minutes , then loosen center and sides with plastic spatula. Invert and tip on wire rack to cool. Can ice with cream cheese icing or use Cool Whip to serve.', '1 (11 oz.) pkg. spice cake mix', '1 c. canned pumpkin', '1/2 c. salad oil', '3 eggs', '1 (3 3/4 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding', '1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 c. water', '1 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2816, ' Mix pumpkin , milk , sugar , salt , pumpkin pie spice and eggs. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Dot with margarine. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350&deg; for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.', '1 (16 oz.) can pumpkin', '1 (13 oz.) can evaporated milk', '1 c. sugar', '1/4 tsp. salt', '2 Tbsp. pumpkin pie spice', '3 eggs', '1 pkg. cake mix (such as spice cake)', '3/4 c. margarine , sliced', '1 c. coarsely chopped walnuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2818, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Combine peach pie filling and cranberry sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine dry cake mix , cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives; mix in nuts. Sprinkle evenly over fruit in pan. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream , if desired. Makes 16 servings.', '1 pkg. yellow cake mix', '1 (21 oz.) can peach pie filling', '1 (16 oz.) can whole cranberry sauce', '1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1/4 tsp. ground nutmeg', '1 c. (2 sticks) butter or margarine , softened', '1/2 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2825, ' Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread bean mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Layer remaining ingredients in order listed: avocado dip , sour cream , ripe olives , tomatoes , onion , green chilies and Monterey Jack. Serve with corn chips. Yields appetizers for 15 to 20.', '1 (16 oz.) can refried beans', '1/2 (1.25 oz.) pkg. taco seasoning mix', '1 (6 oz.) carton avocado dip', '1 (8 oz.) carton sour cream', '1 (4 1/2 oz.) can chopped ripe olives', '2 large tomatoes , diced', '1 small onion , finely chopped', '1 (4 oz.) can chopped green chilies', '1 1/2 c. (6 oz.) shredded Monterey Jack cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(2830, ' Saut&eacute; onion in margarine. Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain off excess liquid. Add all ingredients in a double boiler and cook until cheese is melted.', '2 (6 oz.) Kraft garlic links', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', '1 small jar chopped mushrooms', '1 small onion , saut&eacute;ed', '2 pkg. frozen chopped broccoli', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
