(3537, ' Preheat oven to 425&deg;. Combine yeast , beer and sugar in mixing bowl. Allow to stand until yeast is dissolved and begins to foam (about 5 minutes). Stir in salt and flour. Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic. Separate dough into 12 equal pieces. Roll each piece into 20 inch long rope and form pretzel shape. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with egg and sprinkle with kosher salt. Bake 15 minutes until golden brown. Remove and cool.', '1 pkg. active dry yeast (2 1/4 tsp.)', '1 bottle of your favorite beer', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '4 c. flour', '1 egg , slightly beaten', ' coarsely ground Kosher or sea salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(3543, ' In saucepan combine spinach and onion; cook according to spinach package directions. Drain well , pressing out excess liquid. Combine eggs , cheeses , salad dressing , butter or margarine , and garlic powder. Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well. Cover and chill. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Cover and chill till serving time. (Or place in a freezer container; seal , label , and freeze.) To serve , place chilled or frozen puffs on a baking sheet. Bake in a 350&deg; oven until light brown. Bake chilled puffs for 10 to 12 minutes; bake frozen puffs for 12 to 15 minutes. Serve warm. Makes about 60. The taste of these top-rated tidbits is similar to spinach dumplings.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped spinach', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '2 eggs , slightly beaten', '1/2 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '1/2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1/2 c. Blue cheese salad dressing', '1/4 c. butter or margarine , melted', '1/8 tsp. garlic powder', '1 (8 1/2 oz.) pkg. corn muffin mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
