(4116, ' Combine beef , cheese and ripe olives with mayonnaise. Spread 1 tablespoon of the mixture on each cracker. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 375&deg; for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. thinly sliced smoked beef , chopped', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 c. sliced ripe olives', '1/2 c. mayonnaise', '2 1/2 doz. whole grain rye crackers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4119, ' Combine beef , salt , pepper , water chestnuts and water. Mix thoroughly. Form into small balls. Roll lightly in flour. Heat oil. Brown meatballs; drain. Makes 27 to 30 meatballs.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. black pepper', '1/4 to 1/2 c. chopped water chestnuts', '1/4 c. cold water', '2 Tbsp. flour', '4 Tbsp. oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4120, ' Combine all ingredients. Fill pastries with salad. Garnish with slices of green and ripe olives and fresh parsley. Yield: 36.', '4 c. cooked chicken , chopped', '4 Tbsp. chopped green olives', '4 Tbsp. chopped ripe olives', '1 c. celery', '1 c. toasted chopped almonds', '4 Tbsp. salad pickles', '4 hard-cooked eggs , chopped', '1 1/2 c. mayonnaise', '1 Tbsp. cooking sherry', '1 recipe Puff Pastry (recipe follows)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4123, ' Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs form. Add milk. Mix well. Knead dough about 1 minute on floured surface. Divide dough into 2 parts. Roll each into 1/4-inch thick squares. Spread each with 1/2 pound sausage. Roll up from one end. Refrigerate 1 hour.', '2 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. salt', '2 tsp. baking powder', '2 Tbsp. white cornmeal', '1/4 c. vegetable shortening', '3/4 c. plus 1 Tbsp. milk', '1 lb. hot sausage , at room temperature', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4131, ' Saut&eacute; onions and celery in butter. Add two cheeses and soup and melt together. Stir in cooked and drained broccoli. Add almonds. Serve hot with crackers. Makes 1 1/2 to 2-quarts.', '2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen , chopped broccoli', '2 rolls garlic cheese (Kraft)', '2 (8 oz.) cream cheese', '3 c. celery , chopped', '2 medium onions', '1 stick butter', '2 cans cream of mushroom soup', '2 small pkg. slivered almonds', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4140, ' Heat shortening or oil in medium-size skillet over medium heat. Saut&eacute; chopped onion in shortening. Add flour. Cook 1 minute. Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Serve over enchiladas or burritos.', '1 Tbsp. shortening or oil', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 c. chopped canned green chili', '1 c. vegetable or chicken broth', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '3/4 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4145, ' Place all ingredients in a double boiler and mix well. Cook over boiling water until thick. When still somewhat runny , cool and put in container. Refrigerate. It will thicken when cool. Serve as dip for vegetables.', '1/2 c. tomato soup or tomato sauce', '1/2 c. cider vinegar', '1/2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. butter or margarine', '1/2 c. French mustard', '1 egg yolk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4156, ' Defrost chicken wings and rinse in cold water; pat dry. Combine all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours. Discard marinade and bake wings in single layer at 350&deg; for about 1 hour. Serve with duck sauce , if desired.', '5 lb. chicken wings', '1 can consomm', '1/2 c. ketchup', '1/2 c. honey', '3 cloves garlic', '1/2 c. soy sauce', '2 Tbsp. dark brown sugar', ' Five Spice powder (available in most stores or special kitchen shops)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4157, ' Mix all ingredients except wings together and pour over chicken. Dot with butter. Bake at 400&deg; for 1 1/2 hours. Turn occasionally while baking.', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1/2 c. honey', '1/2 c. cooking oil', '1/2 c. soy sauce', '1/2 c. sherry wine', '2 c. chicken bouillon', '1 clove garlic , crushed', '1/4 tsp. curry powder', '1/4 tsp. dry mustard', '1 tsp. salt', ' enough wings to fit into roasting pan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4159, ' Saut&eacute; mushrooms in butter. Stir in flour. When mushrooms are golden and tender , remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and dry onion soup. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350&deg; about 20 to 25 minutes. Can be made the day before. This is good served on Toasted Batard Bread.', '12 oz. fresh mushrooms , sliced', '2 Tbsp. butter', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1/2 c. sour cream', '2 tsp. dried onion soup mix', '1/2 c. grated cheese (Parmesan)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4162, ' Trim stem and remove strings from sides of each pod. Blanch pea pods in lightly salted , boiling water 2 to 3 minutes. Drain and rinse in cold water. Using a sharp knife , slit each pea pod open along straight edge.', '2 doz. fresh snow pea pods', '1/8 lb. deli roast beef , sliced paper thin', '4 oz. (1/2 of 8 oz. pkg.) cream cheese , softened', '1/4 c. sour cream', '1 tsp. curry powder', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '1/4 tsp. granulated sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4164, ' Heat oven to 325&deg;. Line pan with foil and grease foil. In saucepan over medium heat , combine honey , butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Bring to a boil. Cook 2 minutes , stirring constantly. Put nuts into medium bowl. Pour honey mixture over nuts and stir until evenly coated. Spread on prepared foil-lined pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until nuts are glazed and lightly browned. Cool in pan for 20 minutes. Remove from pan. In medium bowl , combine sugar and remaining cinnamon. Toss with glazed nuts to coat. Makes 4 cups.', '1/4 c. honey', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '1 tsp. cinnamon , divided', '4 c. nut halves (walnuts or pecans)', '2 to 3 Tbsp. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4169, ' Beat cream cheese and dressing mix in a large bowl until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients except tortilla chips. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 4 cups spread , but can easily be halved using 4 teaspoons of dressing mix.', '2 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1 (1 oz.) pkg. Ranch salad dressing mix', '2 (4 1/2 oz.) cans chopped ripe olives , drained', '1 (11 oz.) can whole kernel corn , drained', '1 (4 oz.) can chopped green chilies , drained', '1 medium red bell pepper , chopped', ' tortilla chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4175, ' Mix together and serve with corn chips.', '2 cans Mexican corn , drained', '1/2 cup miracle whip salad dressing', '1/2 cup sour cream', '2 cups sharp cheddar cheese', '1 bunch green onions , chopped', ' garlic salt', ' salt', ' pepper', ' crushed red peppers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4176, ' Mix by hand and roll into ball , then roll in pecans. Chill. Serve with crackers.', '2 8 oz. pkg. cream cheese , softened', '2 small pkg. dried beef , cut up fine', ' 2-3 green onions , chopped fine', '2 Tbsp. Accent', ' pecans , chopped fine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4185, ' Simmer first five ingredients in skillet 5 minutes stirring constantly. Mix together all other ingredients , then pour first mixture over this and mix well. Bake at 250 degrees for 1-2 hours stirring every 20 minutes. Store in tightly covered containers. This recipe is easier if you split it up and make in 2 batches.', '1 c. bacon grease', '1 stick butter', '2 Tbsp. garlic salt', '1 tsp. Accent', '2 tsp. Tabasco', '2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 box each Wheat Chex , Rice Chex , Corn Chex and Cheerios', ' Pretzels', ' Mixed nuts', ' Chow Mein noodles', ' Potato Sticks', ' Pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4187, ' Brown the ground beef and mix with taco mix. Put refried beans in the bottom of an 11 x 7 pan , top with ground beef , then sour cream , then salsa and sprinkle cheese over all. Put in 350 degree oven until cheese melts.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 pkg. taco seasoning mix', '1 can refried beans', '1 8 oz. sour cream', ' salsa', ' cheddar cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4188, ' Stir together all ingredients. Serve with corn chips.', '2 15.5 oz. cans blackeye peas , rinsed and drained', ' 1-2 Tbsp. diced jalapeno pepper', '1 10 oz. can diced tomatoes and green chilies', '2 avocados , diced', '1 small green bell pepper , diced', '1/2 purple onion , diced', '3/4 c. Italian salad dressing', '1 Tbsp. lime juice', '1/4 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4191, ' Place cream cheese , milk , dressing mix and dill weed in blender and blend until smooth. Store , tightly sealed , in refrigerator. Serve dip with vegetables and breadsticks.', '4 oz. cream cheese', '2 Tbsp. milk', '1/2 pkg. dry ranch salad dressing mix', '1 1/2 tsp. dried dill weed of 1 Tbsp. fresh dill', '4 c. raw vegetables (such as cherry tomatoes , celery sticks , baby carrots , broccoli florets , cucumber slices , zucchini slices , bell pepper)', '8 unsalted breadsticks', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4194, ' Combine cheese and next 4 ingredients. Chill 4 hours or until firm. Shape into ball to resemble a pumpkin.', '16 oz. sharp cheddar cheese , shredded', '1 8 oz. cream cheese', '1 8 oz. chive and cream cheese dip', '2 tsp. paprika', '1/2 tsp. red pepper', '1 stalk broccoli', ' red and green apple wedges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4203, ' Preheat oven to 300&deg;. In a large mixing bowl , combine the oats , almonds and wheat germ; set aside. Stir together honey and apple juice concentrate. Pour over oat mixture , stirring until coated. Spread mixture evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Bake , uncovered , for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown. Stir every 15 minutes and several times during the last 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir in raisins and dried fruit. Transfer to another pan and cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.', '2 1/2 c. rolled oats', '1/2 c. slivered almonds', '1/2 c. toasted wheat germ', '1/4 c. honey', '1/3 c. frozen apple juice concentrate', ' vegetable cooking spray', '1/4 c. raisins', '1/2 c. dried fruit , chopped (apples , apricots or any other dried fruits)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4207, ' Preheat oven to 400&deg;. Twist off stems from mushrooms. Spray in large shallow pan with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange mushrooms , rounded side up , in pan. Spray lightly with cooking spray. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook in oven for 8 minutes and remove.', '1 lb. large , fresh , white mushrooms (12 to 18 mushrooms)', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. freshly ground pepper', '8 oz. spinach', '2 tsp. olive oil , divided', '1 c. diced onion', '3 oz. Canadian bacon , finely chopped', '2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese , grated', '1/3 c. plain dry breadcrumbs', '1/4 c. chopped parsley', '1 Tbsp. plus 1 tsp. toasted crushed pine nuts', '2 tsp. minced garlic', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4217, ' Mix all together and season to taste.', '4 pkg. cream cheese', '1/2 c. processed sharp Cheddar', '1/2 c. French dressing', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1 tsp. celery salt', '1/4 c. parsley flakes (optional)', ' dill weed (optional)', ' salad greens (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4218, ' ', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '2 Tbsp. milk', '1 c. sour cream', '1/4 c. green pepper , chopped', '4 green onions (and part of the tops) , chopped fine', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4228, ' Prepare all ingredients and layer on a large platter in the order listed. Blend chili beans in blender; add more juice if needed. Mix avocados , lemon juice , salt and pepper. Mix sour cream , mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix. Layer the next 4 ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips tucked under the edge of the mixture on the plate. To eat , just dip chips and enjoy,', '2 cans (10.5 oz.) chili beans , partially drained', '3 medium avocados , peeled and mashed (optional)', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 c. sour cream', '1/2 c. mayonnaise or salad dressing', '1 pkg. taco seasoning', '3 medium tomatoes', '2 cans pitted black olives', '1 c. chopped onion', '2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', ' tortilla chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4229, ' Cut the corned beef and cheese into pieces to fit on the bread. Lightly butter 1 slice of bread; top with 2 slices of corned beef , 1 slice cheese , 1 teaspoon sauerkraut and 1/4 teaspoon mustard. Top with another slice of bread and bake in a preheated 400&deg; oven for 10 minutes. Makes about 18 sandwiches.', '1 loaf party rye bread', '1/2 stick butter', '3 to 4 oz. thinly sliced corned beef', '8 oz. sliced Swiss cheese', '1 (8 oz.) can sauerkraut , drained', '4 to 5 tsp. mustard (spicy mustard is good)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4230, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Spray a large skillet with vegetable oil. Cook mushrooms , onion and garlic in skillet over medium heat until onion is tender , about 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in cilantro and remove from heat. Arrange 1/3 of the mushroom mixture on half of 1 tortilla. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the cheese. Fold the other half of the tortilla over the cheese. Place on a baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining ingredients to make 3 quesadillas total. Bake quesadillas about 5 minutes or until filling is hot and cheese melts. Cut each quesadilla into 4 wedges. Serve warm with salsa , if desired. Serves 6 (2 wedges per serving).', ' vegetable oil spray', '8 oz. fresh sliced mushrooms', '1/2 medium onion , thinly sliced and separated into rings', '1 tsp. minced garlic', '3 Tbsp. chopped fresh cilantro', '3 (8-inch) flour tortillas', '6 Tbsp. shredded low-fat Monterey Jack cheese (with jalapeno peppers) or low-fat Cheddar cheese', ' commercial salsa or Fresh and Chunky salsa', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4234, ' Saut onion , garlic and cumin in oil in skillet over medium heat until onion is golden brown. Add red and green peppers and cook until pepper begins to soften. Add remaining ingredients and heat through. Serve warm with chili tortilla chips.', '1 (15 oz.) can fat-free refried beans', '1 (15 oz.) can picante beans', '1 c. medium-hot salsa', '1/2 c. shredded Monterey Jack cheese', '1/4 c. medium taco sauce', '1 large onion , diced', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 tsp. cumin', '1/2 green pepper , diced', '1/2 red pepper , diced', '2 cloves garlic , minced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4237, ' Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 350&deg; oven for 30 minutes. Keep warm in a slow cooker. Serve on cocktail rye.', '3 (2.5 oz.) pkg. Buddig corned beef , chopped', '1/4 c. onion , chopped', '1 1/2 c. mayonnaise (not Miracle Whip)', '1 (14 oz.) can Bavarian-style kraut', '1 1/2 c. shredded Swiss cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4239, ' In a large saucepan , bring soup to a boil , stirring often. Reduce heat and add cream cheese. Stir until smooth. Stir in celery , green onions , water chestnuts , shrimp , mayonnaise and dill. Heat through. Put dip in small slow cooker to keep warm. Serve with crackers.', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of mushroom soup', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. low-fat cream cheese', '2 (6 oz.) cans small shrimp , rinsed and drained', '1/2 c. finely chopped celery', '1/2 c. finely chopped green onions', '1/2 c. finely chopped water chestnuts', '1/4 c. light mayonnaise', '1 tsp. dill weed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4243, ' For the bottom layer , mix taco seasoning with refried beans. The next layer is sour cream mixed with dry party seasoning mix. Top with lettuce , cheese , tomatoes , peppers , olives , onions as desired. Serve with nacho chips.', '1 pkg. taco seasoning', '1 can refried beans', '16 oz. sour cream', '1 pkg. dry party seasoning mix', ' lettuce , cheese , tomatoes , peppers , olives , onions as desired (for topping)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4249, ' Have cheese at room temperature , mix all ingredients well. Chill then form into a ball. Roll in parsley and chopped nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.', '2 pkg (8 ounces each) cream cheese', '1 pkg (4 ounces) blue cheese', '2 Tbsp. chopped chives', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', ' parsley', ' chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4257, ' Pop off mushroom stems and chop. In a large sauce pan brown ground beef , chopped mushroom stems , parsley , onions , salt , pepper , and garlic powder. Remove from heat. Add bread crumbs , cheese , and eggs. Fill cavity of mushroom tops with meat mixture. Place in baking dish and bake at 450 degrees for approximately 15 minutes.', '2 pounds whole , fresh mushrooms', '1 pound ground beef', '1 Tbsp. parsley', '1/2 cup onion , chopped', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '1/4 cup bread crumbs', '2 eggs , beaten', '4 ounces mozzarella cheese , shredded', ' dash of pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4260, ' Mix together cherry jello , lime jello and crushed pineapple. Put on stove and cook until boiling. Take off stove and add Coke and nuts to mixture. Stir in pan well; pour in bowl and refrigerate.', '2 small pkg. cherry jello', '1 small pkg. lime jello', '1 large can crushed pineapple', '2 1/2 c. Coca-Cola', '1/2 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(4266, ' Cook pork or ground beef , onions and garlic until meat is browned and onions tender. Drain off fat. Stir in tomato sauce , undrained tomatoes , chili peppers , flour and chili powder. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. In salad bowl , mix lettuce , beans and olives. Toss. Top with meat mixture. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Top with cherry tomato halves and green pepper strips. Peel and slice avocado. Arrange slices on top of salad.', '1 lb. pork or ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 clove garlic', '1 (8 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 can chopped tomato', '1 (4 oz.) can green chili peppers , chopped', '2 Tbsp. flour', '2 tsp. chili powder', '6 c. torn lettuce', '1 (15 1/2 oz.) can garbanzo beans , drained', '1/2 c. sliced pitted ripe olives', '1 c. shredded Monterey Jack or Cheddar cheese (4 oz.)', '1 c. cherry tomatoes , halved', '1 c. green pepper strips', '1 avocado', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
