(7635, ' Fix macaroni as directed on box. Brown hamburger with onions. Salt and pepper to taste. Layer macaroni , hamburger and sauce in casserole dish. Mix mushrooms in with hamburger after it is browned. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350&deg; until hot through. Sometimes I mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.', '3 boxes macaroni and cheese mix', '3 lb. hamburger', '2 c. pizza sauce or catsup', '2 medium onions , finely chopped', '1 c. shredded cheese', '1 can mushrooms , drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7673, ' Mix together your favorite meat loaf and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (should be fairly thin). Bake at 350&deg; for 1/2 to 3/4 hour. While hot , spread soup over meat loaf , then spread on green beans. Next add Tater Tots in rows. (Sometimes I use a biscuit recipe and drop unbaked biscuits on top in rows.) Put back in oven and bake at 350&deg; until all ingredients are hot or biscuits are done , approximately 25 to 30 minutes. You can keep a meat loaf ready in the 9 x 13-inch pan in freezer.', ' your favorite meat loaf (using 1 to 1 1/2 lb.) hamburger', '1 can golden mushroom soup', '1 qt. green beans , partially drained', '1 large bag Tater Tots', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7679, ' Mix all ingredients together and put in 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes. Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and heat until cheese melts.', '2 c. cooked macaroni', '1 to 1 1/2 lb. browned hamburger', '4 oz. mushrooms , drained', '2 c. pizza sauce', '8 oz. tomato sauce', '1 c. Parmesan cheese', '1/2 pkg. pepperoni , sliced', '1/2 c. onions', ' salt and pepper', ' oregano', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7681, ' Combine hamburger , bread crumbs , onion , salt , pepper and evaporated milk. Press firmly onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350&deg; for 35 to 40 minutes. Spoon off drippings.', '1 lb. hamburger', '1/2 c. fine dry bread crumbs', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '2/3 c. evaporated milk', '4 oz. spaghetti , cooked and drained', '1 egg , beaten', '1/4 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 (8 oz.) pizza sauce', '1/2 tsp. oregano', '1 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7684, ' Preheat oven to 400&deg;. Brown hamburger and onion. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside. Combine flour , salt , pepper , oregano , eggs and milk , making a soft batter. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cornmeal. Pour batter in pan. Sprinkle meat over batter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Spread pizza sauce and cheese over meat. Bake 15 more minutes. Yields 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.', '1 lb. hamburger', '1 onion , chopped', '1 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1/8 tsp. oregano', '2 eggs', '2/3 c. milk', '1 (15 oz.) can pizza sauce (pt.)', '1 1/2 to 2 c. grated cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7686, ' Mix flour , baking powder and salt. Add milk and oil. Pat dough into bottom on greased pizza pan. Mix pizza sauce , water and seasonings. Spread over dough , then sprinkle on onion , mushrooms (well drained) , hamburger and cheese. Bake at 425&deg; for 20 to 25 minutes.', '2 c. all-purpose flour', '1 Tbsp. baking powder', '1 tsp. salt', '2/3 c. milk', '1/3 c. oil', '2 c. pizza sauce', '1/4 c. water', '1 tsp. ground oregano', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 c. onion', '1 (4 oz.) can mushrooms', '1 lb. browned hamburger', ' shredded cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7769, ' In a large skillet over medium heat , brown ground beef and drain excess liquid. Add taco seasoning spices as directed on the package and stir to blend; reserve.', '1 lb. lean ground beef', '1 packet taco seasoning mix', '1 Tbsp. butter', '1 large onion , chopped', '1 large green pepper , chopped (optional)', '1 large box shell pasta', '2 cans stewed tomatoes', '1 jar chunky salsa', '2 c. Cheddar cheese , grated', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7784, ' Cook penne to desired doneness on package; drain. Combine bread crumbs and cheese in plastic bag. Add pork. Shake to coat. In a large nonstick skillet , heat oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add pork; cook 4 to 6 minutes until brown on each side. Add tomatoes , tomato sauce , onion and oil to pork. Stir gently to mix. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until pork is tender , stirring occasionally. Serve pork over penne.', '8 oz. (2 1/2 c.) uncooked penne pasta', '2 Tbsp. plain bread crumbs', '2 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese', '1 (3/4 lb.) pork tenderloin , sliced', '2 tsp. olive oil', '1 (14 1/2 oz.) can diced tomatoes with garlic , oregano and basil (undrained)', '1 (8 oz.) tomato sauce', '1/2 c. sliced green onions', '1 (2 1/2 oz.) can sliced ripe olives , drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7820, ' Pour butter into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange onion evenly on bottom of dish. Place fish filets in a single layer atop the onion. Combine mayonnaise , cheese , lemon juice , Worcestershire sauce , paprika and salt. Spread evenly on top of fish. Sprinkle , to taste , with oregano and parsley. Bake at 350&deg; for 35 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.', '3 Tbsp. margarine , melted', '1 onion , thinly sliced', '1 1/2 lb. fish filets', '1/2 c. mayonnaise', ' Oregano', ' Chopped parsley', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 tsp. Worcestershire Sauce', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7821, ' Combine all ingredients (except for fish filets) and marinate fish filets in the mixture for 1/2 hour or more. Broil 12 to 15 minutes. Serve with tartar sauce.', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '2 Tbsp. corn oil', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1 tsp. paprika', '1 tsp. chili powder', ' Fish filets', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7822, ' Mix milk and salt. Dip fish in salted milk. Mix together bread crumbs and paprika. Roll fish in bread crumbs. Place fish side by side in oiled , shallow baking dish. Drizzle melted butter over fish. Bake at 525&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is golden and flakes easily with fork. Watch closely.', '2 fish filets', '1/4 c. milk', '2 tsp. salt', '1 c. bread crumbs', '1/2 tsp. paprika', '2 Tbsp. melted butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7823, ' Mix mayonnaise , lemon juice , dill and lemon peel. Place fish on greased grill over medium coals. Brush with 1/2 of the mayonnaise mixture. Grill 5 minutes , turn. Brush with remaining mayonnaise mixture. Grill an additional 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.', '1/2 c. Kraft Light Mayonnaise', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 tsp. dill weed', '1/2 tsp. grated lemon peel', '1 lb. firm-textured fish filets (such as cod , catfish or salmon)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7861, ' Cut artichoke hearts into quarters. Combine with prosciutto , olives and spaghetti sauce in a medium saucepan and simmer 10 minutes. Toss with cooked pasta. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on individual servings. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1 (16 oz.) can artichoke hearts in water', '4 oz. prosciutto , chopped', '1/2 c. imported black olives , pitted', '1 (30 oz.) jar spaghetti sauce', '1 lb. pasta shells , cooked and drained', ' Parmesan cheese , grated', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7866, ' ', '1 (13.5 oz) can coconut milk', '2 cups water', '2 Tbsp. basen (gram flour)', '1/4 small onion , thinly sliced', '4 Tbsp. oil', ' 3-4 curry leaves', '1/2 Tbsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. haldi (turmeric)', '1/4 tsp. cayenne pepper', '1/2 Tbsp. sugar', '1 tsp. monosodium glutamate', '1 lb. thin spaghetti (or capellini for a thinner pasta)*', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7882, ' Cook pasta as per packet directions; drain. In small skillet , cook garlic in oil until golden. Add water and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves. In large bowl , toss hot angel hair with garlic mixture and parsley. Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.', '1 (12 oz.) pkg. angel hair pasta', '4 cloves garlic , finely chopped', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1/2 cup water', '2 tsp. chicken bouillon cubes', '1/2 cup chopped parsley', ' Grated Parmesan cheese , optional', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7890, ' Boil lasagna noodles as per package directions. Keep al-dente , meaning fully cooked , but not overly soft. Keep noodles in cold water until ready to use. Remove stems from spinach and dry spinach leaves. (Spinach is optional.) Spread 1/4 cup of pasta sauce evenly over bottom of a 13x9x2 baking pan. Set aside', '9 pieces lasagna noodles', '1 bunch spinach , washed and thoroughly drained', '1 lb. ground beef , washed and drained well', '2 tsp. oregano*', '1-1/2 tsp. Italian seasoning*', '1-1/2 tsp. basil*', '1/2 tsp. black pepper powder*', '1 tsp. salt , or per taste*', '1/2 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes*', '1-1/2 tsp. garlic powder*', ' pinches each , onion powder and onion salt*', '1 large bottle + 1/2 cup pasta sauce', '1/2 cup water', '1/4 cup chopped green/red peppers', '3/4 cup mushrooms , sliced', '1/2 cup onions , chopped', '2 cups (15 oz.) Ricotta cheese', '2-1/2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1/8 cup grated Parmesan cheese', '1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley', '2 eggs , beaten', '1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella , for the top', '1 Tbsp. olive oil', NULL),
(7903, ' Cook the pasta as per package instructions. Cut the onion and fry it with 2-3 tsp. oil. Add all-spice and the beef. Braise until meat turns brown. Then add water and tomato sauce and salt. Cook meat for 10 minutes.', '1 pkg. macaroni pasta', '1 large onion', ' 2-3 tsp. oil', '2 tsp. all-spice', '1 lb. beef', '1/2 cup water', '1 small can tomato sauce', '1 tsp. salt', '6 Tbsp. flour', '4 cups milk', '1 egg , beaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7965, ' Mix together all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes. Shape 1/3 cups of mixture into patties. Heat large nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat. Add patties and cook approximately 3 minutes on each side. (Or , until patties are golden brown on both sides.) Turn carefully. Makes 12 salmon patties.', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. Stove Top stuffing mix (use your favorite flavor)', '1/3 cup mayonnaise', '2 (6 oz. each) cans salmon , drained and boned', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese', ' chopped green onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7974, ' Preheat oven to 500 degrees. Season prime rib with you favorite seasonings. Place in a roasting pan fat side up. Cook exactly 10 minutes per pound. After proper cooking time , turn off the oven and do not open the door for 8 hours. This is perfect for cooking overnight. This is great and you won''t be sorry you tried it.', '1 prime rib', ' favorite seasoning', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(7989, ' Heat 1 inch or more of oil in a cast iron skillet on camp stove or fire. Put a wooden match into oil. When it ignites , the oil is ready. Shake walleye fillets in plastic bag of fish coating. Fry in hot oil.', ' walleye fillets', ' fish coating', ' cooking oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8001, ' Roll out bread dough , use flour underneath. Brush with butter/oregano mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and meat. Add mushrooms. Roll up the long way and pinch dough together. Lay the dough on cookie sheet , pinched side down. Brush with butter/oregano mixture again. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes , or until it bursts open and cheese oozes out. Cut into slices and dip in pizza sauce.', '1 loaf frozen bread dough , thawed', '3 Tbsp. butter , melted', '1 tsp. oregano , add to melted butter', '8 oz. shredded Mozzarella cheese', ' pepperoni , or other meat of your choice', ' mushrooms , if desired', ' pizza sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8018, ' Brown beef and pork seasoned with pepper. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 to 45 minutes. 15 minutes before done , sprinkle top with sharp Cheddar cheese.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 lb. ground pork', ' pepper', '1/2 pkg. rotelle pasta', '1 can Cheddar cheese soup', '1 c. Mozzarella cheese', '1 jar Ragu Robusto (sausage and cheese)', '1 small can tomato sauce', '1 tsp. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8108, ' Cook pasta according to directions on pkg. Then drain. Brown ground beef along with onion , green pepper , garlic , salt and pepper. Drain off as much fat as possible from cooked meat mixture. Add the cooked meat mixture to cooked pasta. Add the tomato soup and both cans of chopped tomatoes. (Do not drain the chopped tomatoes.) Mix all ingredients together. Heat on low on top of stove until good and hot. Before serving , you may sprinkle on cheese. Makes 4 generous servings. Goes well with a salad and hot corn bread.', '1 lb. pkg. of pasta , your choice', '2 lb. ground beef', '1 medium onion , chopped fine', '1 medium green pepper , chopped fine', '1 Tbsp. garlic , chopped', ' salt to taste', ' pepper to taste', '1 (10 1/2 oz.) can of tomato soup', '2 (1 lb.) cans of chopped tomatoes , your choice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8112, ' Combine all ingredients , except corn and sweet potatoes and refrigerate two hours. To serve place in a large dish. Garnish with the corn and sweet potatoes. Serving size: 8.', '2 lb. mixed seafood (shrimp , clams , firm fish)', '1 large onion , thinly sliced', '1/4 c. chopped cilantro or parsley', '2 cans green chilies , finely sliced', '3 tsp. olive oil', ' salt to taste', ' pepper to taste', ' lime juice to cover (or mixture of lemon and lime juice)', '2 ears of corn , cooked and chopped', '2 sweet potatoes , cook', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8119, ' Break ground beef into small particles and saut&eacute; in butter or olive oil. Mix thoroughly meat , egg , Mozzarella , milk , bread , chopped parsley , salt and pepper. Fill cooked shells. Cover bottom of baking dish with pasta sauce. Arrange filled shells side by side in single layer in baking pan. Pour remaining sauce over filled shells and bake at 350&deg; for about 30 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve.', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef or 1/2 beef and 1/2 pork', '1 egg', '1/2 lb. Mozzarella cheese , diced', '1/2 c. milk', '2 slices bread', '1 Tbsp chopped parsley', ' salt and pepper', ' jumbo shells', ' pasta sauce', ' grated cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8143, ' In a large skillet , saut the red pepper , mushrooms , onions and garlic in butter. Add the cream , basil , chicken and salt. Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Serve over pasta. Yields 4 servings.', '1 c. julienne sweet red pepper', '1 c. sliced , fresh mushrooms', '1/4 c. chopped green onions', '3 garlic cloves , minced', '1/4 c. butter', '2 c. whipping cream', '1 tsp. dried basil', '2 grilled , boneless , skinless chicken breast halves , thinly sliced', '1/2 tsp. salt', ' hot , cooked angel hair pasta', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8145, ' Saut onions in butter until clear , then place in the bottom of casserole dish. Mix the salsa , cheese dip and soup thoroughly. Add spaghetti and chicken and stir well. Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese. Bake in 350&deg; oven until bubbly. Allow to set for 10 minutes before serving.', '3/4 c. onions', '3 Tbsp. butter', '1 jar mild salsa', '1 jar mild or medium nacho cheese dip (all depends on how spicy you want your casserole)', '1 can cream of mushroom soup', ' chicken that has been boiled and cut up into bite size pieces', ' cooked spaghetti', '2 c. grated cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8148, ' Prepare pasta as directed on package , adding broccoli to water during last 3 minutes of pasta cooking time; drain.', '1 (9 oz.) pkg. Di Giorno tortellini (any flavor)', '2 c. broccoli flowerets', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. Di Giorno Alfredo sauce', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. Louis Rich grilled chicken breast strips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8197, ' In a large skillet , saut the sausage; cool. In a bowl , combine the sausage , cheese , 1 egg that has been scrambled , parsley , onion salt and garlic salt; mix well.', '1 lb. smoked sausage', '1 1/2 c. (6 oz.) shredded Mozzarella cheese', '2 eggs (1 scrambled and 1 used to seal the crust)', '1 1/2 tsp. minced , fresh parsley', '1/2 tsp. onion salt', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '1 (10 oz.) tube refrigerated pizza dough', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8256, ' Brown meat; drain. Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour pizza sauce over meat. Top with cheese. Add biscuit mix , milk and eggs. Pour over meat and cheese; cover. Bake at 400&deg; for 30 minutes.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. Mozzarella cheese', '1 1/2 c. milk', '1 (14 oz.) jar Pizza Quick sauce (Ragu)', '3/4 c. biscuit mix', '2 eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8257, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Crumble sausage into a medium skillet; cook over medium heat until browned , stirring occasionally. Remove sausage and drain on paper towels. In a large lightly greased casserole dish , layer 1/2 of the noodles , 1/2 of the sausage and 1/2 of the remaining ingredients. Repeat with second layer of noodles , sausage and remaining ingredients. Reserve several pepperoni slices to garnish top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 6 to 8.', '1 lb. Italian sausage', '12 oz. wide noodles , cooked according to pkg. instructions', '2 (14 oz.) jars pizza sauce', '2 c. Cheddar cheese , shredded', '6 oz. pepperoni , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8290, ' Unroll dough. Place on greased cookie sheet. Press dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread sauce on dough to within 2-inches of long side. Top with ham , cheese , green peppers and Italian seasoning. Fold long side of dough over filling. Pinch to seal. Bake at 400&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.', '1 can Pillsbury pizza crust', '1/4 c. pizza sauce', '1/2 lb. ham , thinly sliced', '1 c. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', '1/4 c. green peppers , chopped', '1/4 tsp. Italian seasoning', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(8294, ' Empty package into a medium sized saucepan. Let simmer in the whole bottle of barbecue sauce. This is a great appetizer.', '1 (16 oz.) pkg. little wienies or Little Smokies sausage', '1 (16 oz.) bottle your favorite barbecue sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
