(9217, ' Preheat oven to 400 or 450&deg;. Arrange a single layer of salmon in a shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour half of the sauce mixture over the fish or salmon. Bake for 20 minutes , basting with the remaining sauce. Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley. Serves 4.', '1 lb. fish fillets or canned salmon , drained', '1 Tbsp. cider vinegar', '1 Tbsp. worcestershire sauce', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. prepared mustard', '1/8 tsp. black pepper', '1/2 c. melted butter or margarine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9226, ' Mix all ingredients except pork until well blended. Serve over hot sliced pork. Makes 12 servings , 3 oz. cooked pork and 2 Tbsp. salsa each.', '1 can (8 oz.) pineapple tidbits , drained', '1 seedless orange , peeled , chopped', '1/4 c. green onion slices', '1/4 c. Baker''s Angel Flake coconut', '2 Tbsp. Kraft Light Done Right Ranch reduced fat dressing', '1 Tbsp. chopped seeded jalapeno pepper , optional', '3 pork tenderloins (1 lb. each) , grilled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
