(9316, ' Cut peppers and onions into small strips. Place in large skillet with margarine and wine. Cook on medium-high heat , stirring occasionally , until wine is almost absorbed and peppers and onions are done.', '4 bell peppers', '1 large onion', '1 Tbsp. margarine', '2 c. white Zinfandel wine', '32 oz. (2 pkg.) grilled chicken strips (frozen)', '10 (1 pkg.) flour tortillas', '8 oz. (1 tub) sour cream', '16 oz. (1 jar) salsa', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9339, ' In large skillet , melt butter. Baste mushroom caps with butter and place on baking sheet. Baste inside of caps with butter. In skillet with remainder of butter , saut&eacute; vegetables. When about half done , add chicken and finish saut&eacute;ing , adding Worcestershire Sauce. Spoon filling into caps. Top with a liberal amount of your favorite type of shredded cheese. Either in oven or on the grill , heat mushrooms just until cheese melts , then serve warm.', '4 large Portabello mushrooms , stem and scrape bottom of cap', '1 yellow bell pepper , chopped', '1 red bell pepper , chopped', '1 green bell pepper , chopped', '1 bunch of green onions , chopped', '4 to 5 regular mushrooms , diced', '2 large chicken breasts , grilled and diced', '1 stick butter', '1 Tbsp. Worcestershire Sauce', ' Shredded cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9354, ' In a large bowl , combine spring greens , chicken breasts , raspberry chipotle ranch dip , avocados and cheese. Place 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll into a cone. Secure each wrap with a sheet of foil or plastic wrap. Refrigerate until ready to serve.', '1 5 oz. pkg. spring mix greens', '2 Fully Cooked Seasoned Chicken Breasts', '3/4 c. Good to Go Raspberry Chipotle Ranch Dip', '2 Fresher Lasting Jumbo Avocados , sliced', '2 c. shredded monterrey jack cheese', '10 flour tortillas , room temperature', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9357, ' Heat oven to 450 degrees. Place 2 oven racks in bottom half of oven. Remove fajitas from packaging and place in a microwave safe dish. Heat on HIGH power until pieces begin to thaw; stir and rearrange fajitas in dish as necessary. Pull apart to separate; tear or cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Meanwhile , line 2 large baking sheets with foil. Lay 3 pita shells on each baking sheet. Combine mayonnaise with pesto; spread evenly over tops of pita bread , about 2 tablespoons on each. Place chicken , artichoke hearts , and mushrooms over pesto layer. Cut pepper into thin strips; lay strips over tops of pizzas and sprinkle evenly with cheese , 1/3 cup over each pizza. Bake 15 to 20 minutes , or until cheese melts and begins to brown. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes , cut into slices and serve.', '1 12 oz. bag frozen Fully Cooked Chicken Breast Fajitas', '6 KRONOS Authentic Pita flat breads', '2/3 c. regular or reduced fat mayonnaise', '2 Tbsp. Racconto Traditional Basil Pesto', '1 14 oz. can Reese Quartered Artichoke Hearts , drained', '1 6 oz. jar Harvest Moon Sliced Mushrooms , drained', '1 small red bell pepper , seeds removed', '2 c. shredded four cheese pizza blend', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9370, ' Cool pasta , according to directions. Meanwhile , in large skillet , saut&eacute; garlic in oil until tender. Stir in crab , shrimp , lemon juice and pepper. Cook and stir 1 minute. Add Alfredo sauce and peas. Cook and stir until heated through. Drain pasta. Top with seafood mixture and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.', '1 12 oz. pkg. bow-tie pasta', '2 garlic cloves , minced', '2 Tbsp. olive oil or vegetable oil', '1 8 oz. pkg. imitation crabmeat , flaked', '1 5 oz. frozen cooked salad shrimp , thawed', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1 16 oz. jar Alfredo sauce', '1/2 c. frozen peas , thawed', '1/4 c. parmesan cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9376, ' Place pizza crust on ungreased cookie sheet. Toss chicken with barbecue sauce; place evenly on crust. Top with peppers , onion and cheese. Bake at 450 degrees on bottom oven rack for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted and pizza crust is golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.', '1 Boboli Italian Pizza crust , 12 inch', '1 6 oz. pkg. Louis Rich Grilled Chicken Breast Strips', '1/3 c. Kraft Original Barbecue Sauce', '1 green pepper , cut into strips', '1 small red onion , thinly sliced', '1 8 oz. pkg. Kraft Natural Shredded Mozzarella and Cheddar Pizza Cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9399, ' In a large bowl , mix vinegar , olive oil and chipotles. Season to taste with salt , about 1/4 teaspoon. Add cabbage , carrot , onion , cilantro and chicken. Toss and let stand 15 minutes. Put into a wide , shallow serving bowl , dot with avocado and sprinkle with cheese. Serve with tortillas. Makes about 4 cups , enough to fill 12 to 16 tacos and serve 4.', '2 Tbsp. balsamic vinegar', '1/3 c. extra virgin olive oil', '2 canned chipotles en adobo , finely chopped', ' salt , to taste', '2 1/2 c. thinly sliced cabbage', '1 large carrot , peeled , chopped into 1/4 inch pieces', '1 small red onion , thinly sliced', '1/4 c. chopped fresh cilantro', '1 1/2 c. coarsely shredded cooked chicken , grilled or roasted', '1 large ripe avocado , peeled , pitted , cut into 1/2 inch cubes', '1/3 c. coarsely grated parmesan cheese', '12 to 16 warm corn tortillas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9416, ' Saut&eacute; garlic and beef in oil. Drain fat. Add all remaining stuff , except mozzarella and pasta. Simmer while boiling pasta. Drain pasta and mix with above. Pour into 3 quart baking dish , and top with mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Serves 6.', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 lb. ground beef', '3 cloves garlic', '3/4 c. spaghetti sauce', '3/4 c. brown gravy', '1/2 cup half and half', '1/4 c. parmesan cheese', '1 tsp. oregano', '1/2 tsp. rosemary', '3/4 lb. penne pasta', '1 c. mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9428, ' Spray broiling pan with Pam. Place fish skin side down. Drizzle each fillet with lemon juice. Drizzle each fillet with butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika. Salt and pepper to taste. Broil fillets on top rack for 10 to 15 minutes.', '4 fish fillets', '1 stick melted butter', ' lemon juice', ' Parmesan cheese', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9430, ' Fry chicken wings in hot oil. Melt butter and mix with Texas Pete. Coat chicken wings completely. Spread on shallow pan and bake 10 minutes at 350&deg; in oven.', ' Texas Pete', '1 stick butter', ' chicken wings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9435, ' Cook pasta according to directions. Cook sausage. When half done , add green pepper and onion. When done , drain. Drain pasta. Put all ingredients in large pan except for cheese. Mix well. Pour 1/2 of mixture in large baking dish. Put a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Pour remaining mixture on top of cheese. Put remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350&deg; until warm and cheese has melted.', '1 box spiral noodles', '1 pkg. pepperoni', '2 pkg. sausage', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 to 2 large jars your favorite spaghetti sauce', '1 small jar mushrooms (optional)', '1 to 2 pkg. sliced Mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9451, ' Boil chicken until tender and reserve broth. Remove skin and bones and chop. Crumble cornbread and add to stuffing mix. Add other ingredients including chicken and mix together. Then mix in chicken broth until the mixture is very moist. If there is not enough of the broth from the chicken , you can use a can of broth. Put into a greased 9 x 13 pan or bowl and bake at 350&deg; for 1 hour.', '1 pkg. Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix', '1 small cake cornbread', '2 cans cream of celery soup', '3 eggs', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 Tbsp. sage', '1 small to medium chicken', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9462, ' Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. In a bowl , beat the eggs; stir in Cheddar cheese and macaroni. Spread onto a 14-inch pizza pan. Bake at 375&deg; for 15 minutes.', '8 oz. uncooked elbow macaroni', '3 eggs', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 lb. ground beef', '3/4 c. chopped onion', '1 (15 oz.) can pizza sauce', '1 (4 oz.) can mushroom stems , drained', ' pepperoni slices', '1 c. shredded Mexican cheese blend', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9478, ' Cook macaroni according to package directions. Saut onion and bell pepper in butter. Brown ground beef and add onion , bell pepper and pizza sauce. Mix with cooked macaroni. Put 1/2 macaroni in Pyrex dish. Add 1/2 cheese. Add remaining macaroni and top with remaining cheese. Bake 25 minutes in 350&deg; oven , until cheeses are melted.', '16 oz. elbow macaroni', '2 (16 oz.) jars pizza sauce', '2 c. Cheddar cheese', '2 c. Mozzarella cheese', '3/4 c. chopped onion', '1/2 c. chopped bell pepper', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '2 Tbsp. butter', ' salt to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9489, ' Cook sausage and onion over medium-high heat in skillet until crumbled and no longer pink. Drain. Blend in tomatoes and paste. Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and keep warm.', '1 lb. kielbasa sausage , casing removed', '1 medium onion , chopped', '2 (14.5 oz.) cans Hunt''s diced tomatoes with basil , garlic and oregano', '1 (6 oz.) can Hunt''s tomato paste', '3 c. (6 oz.) twists pasta , cooked according to directions and kept warm', '2 c. (8 oz.) shredded Mozzarella , divided', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9492, ' Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and rinse with water. Combine Ricotta , Mozzarella , Parmesan , parsley flakes and basil. Spread 1 cup of pasta sauce over bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. Stuff each shell with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese mixture. Place in a single layer over sauce. Spread remaining sauce over shells. Cover with foil and bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes , until hot and bubbly.', '1 (15 oz.) Ricotta cheese', '1 3/4 c. shredded reduced fat Mozzarella cheese', '1/2 c. shredded Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. parsley flakes', '1 Tbsp. dried basil', '12 oz. box jumbo pasta shells', '26 oz. jar pasta sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9535, ' Put rice in a saucepan and add cold water to cover by 3/4-inch. Bring to a boil , uncovered. Turn the heat down to low , cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let it stand , covered , for at least 10 to 15 minutes. While rice is cooking , heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until it is hot , but not smoking. Add shrimp and saut&eacute; for 3 minutes , moving the pan continuously to avoid sticking or burning. With a slotted spoon , remove cooked shrimp and set aside. Turn heat down to medium-low and add garlic , chestnuts , coconut milk , fish sauce , pepper flakes , minced onion , lime juice and curry mix. Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes. Add cornstarch paste and simmer for 5 more minutes , until mixture thickens. Put shrimp back into the sauce along with cilantro and half the sliced green onion. Simmer for 3 more minutes. Transfer to a heated serving bowl and garnish with remaining sliced green onion. Makes 5 servings.', '2 c. uncooked Asian or basmati rice', '2 lb. medium shrimp (18 to 24 shrimp) , peeled and set aside', '1/4 c. olive oil', '2 Tbsp. minced garlic', '1/2 c. water chestnuts , sliced , rinsed and drained on paper towel', '2 cans unsweetened coconut milk', '1 c. Asian fish sauce or clam juice', '1/2 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes', '1/2 c. green onion , minced', '2 green onions , cut in thin slices on a diagonal', '4 Tbsp. lime juice', '1 1/2 tsp. Garam Masala curry paste', '2 Tbsp. cornstarch , mixed with 3 Tbsp. water', '1/4 c. chopped fresh cilantro', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9540, ' Melt margarine. Add flour. Cook and blend. Slowly add clams and juice. Stir until smooth. Add milk. Stir to thicken. Add cheese; heat until melted. Serve over cooked pasta. Serves 4 to 6.', '2 (7 1/2 oz.) cans minced clams (undrained)', '1 Tbsp. margarine', '1 to 2 Tbsp. flour', '1/2 to 2/3 c. milk', '4 oz. shredded Cheddar cheese', ' cooked pasta', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9544, ' Saut&eacute; onion , celery and garlic in butter. Add all other ingredients , except fish , and simmer for 30 minutes. Add fish in chunks and cook gently for 7 to 10 minutes.', '1 large onion , chopped', '1/2 c. celery , chopped with leaves', '1 large garlic clove', '2 Tbsp. butter', '2 (1 lb.) cans chopped tomatoes', '1/2 c. dry white wine', '1/2 c. minced parsley', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. rosemary', '1/4 tsp. pepper and thyme', '1 lb. fish (any whitefish , cod is very good)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9546, ' Saut&eacute; onion and garlic in oil. Add tomatoes , clam juice , wine , parsley , salt , thyme , bay leaf and pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add shrimp , fish , scallops and crab legs. Cook 5 minutes. Add clams and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with salad and garlic bread.', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 clove garlic', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 (28 oz.) can tomatoes (undrained)', '1 (12 oz.) can clam juice', '1 c. dry white wine', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 bay leaf', ' pepper to taste', '1/4 tsp. thyme', '1 lb. medium shrimp (raw) , peeled', '1 lb. firm , fresh fish', '1/2 lb. scallops', '1/2 lb. crab legs', '2 (6 1/2 oz.) chopped clams (undrained)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9548, ' Heat oil and butter in skillet. Add celery , onions and garlic. Cook lightly. Add flour and stir until incorporated. Lower heat. Add cream and stir until blended. Add clams and broth. Partially cover skillet and cook at lowest heat for 10 minutes. Add parsley.', '1/4 c. olive oil', '2 Tbsp. butter', '3/4 c. finely chopped celery', '3/4 c. finely chopped onion', '3 cloves garlic , diced', '1 Tbsp. flour', '1/2 c. dry white wine', '1 c. clam broth', '1 1/2 c. chopped clams', '1 lb. pasta (linguine , spaghetti , etc.)', '1/3 c. chopped parsley', '1 c. cream (light or half and half)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9556, ' In large skillet , saut peppers , carrots , celery , garlic and oregano. Add diced tomatoes , pesto , water , tomato sauce , salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes. Add shrimp. Cook only until shrimp turn pink. Serve over cooked and drained pasta. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '4 large red bell peppers , cut small', '1 c. diced carrots', '1 c. diced celery', '3 cloves garlic , diced', '1 Tbsp. oregano', '1 lb. fresh , cleaned shrimp', '1 (14 oz.) can diced tomatoes', '2 c. pesto', '1 c. water', '1 (15 oz.) can tomato sauce', ' salt and pepper to taste', '1 lb. pasta', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9575, ' Mix equal amounts of bread crumbs and cheese (enough to dredge chicken breasts). Mix egg whites with a few drops of water and pinch of salt. Dip chicken breasts in egg whites and then dredge in bread crumb mixture. Saut&eacute; in olive oil until browned on outside , but not cooked through. Remove and keep warm. Add more oil , if needed , to saut&eacute; onions until soft. Add sun-dried tomatoes with their oil , mushrooms and artichoke hearts. Stir and toss until mushrooms wilt. Add chicken broth , basil , olives and zest and return chicken to pot. Simmer , covered , until chicken is cooked through and sauce is hot. Serve over angel hair pasta and sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serves 4.', '4 medium , boneless chicken breasts', '2 egg whites', ' fine bread crumbs', ' grated Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 medium chopped onion', '1/4 c. sun-dried tomatoes , reconstituted in olive oil*', '2 c. sliced mushrooms (white and/or combination)', '1 can artichoke hearts', '1 c. chicken broth', '1 Tbsp. basil', '1/4 c. Greek olives , cut in half', '1 tsp. lemon zest', ' angel hair pasta', ' chopped parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9580, ' Cook pasta in boiling water 4 minutes. Add asparagus; cook 2 minutes or until tender. Drain.', '8 oz. uncooked angel hair pasta', '2 1/2 c. (1-inch) sliced asparagus (about 1 lb.)', '1 Tbsp. butter or stick margarine', '1/2 c. chopped green onions', '1 1/2 tsp. grated lemon rind', '3 Tbsp. fresh lemon juice', '3/4 c. fat-free milk', '2 large eggs', '1 Tbsp. chopped , fresh or dried dill', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. ground nutmeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9581, ' Heat oil in a large skillet. Add onion; saut&eacute; until tender (not brown) , 5 minutes. Stir in garlic. Add tomatoes , vodka and red pepper; break up tomatoes with side of spoon. Cook until sauce is reduced by 1/3 and thickened , 15 minutes. Stir in cream; simmer , stirring (do not allow to boil) 5 minutes. Season with salt.', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 clove garlic , finely chopped', '1 (28 oz.) can plum tomatoes with juice', '1/2 c. vodka', '1 tsp. crushed dried red pepper', '1/2 c. heavy cream (at room temperature)', ' salt', '12 oz. fresh or dried pasta', '2 Tbsp. parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9584, ' Trim asparagus and rinse in cold water. Remove the tips; set aside. Bias-slice remaining asparagus stalks into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces and set aside.', '16 thin stalks fresh asparagus', '1 Tbsp. olive oil', '4 cloves garlic , thinly sliced or minced', '6 medium plum tomatoes , seeded and chopped', '1/4 c. dry white wine', '1/4 tsp. each salt and pepper', '1 Tbsp. butter', '1 (9 oz.) pkg. refrigerated angel hair pasta', '1/4 c. shredded fresh basil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9620, ' Mix soup and ground beef , stir well. Add Pizza sauce and noodles. Pour into a large casserole dish , top with mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices. Cover loosely with foil and bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer. Makes a very large casserole. Will freeze well.', '2 1/2 lb. ground beef , browned &amp; drained', '7 oz. bag egg noodles , cooked &amp; drained', '2 cans cheddar cheese soup', '2 (14 oz) jars Ragu pizza sauce', ' Mozzarella cheese', ' Pepperoni slices', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9653, ' Put first 5 ingredients in a sauce pan and simmer on low until it is all melted/mixed well. Keep warm while doing the chicken.', '1 bottle (8 oz.) Durkee Red Hot Sauce (trust me,)', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '1 Tbsp. garlic wine vinegar', '1 Tbsp. honey', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', ' 2-3 pkgs. chicken wing drumettes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9656, ' Broil drumettes 20-25 minutes. Combine margarine , hot sauce &amp; vinegar in saucepan. Heat until melted and blended. Add chicken. Toss to coat evenly.', '12 pieces chicken wings - drumettes', '2 Tbsp. margarine - melted', '2 Tbsp. hot sauce', '1 1/2 Tbsp. red wine vinegar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9686, ' In a frying pan , heat oil and add seasoned chicken breast (salt and pepper). Brown chicken on both sides (10 to 15 minutes). Add 1/2 to 3/4 of the jar of spaghetti sauce. Cover and heat through for additional 15 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta. Put cheese on top of chicken breast and let melt. Put pasta on plate and serve chicken and sauce on top. Makes 2 servings.', '4 chicken breasts (boneless and skinless)', '1 tsp. olive oil', '1 (28 oz.) jar spaghetti sauce', '4 to 5 oz. pasta (any kind you like)', ' shredded Mozzarella cheese (1/2 oz. per chicken breast)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9690, ' Place chicken between 2 sheets heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thick with a rolling pin. Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs. Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray over medium heat. Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Spoon pasta sauce over chicken; cover , decrease heat and simmer , covered , 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Spoon 3/4 cup pasta on 4 plates; top each with a chicken breast and divide sauce evenly. Makes 4 servings.', '4 (4 oz.) skinned boned chicken breast halves', '1 egg , lightly beaten', '1/2 c. Italian seasoned bread crumbs', '1 1/2 tsp. margarine , melted', '1 3/4 c. tomato and garlic pasta sauce', '1/2 c. shredded part-skim Mozzarella', '1 Tbsp. grated Parmesan', '1/4 c. chopped fresh parsley', '3 c. hot cooked pasta', ' cooking spray', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9693, ' Rinse fish and dry with paper towel. Brush fish with olive oil. Salt and pepper both sides of the fish and place on a baking dish. Rub the top of the fish with the fresh garlic and sprinkle the fish with herbs. Bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes. Serve with your favorite side dishes. (I like to slice a lime and squeeze on my fish.) Makes 2 servings.', '2 fish fillets (flounder)', '2 tsp. olive oil', '2 tsp. crushed fresh garlic', '1 Tbsp. chopped parsley', '1 Tbsp. chopped basil or any herb you like', ' salt', ' pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9694, ' Spread softened cream cheese over 1 side of fillets. Place fillets cream side up in a sprayed nonstick 9-inch square pan. Thinly slice 1 lemon and place over top of fillets. Squeeze juice of other lemon over fish. Sprinkle top of fish with dill weed. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes. Yield: 4 servings.', '1 lb. fish fillets', '3 oz. fat-free cream cheese', '2 fresh lemons', '1 tsp. dill weed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9697, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Rinse fillets and pat dry. Combine all dry ingredients. Coat fillets evenly and shake off excess coating. Heat 1 tablespoon each of butter and oil over medium-high heat in large skillet until butter foams , but doesn''t burn. Cook 2 fillets , rounded side down , for 2 minutes. Turn fillets and cook 2 minutes. Transfer to a baking sheet , rounded side up. Wipe skillet; add remaining butter and oil. Repeat cooking process with remaining fillets. Spread fillets with pesto. Bake for 6 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Makes 4 servings.', '4 catfish fillets or fish of choice', '2 c. all-purpose flour', '1 Tbsp. salt', '1 tsp. ground red pepper', '2 Tbsp. butter , divided', '2 Tbsp. olive oil , divided', '1 jar pesto', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9714, ' Saut&eacute; mushrooms in cooking spray and set aside. Cook carrots in cooking spray and set aside. Cook frozen spinach and strain as much water out as possible.', ' vegetable cooking spray', '2 c. sliced fresh mushrooms', '2 c. chopped spinach (frozen)', '1 1/2 c. coarsely shredded carrots', '1 c. lite Ricotta cheese', '1/2 c. egg substitute', '2 Tbsp. fresh chopped parsley', '9 cooked lasagna noodles', '26 oz. jar pasta sauce', '1 c. low-fat shredded Mozzarella', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
