(9754, ' Generously spread olive oil over top of Boboli bread and bake at 350&deg; for 10 minutes. Spread fresh garlic from garlic press or Polaner chopped garlic on olive oil. Precook chicken breasts and cut into bite-sized pieces. Spread over crust. Top with mushrooms , onions , cheese , garlic salt and oregano. Bake at 350&deg; for about 1/2 hour.', '1 large Boboli bread pizza crust (thin or pan style)', ' olive oil', '2 or 3 chicken breasts', ' fresh mushrooms', '1 bag Sicilian shredded cheese', ' fresh garlic or Polaner real chopped garlic', ' onions', ' garlic salt', ' oregano', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9794, ' Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Grease a 14-inch pizza pan. Mix together first 6 ingredients. Press onto pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes. Top with remaining ingredients and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.', '1 cup whole wheat flour', '1 cup oat flour (1/4 cup rolled oats blend until fine)', '1/4 cup corn meal', '1 tsp. baking powder', '2/3 cup milk', '1/4 cup oil', '5 slices bacon (cooked , drained , and crumbled)', '1/2 pound ground beef (browned and drained)', '1 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese', '2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese', ' pizza sauce , peppers , onions , olives , as desired', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(9878, ' Mix first 5 ingredients. Dip tomatoes in batter. Fry in 2-inches of hot oil (375&deg;). Turn once during browning. Don''t drain on paper; it makes them soggy.', '3/4 c. flour', '1/4 c. cornmeal', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '3/4 c. milk', '4 green tomatoes , cut 1/4-inch thick', ' buttermilk or Ranch dressing (for dipping)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10067, ' Brown ground beef and drain , add 2 or 3 cans diced tomatoes , sliced green pepper , sliced onion , mushrooms , clove of garlic , black olives , and sliced sausage. Add seasoning salt , Cavender''s Greek Seasoning , 3-4 dashes of Worcestershire Sauce , 3-4 dashes of hot sauce; all to cooks desire. Simmer until all onions and peppers are done , then add box of cooked bowtie pasta. Serve with shredded cheddar cheese , parmesan cheese , and garlic bread. You can substitute the sliced sausage with ground sausage , or add both and also can add any left over chicken you may have.', ' 1-2 lb. ground beef', ' 2-3 cans diced tomatoes', ' sliced green peppers to taste', ' sliced onion to taste', '1 can mushrooms', '1 garlic clove', '1 pkg. smoked kielbasa or smoked sausage', ' seasoning salt', ' Cavender''s Greek Seasoning', ' Worcestershire sauce', '1 pkg. bowtie pasta , cooked', ' your favorite shredded cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10194, ' Place margarine and onion in a 1-cup glass measure and cook on full power 1 1/2 minutes or until onion is soft. Arrange fish in a shallow baking dish with thicker edges of fish to outside of dish. Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish; cover with diced tomato pieces. Spread margarine and onions evenly over tomatoes. Cover with wax paper; cook 3 minutes on full power. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with waxed paper; cook 1 minute more or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Sprinkle with paprika. Makes 4 servings.', '1 Tbsp. margarine', '2 Tbsp. finely chopped onion', '1 lb. fish fillets (such as cod , flounder or trout)', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. black pepper', '1 large tomato , diced', '3 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese', ' paprika (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10265, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. Cook and drain pasta shells as directed on package. Spread spaghetti sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients , except pesto. Fill each pasta shell with about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture. Arrange filled shells on spaghetti sauce. Cover and bake approximately 45 minutes or until hot. Serve with pesto.', '24 uncooked jumbo pasta shells', '2 c. spaghetti sauce', '2 c. Ricotta cheese', '1 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese (4 oz.)', '1/2 c. grated Parmesan cheese', '2 Tbsp. chopped fresh parsley', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '2 eggs', '1 c. pesto (if desired)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10456, ' Fry bacon until crispy. Add onions and peppers and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in sugar , barbecue sauce and syrups. Put the beans in a 12 x 6 x 3-inch foil pan. Add bacon mixture , beer or apple juice and brisket ends. Stir to mix. To grill , set the pan on the grill over hot coals. Cover grill and , stirring three times , cook 40 to 60 minutes , depending on the amount of liquid desired. To cook indoors , heat oven to 400&deg; , assemble as directed , cover pan with loose foil tent and bake 40 to 60 minutes , stirring three times. Makes 6 cups.', '8 oz. sliced bacon , diced', '1 c. onion , diced', '1 red bell pepper , diced', '1 green bell pepper , diced', '1 c. packed dark brown sugar', ' Pulverized , burned ends of grilled brisket (optional)', '1 c. barbecue sauce', '1/3 c. maple pancake syrup', '1/3 c. light corn syrup', '3 (28 oz.) cans pork &amp; beans , drained', '2/3 c. beer or apple juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10463, ' Heat oven to 350&deg; F. Lightly grease a shallow 3-quart baking dish. Melt butter , toss with cracker crumbs to moisten evenly. Whisk soup mix , dry mustard and nutmeg in large bowl to blend. Whisk in cream , eggs and egg yolks until very well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour all into prepared baking dish. Sprinkle cracker crumb mixture on pudding near edges of dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until a knife inserted near center comes out clean and temperature of center registers 160&deg; on an instant meat thermometer. (Center will jiggle when dish is moved , that''s ok.) Serves 12.', '2 Tbsp. butter', '12 saltine crackers , crushed into crumbs', '1 (1.8 oz.) pkg. leek soup and dip mix', '2 tsp. dry mustard', '1/2 tsp. ground nutmeg', '1 c. heavy whipping cream', '2 large eggs', ' Yolks from 2 large eggs', '2 (15 1/4 oz.) whole kernel corn , drained', '2 (4 3/4 oz.) cans cream style corn', '1 (2 oz.) jar roasted red pepper , drained , patted dry and chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10507, ' Trim and discard tough stems from mushrooms , rinse and drain. Cut caps into thin strips. Cut stems or stalks from greens , removing wilted leaves. Slice stem or stalks diagonally into 1/2 inch wide pieces. Cut leaves crosswise into 1/2 inch wide strips. Wash well and drain.', '1/4 lb. fresh mushrooms', '1 1/2 lbs. your favorite greens (may mix different greens)', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', ' salt to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10508, ' Wash and cut the eggplant in half lengthwise. Remove as much of the white portion as possible without breaking the shell. Cut the pulp into small pieces and cook in small quantity of hot water for 10 minutes , or until tender. Drain. Mix together the melted butter and bread crumbs. Reserve 1/2 of the crumb mixture for the topping. To the remaining crumbs add the onion , beans , salt , pepper and the eggplant pulp. Mix thoroughly. Pile lightly into the eggplant shells. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Place in a shallow baking dish. Pour a few tablespoons of hot water around the shells to keep them from sticking. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Serve hot.', '1 large eggplant', '4 Tbsp. butter', '1 1/2 cups bread crumbs', '1 small onion , finely chopped', '1 cup cooked green beans (or other favorite vegetable)', '1 tsp. salt', ' pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10654, ' Melt butter and garlic. Stir-fry vegetables 5 minutes. Add milk and basil. Stir in Velveeta. Cover and simmer until cheese melts and sauce thickens. Add rotini pasta; cover and let set.', '1 c. fresh cut broccoli', '1 c. julienne cut carrots', '1 c. julienne cut zucchini', '1 c. julienne cut green peppers', '1/2 stick margarine', '1 Tbsp. fresh garlic', '1 c. milk', '1 1/2 c. Velveeta cheese , cubed', '1 1/2 c. cooked rotini pasta', '1 tsp. basil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10672, ' Cook broccoli and pasta separately. When pasta and broccoli are done , mix together. Add Parmesan garlic sauce. Mix well and serve. If you like , sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano cheese.', '2 (16 oz.) bags cut broccoli', '1 (16 oz.) box twist pasta', '2 (26 oz.) jars Ragu garlic Parmesan sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10710, ' Cover with water and cook until tender.', '3 c. sliced potatoes', '1 onion , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10753, ' Saut&eacute; onion. Pour soup into a quart casserole dish. Add saut&eacute;ed onion , green beans , mushroom pieces and pepper. Mix well. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.', '3/4 c. chopped Onion', '1 can low fat cream of mushroom Soup', '2 cans Green Beans , drained', '1 can Mushroom pieces', ' Dash of Black Pepper', '1/2 c. reduced fat Potato Chips , crushed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10826, ' Empty potato slices and packet of seasoned sauce mix into ungreased 2 quart casserole dish. Heat tomatoes , and water to boiling , stir into potatoes. Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400&deg; for 30 to 35 minutes uncovered.', '1 pkg. scalloped potatoes', '1 (16 oz.) can tomatoes or pizza sauce', '1 1/2 c. water', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. sliced pepperoni', '1 pkg. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10830, ' In a small sauce pan , saut&eacute; onions &amp; garlic in olive oil until browned. In large sauce pan , melt butter. Add flour &amp; stir. Slowly add Half &amp; Half and milk , simmer , stirring constantly till thickened. Add cheese &amp; seasonings. Stir until cheese melts and add tomatoes , spinach and onion mixture. Heat through. Pour over warmed pasta toss and serve.', '1 8 oz. pasta , cooked &amp; drained', '1 tbsp. extra virgin olive oil', '1 med. onion , chopped', '2 cloves garlic , crushed', '2 tbsp. butter', '3 tbsp. flour', '1 1/2 c. skim milk', '1 1/2 c. fat free Half &amp; Half', '1 c. gr. Parmesan', '2 tsp. dried Ital. seasoning', ' Salt , pepper to taste', '1 14 oz can diced tomatoes , seasoned', '1 10 oz. pkg. frozen chopped spinach , thawed &amp; drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10982, ' Cook pasta to directions on box. DO NOT OVERCOOK. In large skillet , heat oil. Stir-fry onions and garlic for 1 minute. Add tomatoes , basil , salt and pepper. Stir and cook for 2 minutes. Toss sauce with hot pasta. Sprinkle with cheese.', '1/2 lb. angel hair pasta', '1/2 c. olive oil', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1/4 c. fresh basil (leaves only) , chopped', '3 large tomatoes , peeled and chopped', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', ' Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11305, ' Preheat oven to 400&deg;. Combine first 8 ingredients in a large roasting pan. Add olive oil and toss to coat well. Bake until vegetables are tender , stirring occasionally , about 45 minutes. Add broccoli. Bake until crisp and tender (about 10 minutes).', '1 small eggplant , cut into 3/4-inch pieces', '2 to 3 small potatoes (unpeeled) , cut into 3/4-inch pieces', '2 to 3 carrots , thinly sliced', '1 1/2 medium red onions , cut in 1-inch pieces', '1 c. mushrooms , quartered', '8 large garlic cloves , crushed', '1/2 tsp. crumbled thyme', '1/2 tsp. crumbled rosemary', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '2 c. broccoli florets', '1 lb. rigatoni (shell or fusilli pasta)', '2 Tbsp. grated Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11324, ' Cook eggplant in boiling water 5 minutes - drain. Place in lightly greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole; add mozzarella cheese &amp; top with marinara or spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese &amp; bake about 5 minutes.', '1 large eggplant , peeled &amp; cubed', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. mozzarella cheese , shredded', '1 (15 oz.) jar marinara sauce (or your favorite spaghetti sauce)', '1/3 c. grated parmesian cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11362, ' This dish will probably need to be done in at least 3 batches , depending on the size of your wok or pot. Divide the ingredients proportionally for each batch. Saut the garlic and ginger in oil on medium heat for 1 or 2 minutes. Add the greens and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add the remaining ingredients , except the soy or fish sauce. Continue to stir-fry until the greens are tender. Toss the soy or fish sauce with the greens right before serving.', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '10 cloves garlic , pressed', ' ginger root (fresh) , grated', ' greens (kale , collards , chard , mustard , bok choy , rapini; fresh) , chopped', ' sherry , Chinese rice wine or mirin', ' white vinegar or lemon juice (fresh; optional)', ' sugar or honey', ' water', ' soy sauce or fish sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11455, ' Cook sausage and onions. Mix with cheeses and eggs , salt and pepper. Spread one pizza dough in the bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Top with sausage mix. Spread second tube of pizza dough on top of sausage mixture. Bake in 350&deg; oven for 30 minutes.', '2 tubes Pillsbury pizza dough (In dairy case)', '1 1/2 lb. Bob Evans sausage', '2 c. Cheddar cheese , shredded', '2 c. Swiss cheese , shredded', '2 eggs', '1/2 c. onion , chopped', ' Salt &amp; pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11460, ' Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk , add eggs and sour cream. Sift together flour and salt and cut in butter or margarine as for pie dough. Add yeast mixture. Mix well and chill overnight. Divide dough in 4 parts. Roll each to a rectangle , brush with melted butter and sprinkle with a little cinnamon and spread liberally with nuts , raisins and a hand full of brown sugar. Roll up like jelly roll sealing edge firmly. Form into a ring sealed side down on greased pan sealing ends. Brush with melted butter or margarine. Let rise 2 hours. Cut about 6 gashes in ring to let steam escape during baking. Bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes or until done. Frost with confectioners icing. Butter rings also are delicious with prepared poppy seed or Solo filling. Yields 4 rings.', '1 cake yeast', '1/4 c. lukewarm milk', '2 eggs', '1 c. sour cream', '4 c. all-purpose flour , sifted', '1 tsp. salt', '1 c. butter or margarine', ' Melted butter or margarine', ' Cinnamon', ' Chopped nuts', ' Raisins', ' Brown sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11470, ' Mix - keep one cup aside. Press the rest into bottom of pan.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1/2 c. oleo , melted', '1 egg , beaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11490, ' Add enough warm water to milk to make one quart. Add the shortening , melted , to this. Then add yeast cake and sugar to lukewarm water. Let stand 3 minutes. Add salt to liquid. Then add enough flour to make a dough stiff enough to knead. Let rise until double , covered with a wet towel. Knead again until light and springy. Divide in 4 equal parts and shape into loaves. Place in greased pans and let rise until light , not quite so much as double in bulk. Bake in 350&deg; oven for 30 minutes.', '1 can Eagle Brand milk', '1/3 c. shortening', '1 yeast cake', '1/4 c. lukewarm water', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '1 Tbsp. salt', '11 c. flour (approximately)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11510, ' Bowl #1: Mix sugar , water and yeast. Wait approximately 5 minutes or until bubbly.', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 1/2 c. lukewarm water', '1 cake yeast', '1/2 c. Crisco shortening', '1/2 tsp. salt', '5 c. all-purpose flour (enough to mix well)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11562, ' In a mixing bowl , beat cream cheese , sugar and egg yolk. Separate dough into 16 triangles. Place on lightly greased baking sheets. Spread 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture near the edge of the short side of each triangle. Top with 1 tablespoon of pie filling. Fold long point of triangle over filling and tuck under dough. Lightly beat egg white; brush over rolls. Bake at 350&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. YIELD: 16 rolls.', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1 c. confectioners sugar', '1 egg , separated', '2 (8 oz.) tubes refrigerated crescent rolls', '1 (21 oz.) can cherry pie filling or your favorite flavor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11571, ' Mix together and pour into bread pans (2 large or 3 mini). Bake at 350&deg; for 20 to 30 minutes.', '1 box lemon cake mix', '1 box lemon pudding (instant)', '1/3 c. oil', '4 eggs', '1 c. boiling water', '1 to 2 tsp. poppy seeds', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11744, ' ', '1 1/2 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. plus 2 Tbsp. oil', '3 Tbsp. cold milk in cup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11763, ' Melt butter , put aside. Beat eggs well. Add sugar. Add extract. Add seeds and mix. Add melted butter; mix. Add baking powder and flour. Mix until you get a dough texture.', '4 Extra Large Eggs', '1 1/2 cups Sugar', '1/4 lb. Butter', '3 tbsp. Baking Powder', '2 tbsp. Anise Extract', '1 heaping tbsp. Anise Seed', '3 1/2 cups Flour (sifted)', '1 tsp preserves of your choice for each 1/4 scoop (Our favorite is strawberry or apricot)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11835, ' Dissolve the sugar in lukewarm water. Stir into the yeast and leave in a warm place for 10 to 15 minutes until frothy. In a large bowl , mix the flour with the salt and rub in the margarine. Beat the yeast liquid into the flour to form a dough. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead by folding the dough toward you , then pushing away with the palm of the hand for about 10 minutes , until firm and elastic. Place the dough in bowl. Cover with lightly oiled polythene and leave to rise until double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours in warm place). Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead for about 2 minutes until firm. Shape to fit a lightly greased 450-g/1-pound loaf pan; cover with oiled polythene and leave in a warm place for about 45 minutes until the dough is just rounded over the top of the pan. Heat the oven to 450&deg;. Bake the loaf for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown and sounds hollow if tapped underneath. Cool on a wire tray.', '1 tsp. sugar', '1 1/2 tsp. dried yeast or 15 g/1/2 cake compressed yeast', '450 g/4 c. whole-wheat flour', '1 tsp. salt', '15 g/1 Tbsp. polyunsaturated margarine', '250 ml/1 1/8 c. (approximately) lukewarm water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11875, ' Beat egg yolks in bowl until thick. Add and blend sugar , salt and brandy. Add flour alternately with sour cream until all blended. Turn dough on floured board. Cover and let rise for 10 minutes. Knead dough until it blisters. Roll very thin. Cut into strips 1-inch wide and 4-inches long. Cut gash in center and pull one end of strip through. Fry in deep fat at 370&deg; until light brown; turn over. Cool and dust with powdered sugar.', '5 egg yolks', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. sugar', '2 shots banana brandy', '2 c. flour', '5 Tbsp. sour cream', ' fat or oil (for frying)', ' powdered sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11876, ' Beat eggs with sugar; add cool melted butter and beat well. Add rind , salt and warm cream. Beat well. Add flour slowly and continue to beat. Add yeast , dissolved in warm milk and mix thoroughly. Beat dough about 10 minutes and set in bowl to rise. When doubled , punch down and let rise again. Proceed to fill and fry.', '4 c. warm flour', '3 whole eggs', '1/2 c. butter , melted', '6 egg yolks', '2 cakes yeast', '1 orange rind , grated', '1 c. half and half', '3/4 c. sugar', '1 tsp. salt', '1 Tbsp. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11877, ' In large bowl , beat eggs and sugar until lemon in color. Add melted butter and lemon juice. Add yeast that was mixed with 1/2 cup warm milk and water. Add flour alternately and rest of milk and water until all used up (if dough is too sticky , add a bit of flour). Dough should be heavy enough to drop off spoon , but not runny. Let rise until double. Drop by tablespoon into oil (375&deg;). Fry 2 to 3 minutes until dark brown in color so they are not raw inside. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.', '7 1/2 c. flour', '5 eggs (room temperature)', '1 c. sugar', '2 sticks oleo , melted', '1 can Pet milk', '1 c. water (warm , not hot)', '1 cake yeast', '1 tsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11904, ' ', '1 pkg. yellow cake mix', '1 egg', '1/2 c. melted butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11921, ' Beat egg well; add crumbled yeast , sugar and salt. Add Crisco. Then add flour and milk gradually. Knead lightly. Let rise , then knead down and make rolls. Let rise and bake in hot oven. Leftover dough may be put in bowl , covered and refrigerated until the next day.', '1 egg , well beaten', '1 yeast cake , crumbled in egg', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '2 tsp. salt', '3 Tbsp. Crisco', '6 c. flour', '1 c. canned milk', '1 c. dairy milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11969, ' Mix cake mix , oil , and eggs. Beat well. Add soda. Add mashed bananas last. If desired , add nuts. Bake in two loaf pans at 325&deg; for about 35 to 40 minutes.', '1 box white cake mix', '1 c. oil', '3 ripe bananas , mashed real well', '1/2 tsp. soda', '4 eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(11992, ' Mix together and spoon in 12 count muffin pan (regular size). Bake at 350&deg; for 20-25 minutes.', ' One package cake mix (any kind but lowest fat gram is best)', '1/2 c. water', '1 (15 oz.) can pumpkin (not pie filling , just plain pumpkin)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(12177, ' Scald poppy seeds with hot water to cover good. Set a few hours or overnight. Grind , then add sugar , eggs , vanilla , and cinnamon. Or can also add 1/4 to 1/2 cup cream and cook till bubbles in heavy kettle that doesn''t scorch easy , stir all the while.', '1 lb. of poppy seed', '1 c. sugar', '3 or 4 eggs', '2 tsp. vanilla', '1/2 tsp. cinnamon', '1/4 to 1/2 c. cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(12205, ' Cut crusts off slices of bread. Butter each slice lightly. Spread with bacon cheese spread. Roll up and place close together on a cookie sheet. Drizzle with melted butter and broil.', ' slices of bread', ' jar of bacon cheese spread', ' butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
