(13317, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans. In mixer bowl , combine mix , oil and eggs , beat thoroughly. Stir in oranges and their juice. Divide batter among the prepared pans. Bake in preheated oven for 20 - 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes , then turn out and cool on racks.', '1 pkg. two-layer Duncan Hines Deluxe II yellow butter cake mix', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '4 eggs', '1 (11 oz.) can Mandarin oranges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13324, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Prepare cake mix according to package directions , omitting oil and adding 6 Tbsp. coconut. Pour batter into a 13 x 9 inch baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake for 28 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cook in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack.', '1 (18.25 oz.) pkg. reduced-fat white cake mix (such as Sweet Rewards', '3/4 c. flaked sweetened coconut , divided', ' Cooking spray', '1 (14 oz.) can fat-free sweetened condensed milk (Not evaporated milk)', '1 tsp. coconut extract', '1 1/2 c. frozen reduced-calorie whipped topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13327, ' Pour water over gelatin and stir until dissolved. Add frozen berries and stir until thawed. Place cubed angel food cake in a 9 x 13 inch pan and pour jello mixture on top of cake. Frost with whipped topping and refrigerate.', '1 c. boiling water', '2 boxes (4 serving size) strawberry gelatin', '2 pkg. (10 oz.) frozen strawberries', '1 angel food cake , cubed', '1 carton whipped topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13328, ' Spray 9 x 13 inch baking pan with Pam. Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan. Bake according to package directions at 350&deg;. Batter will be thick.', '1 box devils food cake mix', '1 can cherry pie filling', '2 eggs', '1 tsp. almond extract (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13329, ' Prepare 9 x 12 inch cake pan by greasing and flouring the sides. Mix cake as directed on box. Put sugar and butter in pan and bring to boil. Pour sugar mixture in cake pan and arrange pineapple slices on top of sugar mix. Put cherries in center of pineapple slices. Pour batter over pineapple. Bake at 350&deg; for 40 - 50 minutes. Remove from oven , cool 5 minutes , and turn upside down on cake plate.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1/2 cup melted butter or oleo', '1 cup brown sugar', ' Pineapple slices', ' Maraschino cherries', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13331, ' Mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Bake in 3 round layers or 9 x 13 inch baking pan for 30 minutes at 350&deg;. Cool. Frost.', '1 box butter cake mix (Duncan Hines)', '1 (11 oz.) can Mandarin oranges with juice', '1/2 c. oil', '4 eggs', '1/2 to 1 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13333, ' Beat egg yolks until thick. Add sugar and beat until well blended. Sift flour. Measure required amount after sifting. Sift again with the rest of the dry ingredients. Add alternately with cold coffee and vanilla to egg mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter. Fold in nuts , reserving a few for the top. Pour batter into 2 ungreased 9 inch cake pans and bake in a preheated 350&deg; oven for 25 - 30 minutes.', '5 egg yolks', '1 c. granulated sugar', '1 c. sifted cake flour', '1 tsp. baking powder', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', '5 egg whites', '1 c. ground nuts', '5 Tbsp. cold strong coffee', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13334, ' Mix cake mix as directed except decrease water to 1 cup. Stir in zucchini. Bake in 9 x 13 inch baking pan or 2 (8 or 9 inch) round pans in 350&deg; preheated oven for 37 to 39 minutes. Frost with your favorite icing.', '1 Betty Crocker Super Moist Devils Food cake mix', '2 c. shredded zucchini', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13361, ' Put angel food cake mix in bowl. Stir in crushed pineapple (juice and all). The juice from the pineapple will serve in place of the liquid to mix your cake. Be sure to stir in...do not use a mixer. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake as directed on cake box. Remove from oven. Take a toothpick and poke holes in cake. Mix your Jello in a bowl; pour over cake. Refrigerate and let Jello set up. Spread Cool Whip (can be fat-free) over Jello. Cut and serve.', '1 box one-step angel food cake mix', '1 (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. Jello mix (any flavor)', '1 large carton Cool Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13368, ' Mix cream cheese , sugar , cinnamon and 1/2 tsp. orange extract. Mix till smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip and cranberry sauce. Set aside. Using an 8 inch square pan , arrange 1/3 of cake slices on bottom of pan. Mix together milk , vanilla and 1/2 tsp. orange extract. Drizzle approximately 2 Tbsp. of milk mixture over cake slices. Spread 1/3 of cream cheese over cake slices. Repeat for second and third layers. You will end up with cream mix on top. Top with slices of almonds and cinnamon.', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1 tsp. pure orange extract', '2 c. Cool Whip', '1 c. whole cranberry sauce', '1 small loaf (10 - 12 oz.) pound cake , thinly sliced', '1/2 c. milk', '1 tsp. vanilla', ' Sliced almonds', ' Cinnamon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13374, ' In a double boiler , melt chocolate chips with hot water. Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks and sugar. Set aside to cool. Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat whipping cream until stiff. Fold egg whites and cream together. Then add to cooled chocolate mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Break angel food cake into small pieces. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour chocolate mixture over cake in pan. Mix with a fork and spread evenly. Refrigerate overnight.', '2 small pkg. chocolate chips', '3 Tbsp. hot water', '4 Tbsp. powdered sugar', '4 egg yolks , beaten', '4 egg whites , beaten', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', '1 angel food cake', '1/2 pt. whipping cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13375, ' ', '1 pkg. yellow cake mix', '3/4 c. Crisco oil', '3/4 c. apricot nectar', '4 eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13376, ' Slice bananas into large mixing bowl. Beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients. Blend. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into 10-inch well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350&deg; for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool in pan at least 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Finish cooling on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar , if desired. (May be baked in 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.)', '1 to 2 small ripe bananas', '1 (2 layer size) pkg. yellow cake mix', '1 (4 serving size) pkg. banana or vanilla instant pudding', '4 eggs', '1 c. water', '1/4 c. oil', '1/2 c. chopped nuts (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13377, ' Mix cake mix , softened butter and egg. Press mixture in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle evenly Bits ''o Brickle and chopped pecans over the mixture. Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top of the mixture evenly. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350&deg;. Slice into bars to serve.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1 stick butter , softened', '1 egg', '1 can sweetened condensed milk', '1 pkg. Bits ''o Brickle', '1 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13380, ' Measure out 1 cup of dry cake mix. Set aside. In large mixing bowl , stir together remaining dry cake mix , 1 egg and Crisco oil (mixture will be crumbly). Press crust mixture into bottom and 3/4 of the way up sides of a greased 13 x 9 pan. In same bowl , blend cream cheese and sugar together. Add 3 eggs and rest of cake mix. Beat 1 minute at medium speed. At low speed , gradually add milk , lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Pour into crumb crust. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes , until center is firm. Cool. Spoon cherries over cake and chill 1 hour. Store , covered , in refrigerator.', '1 box Duncan Hines Deluxe II yellow cake mix', '2 Tbsp. Crisco oil', '2 (8 oz.) cream cheese , softened', '1/2 c. sugar', '4 eggs', '1 1/2 c. milk', '3 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 large can cherry pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
