(13391, ' Bake cake as directed on cake mix box. Bake in 9 x 13 pan. While cake is hot , punch holes all over cake with fork. Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk. Pour over cake while cake is still warm. Let cool completely. Mix cup of coconut (more coconut if you prefer) into Cool Whip. Spread on top of cake. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake. Keep in refrigerator.', '1 box yellow or white cake mix', '1 can cream of coconut', '1 can Eagle Brand milk', '1 medium Cool Whip', ' coconut', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13392, ' Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cool. Use drinking straw (or similar size) to punch holes all over surface. Mix together cream of coconut and milk. Pour over cake. Refrigerate overnight. Next day , spread Cool Whip over cake , then sprinkle coconut on top. Serve.', '1 box white cake mix', ' small can cream of coconut', ' small can Eagle Brand milk', '1 (12 oz.) container Cool Whip', '6 oz. flaked frozen coconut', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13393, ' Mix all ingredients together. Beat well for 3 minutes. Bake at 350&deg; in 9 x 13 x 2 pan for 30 to 35 minutes or until done in middle.', '1 box Duncan Hines White or yellow cake mix', '1/4 c. Crisco oil', '3 eggs , well beaten', '1 c. sour cream', '1 (8 1/2 oz.) can cream of coconut', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
