(13721, ' Make a crust of margarine , flour , and nuts. Put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes; let cool. Cream together cream cheese , powdered sugar , and 1 c. Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Mix pudding and milk; when thickened , spread over the top. Cover all with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and more nuts.', '1 stick margarine', '1 c. plain flour', '1/2 c. nuts , chopped (plus extra for topping)', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1 c. powdered sugar', ' Cool Whip', '2 pkg. instant chocolate pudding (or your favorite)', '3 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13726, ' In pot , combine apples , water , 1 c. (2 sticks) margarine , and sugar; season with apple pie spice to taste. Cook till hot and flavors are blended.; remove from heat and thicken with a little cornstarch and water.', '1 gal. apples , cut up', '4 c. water', ' apple pie spice', '1 c. brown sugar', '2 boxes yellow cake mix', '1 box vanilla instant pudding mix', '1 1/2 to 2 c. nuts , chopped', '3 c. margarine (6 sticks) divided', '2 c. granulated sugar', ' cornstarch', ' nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13733, ' Spray bottom of 12 x 18 pan with Pam. Pour blueberries over bottom of pan , making sure the bottom is covered completely. Sprinkle sugar over berries; sprinkle pineapple with liquid over berries and sugar. Sprinkle dry cake mix (about 1 and 1/2 box) over pineapple. Top with nuts; drizzle melted margarine over all. Bake at 350&deg; for about 1 hour. If using convection oven , bake between 300&deg; and 325&deg;. Juices will bubble up through cake mix. Serve hot with Cool Whip or ice cream. About 25 good size servings.', ' about 1 gal. fresh blueberries', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 large can crushed pineapple (with liquid)', '2 boxes yellow cake mix', '2 c. margarine , melted', '1 1/2 to 2 c. nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13739, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Beat sugar , vanilla , cinnamon , milk , and eggs together. Blend in pumpkin. Pour into pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top; sprinkle nuts then drizzle margarine over. Bake about 45 minutes. If pecans begin to brown too fast , reduce heat or cover with a sheet of foil.', '1 (12 oz.) can evaporated milk', '3 eggs', '1 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '2 c. pumpkin (16 oz. can)', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1 1/2 c. pecans , chopped', '1 1/2 sticks butter , melted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13746, ' Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in egg yolks , one at a time. Add baking powder and salt to flour and sift four times. Add milk and flour alternately to batter; add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour into three round cake pans , which have been greased and floured. Bake at 350&deg; for about 20 minutes , or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.', '1 c. margarine', '2 c. sugar', '3 c. cake flour', '4 eggs , separated', '1 c. milk', '1/2 tsp. salt', '2 rounded tsp. baking powder', '1 tsp. vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13756, ' Mix cake mix according to pkg. directions. Divide the batter into three 8 or 9 inch pans that have been sprayed with Pam. Bake according to directions. Remove from oven and allow to cool.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '3 egg whites', '3/4 c. Karo (white)', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '3 or 4 c. pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13758, ' Combine cake mix , water , pudding mix , and bananas; blend well. Add eggs , one at a time , beating after each addition. Stir in spices; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan; fill with batter and bake at 350&deg; for 60 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes and turn on rack to cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar and serve.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '4 eggs , room temperature', '1/3 c. cooking oil', '1/2 c. water', '1 1/3 c. ripe mashed bananas (about 4 medium size)', '1 (3 3/4 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding mix', '1/2 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 tsp. nutmeg', ' powdered sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13760, ' Sift flour , baking soda , salt , and sugar; set aside. Cream margarine and blend in lemon rind. Add flour mixture , buttermilk , and vanilla; mix until flour is damp , then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Add eggs and beat 1 minute longer. Pour into two 9 inch cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 350&deg;.', '2 1/2 c. cake flour', '1/2 tsp. soda', '1 tsp. salt', '3/4 stick margarine', '1 c. buttermilk', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 1/2 tsp. baking powder', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '2 tsp. grated lemon rinds', '3 eggs , unbeaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13763, ' Prepare cake according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch cake pans. Bake at 325&deg; for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove and finish cooling on wire racks. Beat cream cheese , powdered and granulated sugars until mixture is creamy. Chop 8 of the candy bars. Fold candy bars and cream cheese into Cool Whip. Spread between cake layers , on top , and sides. Chop remaining candy bars and press on top and along bottom edge of cake. Very rich and delicious,', '1 box Swiss Chocolate cake mix', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1 c. powdered sugar', '1/2 c. granulated sugar', '10 (1.5 oz.) Hershey candy bars with almonds', '1 (12 oz.) Cool Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13764, ' Mix cake according to directions. You can add the 4 egg yolks that will be left over from the Coconut Divinity Icing recipe listed below. Pour into 3 round pans and bake according to pkg. directions. Allow to cool before icing.', '1 box Duncan Hines Butter Recipe cake mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13766, ' Mix all ingredients; beat well. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 350&deg; for 35 minutes or until done. Frost.', '1 box white cake mix', '1/4 c. cooking oil', '3 eggs', '1 small carton sour cream', '8 1/2 oz. cream of coconut', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13769, ' Mix all ingredients together with a spoon. Do not use a mixer because it will tear up the cherries. Put in a greased and floured 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Bake about 40 minutes at 350&deg;. Make icing and pour over the still warm cake.', '1 box of Devils Food cake mix with pudding', '2 eggs', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 can cherry pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13773, ' Cream together butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar; beat well. Beat in eggs , one at a time; add vanilla. Combine flour , salt , and baking powder; add to cream cheese mixture. Blend in raisins. Heavily grease a tube pan; sprinkle 6 Tbsp. of chopped pecans in pan. Pour batter in pan and bake at 300&deg; approximately 1 1/2 hours. Let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing.', '1 lb. butter', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '2 tsp. vanilla', '4 eggs', '2 1/4 c. sifted cake flour', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 1/2 c. seedless raisins , chopped', '6 Tbsp. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13776, ' Combine coconut and pecans; spread on bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan that has been greased and floured. Mix box of cake mix according to pkg. directions; pour into pan. Combine cream cheese , powdered sugar , and butter. Drop by teaspoonfuls over top of cake batter. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes.', '1 c. coconut', '1 c. pecans , chopped', '1 box German chocolate cake mix', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1 (16 oz.) box powdered sugar', '1 stick butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13778, ' In a small bowl sift together cake flour , sugar , baking powder , and salt; Make a well in the center. Add cooking oil , egg yolks , water , lemon peel , and vanilla. Beat mixture at high speed with electric mixer about 5 minutes or until satin smooth. Wash beaters. Make sure they are completely dry before next step.', '2 1/4 c. sifted cake flour', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '1 Tbsp. baking powder', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. cooking oil', '5 egg yolks', '3/4 c. water', '2 tsp. finely shredded lemon peel', '1 tsp. vanilla', '8 egg whites', '1/2 tsp. cream of tartar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13791, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Grease and flour a bundt pan. Combine cake mix , eggs , water , and oil. Beat with mixer until well blended. Pour into pan. Bake for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan 25 minutes. Invert onto serving plate; cool completely.', '1 box Lemon Supreme cake mix', '4 eggs', '1/3 c. oil', '1 box lemon pudding mix (3.4 oz.)', '1 c. milk or water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13793, ' Cream oleo and sugar; add egg and beat 1 minute. Mix flour , soda , salt , and spices; stir in raisins and pecans. Heat persimmon pulp to boiling; add all ingredients together , beating well. Bake in 2 greased and floured 8 inch pans at 375&deg; for 25 to 30 minutes. (In a loaf pan , bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350&deg;.) Cake keeps well frozen.', '1/2 c. oleo', '2 c. sugar', '1 egg', '1 3/4 c. cake flour', '1 tsp. soda', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. cinnamon (or more)', '1 tsp. ground cloves', '1 c. raisins', '1 c. pecans', '1 c. persimmon pulp', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13794, ' Bake cake mix according to pkg. directions in two 9 inch round cake pans. When cooled , slice layers in half forming 4 round layers. Combine pineapple , sugar , and corn starch in sauce pan and cook over medium heat until thickened. When cake is thoroughly cooled , place layers on cake plate and put a layer of filling between each layer. Frost with pineapple icing.', '1 box of yellow cake mix', '1 large can crushed pineapple', '1 c. sugar', '2 Tbsp. corn starch', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13798, ' Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle one box of yellow cake mix (or butter cake mix) on top. Drizzle melted oleo over top. Bake at 350&deg; for 50 to 55 minutes. Before the last 15 minutes of baking time is over , add chopped pecans to top and finish cooking. Cool and serve with Cool Whip.', '1 can pumpkin', '1 (12 oz.) can evaporated milk', '3 eggs', '1/2 c. sugar', '4 tsp. pumpkin pie spice', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1 c. oleo , melted', ' nuts , chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13802, ' Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a 17 x 10 x 1 inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350&deg; until done.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '1 can solid pack pumpkin', '3 eggs', '1/3 c. sugar', '1/3 c. oil', '1 Tbsp. pumpkin pie spice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13805, ' Mix all and beat for 4 minutes on medium speed. Pour into a 12 x 18 inch pan that has been greased and floured. Tap to remove all air bubbles. Bake at 350&deg; for about 45 minutes. Cut into 25 to 28 pieces.', '2 boxes yellow cake mix', '8 eggs', '1/2 c. oil', '2 c. water', '2 tsp. vanilla', '2 pkg. Dream Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13807, ' Mix all ingredients together except coconut. Cook on medium heat until thick. Remove from heat; add coconut and mix well. Use as filling between layers and on top.', '1 box instant lemon pudding', '1 box lemon cake mix', '1 c. oil', '4 eggs', '10 oz. Seven-Up', '1 large can crushed pineapple', '3 egg yolks', '1 Tbsp. cornstarch', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '1 can flaked coconut', '1 stick oleo', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13808, ' In large bowl , blend together cake mix , oil , and butter. Beat in eggs , one at a time; beat well. Fold in sour cream and pecans. Pour half of the batter into greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over batter in pan; cover with rest of batter. Do not stir.', '1 box yellow cake mix', '4 eggs', '3/4 c. cooking oil', '1 c. pecans , chopped', '1/2 pt. sour cream', '1 stick butter', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '1 Tbsp. cinnamon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13841, ' Mix all together. Bake in 13 x 9 pan at 325&deg; for 50 minutes.', '1 box white cake mix', '2/3 c. oil', '4 eggs', '3 oz. box raspberry juice', '10 oz. pkg. frozen red raspberries , thawed (do not drain)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13843, ' Peel , core and slice apples. Place in a deep baking dish. Combine cake mix , sugar , cinnamon , butter and nuts in a separate bowl. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender at 350&deg;.', '5 apples', '9 oz. yellow cake mix', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '1 Tbsp. ground cinnamon', '1/4 c. butter or margarine , melted', '1/2 c. nuts (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13859, ' Heat the blueberries and sugar until sugar melts. Place blueberry mixture into a greased 9 x 13 glass pyrex. Cover this with the pineapple. Sprinkle the cake mix over this mixture. Drizzle the melted margarine over the cake mix and top with the nuts. Bake at 350&deg; for 40 minutes.', '2 c. frozen or fresh blueberries', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 large can crushed pineapple', '1 1/2 sticks margarine , melted', '1 1/2 c. pecans , chopped', '1 box yellow cake mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13860, ' Preheat oven to 325&deg;. Spray bundt pan with Pam and dust with confectioners sugar. Mix together cake mix , sugar , oil , eggs , sour cream , almond and vanilla extract. Blend well. Pour half of the batter into the bundt pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over the batter and add the remaining batter. Bake at 325&deg; for one hour and 10 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle cooled cake with confectioners sugar. Store covered in refrigerator.', '1 -18 1/2 oz. box Duncan Hines Moist Deluxe Butter Recipe Golden Cake mix', '2 tsp. almond extract', '2 tsp. vanilla extract', '3/4 c. sugar', '2 Tbsp. sugar and 2 Tbsp. cinnamon mixed together', '3/4 c. Wesson canola oil', '4 eggs , beaten', '8 oz. Breakstone fat-free sour cream', ' Pam cooking spray', ' Confectioners sugar 10X', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13866, ' Spread pie filling in bottom of 8 inch square pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle pecans over the butter. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes until top is brown and filling bubbles. Cut apple slices into 2-3 pieces.', '1 -21 oz. can apple pie filling', '1 small box of white or yellow cake mix (Jiffy)', '1 stick margarine', '1 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13867, ' Mix cake mix as directed on box. Mix coconut and nuts and spread into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixed cake mix over coconut and nuts. Melt cream cheese and margarine; mix into powdered sugar and pour this over cake. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes.', '1 box German Chocolate Cake mix', '1 1/2 c. pecans , chopped', '1 1/2 c. coconut', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1 stick margarine', '4 c. powdered sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13885, ' Mix the cream cheese , Cool-Whip , milk , and lemon juice until very creamy. Split mixture into the two pie shells and chill if not still somewhat firm. Once filling is firm , pour your favorite fruit topping over them and chill again before serving. One can will cover both pies.', '2 graham cracker pie shells', '1/2 stick butter', '8 oz. cream cheese (room temperature)', '16 oz. container Cool-Whip', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 can condensed milk', '1 can favorite fruit pie filling for topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14192, ' ', '6 c. peeled and sliced favorite apples', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1 Tbsp. water', '1 tsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14255, ' Blend cream cheese and milk. Add the sugar gradually , blending it in well. Then add your selected flavoring and mix again. Enough to frost and fill an 8-inch , 2 layer cake.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. Philadelphia cream cheese', '1 Tbsp. milk', '2 1/2 c. sifted confectioners sugar', ' vanilla or favorite flavor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `ingredients` (`recid`, `method`, `ing1`, `ing2`, `ing3`, `ing4`, `ing5`, `ing6`, `ing7`, `ing8`, `ing9`, `ing10`, `ing11`, `ing12`, `ing13`, `ing14`, `ing15`, `ing16`, `ing17`, `ing18`, `ing19`, `ing20`, `ing21`, `ing22`, `ing23`, `ing24`) VALUES
(14454, ' In a heavy 2-quart saucepan combine the 1 cup whipping cream , chocolate pieces , butter , and sugar. Cook over low heat , stirring constantly , till chocolate is melted. This should take about 10 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat. Gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks. Return egg mixture to saucepan. Cook over medium-low heat , stirring constantly , till mixture is slightly thickened and nearly bubbly , about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat (mixture may appear to separate). Stir in creme de cacao or whipping cream. Place saucepan in a bowl of ice water; stir occasionally till mixture stiffens and becomes hard to stir (20 minutes).', '1 baked 8 or 9-inch pie shell', '1 c. whipping cream', '1 pkg. (6-oz.) semisweet chocolate pieces', '1/3 c. butter', '1/3 c. sugar', '2 beaten egg yolks', '3 Tbsp. creme de cacao or whipping cream', ' Whipped cream or whipped dessert topping (optional)', ' Chocolate curls or miniature chocolate pieces (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14458, ' In an extra large bowl , combine sugar , cinnamon , and nutmeg. Add apple slices; toss to coat. In another extra large bowl , stir together the flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. With a pastry blender , cut in the shortening till pieces are the size of small peas. In a small bowl , combine eggs , 6 tablespoons water , and lemon juice. Add to flour mixture; mix till flour mixture is moistened.', '1 1/2 c. granulated sugar', '1 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1/2 tsp. ground nutmeg', '8 c. sliced , peeled cooking apples (7 large apples , about 3 lb.)', '4 c. all-purpose flour', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1 1/2 c. shortening', '2 beaten eggs', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 c. powdered sugar', '2 Tbsp. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14468, ' In large bowl , combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with one-third each of the wafers , bananas , and pudding. Repeat layering twice , ending with pudding. Chill. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 8 to 10 servings.', '1 can (14-oz.) Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk', '1 1/2 c. cold water', '1 pkg. (4-serving size) instant vanilla flavor pudding mix', '2 c. whipping cream , whipped', '36 vanilla wafers', '3 medium bananas , sliced and dipped into lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14522, ' Melt 1 stick margarine , mix with nuts and flour. Put evenly in pan and bake. Let cool.', '1 stick margarine', '1 c. chopped nuts', '1 c. flour', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '1 c. confectioner sugar', '1 c. Cool Whip for layer , more to top whole dessert', '1 box vanilla instant pudding', '1 box chocolate instant pudding', ' Enough milk to make puddings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14539, ' Stir pie filling , yogurt and Cool Whip until mixed well. Break cake into bite-size pieces. Layer filling , cake , filling , etc. into container. Garnish with lemon slices if desired. Can also be used as frosting. Slice cake into 3 or 4 layers and frost between each layer with filling/yogurt/Cool Whip mixture.', '1 can lemon pie filling', '1 (8 oz.) lemon non-fat yogurt', '1 (8 oz.) cool whip lite', '1 angel food cake', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14677, ' Preheat oven to 375&deg;. In large mixing bowl , cream margarine , sugar , egg yolk and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour , potato chips and chopped nuts. Mix well. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Grease bottom of a glass about 3-inches in diameter. Dip greased glass into sugar and use to flatten each ball. Place nut half in center of each cookie. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheets. Then cool on wire racks. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.', '3/4 c. margarine , softened', '3/4 c. sugar', '1 egg yolk', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 1/4 c. all-purpose flour', '3/4 c. finely crushed potato chips', '3/4 c. finely chopped walnuts or pecans', '3 Tbsp. sugar (for dipping)', ' pecan or walnut halves (for cookie tops)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14795, ' Prepare cake batter. You might have to adjust the eggs , oil and/or water amounts according to the directions on the package. Stir in approximately 1 cup of your favorite snack. Bake according to directions on box.', '1 Duncan Hines Cake mix , any flavor', '2 eggs', '1/2 c. oil', '2 tsp. water', '1 c. your favorite snack*', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15186, ' Beat Crisco until fluffy. Add flavoring. Gradually add powdered sugar and milk. (May thin icing more if too stiff by adding milk 1/4 teaspoon at the time. If using liquid food coloring , color icing before thinning.)', '6 Tbsp. Crisco shortening', '1 box 10x powdered sugar', '1 tsp. flavoring (vanilla or favorite)', '2 Tbsp. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15240, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Place butter in an 8-inch square baking dish. Place dish in oven at 350&deg; for 3 to 5 minutes or until butter melts. Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; add milk and almond extract , stirring until smooth. Pour batter over melted butter. (Do not stir.) Pour blackberries over batter. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Makes 6 servings.', '1/4 c. butter', '3/4 c. self-rising flour', '1/2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. milk', '1/4 tsp. almond or vanilla extract', '1 (16 oz.) can blackberries or your favorite canned fruit (undrained)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15478, ' Melt margarine. Pour into a baking dish. Mix sugar , flour and milk. Put the mixture in the same dish. Don''t mix. Dump the fruit in. Don''t mix. Bake at 350&deg; for 1 hour.', '1 stick margarine', '1 c. self-rising flour', '1 c. sugar', '1 c. milk', '1 can favorite fruit , drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15560, ' Soften butter to room temperature. Add cream cheese , salt and sugar to butter. Cream until well blended. Work in the flour with fingers. Chill for several hours. Divide dough into thirds; roll out each portion on a floured board to about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into 3-inch squares. Place 1/2 teaspoon jam or canned filling in center of each one. Fold so corners overlap in center to enclose jam. Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350&deg; for 16 to 18 minutes until golden brown.', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1/4 tsp. salt', '3 Tbsp. sugar', '2 sticks butter', '2 c. flour , sifted', ' your favorite flavor jam', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
