(19262, ' Combine cream cheese and Italian seasoning. Spread into the bottom of an 8 inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup mozzarella and 1/2 cup parmesan evenly on top of the cream cheese mixture. Pour pizza sauce uniformly over the cheeses. Sprinkle remaining cheeses evenly over pizza sauce. Top with chopped onion. Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve with bread sticks.', '8 oz. softened light cream cheese', '1 T. dried Italian seasoning', '1 c. shredded mozzarella', '1 c. shredded parmesan', '8 oz. pizza sauce', '1/4 c. chopped green onion tops', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19266, ' On a 9 by 13-inch cookie sheet , roll out 1 can pizza dough to edges of cookie sheet. Spread pizza sauce evenly over crust leaving 1/2-inch space around the edges of the crust. Sprinkle pepperoni and cheese evenly over sauce. Roll out remaining can of dough into a 9 by 13-inch rectangle. Carefully place this on top. With a pizza cutter , score into 16 rectangles. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes. Serve warm.', '2 pkgs. refrigerated pizza crust dough', '4 oz. pizza sauce', '1/2 c. chopped pepperoni', '1 c. shredded pizza blend cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19270, ' Mix first four ingredients well. Mold around each olive and bake on a well greased cookie sheet on broil for 10 minutes. Serve hot with fancy toothpicks.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 beaten egg', '1/2 c. Italian bread crumbs', '8 oz. jar pizza sauce', '1 large jar Spanish olives', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19294, ' Brown beef and sausage; drain fat and stir in cubed cheese. Add remaining ingredients , except bread; spread on bread. Put in single layer on cookie sheets and freeze. Microwave when you are ready to eat.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. pork sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese , cut in cubes', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '2 loaves party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
