(19527, ' Take a slice of bread , spread with 1 tsp of pizza sauce , sprinkle your favorite topping and finish with sprinkling some cheese. Put it in the toaster oven and let it bake for 5 minutes or until crispy. To make whole lot at one time put it on pizza pan and bake in the oven until crispy and cheese is melted.', ' bread slices', ' shredded cheese', ' Mozzarella cheese', ' pizza sauce', ' choice your own topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19560, ' Preheat oven to 350 F. Mix dressing and chiles in a blender until smooth. Transfer to a small bowl , chill. Combine flour and taco mix in a shallow dish , mix well. Stir in oil until mixed well. If using wings remove tips first. Coat chicken with mixture on all sides. Place on slightly greased cookie pan. Bake for 15 minutes , turn over and bake an additional 15 minutes , or until chicken is tender. Mix parsley in with ranch dressing. Use dressing as a dipping sauce.', '24 chicken drumsticks or wings , approx. 2 lb.', '1 - 4 oz. can green chiles , chopped', '1/2 cup flour', '1 pkg. taco seasoning mix', '2 tsp. oil', '1 Tbsp. dried parsley', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(19565, ' Heat , in 1 inch boiling water , heat cabbage to boiling. Cook cabbage 1 minute; drain. Immediately run cold water over cabbage to cool. With hands , squeeze as much water out of cabbage as possible. Finely chop cabbage.', '2 cups nappa cabbage , sliced , packed', '1/2 lb. ground pork', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1 Tbsp. dry sherry', '2 tsp. cornstarch', '1 1/2 tsp. gingerroot , peeled , minced', '1 green onion , minced', '36 wonton-skin wrappers , (3 1/2 by 3 1/4-inch (3/4 12-ounce package)*', '1 large egg white , beaten', ' Green onions for garnish', ' Soy Dipping Sauce (See Below)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
