(22084, ' For the stock , boil the shrimp shells in 1 1/2 c. water. Saut&eacute; the garlic , onions , ground pork , shrimp , and tofu. Add the potatoes and 1/2 c. stock. Cook for 10 minutes , stirring constantly. Add the beans and cook for another 5 - 10 minutes. Then add turnips , soy sauce , vegetable oil , salt and pepper (to taste) , and fish sauce. Continue to stir and cook for 5 more minutes. Drain and save the broth for the dipping sauce. Allow the mixture to cool.', '1 lb. ground pork , browned and fat drained', '1/2 lb. shrimp , shelled (save the shells,)', '3 pcs firm tofu , fried and cut into cubes', '1 large onion , sliced', '3 pcs cloves garlic , crushed', '1 lb. turnips , cut into strips', '1 lb. potatoes , cut into cubes', '2 lb. pole beans , cleaned and cut crosswise', '1 bunch lettuce (not iceberg)', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '4 Tbsp. vegetable oil', ' salt &amp; pepper', '2 Tbsp. fish sauce (&quot;patis&quot;; optional)', '2 Tbsp. accent salt (optional)', '1 pkg. lumpia wrappers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
