(23502, ' Brown the ground chuck. Chop it into small pieces. After it is almost done , add diced onion and let them saut&eacute; and add tabasco sauce if you want to. Boil rice according to directions on box and add to meat along with salsa , undrained tomatoes and cheese and let simmer until cheese is melted. Save a little cheese to sprinkle on top. Serve with corn chips to dip with.', '1 lb. ground chuck', '1 large jar of salsa', '1 12-oz. pkg. of shredded cheese , your favorite kind', '1 can diced tomatoes', '1 cup Minute Rice', '1/2 onion , diced', ' Few drops of Tabasco sauce , optional', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23506, ' Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile , in a large skillet , cook beef , green pepper and onion until meat is done; drain. Stir in the spaghetti sauce and sloppy joe sauce; heat through. Drain pasta; top with beef mixture.', '1 pkg. (16 oz.) wagon wheel pasta', '2 lb. ground beef', '1 medium green pepper , chopped', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 (28 oz.) jar meatless spaghetti sauce', '1 (15 1/2 oz.) jar sloppy joe sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23526, ' Boil water and soften the bowtie pasta. Grill the chicken then chop into bite sized pieces. Dust the chicken lightly with basil. Chop the garlic into fine pieces , slice the green pepper into long , narrow slices , and dice the onion. In a pan or skillet , heat olive oil (cover the bottom of the pan) and add the garlic. When garlic begins to simmer , add the spaghetti sauce. Cut the chicken in bite sized pieces. Add to the sauce the rosemary , thyme , basil , oregano , salt , pepper and mushrooms. When the sauce is bubbling , add the green peppers and onions. Let it heat , then add the pasta and chicken. Incorporate all ingredients together. Serve hot.', '4 pieces chicken breast', '1 clove garlic', '1 green pepper , sliced', '1 onion , diced', '1 can sliced mushrooms', '1 jar spaghetti sauce', ' Thyme', ' Basil', ' Oregano', ' Rosemary (optional)', ' Bowtie Pasta', ' Extra virgin olive oil', ' Salt', ' Pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23545, ' Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat. Cook chicken and onion in skillet 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken is light brown. Stir in water; heat to boiling. Stir in pasta. Cook 8 to 10 minutes , stirring occasionally , until pasta is almost tender (do not drain). Stir in packet of sauce mix from stir-fry mix until well blended. Stir in vegetables. Cover and cook 8 to 9 minutes , stirring occasionally , until vegetables are crisp-tender. Sprinkle with peanuts from stir-fry mix. (I leave off the peanuts.)', '4 skinless boneless chicken breast halves (about 1 lb.) cut into 3/4 to 1 inch pieces', '1 medium onion , cut into thin wedges', '2 c. water', '1 1/2 c. uncooked fusilli pasta (3 oz.)', '1 pkg. (1 lb. 5 oz.) frozen Sichuan stir-fry mix with vegetables , Sichaun sauce and peanuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23550, ' Cut each chicken breast half into 4 pieces. Heat oil in wok or 12 inch skillet over medium high heat. Cook garlic and chilies in oil , stirring constantly , until garlic is golden brown. Add chicken; stir-fry 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center. Stir in fish sauce and sugar. Sprinkle with basil and mint. This has 5 grams carbohydrates.', '4 skinless boneless chicken breast halves (about 1 lb.)', '2 tbsp. vegetable oil', '3 cloves garlic , finely chopped', '2 red or green jalapeno chilies , seeded and finely chopped', '1 Tbsp. fish sauce', '1 tsp. sugar', '1/4 c. chopped fresh basil leaves', '1 Tbsp. chopped fresh mint leaves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(23554, ' Heat oven to 400&deg;. Unroll dough , place on greased cookie sheet. Press dough in 12 x 8 inch rectangle. Spread sauce on dough to within 2 inches of long sides and 1/2 inch of short sides. Top with Canadian bacon , pepperoni , cheese , peppers , onions and Italian seasoning. Fold long sides of dough over filling. Pinch to seal. Pinch short sides to seal also. Bake at 400&deg; for 15-20 minutes until golden brown.', '1 can Pillsbury pizza crust', '1/3 c. Ragu Pizza Quick sauce', '1 (3.5 oz.) Canadian style bacon', '1 (3.5 oz.) pepperoni', '1 c. shredded mozzarella cheese', '1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1/4 c. chopped onion', '1/4 tsp. dried Italian seasoning', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
