(26204, ' In a greased 13 x 9 baking pan , arrange the bread slices. In a bowl , combine eggs , orange juice , milk , sugar , vanilla and nutmeg. Whisk until well blended. Pour over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight.', '1 loaf French bread , cut into 1-inch slices', '4 eggs', '2/3 c. orange juice', '1/3 c. milk', '1/4 c. sugar', '1/2 tsp. vanilla extract', '1/4 tsp. ground nutmeg', '1/2 c. butter or margarine , melted', '1/2 c. chopped nuts (your choice)', ' powdered sugar (optional)', ' favorite syrup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(26362, ' Dissolve yeast in water. Melt margarine , pour in yeast water. Add sugar. Beat eggs , add to mixture. Add flour cup at a time. Bake in greased muffin pan 20-25 minutes.', '1 pkg. dry yeast', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 1/2 stick margarine', '2 c. hot water', '1 egg', '4 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(26527, ' In pan , bring milk just to boiling. Remove from heat. Add Crisco , sugar and salt. Let cool to lukewarm. Add yeast to 1/2 cup lukewarm water and dissolve. Slowly stir flour into Crisco , milk and sugar mixture. Beat well with spoon. Stir in yeast mixture. Mix well. Knead this mixture. Place in greased bowl. Let rise 1 1/2 hours or until double in size. Punch down. Shape into rolls or roll out in rectangle and spread with melted margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon , sugar , nuts or raisins. Roll up and slice. Place in pans. Let rise until double in size , about 45 minutes. Bake at 350&deg; for 15 minutes.', '1 1/2 c. whole milk', '1/2 c. lukewarm water', '1/2 c. sugar and pinch of salt', '2 pkg. yeast', '1/2 c. Crisco', '5 1/2 c. plain White Lily flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
