(27401, ' In a small skillet cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. In bowl combine the egg and milk. Stir in dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in cheese and add sausage. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from muffin pan. Serve warn. Refrigerate left overs.', '8 oz. pork sausage', '1 3/4 c. biscuit baking mix', '3/4 tsp. sage', '1/4 tsp. dried thyme', '1 egg', '1/2 c. shredded swiss cheese (or your favorite)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27408, ' Preheat oven to 350 F. In a large bowl combine flour , baking powder , and salt. Stir in bananas , coconut milk , vanilla , and butter. Add raisins and nuts. Pour into a greased 5 x 9 inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Makes 1 loaf , 16 slices.', '4 cups mashed bananas', '1/2 cup coconut milk', '1/2 cup melted butter', '3 cups flour', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', '1/2 raisins', '1/2 cup or your favorite nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27572, ' Coat bread dough with butter; let rise per directions on the package. Roll out dough; layer pepperoni and cheese as thick as you like. Fold over and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350&deg;. Makes 1 loaf.', '1 loaf frozen bread dough', '1 pkg. pizza cheese (Mozzarella)', '1 pkg. pepperoni slices', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27573, ' Beat together cream cheese and eggs until smooth. Add cream cheese , Parmesan cheese and spices and mix together again. Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle 2 cups of Italian cheese onto pan and pour the egg mixture over the cheese. Bake at 375&deg; for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 5 minutes; add pizza sauce and favorite pizza toppings.', '4 oz. cream cheese', '3 eggs', '1/3 c. cream', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', '1/2 tsp. oregano (optional)', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '2 c. mixed Italian cheese', '1/2 c. pizza sauce', '1 c. Mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27632, ' Combine first 4 ingredients. To prepare rolls , place water in bread machine pan. Add roll mix. Top with butter and yeast. Select dough setting. After 5 minutes , check mixture. Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water or flour if needed. When cycle is complete , turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Punch down. Cover and let stand for 10 minutes. Divide into 12 portions. Shape each into a ball. Place on lightly greased pan. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 350&deg; for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.', '3 c. bread flour', '3 Tbsp. sugar', '3 Tbsp. nonfat dry milk', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1 c. water (warm)', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '1 1/2 tsp. dry yeast', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27658, ' Place ingredients in bread machine in order given. Select white bread cycle. Push start. When cycle is done , remove dough and make into rolls. Place in pan and let rise for 2 hours in a warm place , like oven with light on. After rolls rise , remove from oven. Set oven for 400&deg;. Bake 20 minutes. Turn oven to 350&deg;. Bake another 20 minutes.', '2 pkg. dry yeast', '3 c. plain flour', '1/3 c. sugar', '1 tsp. salt', '1 egg', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 1/4 c. warm milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(27700, ' Pour over this 1 cup boiling water. Stir until lard melts. Add 1 cup cold water. Add 1 cup lukewarm water with 1 package dry yeast dissolved in it. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Knead a little and put in a bowl to raise. You can put in refrigerator to raise if you want. Punch down and make into bread or rolls to raise again until double. Bake bread at 350&deg; or rolls at 400&deg;. Makes 3 loaves or lots of rolls.', '1/2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. lard', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28213, ' Melt butter in pan. Mix all other ingredients except fruit and pour over butter. Pour fruit on top of batter. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 minutes.', '1 stick butter', '1 c. sugar', '1 c. flour', '1 Tbsp. baking powder', '2/3 c. milk', '1 can favorite fruit', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28922, ' Mix first 3 ingredients together. When they are well blended , pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze for several hours. Let thaw for 1/2 hour before serving.', '1 can sweetened condensed milk', '1 regular sized Cool Whip , thawed', '1 small can frozen lemonade , thawed', '1 graham cracker dessert crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28941, ' Cut butter into flour. In a separate bowl , combine egg yolks , salt and rum. Combine. Knead dough on a floured board. This can also be done in a bread machine or pasta maker. Let the dough set in a bowl for about 30 minutes. Roll out a small about of dough , about 1/8 inch thick. The thinner the dough the better. Cut into strips about 1 X 4 inches long. Pull one end through the slit. Fry in hot oil a few at a time. Drain. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.', '2 Tbsp. butter', '2 c. sifted flour', '5 egg yolks , lightly beaten', '1/4 c. milk', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1 Tbsp. rum', ' confectioners sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28984, ' Heat over to 350 degrees. Stir together flour , granulated sugar , 2 Tbsp. cocoa , baking powder , and salt. Mix well. Add milk , oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in a 9 X 9 inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 c. cocoa. Pour hot water over batter. Bake 40 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes. Cut into squares. There will be a thick chocolate sauce underneath the cake when you take it out. Top each square with ice cream and spoon sauce over it.', '1 c. flour', '3/4 c. sugar', '2 Tbsp. cocoa', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. milk', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 cup chopped nuts (optional)', '1 c. brown sugar , packed', '1/4 c. cocoa', '1 3/4 c. hottest tap water', ' favorite ice cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29048, ' Mix and press onto sided cookie sheet the butter , flour and sugar. Bake 20 minutes at 350&deg;. Cool.', '2 sticks butter , softened', '2 c. flour', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '8 oz. Cool Whip', '2 (21 oz.) cans favorite pie filling', '8 oz. cream cheese', '3/4 c. powdered sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29054, ' In large mixing bowl , combine milk and water (it sounds awful , but do it anyway). Add pudding mix; beat until well blended. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers , bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice , ending with pudding mixture. Chill thoroughly. Garnish as desired. (I use a few vanilla wafers and banana slices on top.) Refrigerate leftovers.', '1 (14 oz.) can Eagle Brand milk', '1 1/2 c. cold water', '1 (3 1/2 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding', '2 c. (1 pt.) whipping cream , whipped', '36 vanilla wafers (no need to count)', '3 medium bananas , sliced and dipped in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29065, ' Spoon 1/2 cup of the fudge topping into bottom of crust. Place in freezer 10 minutes. Whisk peanut butter and milk in a large bowl until well blended. Add pudding mixes. Beat for 2 minutes or until smooth. (Mixture will be thick.) Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Gently spoon over chocolate layer. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Drizzle with remaining 1/4 cup fudge topping just before serving. Makes 10 servings.', '3/4 c. hot fudge dessert topping , divided', '1 graham cracker pie crust (6 oz.)', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip whipped topping , thawed and divided', '1/2 c. creamy peanut butter', '1 1/4 c. cold milk', '2 pkg. (4 serving size) Jell-O brand vanilla flavor instant pudding and pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29070, ' Mix container of apple dip with 1/2 cup of vanilla flavored yogurt and ground cinnamon; chill. Just before serving , stir in toasted pecans. Serve with sliced apples. Refrigerate leftover dip.', '1 (8 oz.) container caramel apple dip', '1/2 c. vanilla flavor yogurt', '1/8 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1/3 c. finely chopped pecans , toasted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29506, ' Spoon 1/2 cup of the fudge topping into batter of crust. Place in freeze 10 minutes. Whisk peanut butter and milk in a large bowl until well blended. Add pudding mix. Beat for 2 minutes or until smooth. The mixture will be thick. Stir in 1/2 whipped topping. Gently spoon over chocolate layer. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours. Drizzle with 1/4 of fudge topping just before serving.', '3/4 c. hot fudge dessert topping , divided', '1 Honey Maid graham pie crust (6 oz.)', '1 (8 oz.) Cool Whip topping , thawed and divided', '1/2 c. creamy peanut butter', '1 1/4 c. cold milk', '2 pkg. (4 serving size) Jell-O vanilla instant pudding and pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29531, ' In large bowl , combine milk and water. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon in 1 cup pudding mixture in glass dish or bowl. Top with wafers and bananas. Repeat layers , ending with pudding.', '1 can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk', '1 1/2 c. cold water', '1 pkg. vanilla instant pudding', '2 c. Borden whipped cream or Cool Whip', ' vanilla wafers', '3 medium bananas , sliced and dipped in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29669, ' Beat egg yolks. Add in salt , sugar and vanilla. Beat well and add in alternately the flour and cream. Turn dough onto floured board and cover. Allow to rise 10 minutes. Knead until dough begins to blister. Roll thin. Cut into strips about 1 x 4-inches. Cut slit in center of each strip and twist one end through slit. Fry in deep fat at 375&deg; until lightly browned. Drain on paper towel. Dust with powdered sugar when cool.', '5 egg yolks', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '2 1/4 c. flour', '5 Tbsp. cream (sweet or sour)', ' oil (for frying)', ' powdered sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29853, ' Combine peanut butter , margarine , and confectioners sugar in a large bowl. Blend together well. Add rice cereal and blend into peanut butter mixture. Form into 3/4 inch balls and dip in dipping chocolate. Makes about 75 centers.', '2 cups crunchy peanut butter', '1/2 cup margarine', '1 lb confectioners sugar', '3 cups crisp rice cereal', ' dipping chocolate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30037, ' In a trifle bowl layer brownies , then pudding , then Heath bars , then Cool Whip. Repeat layers ending with Cool Whip. Garnish with shaved chocolate.', '1 (9 x 13) pan of brownies , baked and broken into pieces', '2 pkg. instant chocolate mousse , prepared (or may use your favorite pudding recipe)', '6 large Heath bars , crushed', '1 large tub Cool Whip', '3 Tbsp. shaved chocolate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30063, ' To reserved pineapple liquid , add enough water to make 1 1/2 c. In large bowl , combine Eagle Brand milk and pudding mix. Beat well. Add pineapple. Chill 10 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 1/2 c. pudding into 3-4 qt. glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the chocolate wafers , bananas and pudding. repeat layering twice , ending with pudding. Garnish with nuts and cherries if desired. Chill and keep refrigerated after serving.', '1 (15 1/4 oz.) can crushed pineapple , well drained , reserving liquid', '1 (14 oz.) can Eagle Brand Milk', '2 (4 serving size) pkg. instant banana cream or vanilla pudding and pie filling mix', '2 c. (1 pint) whipping cream , whipped', '1 (15 1/4 oz.) pkg. chocolate wafers (40 wafers)', '4 medium bananas , sliced and dipped in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30100, ' Spray pie pan with nonfat nonstick cooking spray and set aside. Mix the first three ingredients well and press into the bottom and up the sides of the pie pan. Set aside. Mix the pudding mixes and milk until thick. Pour into pie crust. Chill and top with cool whip.', '2 c. rice krispies', '4 T. reduced fat peanut butter', '1 1/2 t. brown sugar substitute', '2 small packages instant sugar free chocolate pudding mix', '3 c. skim milk', '8 oz. fat free cool whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30262, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. Mix Wesson oil and sugar thoroughly. Add egg and beat well. Stir in molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and add.', '3/4 c. Wesson oil', '1 c. sugar', '1 egg', '1/4 c. molasses', '2 c. sifted all-purpose flour', '2 tsp. soda', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. cinnamon', '1/4 tsp. ginger', '1/4 c. sugar (for dipping)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30331, ' Prepare pastry shells. In large skillet , melt butter or margarine; stir in coconut and pecans. Cook and stir over medium heat until coconut is golden , about 6 to 8 minutes. Cool. In large mixing bowl , beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk on low speed. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon in 1/4 of the mixture into each pastry shell; drizzle each with 1/4 of the caramel topping and sprinkle with 1/4 of the coconut mixture. Repeat layers. Cover and freeze 5 hours or until firm. Serve or freeze , covered , for up to 2 weeks. Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving , if frozen.', '2 baked pastry shells (graham cracker crust works well)', '1/4 c. butter or margarine', '1 1/3 c. flaked coconut', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese , softened', '1 (14 oz.) can sweetened condensed milk', '1 (16 oz.) carton frozen whipped dessert topping , thawed', '1 (12 oz.) jar caramel ice cream topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30375, ' Combine pudding and milk; mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Layer 1 package of graham crackers in bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan. Spread half of pudding mixture evenly over the graham crackers. Repeat with the second package of graham crackers and the rest of the pudding mixture. Place third package of graham crackers on top. Immediately spread the chocolate frosting over all. Place a piece of plastic wrap over cake and refrigerate overnight. (This is a must so that the graham crackers will get soft.) Enjoy.', '2 pkg. French vanilla instant pudding', '2 c. milk', '1 (12 oz.) carton whipped topping', '1 box graham crackers', '1 can your favorite chocolate frosting', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30533, ' In a large bowl , combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of wafers , bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice , ending with pudding. Chill thoroughly.', '1 (14 oz.) can sweetened condensed milk', '1 1/2 c. cold water', '1 (4 serving size) pkg. instant vanilla pudding', '2 c. (1 pt.) Cool Whip', '36 vanilla wafers', '3 medium bananas , sliced and dipped in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30540, ' Stir together sugar , Crisco , flour , salt , baking powder and milk in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix fruit , sugar and fruit juice together and pour over the batter. Dot the batter with butter and bake at 350&deg; about 30 minutes or until done.', '1/2 c. sugar', '3 Tbsp. Crisco', '1 c. flour', ' salt', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/2 c. milk', '2 c. fruit (strawberries , peaches are favorites)', '1 c. sugar (I use 2/3 c. to reduce calories)', ' butter', '1 c. fruit juice (made by mashing up some extra fruit)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30662, ' Cream margarine and milk. Add rum and powdered sugar; mix well. Add nuts , fruit and coconut; mix well. Chill well about 2 hours. By hands , form small balls (3/4-inch). Keep hands coated with powdered sugar. Put balls on wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Melt chocolate. With toothpick , dip balls in chocolate; place on wax paper to dry. Melt white chocolate. Hand dip so topped with white chocolate (to cover toothpick marks). Chill and then package.', '2 lb. powdered sugar', '3/4 can Eagle Brand milk', '4 oz. rum (optional)', '2 sticks margarine , softened', '8 oz. coconut', '8 oz. candied cherries , chopped', '2 c. nuts', '1 lb. chopped dates (optional)', ' Ghirardelli candy making and dipping bar pack (double chocolate flavor)', '4 oz. white chocolate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30775, ' Combine eagle brand milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 c pudding mixture into 2 1/2 qt serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers , bananas , and pudding. Repeat layering twice ending with pudding. Cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve.', '1 14 oz eagle brand milk', '1 1/2 c cold water', '1 4 serving , box vanilla flavored instant pudding mix', '1 pt whipping cream , whipped', '36 vanilla wafers', '3 medium bananas , sliced and dipped in lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30930, ' Cream together sugar , cream cheese , eggs , Milnot , butter , and vanilla. Stir together dry ingredients in another bowl , then add to batter. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased cake pan. Place preserves in spoonfuls on top of batter. Cover preserves with remainder of batter. Bake for 45 mins. at 350&deg;.', '1 1/4 c. sugar', '8 oz. cream cheese , softened', '2 eggs', '1/2 c. butter , softened', '1/4 c. Milnot', '1/2 tsp. Griffin''s Vanilla', '2 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. baking powder', '1/8 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. baking soda', '12 oz. of your favorite Griffin''s Preserves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
