(52587, ' In a skillet , cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Meanwhile , quarter the biscuits; place in a 3 quart greased , shallow baking dish. Top with the pizza sauce. Drain beef; sprinkle over biscuits and sauce. Layer with green peppers , onion , mushrooms , pepperoni and cheeses. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.', '1 lb. ground beef', '2 tubes (12 oz.) refrigerated buttermilk biscuits', '1 can (15 oz.) pizza sauce', '1 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 can (4 oz.) mushroom stems and pieces , drained', '1 pkg. (3 1/2 oz.) sliced pepperoni', '1 c. shredded mozzarella cheese', '1 c. shredded cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52595, ' Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt the butter in a 9 x 13 pan in the oven. While it melts , combine everything else except the fish , in a pie plate. Dip the fish around in the melted butter , dip each piece of fish in the crumb mixture and return it to the baking pan. Bake the fillets for 20 to 25 minutes , or until the fish flakes with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges. Yield: 4 servings.', '4 Tbsp. unsalted butter (1/2 stick) , can substitute olive oil', '2/3 C. crushed crackers (Ritz) OR cornflake crumbs', '1/4 C. grated Parmesan cheese (about 1 oz.)', '1/2 tsp. dried basil', '1/2 tsp. dried oregano', '1/4 tsp. garlic powder', '1 lb. sole , scrod , perch or other mild-tasting fish fillets', ' lemon wedges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52596, ' Thaw salmon if frozen. Rinse fish , pat dry , place in plastic bag set in a shallow baking dish. In a small bowl , stir together bourbon , brown sugar , honey , soy sauce , ginger and pepper. Pour over fish in bag. Close bag. Marinate fish in refrigerator one hour , turning occasionally. Drain fish , reserving marinade. Coat rack with oil or spray. Place fish on rack of uncovered grill directly over medium heat. Grill 8 to 12 minutes or until fish begins to flake easily with fork , turning once. Brush once with reserved marinade half-way through grilling time. Discard remaining marinade. Serves: 2.', '2 - 6 to 8 oz. fresh or frozen salmon steaks , cut 1 inch thick', '6 Tbsp. bourbon whiskey', '1/4 C. brown sugar , packed', '1 Tbsp. honey', '1 tsp. soy sauce', '1/4 tsp. ground ginger', '1/8 tsp. pepper', ' Cooking oil or cooking spray for grill rack', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52600, ' ', '6 or 8 filets of fish , medium sized--flounder or any mild fish', '1/4 pound butter or margarine , melted', '1/4 C. lemon juice', '2 tsp. salt', '2 Tbsp. water', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52659, ' Cut the steak into 6 serving sized pieces. Combine the flour , salt and pepper and pound into steak. Pour the oil in a skillet and brown the meat slowly on both sides. Transfer to a 12x7 baking dish.', '2 lbs. beef round steak , about 1 inch thick', '2 Tbsp. flour', '2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '3 Tbsp. shortening or oil', '1 - 8 oz. can tomato sauce', '1 - 8 oz. can pizza sauce', '1/2 C. water', '1/2 tsp. dried oregano , crushed', '1/2 tsp. sugar', '1 medium onion , sliced', ' Cooked noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52735, ' In skillet , cook beef and onion until tender. Drain. Stir in flour , salt and pepper until blended. Add pizza sauce and corn. Simmer 5 minutes. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Separate biscuits and arrange over beef mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden and cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. flour (all-purpose)', '1 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. pepper', '1 (15 oz.) can pizza sauce', '10 oz. can corn (frozen or canned)', '1 tube refrigerated buttermilk biscuits', '1 c. (4 oz.) Cheddar cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52763, ' In a large bowl , combine the biscuit mix and the Italian seasoning. Combine eggs and milk; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in the cheese , pepperoni , tomatoes and green peppers. Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle. Turn when bubbles form on top. Cook until the second side is golden brown. Serve with pizza sauce. Yields 14 pancakes.', '2 c. biscuit/baking mix', '2 tsp. Italian seasoning', '2 eggs', '1 c. milk', '1/2 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1/2 c. chopped pepperoni', '1/2 c. chopped plum tomatoes', '1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1 (8 oz.) can pizza sauce , warmed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52771, ' Heat oven to 425&deg;. In a large skillet , cook beef and onion over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until beef is no longer pink; drain well. Season with salt and pepper; stir in cheese and sauce. On a lightly floured surface , unroll pizza dough. Cut into 6 sections. Divide and spoon filling into center of each section. Bring together 4 corners of each rectangular section , pinching to seal. Loosely close straight edges of dough to form pockets. (It''s not necessary to seal edges completely.) Carefully transfer to ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.', '3/4 lb. ground beef', '1/3 c. chopped onion', '1/4 tsp. each salt and pepper', '1/2 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese (2 oz.)', '1/2 c. pizza sauce', ' flour', '1 (1 oz.) can refrigerated pizza crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52904, ' Wash , peel and slice eggplants into 1/4-inch slices. Mix egg and milk and set aside. Mix all other ingredients. Dip slices of eggplant into egg mixture , then into crumb mixture. Lay flat on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes. Turn once. Spoon a little sauce on the bottom of a large casserole dish. Layer slices of eggplant , sauce and grated Mozzarella. On top layer , sprinkle more sauce , Mozzarella and grated Romano cheese. Bake in a 350&deg; oven for 30 or 40 minutes until bubbly.', '2 large eggplants', '1/2 to 1 c. bread crumbs', '1/2 c. grated Romano', '1 Tbsp. parsley', '1 Tbsp. basil', '1/2 tsp. black pepper', '1 egg', '1/4 c. milk', ' salt (optional)', '1 lb. Mozzarella cheese , grated', ' your own favorite tomato sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52921, ' Spray baking sheet to coat. Combine cornmeal , thyme , basil and Old Bay seasoning on large platter. Dip each fillet into until coated on both sides. Place on baking sheet and spray lightly with cooking spray. Bake at 400&deg; for 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350&deg; and bake another 5 minutes until golden and fish flakes easily.', ' vegetable oil cooking spray', '1/4 c. cornmeal', '1 tsp. dried thyme', '1 tsp. dried basil', '2 tsp. Old Bay seasoning', '4 fish fillets (catfish , flounder or sole)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52931, ' Cut chicken into thin strips. Saut&eacute; chicken in oil until no longer pink. Add taco seasoning along with water. Spread salsa on crust. Sprinkle the chicken over the salsa. Top with green onions , green pepper and black olives. Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over entire mixture. Bake according to crust package instructions.', '1 Boboli pizza crust', '2 boneless chicken breasts', '1 Tbsp. water', '1 Tbsp. salad oil', '1.25 oz. pkg. taco seasoning', '1 c. salsa', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
