(52947, ' Mix lemon juice , wine , water , margarine , chicken base , pepper and garlic in a 2-quart saucepan and heat. Add cornstarch. Put aside. Cut up chicken cutlets into 2 ounce pieces. Dip chicken pieces in flour. Turn in beaten eggs. Heat corn oil in pan. Cook chicken approximately 3 minutes on each side until light brown. Drain oil and add sauce you put aside. Simmer for approximately 5 minutes. Makes 2 servings.', '1 c. concentrate lemon juice', '2 c. white wine', '2 c. water', '1/2 c. margarine', '2 Tbsp. chicken base', '1 tsp. pepper', '1 tsp. granulated sugar', '2 Tbsp. cornstarch', '1 lb. chicken cutlet', ' eggs (for dipping chicken)', ' corn oil (for cooking)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52983, ' Cut fillets into serving pieces. Place in greased shallow baking dish or pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice , paprika and a dash of salt and pepper. In saucepan , blend 2 tablespoons of butter with flour and dash each of salt and pepper; add milk all at once. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly; pour over fish. Blend crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle over fish. Bake at 350&deg; for 35 minutes.', '2 lb. fish fillets', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/4 tsp. paprika', '6 Tbsp. melted butter', '2 Tbsp. flour', '1 c. milk', '1/2 c. dry bread crumbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52991, ' Put the crust on a cookie sheet and spread the sauce onto it. Spread the pesto over the tomato sauce. Pile on the cheese, If you want to make the crust crunchy , spread the butter around the edges and sprinkle on the salt. Cook at 400&deg; for 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Cooking times may vary according to crust types.', ' your favorite pizza crust', ' tomato sauce (as much as you want)', ' about 3 Tbsp. pesto', ' cheese (as much as you want)', '1 tsp. butter (optional)', '1/2 tsp. salt (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53003, ' Make crust , following directions on package. While dough is rising , mix cheeses , egg and other fillings , as desired. Make circle of half of dough. Add filling. Put other half of dough circle on top. Pinch edges together. Sprinkle top with water and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400&deg; for 18 to 20 minutes.', '1 pkg. pizza crust mix', '1 c. Ricotta or cottage cheese', '1 c. shredded Mozzarella', '3/4 c. shredded Parmesan cheese', '1 egg', ' ham', ' broccoli', ' mushrooms', ' basil', ' oregano', ' garlic salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53214, ' Mix to taste. Chill before serving.', '2 to 3 tsp. lemon juice', '1 or more tsp. cumin', '1 lb. or more cooked fish', '1 onion , chopped', '1 can green chiles', ' tomatoes , chopped (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53236, ' Wash prawns , slit down back with scissors and remove sandy vein , set aside. Scrub and beard mussels , discard any that aren''t firmly closed. Put in pot with little water , steam for about 10 minutes. Discard any which have not opened , set aside. Saut&eacute; scallops in olive oil for 10-15 minutes , set aside.', '500 g. raw prawns', '1 lb. Mussels', '1 lb. Scallops (or add whatever seafood you want)', '4 Tbsp. olive oil', '2 large onions , finely chopped', '6 cloves garlic , finely chopped', '1/2 tsp. saffron strands', '1 c. peeled tomatoes , chopped', '2 tsp. paprika', '2 tsp. salt', '500 g. (approx. 2 1/2 c.) long grain rice', '4 1/2 c. fish or chicken stock or chicken broth', ' lemons for garnish and squeezing over rice at the end', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53245, ' Heat the oil in a wok or large , heavy frying pan. Add the onion and curry paste to the wok and cook for one minute , stirring constantly. Add the coconut milk and water to the wok and bring to a boil. Add the chicken pieces , beans , and lime leaves to the wok , stirring to combine. Reduce the heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the chicken is tender. Do not overcook. Add the fish sauce , lime juice , lime rind , and sugar to the wok; stir to combine. Sprinkle with fresh cilantro just before serving. Serve with steamed rice. Serves 4.', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 onion , chopped', ' 1-2 Tbsp. green curry paste , to taste', '1 1/2 c. coconut milk', '1/2 c. water', '1 lb. chicken thigh fillets or boneless chicken breasts , cut into bite-sized pieces', '1/4 lb. fresh green beans , cut into 1-inch pieces', '6 kaffir lime leaves (if available)', '1 Tbsp. fish sauce', '1 Tbsp. fresh lime juice', '1 tsp. finely grated lime rind', '2 tsp. soft brown sugar', '1/4 c. fresh cilantro , chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53249, ' Cook and drain spaghetti noodles. Mix eggs , milk , 1 c. mozzarella cheese , garlic and a dash or two of salt. Spread into a greased pan and bake 15 minutes at 400&deg;. When done , layer spaghetti sauce , remaining cheese , then whatever pizza toppings you want. Bake 30 minutes at 350&deg;. Let set for 5 minutes. Enjoy,', '1 lb. spaghetti noodles', '2 eggs', '1/2 c. milk', '4 c. shredded mozzarella cheese', '1 clove garlic , crushed', ' salt', '30 oz. spaghetti sauce', ' pizza toppings (whatever you prefer)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53264, ' Saut the onion and garlic in the oil over medium heat for 3 minutes. Add the pepper , cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until the onions are caramelized. Spread mixture out over the pizza crust; add prosciutto , cheese and rosemary. Bake in 400&deg; oven 30 minutes if using a raw crust , 15-20 minutes if pre-baked.', ' Something for a pizza crust , either pre-baked or dough', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1 medium red onion , sliced into rings', '2 cloves garlic', '1 red bell pepper , diced', '4 oz. prosciutto , diced', '4 oz. mozzarella , grated', '2 Tbsp. rosemary', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53314, ' Cook pasta in oil and salt. Brown hamburger. Add ingredients.', '1 lb. hamburger', '2 oz. cans pizza sauce', '1 can mushrooms', '1 Tbsp. oregano', '1 tsp. garlic salt', '2 c. noodles', '2/3 c. milk', '1 Tbsp. oil', '2 c. cheese', ' pepperoni', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53327, ' Dip fish in salad dressing. Place in single layer , skin side down , on buttered 15 x 10 baking dish.', '2 lb. fresh scrod fish fillets (cod can be used)', '1/2 c. Caesar salad dressing or any creamy Hidden Valley', '1 c. crushed potato chips', '1/2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53331, ' Mix all ingredients together. Put in a casserole dish. Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with oregano. Bake in a covered casserole dish in a 375&deg; oven for 30 minutes.', '2 c. cooked shell macaroni', '1 lb. browned hamburger', ' salt and pepper', '1 (4 oz.) can mushrooms', '1 c. pizza sauce', '1 (14 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 c. Parmesan cheese', '1 onion , chopped', ' pepperoni', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53386, ' Bone , skin and flake fish. Melt butter or oleo in saucepan. Blend in flour and salt. Add milk. Cook , stirring until smooth and thickened. Fold in eggs , fish and onions. Serve on buttered muffins or hot biscuits. Sprinkle with paprika.', '1 lb. smoked fish', '3 Tbsp. butter or oleo', '3 Tbsp. flour', '3/4 tsp. salt', '2 c. milk', '3 hard-boiled eggs , cut up', '3 Tbsp. thinly sliced green onions', ' buttered , toasted English muffins', ' paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53389, ' Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour to make a gravy. Add milk , stirring constantly , until mixture thickens. Add tuna fish and peas. Serve over toast or noodles. Makes approximately 4 servings.', '1 can tuna fish', '1 can LeSueur early peas', '3 Tbsp. butter (I Can''t Believe)', ' flour', '2 c. milk', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53405, ' Put meat and water in slow cooker and cook on low 8 to 10 hours. When done , it should shred easily with a fork. Remove from slow cooker and shred meat with 2 forks. Put back into slow cooker (make sure you discard the water and fat) or large casserole dish. Add sauce and serve with rice or on hamburger buns.', '2 to 3 lb. pork butt roast', '1 c. water', '1 bottle your favorite barbecue sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53473, ' Cook pasta and drain. Brown hamburger and onion. Combine hamburger , spaghetti and pizza sauces and sugar. Combine cheeses. In crock-pot , place a layer of pasta , followed by a layer of hamburger mix , then mushrooms , then cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Last layer should be cheese. Warm in crock-pot until cheese melts.', '1 pkg. egg noodle pasta', '1 pkg. shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1 pkg. Cheddar cheese', '1 jar pizza sauce or Ragu', '1 jar spaghetti sauce', '2 lb. hamburger', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 small can mushrooms , drained', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53541, ' Heat oven to 425&deg;. In large nonstick skillet , brown ground chuck over medium 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink , stirring occasionally. Pour off drippings. Pour corn , barbecue sauce , green onions and , if desired , 1/2 teaspoon salt into beef; heat through. Place bread shell on baking sheet. Spoon beef over top. Salt and pepper to taste , if desired. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Cut into 8 wedges. Makes 4 servings.', '1 lb. ground chuck', '3/4 c. frozen corn , defrosted', '3/4 c. prepared barbecue sauce', '1/2 c. sliced green onions', '1 1/2 c. (6 oz.) Co-Jack cheese', '1 large (12-inch) Italian bread shell or prepared pizza crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53558, ' Cut chicken into 2 x 1 1/2-inch strips. In a large plastic bag , mix garlic and onion powder , pepper , seasoned salt and paprika; add chicken and shake to coat. Place a chicken and onion strip in each jalapeno half. Wrap each with a piece of bacon and secure with toothpicks. Grill , uncovered , over indirect medium heat for 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken juices run clear and bacon is crisp , turning once.', '1 lb. boneless skinless chicken breast', '1 Tbsp. garlic powder', '1 Tbsp. onion powder', '1 Tbsp. pepper', '15 jalapeno peppers , halved and seeded', '2 tsp. seasoned salt', '1 tsp. paprika', '1 small onion , cut into strips', '1 lb. sliced bacon , halved widthwise', ' Blue cheese dressing (for dipping)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53632, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.', '12 large manicotti shells', '4 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese , divided', '2 c. Ricotta cheese', '2 Tbsp. dried basil', '1 (26 oz.) jar your favorite spaghetti sauce , divided', '1/2 c. grated Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53640, ' ', '1 (16 oz.) pkg. lasagna , cooked according to pkg. directions; after cooking , lay flat to dry', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 c. onion , chopped', '1 c. celery , chopped', '1 c. fresh mushrooms , chopped', '1 c. chopped spinach (if fresh , cook until tender and drain; if frozen , cook in microwave as directed)', '2 c. leftover cooked chicken or turkey , chopped', '1 c. your favorite spaghetti sauce', '1/2 c. Monterey Jack cheese , grated', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese , grated', '3 c. Cream Sauce (recipe follows)', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53648, ' Saut sausage until browned. Drain and set aside. Combine tomato paste , sauce and spices. Spread each crust with 1/2 tomato mix. Top with remaining ingredients. Bake on lowest rack in preheated 450&deg; oven for 15 minutes.', '1 1/2 lb. Italian sausage (casing removed)', '1 (15 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1 (6 oz.) can tomato paste', '2 cloves garlic , crushed', '1 tsp. basil or to taste', '1/2 to 1 tsp. red pepper', '1/2 tsp. salt', '2 pizza crusts', '1/2 to 3/4 lb. shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1 c. chopped onion', '1 large green pepper , cut in chunks', '1 c. sliced mushrooms', '2/3 c. Romano or Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53667, ' Place top oven rack 4 to 5-inches from heat source.', '1 1/2 lb. fish fillets or steaks', '3 Tbsp. melted butter or margarine', '1 tsp. salt', '1 tsp. dried dill weed or other herb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53668, ' Cut fish fillets into serving-size pieces. Combine flour , salt and pepper. Coat fish with flour mixture. Place fish in a frying pan containing about 1/8-inch hot (but not smoking) oil. Fry at moderate temperature for 4 to 5 minutes or until brown. Turn carefully and fry additional 4 to 5 minutes or until fish is brown and flaky and no longer translucent in the center. Drain on paper towels. Yield: 6 servings.', '2 lb. skinned fish fillets', '1 c. self-rising flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53687, ' Fry wings or bake on cookie sheet at 400&deg; for 30 to 45 minutes , then check for doneness. Mix dry salad mix , melted margarine , lemon juice and hot sauce. Pour mixture over cooked wings. Spread wings on cookie sheet in single layer. Bake 10 to 20 minutes until lightly brown and crisp.', '5 lb. chicken wings', '2 pkg. dry Italian salad mix', '1/2 c. (1 stick) margarine', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1/4 c. hot sauce (start with 1 Tbsp. and add according to taste)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53690, ' Spray or lightly oil meat. Rub dry mix on meat. Grill until almost done. Remove and place into container of liquid ingredients. Baste for approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Grill 2nd time for 5 to 10 minutes , turning often. Do not overcook. Garnish with grilled orange or pineapple slices.', ' chicken parts (dark meat stays juicier on grill; white and dark will marinate fine however)', '8 oz. teriyaki glaze or sauce', '1/2 c. honey or maple syrup', '1/4 c. soy sauce', ' buttery spray or light oil (like canola)', '1 c. pineapple juice', '1 c. orange juice', ' garlic salt', ' Greek seasoning', ' pepper', '1 c. brown sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53757, ' Cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned; drain. Add salt in ketchup and tomato sauce and heat thoroughly; turn into 8 inch square or 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Cut cheese into thin strips and lay over meat. Top with pizza crust. Bake at 425&deg; for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 c. onion chopped', '3/4 tsp salt', '1/8 tsp black pepper', '1/4 c. ketchup', '1 pkg american cheese slices', '1 can pillsbury pizza roll', '1 c. tomato sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53821, ' ', '1 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. paprika', '1/2 tsp. cayenne pepper', '1/2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53910, ' Brown ground beef. In small baking dish , pour in beef and cover with pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Mix Bisquick , milk and eggs together , then pour over meat mixture. Bake at 400&deg; for 30 to 35 minutes.', '1 lb. ground beef', '2 c. (8 oz.) Mozzarella cheese', '3/4 c. Bisquick mix', '2 eggs', '1 (14 oz.) jar pizza sauce', '1 1/2 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53928, ' Gas grill. Sprinkle cheese evenly over bread shell. Top with remaining ingredients. Cover and grill pizza 4 to 6-inches from medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is crisp and cheese is melted (if crust browns too quickly , place a piece of aluminum foil between crust and grill). Makes 4 servings.', '2 c. shredded taco-seasoned cheese (8 oz.)', '1 (16 oz.) pkg. Italian bread shell or ready-to-serve pizza crust (12 to 14-inches in diameter)', '1 1/2 c. chopped cooked chicken', '2 Roma (plum) tomatoes , thinly sliced', '1 small jalapeno chili , seeded and finely chopped', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
