(61407, ' Roll cookie dough out on 1 large pizza pan or 2 small pans. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 minutes or until golden brown.', ' sugar cookie dough (use box mix , refrigerator roll or your own recipe)', '11 oz. (one 8 oz. and one 3 oz.) cream cheese', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 can your favorite pie filling', '1 c. pineapple tidbits (save juice for sliced apples , bananas and pears so they don''t turn brown)', ' bananas', ' pears', '3 colors grapes (slice larger ones)', ' strawberries', ' mandarin oranges', ' Cool Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(61726, ' Heat oven to 375 degrees. Cut each section in half lengthwise. press dough in bottom of ungreased 13x9 in. pan. Bake at 375 for 10-18 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool 15 minutes. In large sauce pan , combine 1 c. chocolate chips , and 1 c. of dip. Cook over medium heat until melted and smooth , stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and pecans. Spread over crust. In a small sauce pan , combine remaining 1 cup chips and 1/2 cup dip. Cook over medium heat until melted and smooth , stirring constantly. Spread over cereal mixture. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until set. Cut into 36 bars.', '18 oz. pkg. Pillsbury refrigerator chocolate chip cookies', '11.5 oz. pkg. milk chocolate chips', '16 oz. caramel apple dip', '3 c. rice crispies', '1 1/4 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(61727, ' In large bowl , combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix , beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2 qt. glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers , bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice , ending with pudding. Chill. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.', '14 oz. can Eagle sweetened condensed milk', '1 1/2 c. cold water', '1 pkg. instant vanilla flavor pudding mix', '2 c. Borden whipping cream , whipped', '36 vanilla wafers', '3 medium bananas , sliced &amp; dipped in Real Lemon juice from concentrate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(62130, ' Cut sugar cookie roll and press into a pizza pan. Bake and let cool. Top with Cool Whip and fruit , starting with less expensive fruit around edges. (I normally use cantaloupe.) Next , circle around your fruits using the most expensive in the middle (uses less and saves money when fruit is not on sale). Cut like a pizza and enjoy,', '1 roll sugar cookies', '4 favorite fruits', '1 tub Cool Whip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(62196, ' Pour all into a mixing bowl and beat at high speed just until batter is smooth. Pour into a greased and floured skillet. Cook at 350&deg; until light golden brown. Let sit for 5 minutes , then loosen edges and turn out upside down. Serve with favorite fruit and whipped cream.', '1 c. self-rising flour', '1 c. sugar', '1/3 c. oil', '2/3 c. whole milk', ' vanilla or other favorite flavoring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(62464, ' Drain apricots , reserving 2 tablespoons syrup. Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Place butter or margarine in a 9x1 1/2-inch round baking pan. Melt butter in pan in oven while preheating. Remove pan.', '1- 8 3/4 oz can unpeeled apricot halves', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '1/3 c. packed brown sugar', '1/4 c. slivered almonds', '1 pkg. 1 layer size yellow cake mix', '1/4 tsp. ground nutmeg', ' Frozen dessert topping for garnish', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(62473, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. In an ungreased square pan ,9x9x2-inch; stir together flour , sugar , 2 Tbsp. cocoa , baking powder and salt. Mix in milk , oil , and vanilla with fork until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water over batter. DO NOT STIR.', '1 c. flour', '3/4 c. granulated sugar', '2 Tbsp. cocoa', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. milk', '2 Tbsp. salad oil', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 c. chopped nuts (if desired)', '1 c. brown sugar (packed)', '1/4 c. cocoa', '1 3/4 c. hottest tap water', ' favorite ice cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
