(63053, ' Boil sugar and water until dissolved; cool. Add fruit juices and bananas. Blend well and freeze. Let thaw about 2 hours before serving. Just before serving , add the ginger ale in punch bowl and stir until slushy.', '6 c. water', '3 qt. ginger ale , Sprite or 7-Up', '5 bananas , mashed', '4 c. sugar', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen orange juice', '1 (6 oz.) can frozen lemonade or 1/4 c. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63063, ' Combine sugar and water in a Dutch oven; cook over high heat , stirring often , until sugar dissolves. Let mixture cool. Add bananas and next 3 ingredients to sugar mixture; stir well. Freeze until firm.', '4 c. sugar', '6 c. water', '4 bananas , mashed', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '2 (12 oz.) cans frozen juice concentrate , thawed (undiluted)', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 (67.6 oz.) bottle lemon-lime carbonated beverage , chilled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63114, ' Separate dough into triangles. Pat out each triangle. Place 3 pepperoni slices slightly overlapping on the center of triangle. Top with cheese. Roll starting with short side of triangle. Place point side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375&deg; for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.', '1 8 oz. can refrigerated crescent rolls', '5 oz. pepperoni', '2 oz. shredded mozzarella cheese', '1 c. pizza or spaghetti sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63176, ' Preheat oven to warm , lowest setting. Heat each tortilla in a skillet until soft. Place on a cookie sheet. Top with meat cheese and vegetables. Any combination. Place in the warm oven. Scramble the eggs. Place on top of the tortilla fillings. Roll them up. Serve warm.', ' flour tortillas', ' cheese , any kind', ' cooked meat , bacon , ham , sausage or grilled chicken', ' cooked vegetables , mushrooms , onions green bell peppers', ' scrambled eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63181, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Spread bean dip in baking pan. In large bowl combine cream cheese , sour cream and taco seasoning. Mix well. Place garlic in mixture and mix well. Spread on top of bean dip. Grate cheddar on top. Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven and top with , olives , tomatoes , onion and garnish with sour cream. Sprinkle top with tortilla chips. Serve warm.', '1 9 oz. can bean dip', '4 oz. cream cheese , soften', '1/2 c. sour cream', '1 tsp. taco seasoning mix', '1 garlic clove , pressed', '1/4 c. shredded cheddar cheese', '1/2 tomato diced', '2 green onion diced', '1/4 c. pitted olives', ' tortilla chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63186, ' Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat and then add the sauce. Stir well and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle cheeses over sauce mixture reserving about 1/4 cup of the parmesan cheese for last. Open crescent rolls and lay on top of the cheese and pinch seams together. If they break apart during baking , it doesn''t matter because you spoon it out onto the plates. Sprinkle with remaining parmesan cheese and bake at 350&deg; for about 15 minutes or until the crescents rolls are browned. Serve with garden salad and bread.', '1 lb. hamburger', '1 medium onion', '1 jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce 15 oz.', '2 c. shredded mozzarella cheese', '1 c. grated parmesan cheese', '1 8 count pkg. crescent rolls', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(63354, ' Dissolve sugar in water to make a light syrup. Mix syrup with next three ingredients and pour into small containers to freeze solid. Approximately 1 hour before serving , remove containers from freezer and place in punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over frozen ingredients. As mixture thaws , rake a fork over ice mixture to make slushy.', '2 c. sugar', '4 c. water', '2 large cans crushed pineapple', '3 to 4 bananas', '1 can orange juice', '1 (3-liter) bottle ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
