(66869, ' In a large pan , bring broccoli , broth , onion and pepper to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and let simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender. Process until smooth , then return to pan. Add 3 1/4 cups of milk to pan and bring to a boil. Stir cornstarch into remaining milk until smooth. Stir into boiling soup; simmer 1 minute , until thick. Reduce heat to medium; stir in cheese until melted. Makes 7 cups.', '2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen chopped broccoli', '1 c. chicken broth', '1 Tbsp. minced onion', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '3 1/2 c. skim milk', '2 tsp. cornstarch', '6 oz. processed cheese (American , Cheddar; pick your favorite,)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(66944, ' Place eggs in a 2-quart saucepan and cover with water. Bring water to a boil. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove eggs from hot water and cool. Press the yolks of hard-boiled eggs through a sieve and set aside. In a large pot , melt the butter over medium-low heat. Add the green onions and celery; cook , stirring occasionally , until the vegetables are soft , about 4 minutes. Add the flour and cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in the stock , milk and cream. Bring to a simmer. Add cooked egg yolks , crabmeat , sherry , salt and pepper and heat through. Ladle into bowls and garnish each serving with a pinch of paprika and a lemon slice.', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 green onion , minced', '1 stalk celery , chopped', '2 Tbsp. all-purpose flour', '2 c. fish stock', '2 c. milk', '2 c. heavy whipping cream', '1 1/2 lb. crabmeat , flaked', '1/4 c. sherry', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. ground black pepper', '2 c. hard-cooked eggs (optional)', '1/2 tsp. paprika', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
