(69478, ' Cook the sausage until browned; drain well. In a large mixing bowl , combine the cheese , chicken soup , sour cream , French onion dip , chopped onion , chopped pepper , salt and pepper to taste. Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes; mix well. Spread 1/2 the hash brown mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Spread half the browned sausage over the hash browns. Repeat layering hash browns , ending with sausage on top. Bake at 350&deg; for about 1 hour or until golden brown.', '2 lb. pork sausage', '2 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 c. cream of chicken soup', '1 c. sour cream', '1 (8 oz.) container French onion dip', '1 c. chopped onion', '1/4 c. each green and red pepper', '1 (30 oz.) pkg. frozen hash brown shredded potatoes , thawed', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69538, ' Rinse salmon. Pat dry with paper towels. Combine lemon juice and soy sauce in shallow glass dish. Add salmon. Let stand at cool room temperature no more than 15 to 20 minutes , turning several times. Remove salmon from marinade. Discard marinade. Season lightly with salt and pepper.', '4 salmon steaks (3/4 to 1-inch thick)', '3 Tbsp. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. soy sauce', ' salt and pepper', '1/2 c. barbecue sauce (KC Masterpiece Original)', ' fresh oregano sprigs', ' grilled mushrooms (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
