(69633, ' In a medium skillet , brown beef; drain. Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms; set aside. Cut bread in half lengthwise and spread with the meat sauce. Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with mozzarella. Bake uncovered at 400&deg; for 10 minutes , or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Use whatever pizza toppings you have on hand and fix this different ways.', '1/2 lb. ground beef', '1 16-oz. can pizza sauce', '1 8-oz. jar sliced mushrooms , drained', '1 loaf French bread', '2 c. grated mozzarella cheese', ' pizza toppings of your choice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69670, ' In a large skillet , brown the garlic and shallots in the olive oil. Add the diced tomatoes. Add the 1 c. liquid you''ve chosen; stir well. Add the salmon , lemon juice , chives and pasta; stir well. Heat through and add 1/2 c. sour cream. Serve immediately.', '1 Tbsp. olive oil', '3 Tbsp. chopped garlic', '2 chopped shallots', '1 - 1-1/2 lbs. Roma tomatoes , seeded', '1 c. fish stock OR chicken stock OR clam juice', '1 lb. cooked smoked salmon', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1/4 c. minced chives', '1 lb. cooked penne', '1/2 c. sour cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69759, ' Make your favorite chili recipe , enough for the number of guests you will be serving. Cook white or brown rice , enough for number of guests. Serve rice with chili on top and allow guests to top as they like with the additional ingredients.', ' your favorite chili ingredients', ' white or brown rice', ' Fritos or tortilla chips', ' shredded cheese of your choice', ' green onions , chopped', ' lettuce , shredded', ' tomatoes , chopped', ' sour cream', ' black olives', ' guacamole or avocado', ' pecans or pine nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69767, ' In a baking dish , arrange fish portions. Sprinkle with lemon pepper and basil. Bake at 375&deg; for 15 minutes. Place tomato slice on each portion. Sprinkle with green onions and cheese. Bake another 10 minutes.', '1 (11 oz.) pkg. frozen fish portions', '1/4 tsp. lemon pepper', '1/4 tsp. dried basil', '1 small tomato , sliced', '2 Tbsp. green onions , sliced', '2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese , grated', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69813, ' Roll fish in beaten egg and then in Ritz cracker crumbs. Place in shallow baking pan and bake at 350&deg; to 400&deg; for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and brush with melted butter. Sprinkle almonds over fish. Bake 10 minutes more.', ' fish fillets , cut into small pieces', '1 egg , beaten', ' Ritz cracker crumbs', ' butter', ' sliced almonds', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69821, ' Prepare potatoes as directed. Set aside. Spray rectangular casserole dish with Pam and spread 1 package of dough on bottom and sides of dish. Bake in oven for 25% of baking time listed on tube. Set aside. Brown hamburger; drain grease. Add 3/4 jar of salsa and all of broccoli. Simmer on low for 5 minutes or until broccoli is no longer firm. Layer potatoes on dough in casserole dish; top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Add hamburger mixture. Spread second pizza dough over hamburger mixture pressing sides of dish. Bake per dough instructions until light golden brown. Remove from oven; top with remaining cheese and parsley. Return to oven for 2 minutes. Remove and let stand 2 minutes before serving. Serves 6.', '1 1/2 lb. lean hamburger', '2 tubes Pillsbury pizza dough', '1 pkg. instant cheese mashed potatoes', '1 small jar Tostitos salsa (&quot;mild&quot;)', '2 c. Cheddar cheese', '1 small pkg. frozen broccoli , finely chopped', '3 Tbsp. parsley', ' Pam cooking spray', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69822, ' Thaw out desired amount of chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Cook desired amount of pasta according to directions; rinse. Thaw vegetables; set aside. Mix chicken , pasta and vegetables; stir in Italian dressing , enough to coat. Sprinkle Nature''s Seasons and toss. Enjoy warm or cold.', ' Tyson grilled chicken strips (precooked frozen)', ' pasta (your favorite kind; rotini , elbow , etc.)', ' Zesty Italian dressing (fat-free)', ' California style vegetables (frozen; broccoli , carrots and cauliflower)', ' Nature''s Seasons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69842, ' In 4-quart saucepan , heat oil. Saut onion , green pepper , mushrooms , garlic , basil , thyme , paprika , salt , pepper and cayenne pepper for 3 to 4 minutes , stirring constantly. Blend in tomatoes , broth , tomato sauce and bay leaves; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Add fish and okra; simmer 5 to 8 minutes. Stir in shrimp; cook for additional 2 to 3 minutes. Remove bay leaves.', '2 Tbsp. olive oil', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. sliced mushrooms', '3 cloves garlic , minced', '2 tsp. dried basil leaves , crushed', '2 tsp. dried thyme leaves , crushed', '2 tsp. paprika', '2 c. frozen sliced okra', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. pepper', '1/8 tsp. cayenne pepper', '3 1/2 c. (28 oz. can) peeled tomatoes and juice , cut up', '1 3/4 (14 1/2 oz. can) chicken broth (undiluted)', '3 bay leaves', '1 lb. firm fish fillet (halibut or snapper) , cut in 1-inch pieces', '2 c. hot cooked rice', '1/2 lb. shrimp , peeled and deveined', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69856, ' Preheat oven to 375&deg;. Brown meat with onion and seasoning mix. Stir in refried beans and mix well over low heat. Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles and place in ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Press over bottom and 1/2 up sides of pan to form crust. Seal any perforations. Spoon meat mixture over dough. Top with Velveeta cheese and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes , until golden brown. Delicious topped with lettuce , tomato and sour cream.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1 pkg. taco seasoning', '17 oz. can (2 c.) refried beans', '8 oz. crescent rolls', '4 oz. Velveeta cheese or Monterey Jack', ' favorite taco/burrito toppings (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69919, ' Preheat oven according to corn bread instructions. Brown the ground beef; drain. In a 13 x 9-inch pan , layer the ground beef , beans and stewed tomatoes. Cover with corn bread batter and bake until the corn bread is done. Serve topped with shredded cheese.', '2 cans Ranch Style beans', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 (14 1/2 oz.) can Mexican style stewed tomatoes', ' favorite corn bread recipe (we like to use 2 boxes Jiffy mix)', '1 pkg. shredded cheese (Mexican mix works well)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69935, ' Heat oven to 425&deg;. In large nonstick skillet , brown ground beef over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink , stirring occasionally. Pour off drippings. Stir corn , barbecue sauce , green onions and salt , if desired , into beef; heat through. Place bread shell on baking sheet. Spoon beef mixture over top; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Cut into 8 wedges. Makes 4 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef chuck', '3/4 c. frozen corn , defrosted', '3/4 c. prepared barbecue sauce', '1/4 c. sliced green onions', '1/2 tsp. salt (optional)', '1 large 12-inch Italian bread shell or prepared pizza crust', '1 1/2 c. (6 oz.) shredded Co-Jack cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69945, ' Oil in heavy pan on medium heat. Add garlic , onion , rice , corned beef and green pepper. Stir about 2 minutes on high heat. Add 1 can Gondulas , 3 cups of water , Sazon , cilantro , tomato sauce and salt for five minutes then lower heat , cover lid with foil and place on pan , about 10 minutes; stir one time only , another 20 minutes done. Serve with main dish.', '1 can Gondulas pigeon peas', '1 (6 oz.) tomato sauce', '2 c. long grain rice', '1/2 c. chopped cilantro', '1/3 chopped onion/green pepper', '2 tsp. corn oil', '1 can corned beef or favorite meat', '3 tsp. salt', '1 pkg. Goya Sazon (Con Culantro Y Achiote)', '2 tsp. garlic', '3 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69980, ' Heat oven to 425 degrees. Spray cookie sheet with non-stick cooking spray. In medium bowl combine mushrooms , bell pepper , zucchini , and onions. Sprinkle with garlic salt and basil; mix well. Unroll dough; place on cookie sheet. Roll dough into 14 inch square; cut into 4-7 inch squares. Place 1/4 c. on 1/2 of each square , spread to within 1/ 2 in. of edge. Top each with 1/4 of vegetable mixture. Fold dough in half over filling; press edges firmly with fork to seal. Brush each with beaten egg white. With sharp knife cut 2 - 3 slits in top of each for steam to escape. Bake at 425 degrees for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with heated pizza or spaghetti sauce for dipping.', '8 fresh mushrooms , sliced (3/4 c.)', '1 small zucchini , halved length wise , thinly sliced (3/4 c.)', '1/2 red or yellow bell pepper , coarsely chopped (1/2 c.)', '1/4 c. sliced green onion', '1/4 tsp. garlic salt', '1/4 tsp. dried basil leaves', '1 egg white beaten', ' 1-10 oz. can Pillsbury Refrigerated All Ready Pizza Crust', '4 oz. (1 c.) shredded mozzarella or provolone cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69987, ' Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place pizza crust on foil lined baking sheet. Top with bacon , veggies , and cheese. Beat eggs with 1/4 c. water and pour over crust. Bake 15-20 minutes , or until set.', '1 lg. (12 inch) prepared pizza crust', '1/2 c. Oscar Mayer real bacon bits', '1 c. chopped veggies (tomatoes , green onions , mushrooms , green peppers)', '1 c. shredded mozzarella cheese', '4 eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(70046, ' Heat oil in frying pan. Mix all ingredients together except flour. Scoop by spoonful. Press into patties and dredge in flour. Fry in skillet to golden brown. Drain on paper towel. Serves 6.', '1 pt. canned fish , drained or 1 lg. can salmon', '1/2 c. crushed cracker crumbs', '2 eggs', '2 tbsp. white vinegar', '1/2 onion , chopped (optional)', '1/2 tsp. seasoning salt', ' flour to dredge patties', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(70105, ' Crumble beef into a 1 1/2 quart casserole , then stir in onion and cook , covered , on 100% power (high) 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or till done. Drain , stir in tomato sauce , water and chili powder. Cook , covered on high , about 6 minutes or until bubbly. Meanwhile , stir together beans and taco sauce. Spread in the bottom of a 12 x 7 baking dish , then spread the meat mixture on top. Cook , uncovered , on high power 7 to 9 minutes or until heated through. Top with cheese and cook , uncovered , for about a minute or until cheese is melted. Top with crushed taco shells or corn chips and lettuce. If desired , top with tomato , green onions , black olives and avocado dip. Makes 6 servings.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 medium onion , chopped (1/2 c.)', '8 oz. can tomato sauce', '1/4 cup water', '1 tsp. chili powder', '16 oz. can refried beans', '1/4 c. taco sauce', '1 1/2 c. shredded cheese', ' taco shells (crushed) or corn chips', ' shredded lettuce', ' tomato (optional)', ' green onions (optional)', ' black olives (optional)', ' avocado dip (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
