(78941, ' Using a glass 8 x 13 casserole , spread refried beans. Mix sour cream in medium bowl with taco seasoning , then spread over refried beans. Next , spread on guacamole. Sprinkle on onions. Next , sprinkle on cheese , followed by tomato and black olives. Serve with tortilla chips.', '1 can refried beans', '1 (8 oz.) carton sour cream', '1 packet taco seasoning', '1 (8 oz.) carton guacamole dip', '6 oz. shredded Cheddar cheese', '1 small can sliced black olives', '1/2 diced onion', '1 diced tomato', ' tortilla chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(78996, ' Blend margarine , poppy seed , Worcestershire sauce , mustard and onion. Split packages of party rolls. Spread top and bottom with margarine mixture. Place ham and Swiss cheese on rolls. Bake at 400&deg; for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.', '1/2 lb. margarine , softened', '3 Tbsp. poppy seed', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '3 Tbsp. mustard', '1 medium onion , chopped fine', '3 pkg. party rolls', '1 lb. ham', '3/4 lb. Swiss cheese (in squares)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(78997, ' Brown both meats in skillet; drain , then add cubed cheese. Stir until melted. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes. Spoon onto rye bread slices. Place on cookie sheet; freeze. Place in Ziploc bags to store. Remove from freezer and heat in oven at 425&deg; until hot and bubbly.', '1 lb. sausage', '1 1/2 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese , cubed', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. oregano', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', ' dash of Tabasco', '2 pkg. Pepperidge Farm party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79007, ' Preheat oven to 375&deg;. Using lightly floured pastry roller , roll crust into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle. Place on cookie sheet or baking stone. Sprinkle crust with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Mix Parmesan , basil , mayonnaise , remaining Mozzarella and garlic. Thinly slice tomatoes over Mozzarella cheese. Spread cheese mixture over tomatoes evenly. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until top is golden and bubbly. Serve warm after cutting into squares.', '1 pkg. refrigerated pizza crust', '2 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese , divided', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese , grated', '2 Tbsp. basil', '2/3 c. mayonnaise', '1 garlic clove', '4 plum tomatoes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79035, ' Roll crescent rolls out onto large cookie sheet , pinching all edges together to form the crust. Brush egg white on top to ensure even browning. Bake according to directions on package. Cool. Using a mixer , beat cream cheese , mayonnaise and envelope of &quot;Dip&quot; mix together until smooth. Spread onto cooled crust. Mix carrots , broccoli , and cauliflower together in large mixing bowl. Spread mixture over cream cheese layer. Top with cheese. Cut into squares.', '2 rolls Pillsbury Crescent Rolls', '1 egg white - beaten', '2 packs softened cream cheese', '1 envelope Hidden Valley Ranch &quot;Dips&quot; (not dressing mix)', '3/4 cup mayonnaise', '1 cup finely chopped carrots', '1 cup finely chopped broccoli', '1 cup finely chopped cauliflower', ' 1-2 cups finely shredded sharp cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79051, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Remove and discard the wing tips and separate each wing into 2 pieces at the joint. Trim excess fat and skin. On a plate , stir together the flour , salt and pepper. Coat the wings with the flour mixture and shake off the excess. Heat oil in a deep fryer or deep , heavy pot to 375&deg;. Heat over medium heat until a corner of a wing held in oil makes a lively sizzle. Add as many wings as will fit in a single layer without crowding; fry , turning once , until golden brown and cooked through , about 10 minutes. Drain on paper towels and keep warm on a baking sheet in the oven. Repeat with remaining wings. Heat butter in a small saucepan over low heat until foaming. Remove from the heat and stir in red wine vinegar and hot red pepper sauce. Transfer the wings to a large mixing bowl , pour the sauce over the wings and toss until evenly coated. Taste and adjust the seasonings. Serve hot with celery sticks and dressing of your choice.', '1 1/2 lb. Chicken wings', '1/3 cup all purpose flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 tsp. Ground black pepper', '3 c. vegetable oil', '3 Tbsp. butter', '2 Tbsp. Red wine vinegar', '2 Tbsp. Hot red pepper sauce or to taste', ' Celery Sticks', ' Blue cheese dressing or Ranch dressing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79054, ' Mix uncooked sausage , cheese , and Bisquick until thoroughly combined. Crumple large sheet of foil , then smooth out and place on cookie sheet. Form mixture into small balls. Place on top of foil , about an inch apart. (Balls may be frozen at this point.) Bake at 350&deg; for 35 - 45 minutes , or until golden brown. Serve hot with mustards.', '1 pkg bulk sausage', '1 lb cheddar cheese , shredded', '1 cup Bisquick', ' Variety of mustards for dipping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79078, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Split buns and hotdogs lengthwise. Place layer of cheese on buns. Add hotdog slices to buns. Top with sauce. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Place on broiler pan until cheese melts.', '4 hotdog buns', '4 hotdogs', '12 slices mozzarella cheese', ' pizza sauce', ' parmesan cheese , grated', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
