(79274, ' Beat together cream cheese , sour cream , oregano and garlic powder. Spread evenly in a 9 or 10 inch pie plate. Spread pizza sauce over the top. Sprinkle with pepperoni , onion and green pepper. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake for 5 minutes more until heated through. Serve with crackers , vegetables or chips.', '1 pkg. cream cheese', '1/2 c. sour cream', '1 tsp. dried oregano', '1/8 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 c. pizza sauce', '1/2 c. chopped pepperoni', '1/4 c. minced onion', '1/4 c. chopped green pepper', '1/2 c. mozzarella cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79285, ' Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut each wing into 2 sections. Place chicken on the unseated rack of a boiler pan. Broil 4-5 inches form the heat about 10 minutes or until chicken is browned. , turning once. Transfer chicken to a 4 quart cooker. Combine chilli sauce and hot pepper sauce , pour over wings. Cover and cook on low heat for 4-5 hours or high heat 2-2 1/2 hours. Serve chicken with Ranch salad dressing. Makes 32 appetizers.', '16 chicken wings (about 3 lbs.)', '1 1/2 cups bottled chili sauce', ' 3-4 Tbsp. bottled hot pepper sauce', '1 bottle of ranch salad dressing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(79305, ' Brown meat and drain. Cube cheese and add to meat mixture with peppers and garlic. Mix until cheese is melted and spread on rye bread. Bake at 325 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes until browned and bubbly.', '1 loaf party rye bread', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. pork sausage', '1 lb. velveeta cheese', '1 tsp. crushed red pepper', '1 tsp. garlic powder', ' salt &amp; pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
