(83027, ' Allow for 2 or 3 pieces of fish for each person. Rinse fish in lemon water. Drain and sprinkle with salt. Roll in flour and cornmeal mixture. Heat oil to about 350&deg;. Fry in iron skillet with at least 1 inch of cooking oil on medium high temperature. Cook about 3 minutes each side or until golden brown and flaky. Serve with lemon slices , cole slaw , French fries , and hush puppies.', ' Fish , your choice', ' salt', ' flour , 1/3 c. or as needed', ' cornmeal , 1/3 c. or as needed', ' lemon juice , 2 or 3 Tbsp.', ' cooking oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(83050, ' Wash fish , dry thoroughly. Cut foil 14 inch square. Place one fish fillet in center of each. Arrange shrimp and mushrooms over fillet. Sprinkle with salt , pepper , paprika , and lemon juice. Top each with 1/4 cup white sauce. Sprinkle with parsley. Fold to seal. Bake at 400&deg; for 35 minutes. Serve in foil. Makes 8 servings.', '8 fillets , Sole , Cod or other white fish', '1/2 lb. raw , shelled , deveined shrimp', '1/2 lb. sliced mushrooms', '1/4 tsp. paprika', '1 tsp. lemon juice', '1/2 c. snipped parsley', ' white sauce , (recipe below)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
