(100527, ' Take a 13 1/2 x 10 1/2 baking pan or cake pan (no stick) , spray liberally with a no stick butter spray. Spread the contents of stuffing mix evenly in the baking pan , including spice packet if there is one. Take barbecue sauce , add water and mix. Roughly 1/3 water to 2/3 barbecue sauce. Pour mixture evenly on stuffing mix. Let it set and soak in a while if you have time. If you don''t , it will work anyway. Take chicken legs , chicken breasts , boneless pork chops or steak , venison chops or try one of your own. Lay them on the mixture in the baking pan and coat them with barbecue sauce. Use as many as will fit or as few as you want. Use as little or as much barbecue sauce as you want. Put in a 350&deg; preheated oven and bake for 50 to 75 minutes. If you are in a hurry , increase temperature and cut time. If you have lots of time , cut temperature to 300&deg; to 325&deg; and bake for 2 hours. When baked to your liking , take out and enjoy.', '6 oz. box stuffing mix', '1/2 to 2/3 (18 oz.) bottle your favorite barbecue sauce', '3 or 4 oz. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100549, ' Alternate layers , beginning with sauce on bottom of 9 x 13 pan (baking dish). Follow with 3 or 4 noodles , depending on size of pan. Mix browned hamburger into remaining spaghetti sauce. Layer sauce , cottage cheese , then 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese. Follow with another noodle layer , sauce , more cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese , then finish with a layer of noodles , sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375&deg; for 35 minutes and let cool before serving.', '26 oz. favorite spaghetti sauce', '9 to 12 lasagne noodles , cooked and cut to fit', '1 lb. ground beef , browned', '24 oz. cottage cheese', '1 large bag shredded Mozzarella cheese (3 to 4 c.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100597, ' Season the tenderloins with lemon pepper seasoning. Place on baking sheet and bake in 350 degree oven for 20 minutes , turning once during baking. While chicken is baking , heat the chicken gravy , Parmesan , and bouillon granules. This mixture can be thinned with a little fat free chicken broth , if desired. When the chicken is done , place the baked tenderloins on a bed of yellow rice. Spoon the gravy over the top. Makes 4 servings. About 1/2 gram of fat per serving.', '12 skinless chicken tenderloins , unbreaded', ' Lemon pepper seasoning', '1 can Franco American fat free chicken gravy', '2 Tbsp. fat free Parmesan cheese', '1 tsp. chicken bouillon granules', ' Cooked yellow rice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100601, ' Heat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the skim milk and Ranch dressing mix. Dip each tenderloin into the milk mixture and then coat with the crushed Bugles. Place on a baking sheet that has been lightly coated with cooking spray. Lightly spray each of the tenderloins with the cooking spray. Bake for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 4 servings.', '1 c. skim milk', '2 Tbsp. Ranch dressing mix', '12 chicken breast tenderloins , unbreaded', '2 c. reduced fat Bugles , finely crushed (about 1 c. crumbs)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100603, ' Roll the dough as flat as possible. Slice into strips. Heat the broth to boiling. Tear each strip of dough into several pieces , dropping them into the boiling broth. Reduce heat to a simmer. Cover and allow to cook for about 6 minutes. Remove cover. Add chicken , black pepper , milk , and margarine. Continue to cook until slightly thickened. Makes 6 servings with less than 2 grams of fat per serving.', '1 recipe of Unbelievable biscuits (made with 1/4 c. skim milk)', '2 cans fat free chicken broth', '1 c. chopped , cooked chicken breast', ' Black pepper , to taste', '1/2 c. skim milk', '1 1/2 tsp. reduced fat margarine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100763, ' Mix. Put on both sides fish. Bake at 350&deg; about 30 minutes or until fish are golden brown.', '6 fish fillets', '1/2 c. Miracle Whip', '1/4 c. butter', ' salt and pepper', '1 c. bread crumbs or cracker crumbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100764, ' Cook onions in oil; stir in tomatoes , seasoning and potatoes. Bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes. Add fish and corn; return to boil. Cook until fish flakes. Good with cornbread.', '2 lb. fish fillet , cubed', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 Tbsp. vegetable oil', '1 can tomatoes , diced', '2 potatoes , chopped', '1 can corn', ' salt and pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(101007, ' Lightly coat fillets with flour; fry in butter until done. Move cooked fish to dish. Fry sliced onions; add garlic and sliced mushrooms. Cook until done. Add cream , clam stock , dill , parsley , brandy/sherry , salt and pepper; cook down. Add Wondra flour to thicken. Place the fried fillets back into thickened mixture to warm. Serve with cooked pasta.', '1 1/2 to 2 lb. salmon fillets', '4 to 8 oz. mushrooms (white or shiitake)', '2 bunches green onions , sliced 1/8 to 1/4-inch pieces', '1 Tbsp. dill', '1/2 Tbsp. parsley (fresh or dried)', '2 to 3 garlic cloves , cut', '8 oz. bottle clam stock', '1/2 pt. whipping cream', '1 oz. brandy', '1 oz. sherry (if not available , use 2 oz. brandy and no sherry)', ' Wondra flour (used to thicken) to taste', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' flour (to coat fish fillets)', ' butter or margarine (as needed)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
