(101086, ' Make a medium sauce of first three ingredients. Add cheese and stir until melted. Then fold in the rest of ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350. Before baking , I put finely crushed potato chips on top of the casserole.', '3 Tbsp. butter', '3 Tbsp. flour', '1 1/2 c. milk', '1/2 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1/2 pkg. egg noodles , cooked', '1 or 2 cans tuna fish', '1 can mushroom or cream of celery soup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102094, ' In a large bowl , dissolve 1/2 cup salt in 1 gallon of water; mix well. Add cut up cabbage (1-inch length). Soak in salted water; sprinkle rest of the salt on top. Let it wilt about 2 hours , turning occasionally. Wash; drain well.', '1 large head Chinese cabbage (2 to 3 lb.)', '1/2 c. salt', '1/4 c. salt', '2 cloves garlic , minced', '2 stalks green onion , sliced', '1/3 c. crushed red pepper', '2 tsp. sugar', '1 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 carrot , shredded', '1 tsp. fish salt', ' dash of Accent', ' dash of sesame oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102301, ' Lightly coat a non-stick skillet with cooking spray. Combine hash browns , zucchini , carrots , onion , and seasoning. Mix well. Pour into skillet and spread evenly. Spray the top with the butter-type spray. For this , I use the &quot;I Can''t Believe It''s Not Butter&quot; spray. To spray the skillet , a regular cooking spray can be used. Cook slowly over low heat , stirring occasionally , until vegetables are tender. Makes about 6 servings with less than 1 gram of fat per serving.', '2 c. frozen , shredded hash browns , thawed', '1 c. shredded zucchini', '1/2 c. shredded carrots', '1 c. chopped onion', '3/4 tsp. Cavender''s Green seasoning', ' Butter type spray', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102493, ' ', '1 medium (1 to 2 lb.) eggplant', '16 oz. favorite sauce', '16 oz. Mozzarella cheese , sliced or shredded', '1/4 c. Goniola oil (to fry)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102713, ' Scald milk and butter; add to oats and let cool.', '2 c. milk', '1 Tbsp. butter', '2 c. oats', '2 pkg. yeast', '1/2 c. warm water', '3/4 c. molasses', '2 tsp. salt', '4 1/2 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102833, ' Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Roll pie crust into a 10-inch square on a lightly floured surface. Cut into sixteen ,2 1/2-inch squares. Combine apples , brown sugar , cinnamon and egg in a large bowl and toss to mix. Place pastry squares on an ungreased baking sheet. Spoon 1 tablespoon apple mixture onto each square , dot with 1/4 teaspoon butter. Fold each pastry over filling to form a triangle:brush pastry with some milk and press to seal. Bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes). Makes 16 turnovers.', '1 ready made pie crust', '2 tart apples (such as Granny Smith) , peeled and finely chopped or grated (about 1 1/2 cups)', '1/3 c. brown sugar , packed', '1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1 egg , beaten', '4 tsp. butter or margarine', '2 Tbsp. milk , divided', '2 Tbsp. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102948, ' In medium bowl , sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften. In a small saucepan , heat 1 cup of the evaporated Low Fat milk just to boiling. Slowly stir hot milk into gelatin. Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Mix in remaining milk , the pumpkin , brown sugar , pumpkin pie spice and vanilla. Set aside. Spray 10 inch glass pie plate with non-stick vegetable spray. Pour mixture into pie plate , chill until firm.', '2 Envelopes Unflavored Gelatin', '2 Tbsp. Cold Water', '2 1/4 Cup Undiluted Evaporated Milk Divided Low Fat', '1 3/4 Cup Pumpkin', '6 Tbsp. Dark Brown Sugar Packed', '1 tsp. Pumpkin Spice', '1 tsp. Vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103334, ' In a small saucepan , heat first 4 ingredients until shortening is melted. Cool to warm.', '1/2 C shortening (Crisco is good)', '1/2 C sugar', '2 tsp salt', '3/4 C milk', '2 pkgs quick rising dry yeast', '1/2 C warm water', '1/2 tsp sugar', '1/4 C wheat bran', '3 C light rye flour', '3 - 4 C white all-purpose flour', '3 beaten eggs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103598, ' Break or cut 1 loaf into small balls or pieces. Place in well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Melt margarine. Turn off heat. Add rest of ingredients; mix well and pour over bread. Add second loaf in small balls. Let rise midway up pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350&deg;. Remove from oven. Turn upside down on larger sheet (to catch caramel syrup).', '2 loaves frozen bread , just thawed', '1 stick margarine', '1 c. brown sugar', '1 large or 2 small vanilla pudding or butterscotch (not instant)', '2 Tbsp. milk', '3 Tbsp. dark Karo', ' cinnamon (if desired)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103632, ' Combine ingredients according to manufacturer''s directions. Process in dough cycle. Remove dough from bread machine. Grease appropriate pans.', '1 c. warm potato water', '3/4 tsp. salt', '1/3 c. Crisco', '1 egg , slightly beaten', '1/3 c. white sugar', '1/2 c. mashed potatoes', '3 1/2 c. flour', '1 pkg. yeast', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103869, ' Mix all ingredients. In mixer , beat until well mixed. Let rise in bowl. Put on lightly floured board. Knead several minutes. Put into 2 loaves , 18 hot rolls or roll thin. Spread oleo on top , then sugar and cinnamon. Roll into log; cut into 22 pieces. Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.', '1 c. oleo', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 c. warm water', '2 Tbsp. yeast', '2 eggs', '1/2 tsp. salt', '6 1/2 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(104137, ' Prepare cake according to package directions. Bake in two 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 1/2 cup cold water. Set aside for 20 minutes. Cool cake 5 minutes in pans. Remove. Place on racks over waxed paper. Using long-tined fork , punch holes in cake , making even rows across cake surface. Spoon gelatin over cake. Chill 1 to 2 hours.', '1 (2 layer size) pkg. white cake mix', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry flavored gelatin', '1 lb. pkg. frozen strawberries , halved and thawed', '1 (3 1/2 oz.) pkg. strawberry whipped dessert mix', '1 (2 or 2 1/8 oz.) pack dessert topping mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(104140, ' Cream butter and sugar. Beat in molasses and egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with 1/2 cup water. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350&deg; for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.', '1/2 c. butter or margarine , softened', '1/2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. molasses', '1 egg', '1 1/2 c. all-purpose flour', '3/4 tsp. baking soda', '3/4 tsp. ground ginger', '3/4 tsp. ground cinnamon', '1 c. canned pumpkin', '1 (4-serving size) pkg. instant vanilla pudding mix', '1/2 c. milk', '1/2 (4 1/2 oz.) carton frozen dessert topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(104854, ' Prepare mix according to instructions. Pour into muffin pans 2/3 full. cream sugar and cream cheese; add eggs and salt. Stir in chocolate morsels. Drop by spoonfuls in center of each cup cake. Bake as directed.', '1 pkg Duncan Hines chocolate cake mix (or your favorite recipe)', '1 8 oz. pkg cream cheese , softened', '1/3 c. sugar', '1 egg', ' dash of salt', '1 pkg (6 oz.) semi-sweet chocolate morsels', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105059, ' Mix cake mix and butter with mixer until crumbly. Press mixture into an oblong pan. Then mix eggs , pecans , Bit O'' Brickle bits , milk and vanilla. Blend well. Pour over cake mixture. Spread evenly. Bake at 325 degrees until browned around edges and slightly on top. Center will be loose but will setup when cooled. Slice into squares.', '1 yellow cake mix', '1 can Eagle Brand milk', '1 stick of butter or margarine', '1/2 c. pecans', '1 tsp. vanilla', '3 eggs', '1/2 c. Bit O'' Brickle bits (usually found during Christmas holidays; orange package)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105335, ' Add margarine to crackers. Put in Pyrex dish or Tupperware container. Beat ice cream and instant pudding mix. Bowl will be cold and have crystals on it When pudding is all mixed in ice cream , pour over cracker crumb mix. Cover top of ice cream mixture with 1 tub of cool whip and put in refrigerator. Chill. It''s actually ready to eat.', '1 1/3 Pack of Ritz Crackers Crushed', '1 Stick Margarine or Butter Melted', '1/2 Gallon of Ice Cream (Vanilla) - Put in Mixing Bowl and let melt a little', '3 Small Boxes of Dry INSTANT PUDDING MIX (Coconut Cream , Vanilla , Chocolate , or Banana Cream) Use Your Favorite; Do NOT Add Any Milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105486, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix the rolled oats , flour , brown sugar and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Spread half of this mixture evenly to cover bottom of the pan. Spread the cranberry sauce evenly over the crumbs. Cover the top with the rest of the crumbs. Bake the dessert 25 minutes. Serve it hot , cut into bars , with a scoop of vanilla ice cream on top. Makes 6 servings.', '1 c. raw quick-cooking rolled oats', '1/2 c. flour', '1 c. sugar', '1/2 tsp. margarine', '1 (1 lb.) can cranberry sauce , whole or jellied , or your favorite preserves', ' vanilla ice cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105687, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Grease 13 by 9 inch cake pan. Beat cake mix , oil , eggs and sour cream in large bowl on medium speed for 2 minutes , scrapping bowl occasionally. Spread half of the batter in the pan. Stir together brown sugar , pecans and cinnamon; spread over the batter. Carefully spread remaining batter over cinnamon and sugar mixture. Place pan in preheated oven for about 45 minutes or until deep golden brown. Prick surface of the warm cake several times with a fork. Spread glaze over the cake. Cool completely. This is also good served warm with butter.', '1 pkg. Betty Crocker super moist yellow cake mix', '2/3 c. vegetable oil', '4 lrg. eggs', '8 oz. tub sour cream', '1 c. packed brown sugar', '1/3 c. chopped pecans (opt.)', '2 tsp. cinnamon', ' Favorite powdered sugar glaze', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(105770, ' Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add yogurt and mix thoroughly. Then add Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serve and enjoy.', '1 small pkg. Jell-O (sugarless , any flavor)', '1/4 c. boiling water', '2 (8 oz.) cartons yogurt (same flavor as Jell-O)', '1 medium container Cool Whip Lite , softened', '1 (8 or 9-inch) graham cracker pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106255, ' Place banana slices in bottom of crust. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes and cinnamon. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours until set. Serve with caramel topping. Makes 8 servings.', '1 large ripe banana , sliced', '2 c. cold milk', '1 Keebler Ready-Crust shortbread pie crust (6 oz.)', '1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon', '2 pkg. (4-serving size) Jell-O white chocolate or vanilla flavor instant pudding', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip whipped topping , thawed', ' caramel dessert topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106422, ' ', '1 1/4 c. all purpose flour', '3 Tbsp. brown sugar', '1/2 c. butter', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', '3 Tbsp. finely chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(106779, ' *Colored decors , assorted candies , such as jelly beans , gumdrops , candy-coated chocolate pieces , nonpariels , black , and/or red shoestring licorice.', '1 (18.25 oz.) pkg. favorite cake mix', '1/2 c. butter or margarine (1 stick) , melted', '2 large eggs', '1 (16 oz.) can vanilla frosting or 1 recipe vanilla frosting', ' food coloring', ' decorations*', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107375, ' Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Stir well until completely dissolved. Allow to cool slightly. Add yogurt and stir until smooth. Add Cool Whip and stir until well blended. Pour into the graham cracker crust and chill in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours before serving. All ingredients can be low-fat or fat-free and it is just as good,', '1/4 c. boiling water', '1 box of your favorite flavored jello', '2 containers (8 oz. each) flavored yogurt (should be the same flavor as the jello)', '8 oz. Cool Whip', '1 prepared graham cracker crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107464, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Stir together eggs , sugar , oil and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Stir in undrained pineapple. Combine flour , baking powder and baking soda. Add to pineapple mixture. Stir just until well combined. Stir in nuts. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Frost with your favorite cream cheese frosting and garnish , if desired.', '2 eggs , beaten', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 c. flour', '1 1/2 tsp. baking powder', '1/2 tsp. baking soda', '1 c. chopped nuts', ' favorite cream cheese frosting', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107988, ' Beat cream cheese and sugar. Then add cool whip and beat till smooth. Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with favorite pie filling or other topping.', '1 pkg. cream cheese', '1/3 c. sugar', '1 8 oz. cool whip', '1 graham cracker crust', ' Favorite pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108079, ' ', ' dried apples', ' water', ' sugar', ' cinnamon', ' nutmeg', ' cloves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108417, ' Mix together peanut butter chips and shortening in a large glass bowl. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted. Stir in pretzel sticks and crackers. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool for 30 minutes.', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. peanut butter baking chips', '2 Tbsp. shortening', '1 1/2 c. thin pretzel sticks', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. plain fish-shaped crackers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108463, ' Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water. Boil sugar in 6 cups of water and cool. Combine tea , sugar water , lemonade , and orange juice. Add bourbon. Mix and freeze 24 hours or serve with ice.', '4 tea bags', '2 c. sugar', '12 oz. frozen lemonade', '12 oz. frozen orange juice', '2 c. bourbon (Optional)', '8 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108562, ' Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water in bowl. Combine gelatin mixture with pineapple juice , lemonade concentrate , almond extract and cold water in large freezer container. Freeze for 3 to 4 days. Let thaw for 6 hours before serving; stir. Pour into punch bowl; ladle into punch cups. Yield: 20 servings.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. any flavor gelatin', '2 c. sugar', '3 c. boiling water', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 (6 oz.) can frozen lemonade concentrate', '1 Tbsp. almond extract', '5 c. cold water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108625, ' Combine sugar and water in a saucepan , bring to a boil , stirring until sugar dissolves , cool. Pour mixture into large bowl , add the next four ingredients and freeze until firm. Remove from freezer several hours before serving (mixture should be slushy). Pour into punch bowl and stir in chilled soda. Yields approximately 2 1/2 gallons.', '4 c. sugar', '6 c. water', ' 1(46-oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 (46-oz.) can orange juice', '5 bananas , mashed', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '2 (2liter) lemon-lime sodas (Sprite)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108661, ' Place spices in cheesecloth. Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot. Put on No. 5 setting for 2 hours , then turn down to No. 2 setting. Keep warm for serving. Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 qt. cranberry juice in jar', '3 c. water', '1 c. brown sugar', '1/2 tsp. salt', '2 Tbsp. whole cloves', '1 Tbsp. whole allspice', '6 cinnamon sticks', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108698, ' Dissolve the sugar in the water in a large freezer container. Add pineapple juice , orange juice , limeade and almond extract and mix well. Freeze , covered , until needed. Let stand until slushy. Combine with the ginger ale in a punch bowl and mix gently. Makes 50 servings.', '2 1/2 c. sugar', '19 c. lukewarm water', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen orange juice concentrate', '1 (6 oz.) can frozen limeade', '1 tsp. almond extract', '1 (1 liter) bottle ginger ale , chilled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(108718, ' Dissolve jello in hot water. Add Kool-Aid , sugar , lemon juice , pineapple juice and water. Freeze. Remove from freezer 2 or 3 hours before serving and flake with a fork until slushy.', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry jello', '2 c. hot water', '2 pkg. strawberry Kool-Aid', '2 c. sugar', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '4 1/2 qt. cold water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
