(114138, ' Mix Tuna and Mayonnaise together. Spread on bread and place on a cookie sheet. Top with pickle. Top with Cheese. Melt under broiler. Serve hot.', ' Tuna Fish', ' Mayonnaise', ' Pickles cut into bite-size chunks', ' slices of Cheese', ' Break', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114140, ' In a bowl beat Eggs. In another bowl combine next five ingredients. Dip fillets in egg , then coat with cornmeal mixture. Heat Oil in skillet. Fry Fish over medium heat for about 3 - 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easy with a fork. Yield 4 servings.', '3 Eggs', '3/4 c. Flour', '3/4 c. Corn Meal', '1 tsp. Garlic Powder', '1/2 tsp. Salt', '1/2 tsp. Pepper', '1 lb. Fish Filet (white fish preferred - haddock , sole , cod , etc.)', ' Oil for frying', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114144, ' In a bowl , beat Egg and Honey. In another bowl combine the next 5 ingredients. Dip Fillets into Egg and Honey mixture then coat with Cracker mixture. In a large skillet , heat Oil. Fry Fillets over medium heat for 3 - 4 minutes or until Fillet flakes easily with fork. Drizzle with Honey and Lemon if desired. Yields: 4 servings.', '2 Eggs', '1 Tbsp. Honey', '1 c. finely crushed Ritz Crackers (about 22)', '1/3 c. Flour', '1/4 tsp. Salt', '1/4 tsp. Pepper', '1 lb. Fish Filet', ' Vegetable Oil for Frying', ' additional Honey', ' Lemon Wedges', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114172, ' Spray a baking dish with Pam-type spray. Line the bottom of the baking dish with Scallops. Shake Bread Crumbs over scallops until lightly covered. Top with half the Margarine slices. Place the Cod on top of the margarine. Repeat the procedure with Bread Crumbs and Margarine. Place in a 400 degree oven for 40 - 45 minutes or until the Cod flakes easily when touched with a fork. Serve immediately with a baked potato and salad. Lemon wedge , optional.', '1-1/2 lb. Sea Scallops', '2 lb. Cod (any white fish can be used)', ' dry Bread Crumbs (plain or seasoned)', '1 stick Margarine , sliced in 1/4 inches', ' fresh Lemon , cut into wedges (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(114203, ' Wash and drain fish. Combine yogurt , oil , lemon juice and seasoning in a shallow dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on wax paper. Dip fish in yogurt mixture and then press in crumbs. Coat both sides. Place fish on slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 475 in oven for 10 minutes or until done.', '1 pound flounder or fish of your choice', '2 Tablespoon non-fat yogurt , plain', '2 teaspoons vegetable oil', '1 1/2 teaspoon fresh lemon juice', '1/4 teaspoon paprika', '1/2 teaspoon Morton Lite salt', '1/8 teaspoon black pepper', '2 slices of toasted whole wheat bread , crumbled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
