(117783, ' Step 1: With an electric mixer or fork or potato masher , mash bananas and add applesauce in bowl.', '1 c. mashed ripe bananas (the browner the better)', '1/2 c. applesauce', '1/4 c. vegetable oil', '1/2 c. granulated sugar', '1/2 c. light brown sugar', '4 egg whites', '1 tsp. baking soda', '3/4 tsp. baking powder', '1 Tbsp. cinnamon', '2 c. flour', ' walnuts , raisins (optional; if using , throw in with oil and mix)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(117848, ' Beat all together. Add 2 c flour gradually. Put in lightly greased bowl and let rise until double. If your thumb print remains in dough , it has doubled. Knead for 5 to 8 minutes and put in greased loaf pan and let rise again. Also great for dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls. Bake at 350&deg;. Yield 1 loaf.', '3/4 c. milk , scald', '1/4 c. crisco', '1/4 c. sugar', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. cold water', '1 pkg. dry yeast', '1 c. flour', '1 egg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(119278, ' Divide the angel food cake cubes among 4 dessert dishes.', '2 c. cubed angel food cake', '1 (8 oz.) carton fat-free lemon yogurt', '1/4 (8 oz.) container frozen light whipped dessert topping , thawed', '1 c. mixed berries (raspberries , blueberries or sliced strawberries)', ' fresh mint (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(120398, ' Soak gelatin in cold water. Let stand. Cook 1/2 cup sugar , milk and egg yolks together. Cook a few minutes. Then mix in gelatin and vanilla. Set in a cool place until thickened. Add egg whites and whipped cream. Mix well and let cool. Crush graham crackers. Mix with oleo and sugar. Put on top and bottom.', '1 pkg. gelatin dessert', '1/3 c. cold water', '1/2 c. sugar', '3/4 c. milk', '2 egg yolks', '1 tsp. vanilla', '2 stiffly beaten egg whites', '1 c. whipped cream', ' graham crackers', ' oleo', ' sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(120520, ' Combine crumbs , 1/2 cup of sugar and butter. Mix well. Blend cream cheese , 1 cup sugar , topping mix and cold milk. Spread the crumb mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2 dish; add half of the cream cheese mix. Spread on pie filling; add remaining cream cheese. Top with crumbs. Refrigerate several hours. Serves 12.', '2 1/2 c. graham cracker crumbs', '1 1/2 sticks melted butter', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '2 cans cherry pie filling', '2 boxes dessert topping mix', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '1 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(121567, ' Combine strawberries and the 2 tablespoons sugar. Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour. In a mixing bowl , stir together flour , the 1 tablespoon sugar , baking powder and baking soda. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine egg and buttermilk. Add to flour mixture all at once , stirring until combined.', '3 c. sliced fresh strawberries', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '1 2/3 c. all-purpose flour', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. baking soda', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 beaten egg', '1/2 c. buttermilk or skim milk', ' nonstick spray coating', '1 (1.4 oz.) envelope whipped dessert topping mix', '1/2 c. skim milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(121975, ' Mix dessert crust mix with 3 tablespoons cream and 2 tablespoons water. Press mixture into 9-inch pie pan and freeze until firm , about 15 minutes. With mixer on high speed , beat remaining cream until soft peaks form; refrigerate. In bowl with mixer at low speed , beat milk with contents of filling mix and peanut butter packet 30 seconds. Increase speed to high and beat 3 minutes. Spread 1 cup mix on crust. Warm topping pouch according to package directions. Spread over mixture in pan and spread 1/4 to 1/2 cup of candy quarters over topping. Fold 3 cups reserved cream into remaining peanut butter mixture. Spread over candy. Refrigerate until firm , about 45 minutes. Spoon remaining cream in dollops on pie. Garnish with remaining candy. Makes 12 servings.', '1 (16 oz.) pkg. Jell-O No-Bake peanut butter cup dessert', '2 1/4 c. heavy cream , divided', '1 1/3 c. cold milk', '24 miniature peanut butter cups , quartered and divided', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(122358, ' 1st layer: Melt butter. Mix with flour and 1 cup chopped pecans. Press over bottom of 9x13 inch baking pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes. Cool completely.', '1 c flour', '1 stick butter or margarine', '1 c chopped pecans', '1 (8 oz) pkg cream cheese', '1 c powdered sugar', '1 13 1/4 oz pkg frozen dessert topping', '2 small pkg chocolate instant pudding', '3 c milk', ' pecans for garnish', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(122953, ' Mix together sugar , Jell-O and water , stir until dissolved , and add pineapple juice. Pour into containers and freeze for at least 24 hr. (Plastic milk jugs work well). Take out of freezer at least 1 hr. before using. Empty container into a large punch bowl; break mixture into chunks with a wooden spoon. Add sprite or ginger ale; mix to a slushy consistency. Makes a wonderful punch. Can add crushed pineapple or frozen strawberries when pouring in the pineapple juice.', '2 c. sugar', '1 lg. pkg. Strawberry Jell-O , or flavor of your choice', '6 c. boiling water', '2 lg. cans pineapple juice', '2- 2- liter sprite or ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(123733, ' In a bowl , let frozen yogurt stand , stirring occasionally until melted , about 15 minutes. Whisk in milk , rum extract and nutmeg. Cover and chill at least 30 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg for garnish , if desired. Makes 8 servings. Ready to serve in 45 to 50 minutes.', '2 pt. low-fat vanilla frozen yogurt', '1/2 c. 1% low-fat milk', '1/4 c. rum or 1/4 tsp. rum extract', '1/4 tsp. ground nutmeg (and more for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(123786, ' Mix sugar with 3 cups water and boil for ten minutes. Let cool. In another container , put bananas , lemon juice , pineapple juice and orange juice. Mix well. Add to cooled syrup and freeze. Take from freezer one hour before using. Use a wooden spoon to break frozen mix apart and stir into a slush. Do not let mix thaw completely. Add 6 cups of water and ginger ale; stir and enjoy.', '2 c. sugar', '9 c. water', '3 mashed bananas', '1/4 c. ReaLemon juice', '1 large can pineapple juice', '1 large can frozen orange juice', '1 qt. ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124710, ' Pour sour cream into small mixing bowl. Add party dip mix. Stir and chill for 5-10 minutes.', '1 pt. sour cream', '1 pkg. Hidden Valley Ranch party dip mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124813, ' Soften cream cheese and mix in all ingredients. Combine until well mixed. Place into small ovenproof bowl or pan. Cook in 400&deg; oven until light brown and bubbly , about 10 minutes. Serve with party rye bread.', '1 c. crab , cleaned', '8 oz. cream cheese', '2 tsp. lemon juice', '1 Tbsp. mayonnaise', '1 tsp. Worcestershire', '4 drops Tabasco', '1 tsp. grated onion', ' dash of pepper and salt', '1 pkg. party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124863, ' Mix dip with sour cream. Add bacon bits and cheese. Mix together and serve with crackers or bread pieces.', '1 oz. packet original Ranch party dip', '1 pt. sour cream', '1/4 c. bacon bits', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
