(128976, ' Brown beef and sausage , drain well. Add cheese , seasonings and stir until cheese is melted. Spread mixture on bread slices , place on cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Serves a party of 20 to 25.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1 tsp. garlic salt', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '3 loaves rye party bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(129004, ' Cook ground beef in a large skillet. Add chopped onion. Cook spaghetti separately until done. In a separate bowl , mix tomatoes , picante and cumin. Add beef. In a casserole dish , mix spaghetti and beef together. Add one cup of cheese to top. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.', '1 lb. ground beef , cooked', '24 oz. spaghetti , cooked', '2 cans diced tomatoes', '1 c. Picante sauce', '1 medium chopped , grilled onion', '1 can stewed tomatoes', '1 tsp. cumin', '2 c. grated cheese , divided', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(130223, ' Bake chicken wings at 375&deg; for 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Mix margarine , Frank''s Red Hot and desired amount of cayenne pepper. Melt in microwave , stirring every 30 seconds. Drain drippings off of chicken and pour sauce over wings.', '4 lb. bag chicken wings', '1/2 c. or 1 stick butter or margarine', '1 c. Frank''s red hot pepper sauce', ' cayenne pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(136428, ' Bake golden butter cake according to directions. Let cool completely and split layers to make 4 layers instead of 2. While cake is baking , pour sour cream , sugar and 2 packages of frozen coconut into bowl. Stir mixture every now and then. Thaw remaining package of frozen coconut , reserving this for the top and sides. Frost and stack layers with the coconut , sour cream and sugar mixture. Cover the top and sides with dessert topping and sprinkle coconut on top and sides.', '1 box golden butter cake mix', '8 oz. sour cream', '2 c. sugar', '3 (6 oz.) packs frozen coconut', '8 oz. Cool Whip dessert topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138106, ' Place tea bags and ginger in a tea pot. Add 4 1/2 cups boiling water. Cover; let steep 3 to 5 minutes or until desired strength. Remove tea bags. Stir in sugar. Cool at room temperature 2 hours. Cover and chill until ready to serve.', '8 single-serving-size tea bags', '1 (1 to 2-inch) piece fresh ginger , thinly sliced', '2 to 4 Tbsp. sugar', '2 (12 oz.) bottles or cans ginger ale , chilled', '1 orange , halved lengthwise and thinly sliced (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138237, ' Combine cheese , bacon , stuffed olives , onion and mayonnaise. Spread 1 tablespoon on each rye slice. Top with black olive slices. Broil 2 minutes.', '1 c. shredded Swiss cheese', '6 slices bacon , cooked and crumbled', '1/4 c. chopped stuffed olives', '1/4 c. mayonnaise', '2 Tbsp. chopped onion', ' sliced black olives', '20 slices party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138472, ' Fry and drain hamburger and sausage. Add cheese and stir until cheese melts. Add remaining seasonings and let cool. Spread on party rye. Freeze on cookie sheet , then store in freezer in zip lock bags. When ready to use , place on cookie sheets and bake in preheated 3 50&deg; oven for 15 minutes. Serve warm.', '1 lb. hamburger meat', '1 - 12 oz. hot sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1 teas. garlic powder', '1 teas. Worcestershire sauce', '1/2 teas. leaf oregano', '1 loaf party rye', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138659, ' Brown meat and drain well. Add all seasonings. Add cheese to meat mixture and stir until melted. Place rye bread on baking sheet and spread mixture on bread slices. Place under the broiler until the bread is lightly toasted and meat mixture bubbles. These may be frozen before broiling for later use. Freeze on a cookie sheet , then store in a freezer bag. Makes about 75.', '1 lb. ground sausage', '1 lb. ground chuck', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '2 Tbsp. parsley flakes', '1 tsp. oregano', '1/2 tsp. basil', '1/4 tsp. garlic salt', '2 pkg. party-type rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138681, ' Combine mustard , butter and poppy seeds. Mix well. Cut rolls in half. Spread mixture on each side. Place small amount of ham and cheese on bottom of each roll. Cover with top half of rolls. Wrap with tin foil. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 to 15 minutes , or until cheese melts. Makes 3 1/2 dozen rolls.', '1 (8 oz.) jar Dijon mustard', '1 c. butter or margarine , softened', '3 tsp. poppy seeds', '2 (7 1/2 oz.) pkg. party rolls', ' approximately 3/4 lb. thinly sliced ham', ' approximately 8 oz. thinly sliced Swiss cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(138705, ' Blend 4 ingredients together in mixer. Split rolls (do not break apart). Spread butter mixture on each side of rolls. Place thinly sliced ham on bottom half; add Swiss cheese. Put top half of rolls on cheese. Put stuffed rolls back on foil tray. Cover with tin foil. Bake at 350&deg; for 15 minutes. Cut rolls apart before serving.', '2 Tbsp. margarine', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '2 Tbsp. mustard', '2 Tbsp. poppy seed', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. Swiss cheese , sliced', '1/2 lb. thinly sliced ham', '2 pkg. party rolls (20 in pkg.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
