(138868, ' In mixing bowl add avocados. Using a fork mash (slightly) the avocados. Add lemon juice , garlic and red onion. Season mixture with salt and pepper , hot sauce to spice it up. I place Romas on grill and cook until blackened. Rotate often. Then peel skin. I leave some on for that &quot;smoked&quot; flavor. Chop and stir in avocado mixture. I add jalapenos for a zing. You can leave it out and add more hot sauce for spice. Serve with cheese quesadillas , chips or with your favorite taco.', '2 avocados , peeled , pitted and chopped', '2 tsp. minced garlic or 1 clove leaf', '1 Roma tomato , grilled to charred', ' pinch of black pepper', '1 Tbsp. chopped jalapeno (optional)', ' juice of 2 lemons or 2 Tbsp. (I use 1 lime and 1 lemon)', '1/4 c. chopped red onion', ' pinch of salt', ' dash of hot sauce (to taste)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
