(151833, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon brown sugar over a baking sheet. Combine oats , remaining 2 tablespoons sugar , and spices in the bowl of a food processor and blend until smooth. Add half the almonds and process until finely chopped. Add remaining almonds. Process until coarsely chopped. Transfer to a shallow bowl.', '3 Tbsp. dark brown sugar', '1/2 c. rolled oats (not instant)', '1/4 tsp. cinnamon', '1/4 tsp. ground ginger', ' pinch of ground nutmeg', ' pinch of ground cloves', '1/4 c. sliced almonds , toasted', '4 apples (McIntosh apples have the best texture for this dessert)', '1 large egg , beaten with 1 Tbsp. milk', ' whipped cream or ice cream', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
