(179264, ' Melt chocolate and add the rest of the ingredients. Break small pretzels into short links and add as much as you like. Drop by spoon on waxed paper. Brown or white chocolate can be used. Directions for melting may be found on package.', '1 1/2 lb. block chocolate (found at Wal Mart during Thanksgiving and Christmas)', '3/4 c. peanut butter', '4 c. Rice Krispies', ' small pretzels', '1 lb. or less chopped walnuts , peanuts or cashews', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(179294, ' Place zucchini and sugar in large heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil; cook for 15 minutes. Add pineapple with juice and lemon juice. Boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat; mix with gelatin powder. Stir well. Pour into sterilized jars. Seal. Store in refrigerator. Yield: 5 pints.', '6 c. zucchini , peeled and grated', '6 c. white sugar', '3/4 c. crushed pineapple (undrained)', '1/2 c. lemon juice', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. apricot gelatin dessert', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(179305, ' Slice each package of rolls horizontally like a sandwich; set aside. Melt the margarine and then add mustard , poppy seed , Worcestershire sauce and onion. Brush this mixture on both sides of the sliced rolls. Layer ham and Swiss cheese on the bottom portion of the rolls and then put the top on. Heat about 10 minutes at 400&deg;.', '3 pkg. small party rolls', '1/2 lb. margarine', '3 Tbsp. mustard', '3 Tbsp. poppy seed', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 medium onion , finely chopped', '1 lb. thinly sliced ham', '1/2 lb. thinly sliced Swiss cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(179511, ' Fry ground beef and sausage. Pour off fat. Add cheese to meat. Heat until cheese is melted. Add garlic powder , Worcestershire sauce and oregano. Spread on rye bread. Yields 3 dozen.', '1 lb. lean ground beef', '1 lb. sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. oregano', ' party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
