(186641, ' In a medium saucepan , crumble pie crust. Mix into boiling water; cook and stir vigorously until pastry forms a ball and leaves the side of pan. Remove from heat. Cool for 10 minutes. Add eggs , one at a time , beating with a wooden spoon after each addition until smooth. For each cream puff , spoon about 1/4 cup of the mixture onto a greased baking sheet. Bake in a 400&deg; oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffs are dry and golden brown. Remove from baking sheet; cool on wire racks. Cut off tops; remove excess webbing.', '1 stick pie crust mix', '2/3 c. boiling water', '2 eggs', '1/2 c. hot fudge sauce', '1 (21 oz.) can cherry pie filling', '1 (4 oz.) carton frozen whipped dessert topping , thawed', ' finely chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187074, ' Parboil broccoli and layer in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix soup , mayonnaise , lemon juice and curry powder. Pour half over broccoli. Lay chicken breasts (cut in strips) over mixture. Pour on remaining sauce. Top with cheese and bake at 350&deg; until brown and bubbly.', '6 large chicken breasts , baked or grilled', '2 (10 oz.) boxes broccoli', '1 (10 oz.) can cream of chicken soup', '1/2 c. Hellmann''s mayonnaise', '1/2 tsp. lemon juice', '1/2 tsp. curry powder', '1 c. shredded Cheddar cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
