(187892, ' Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water and juices. Place in clean milk cartons or plastic soft drink bottles , leaving room for expansion when frozen. Place in freezer for at least 8 hours.', '8 small pkg. Jell-O (any flavor)', '16 c. boiling water', '6 c. sugar', '8 c. cold water', '3 (12 oz.) cans frozen lemonade', '4 (46 oz.) cans pineapple juice', '4 qt. ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187926, ' Cook the drained sauerkraut for 5 minutes with the diced onions and 2 tablespoons butter. Mix corned beef with relish and mustard. Spread on slice of party bread. Top with heaping tablespoonful of sauerkraut mixture and slice of Swiss cheese. Broil until cheese melts. Serve as an appetizer.', '1 (12 oz.) can corned beef', '3/4 lb. sliced Swiss cheese', '1 (No. 1) can Bavarian sauerkraut , drained well', '1/4 c. diced onions', '2 Tbsp. butter', '2 Tbsp. sweet relish', '2 Tbsp. Gulden''s mustard', '1 loaf party bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188030, ' Mix all ingredients. Use half pastry for bottom and half for top. Put in favorite filling. Bake at temperature that is recommended for filling. Makes a 9-inch pie.', '1 1/2 c. sifted all-purpose flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1 1/2 Tbsp. sugar', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '2 Tbsp. cold milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
