(188535, ' Dissolve Kool-Aid , jello , and sugar in boiling water. Add strawberries and pineapple juice. Cool and freeze in Ziploc bags. About 1/2 hour before serving set out. At serving time , add ginger ale and chop to mix. You may use NutraSweet jello and Kool-Aid and leave off sugar for low sugar recipe.', '3 c. boiling water', '2 small pkg. strawberry Kool-Aid', '1 small pkg. strawberry jello', '1 qt. ginger ale', '2 c. sugar', '1 qt. crushed sweet strawberries', '1 large can pineapple juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188627, ' Steam (covered) boil potatoes in small amount of salted water. (A chicken bouillon cube can be substituted for salt.) When tender , drain , retaining liquid. Add Ranch dressing (more or less as needed) and beat potatoes with electric mixer. If needed , add small amounts of retained liquid (or skim milk if desired) until of desired consistency. Add butter sprinkles to taste.', '4 medium potatoes , peeled and chunked', '1/3 c. water', ' salt', '1/4 to 1/3 c. fat-free Ranch dressing (bottled)', ' liquid from potatoes as needed', ' Molly McButter as needed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188666, ' Combine strawberries and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour. In a mixing bowl , stir together flour , 1 tablespoon sugar , baking powder and baking soda. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine egg and buttermilk. Add to flour mixture all at once , stirring until combined. Spray 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray coating. With lightly floured hands , pat dough into pan. Bake in a 450&deg; oven about 10 minutes or until golden. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely , or serve warm.', '3 c. fresh strawberries , sliced', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '1 2/3 c. all-purpose flour', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '2 tsp. baking powder', '1/4 tsp. baking soda', '3 Tbsp. margarine', '1 egg , beaten', '1/2 c. buttermilk or skim milk', '1 (1.4 oz.) envelope whipped dessert topping mix', '1/2 c. skim milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188863, ' Cover raisins and soda with 3 cups boiling water. Cover and let stand overnight. The next day , mix raisins with all other ingredients. Bake at 325&deg; for 1 hour. Reduce heat to 300&deg; for 1/2 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. This makes 2 tube pan cakes.', '1 box raisins', '3 tsp. soda', '3 c. sugar', '3 Tbsp. butter', '1 c. nuts', '6 c. flour', '1 1/2 tsp. baking powder', '3 tins Christmas mixed fruit', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188947, ' Bring pineapple , sugar and water to a boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot mixture. Cool in refrigerator until it is the consistency of egg whites. Add cheese and nuts. Fold in dessert topping. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.', '1 (8 oz.) can crushed pineapple (undrained)', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 c. water', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. orange flavored gelatin', '1/2 c. sharp , grated cheese', '2/3 c. pecans , chopped', '1 c. frozen whipped dessert topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(189556, ' Boil 1 cup of the measured water to dissolved jello. Add all the remaining ingredients except 7-Up and dissolve well. Freeze in 3 (1/2 gallon) milk or juice boxes. Thaw to a slush and add 7-Up just before serving. (Takes about 5 hours to thaw.) To make red punch , substitute strawberry Kool-Aid and jello. To make green punch , substitute lime jello and Kool-Aid. Makes 2 gallons.', '2 pkg. lemonade Kool-Aid (unsweetened)', '2 c. sugar', '4 qt. water', '1 large pineapple juice', '3 Tbsp. almond extract', '4 Tbsp. lemon jello', '4 ripe bananas , blended (optional)', '1 (2 liter) bottle 7-Up or Sprite', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
