(190095, ' Mix in blender at medium speed the first four ingredients and syrup from pineapple 30 seconds or until smooth. Turn into bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix carefully. Spoon into aluminum foil lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan. Freeze. Unmold , slice and serve on lettuce leaves. Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 6 servings.', '1/2 c. blender-made mayonnaise', '8 oz. pkg. cream cheese , cubed', '1/2 c. confectioners sugar', '3 to 4 drops red food color', '1 c. whipped cream or dessert topping', '8 3/4 oz. can crushed pineapple', '1 c. canned whole cranberry sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(190186, ' Boil sugar and cream until it forms soft ball in cold water. Beat until light and add nuts. Add cut up Christmas cake citrus candy. Add flavoring and turn onto buttered dish. Make squares.', '3 c. brown sugar or maple sugar (can be half and half)', '1 c. cream', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1/4 tsp. maple flavoring', '1 c. nuts , cut up', ' Christmas cake citrus candy', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
