(209703, ' Break pretzels up and take off salt. Put in a 9 x 15-inch glass dish. Drizzle oil on pretzels. Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over pretzels. Do not mix. Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes. Mix and microwave 2 to 3 additional minutes. Store in covered container.', '1 large box hard pretzels', '1 pkg. Hidden Valley Ranch party dip', '1 1/2 tsp. lemon pepper', '1 1/2 tsp. dill', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 c. plus a little more oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(210408, ' Separate the chicken wing drumsticks from the wing tips. Deep fry the chicken in medium-hot (380&deg;) peanut oil for 5 to 8 minutes; drain on paper towels. Melt the butter in a large frying pan. Add the Tabasco and vinegar. Roll the chicken wings around in the mixture to coat them. Serve with Blue cheese dip and celery sticks. Serves 6 to 8.', '3 lb. chicken wings', '1/4 lb. butter', '3 Tbsp. Tabasco sauce', '1 Tbsp. cider vinegar', ' peanut oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(210999, ' Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add Cool Whip. Spread on crust , then drain frozen berries. Use that liquid and rest of water to equal 3 cups and mix with Danish dessert topping. Add berries. Cool (Junket) well. When cool , pour over cheese layer , then add another layer of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.', '1/2 c. butter', '1 c. flour', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese', '1 c. powdered sugar', '1 c. Cool Whip', '2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen berries', ' berry liquid + water to equal 3 c.', '2 pkg. Danish dessert topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(211066, ' Drain pineapple (save syrup). Add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid. Let cool. Gently stir in ginger ale. Chill until partially set. Blend fruits; fold gelatin into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill firm. Prepare topping according to package. Blend in cheese. Spread over gelatin. Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon butter at 350&deg; for 10 minutes. Sprinkle on top. Chill. Serves 9.', '1 can crushed pineapple', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. lemon flavored gelatin', '1 (7 oz.) bottle ginger ale', '1 lb. can jelled cranberry sauce', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese , softened', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(211438, ' Brown meats together and drain. Mix oregano , garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Melt cheese and spread on rye bread. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 minutes.', '1 lb. Bob Evans zesty hot sausage', '1/2 lb. ground beef', '1 tsp. oregano', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 lb. Velveeta', '2 loaves Pepperidge Farm party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(211574, ' Coat wings in flour , salt and pepper. Heat Crisco in electric frypan. Fry wings until crispy. Dip fried wings into hot sauce mixture (margarine , garlic powder and celery salt). Place dipped wings in pan. Bake in a 325&deg; oven for 30 minutes. Serve with cut up celery and Marie''s Bleu cheese mixed with 1 tablespoon celery seed.', ' wings', ' flour', ' salt', ' pepper', ' Crisco', '1 bottle hot sauce (Durkee or Louisiana)', '1 stick margarine', '1 Tbsp. garlic powder', ' Marie''s Bleu cheese dressing', '1 Tbsp. celery seed', ' cut up celery', '1 tsp. celery salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(212129, ' Clean mushrooms; cut in small pieces. Saute mushrooms in butter for about 10 minutes. Add lemon juice , sour cream and enough paprika to tint pink. Mix well. Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on each piece of bread. Broil for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve hot. Yields 40 canapes.', '1 lb. fresh mushrooms', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1 tsp. lemon juice', '1 pt. sour cream', ' paprika', '1 loaf party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(212447, ' Bring all ingredients to room temperature and mix together. Spread on party rolls. Broil until cheese melts and is brown.', '1 pkg. Pepperidge Farm party rolls', '1 can (6 1/2 oz.) crabmeat', '1 jar (5 oz.) Old English sharp Cheddar cheese spread', '1 stick butter/ oleo', '2 Tbsp. mayonnaise', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(212719, ' Brown and drain meat in a skillet. Add seasonings and cheese. Allow to melt. Arrange bread on cookie sheets. Put about 1 tablespoonful of mixture on each piece of bread. Freeze. When frozen , put in plastic bags to keep in freezer. When ready to serve , bake on cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes at 350&deg;. Serve hot; delicious,', '1 lb. hamburger', '1 lb. sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', ' garlic powder', ' seasoned salt', '2 loaves party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(212726, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;; arrange bread slices on cookie sheet and spread dressing on one side of bread. On each slice add some beef , cheese and sauerkraut. Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is toasted.', '1 loaf party rye', ' Thousand Island dressing', ' thinly sliced corned beef', '1 c. sauerkraut , shredded and drained', ' sliced Swiss cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(213218, ' Brown and drain meats. Stir in other ingredients. Put on rye bread by teaspoon and bake at 350&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes.', '4 oz. black olives', '2 lb. hamburger', '1 lb. regular pork sausage', '1 small can chopped green chilies', '1 lb. Cheddar cheese , grated', '1 (7 1/2 oz.) can tomato sauce', '1/3 or less c. salad oil', '1 tsp. minced onion', '1 Tbsp. salt', '2 dashes garlic salt', '3 Tbsp. vinegar', '2 loaves Pepperidge Farm party rye bread , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(213418, ' Rub bowl with halved garlic clove. Cream the cream cheese with spoon until smooth. Gradually add remaining ingredients; blend well. Serve with crackers or raw cauliflower pieces. If too thick , add more clam juice. Makes 1 pint.', '1 garlic clove', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '2 tsp. lemon juice', '1 1/2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/4 tsp. salt', ' dash of pepper', '1 (7 oz.) can minced clams , drained', '1/4 c. clam juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
