(214477, ' Remove casing from Italian sausage; crumble sausage into large skillet. Add pork sausage and ground beef. Add the onion and green pepper. Cook thoroughly , stirring constantly , until meat is browned. Drain well on paper towels; also wipe the skillet. Then return meat mixture to skillet. Add seasonings and mix well. Heat through until hot , then stir in cheese until melted. Remove from heat.', '1 lb. Italian sausage', '1 lb. hot bulk pork sausage', '2 lb. lean ground beef', '1 c. finely chopped onion', '1/2 green pepper , chopped fine', '2 Tbsp. oregano', '1 tsp. garlic salt', '1 lb. processed American cheese , cubed', '1 lb. Mozzarella cheese , cubed', '1 lb. Longhorn or Colby cheese , grated', '3 (8 oz.) loaves party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(214614, ' Beat eggs and sugar together until light. Stir in flour , salt and baking powder; mix well. Add boiling water , then extract. Pour into well oiled jelly roll pan and bake in a 400&deg; oven for 15 minutes. Turn out on cloth wrung from hot water. Trim edges and spread with jelly. Roll immediately. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.', '1 c. sugar', '3 whole eggs', '1 c. all-purpose flour', '1/2 c. boiling water', '1 tsp. baking powder', '1 tsp. vanilla or lemon extract', ' pinch of salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
