(216313, ' In small mixer bowl , beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk; beat until smooth and creamy. Prepare dessert topping mix according to package directions; fold into peanut butter mixture. Turn into prepared crust 5 to 6 hours or overnight.', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '3/4 c. sifted powdered sugar', '1/2 c. peanut butter (crunchy or smooth)', '2 Tbsp. milk', '1 envelope Dream Whip dessert topping mix', '1 (8-inch) graham cracker pie shell', ' sprinkle coarsely chopped peanuts on top', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(216810, ' Brown beef and sausage. Drain off fat. Cut cheese into small cubes and add it and seasonings to meat. Mix until cheese almost melts. Spread on bread slices. Freeze on cookie sheet and then store in plastic bags in freezer. Either broil or heat in hot oven until they brown on top when ready to serve.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 Tbsp. oregano', '2 rolls party rye bread', '1 lb. hot sausage', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1/2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
