(248605, ' In cup , stir marmalade and mustard until mixed. Set aside. Cut ham slices to fit on half of the bread slice; cut cheese slices to fit on top of ham , then top with a dollop of marmalade mixture and another bread slice. Preheat oven to 450&deg;. In 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan , melt butter; remove pan from oven. In pie plate with fork , beat milk and egg until mixed. Dip sandwiches , one at a time , into egg mixture to coat all sides. Place sandwiches in one layer in jellyroll pan. Bake until sandwiches are golden brown on both sides , or about 20 minutes , turning once. Cut each sandwich in half. Serve hot.', '2 Tbsp. orange marmalade', '1/2 tsp. dry mustard', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. sliced cooked ham', '1 (8 oz.) loaf party rye bread (slices)', '1/2 (8 oz.) pkg. sliced cheese', '2 Tbsp. butter', '1/4 c. milk', '1 egg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
