(262867, ' Drain pineapple juice into a measuring cup , reserve pineapple. Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid. Bring to a boil and add jello. Add cold water. Chill 30 minutes. In a bowl combine drained pineapple and cranberry sauce. When well blended , put in a 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm and spread with Creamy Cheese Frosting. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.', '1 (13 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry jello', '3/4 c. cold water', '1 (16 oz.) can jellied cranberry sauce', '1/3 c. chopped pecans', '1 Tbsp. butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(263433, ' ', '6 c. water', '6 c. rice', '10 sheets sushi nori', ' square bamboo mat (for rolling)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(263888, ' Slice rolls completely through the middle. Cream margarine , poppy seed , Worcestershire sauce , mustard and onion. Spread tops and bottoms with creamed mixture. Then add boiled ham and Swiss cheese , divided evenly over rolls. Wrap in foil. Bake at 400&deg; for 10 minutes. Cut into individual rolls. They may be frozen for later use. Yields 60 rolls.', '3 pkg. party rolls', '1 c. butter or margarine', '3 Tbsp. poppy seed', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '3 Tbsp. mustard', '1 medium onion , chopped', '1 lb. boiled ham , sliced', '1 lb. Swiss cheese , sliced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(264359, ' Combine pie filling mix , sugar and 1/4 cup of the water in saucepan. Blend in beaten egg. Add remaining water. Bring to a full boil over medium heat , stirring constantly. Cool 5 minutes , stirring twice. Measure 1 cup filling , cover and cool completely. (Can be put in freezer ad it will be cool and ready in about 20 minutes.) Pour remaining filling into pie shell. Put in refrigerator. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on envelope. Blend into the cup of cooled filling. Spoon over filling in pie shell. Chill thoroughly. Serves 6 to 8.', '1 pkg. Jell-O lemon pie filling', '2 1/4 c. water', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 egg , slightly beaten', '1 baked (9-inch) pie shell', '1 envelope Dream Whip dessert topping mix', '1/2 c. cold milk', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(264407, ' Combine cream cheese , sugar , milk and vanilla; beat until smooth. Remove small amount of center from each dessert cup; frost cups with cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with coconut. Spoon strawberries into centers at serving time. Yield: 8 servings.', '2 (4 oz.) pkg. whipped cream cheese', '1/2 c. sugar', '2 tsp. milk', '1 tsp. vanilla', '2 pkg. shortcake dessert cups', '1 (3 1/2 oz.) flaked coconut', '1 qt. fresh strawberries , sweetened', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
