(271043, ' Prepare Jell-O according to package directions. Pour mix into a medium mixing bowl. (A metal one is best and speeds the chilling process.) Place Jell-O in the refrigerator until it becomes thickened , but not completely set.', '2 pkg. lime Jell-O', '1 large can pear halves', '1 small container Cool Whip dessert topping', '1 small pkg. English walnuts , chopped (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(271246, ' Combine flour , nuts and butter in a medium bowl. Mix thoroughly and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in the oven at 350&deg; for 20 minutes. Remove and cool.', '1 c. flour , sifted', '1 c. chopped nuts', '1 stick butter , softened (1/4 lb.)', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1 c. confectioners sugar', '2 (8 oz.) cartons whipped dessert topping , divided', '3 c. milk', '2 (3 1/2 oz.) pkg. instant chocolate pudding mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(271279, ' Put Jell-O , pineapple and sugar into a small saucepan. Cook slowly on the stove , on low heat , for about 10 minutes , stirring constantly. (Pineapple juice will make its own liquid.) Remove from the heat. Add the cream cheese and nuts to the mixture. Fold in the entire container of prepared Dream Whip.', '2 pkg. apricot Jell-O (do not prepare as usual with water)', '1 large can crushed pineapple', '1/3 c. sugar', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. Philadelphia cream cheese', '2 large pkg. Dream Whip dessert topping', '1/3 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(271281, ' ', '4 sliced cooking apples , peeled and sliced', '5 1/2 tsp. white sugar (granulated)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(271568, ' Cook sausage and drain. Put Mozzarella cheese on rye bread. Add 1 teaspoon tomato sauce; add crumbled sausage. Sprinkle oregano and dash of garlic salt. Top with mushrooms and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350&deg; until slightly brown and cheese melted. Serve warm. (Can be made ahead and frozen until ready to serve.)', '1 loaf party rye bread', '1 lb. mild sausage', '1 pkg. Mozzarella cheese', '1 jar mushrooms , sliced', ' Parmesan cheese', '1 large can tomato sauce', ' oregano seasoning', ' garlic salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(272407, ' Mix first 6 of ingredients in medium bowl. Add chicken and toss to coat evenly. Heat 2 teaspoons vegetable oil in roasting pan in oven for 5 minutes. Add chicken and bake 40 minutes , turning wings after 20 minutes.', '1 (3 oz.) bottle Louisiana hot sauce', '1 1/2 tsp. pressed garlic', '1 tsp. dried thyme', '1 1/2 tsp. dried rosemary , crushed', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. freshly ground pepper', '2 1/2 lb. chicken wings , cut at joints (discard tips)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(272455, ' All flour should be sifted twice to prevent heaviness. Set oven at 375&deg;. (When baking in quantity , I bake in an approximately 12 x 18-inch cookie tin with a lip and cut into pieces about 2 1/2 to 3-inch square and 1/4-inch thick , 24 pieces , or make fingers by cutting into 48 pieces.)', '1/2 lb. butter (I use regular salted table butter)', '1/2 c. superfine (bar/dessert) sugar', '1 1/2 c. flour', '1 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(272757, ' Add pecans , taffy and cinnamon rolls. Let raise. Bake at 350&deg;.', '1 c. mashed potatoes', '3/4 c. sugar', '3 eggs', ' pinch of salt', '1 1/2 c. scalded milk', '1 c. shortening (I use half margarine)', '1/2 large yeast cake , dissolved in 1/2 c. warm water', '2 c. flour', '4 c. more flour', '1/2 stick margarine', '1 c. brown sugar', ' Karo (maybe 1/4 c.)', '1/3 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(274703, ' Fry and drain sausage. Melt cheese into sausage. Add remaining ingredients. Spread on bread. Can freeze on cookie sheet , then bag them. Bake at 400&deg; for 10 minutes until lightly brown on top.', '1 lb. sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta', '3 tsp. ketchup', '3/4 tsp. oregano', '1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '3/4 tsp. garlic salt', '1 pkg. party rye bread (3-inch square slices)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(274747, ' Heat oven to 375&deg;. Cut wings apart at the joints , throw away wing tips. Heat oil in large heavy skillet over high heat and brown wings lightly , stirring often. Spread in a single layer in a large baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over wings. Bake until very tender , turning often. About 1 hour.', '4 lb. chicken wings', '1 c. stir-fry sauce', '1 tsp. ginger', '2 Tbsp. cooking oil', '2/3 c. pineapple juice', '4 Tbsp. brown sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(275330, ' In 6-quart container , combine sugar and gelatin powder. Add boiling water; stir until dissolved. Add pineapple juice; mix well. Pour into plastic containers and freeze at least 24 hours. About an hour before serving time , put out containers to thaw. Empty containers into large punch bowl; break mixture into chunks with wooden spoon. Add ginger ale; mix to a slushy consistency.', '2 c. sugar', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. flavored gelatin (any one)', '6 c. boiling water', '2 (46 oz.) cans pineapple juice', '4 bottles (1 liter each) ginger ale , chilled', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(275367, ' Combine all ingredients except tortillas. Spread mixture over tortillas and roll up like jelly roll. Refrigerate until firm then slice into rolls. Good for 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese', '1 1/2 c. sour cream', '1 pkg. original Ranch party dip', '1 small jar bacon bits', '1 (10 oz.) frozen , chopped spinach (thaw and squeeze out water)', '1 bunch green onion , chopped', '1 large pkg. flour tortillas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276162, ' Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or until set. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily. Garnish as desired. Store leftovers in freezer.', '1/3 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 1/2 c. cold milk', '1 small pkg. vanilla instant pudding and pie filling', '8 oz. Cool Whip', '6 English toffee bars , chopped', '1 graham cracker pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276237, ' Brown the sausage and ground chuck separately and drain the fat. Over low heat mix the meats , cheese , garlic salt and oregano until cheese melts. Spread over the party rye rounds and freeze. (May store in freezer bags until needed.) Remove from freezer , place on a cookie sheet and broil for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.', '1 lb. sausage', '1 lb. ground chuck', '1 lb. Velveeta', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '1/2 tsp. oregano', ' Pepperidge Farm party bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276544, ' Cut wings in half. Dust in mixture of flour and chili powder. Fry in hot oil 8 to 10 minutes on each side until brown. Drain on paper towels. Heat together barbecue sauce and hot pepper sauce. Add chicken wings and simmer a few minutes. Makes 24 &quot;hot&quot; wings.', '12 chicken wings', '1/2 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. chili powder', '1/3 c. cooking oil', '1/2 c. barbecue sauce', '1/2 tsp. pepper sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276719, ' Combine cream cheese , powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth. Spread around sides of dessert shells , roll shells in coconut that was put on waxed paper and place on tray. Stir almond extract into cherry pie filling and spoon into shells. Chill.', '1 carton whipped cream cheese', '1/3 c. sifted powdered sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '10 dessert shells (like for strawberry shortcake)', '1 c. flaked coconut', '1/8 tsp. almond extract', '1 can cherry pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276765, ' In large skillet sprayed with nonstick spray , brown and saute onion. Spread with mustard and place on sprayed cooking sheet. Place ham on each bread slice , then spoon on sauerkraut. Top with slice of cheese and spoon on onions. Put in 350&deg; oven to get it hot. Then run under broiler.', '1 medium onion', '4 slices rye bread', ' spicy hot mustard', '1/2 lb. lite ham , shaved', '1 (16 oz.) can sauerkraut , well drained', '4 slices Alpine Lace cheese', ' nonstick cooking spray', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276821, ' First fry bacon on stove. Fire the grill up. Cook hamburger on grill (after pattied up). Five minutes before hamburger is done , warm mushroom gravy up on stove. When hamburgers are done , lay slices of cheese on them , then lay 2 to 3 half slices of bacon on them. Spoon on mushroom gravy on top. Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 8 people.', '1 grill', '2 lb. ground chuck', '1 lb. bacon', '8 slices cheese', '16 oz. jar mushroom gravy (beef , Heinz)', '8 hamburger buns', ' salt and pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(276857, ' Slice potatoes up real thin; slice or dice up onions. Crisscross 2 sheets , then the other two. Put potatoes in middle of Reynolds Wrap; slice butter on top of potatoes (covering almost all of the sliced potatoes). Put the onions on top of butter , salt and pepper; wrap them up. Fire grill up. Cook on grill for about an hour (or until potatoes are soft).', '1 grill', '5 lb. potatoes', '4 oz. butter', '2 onions', ' Reynolds wrap , 4 sheets , 17 x 24-inch sheets', ' salt and pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(277143, ' Fry hamburger , sausage and cayenne pepper. Drain grease. Combine cheese and oregano; mix well. Place on party rye bread and place on cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 300&deg;.', '2 lb. hamburger', '1 lb. sausage', '1/4 tsp. cayenne pepper', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '1 tsp. oregano', ' party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(277739, ' Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint. On rack in broiler pan , arrange wings. Broil 6 inches from heat 25 minutes or until browned , turning occasionally. Transfer to serving dish. In a small saucepan over medium heat , heat Tabasco sauce , butter and vinegar. Drizzle evenly over wings. Serve with celery sticks and Blue cheese salad dressing for dipping. Makes 24 appetizers.', '12 chicken wings (about 2 lb.)', '2 Tbsp. Tabasco brand pepper sauce', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine', '1 1/2 Tbsp. red wine vinegar', ' Dole celery sticks', ' Marie''s refrigerated regular or lite Blue cheese salad dressing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(278055, ' Preheat oven to 400&deg;. Peel and core apples. Stuff the centers with mixture of brown sugar , raisins and cinnamon. Roll out pastry and cut into 4 circles approximately 8 inches in diameter , depending on size of the apples. Place an apple in the center of pastry circle and brush the edge with beaten egg. Draw up pastry to enfold the apple , pressing edge to seal. Brush tops of pastry with remaining egg. Bake in shallow dish for 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.', '4 dessert apples', '2 oz. brown sugar', '2 oz. raisins', ' cinnamon to taste', '1 beaten egg', '1/2 pt. cream , whipped', '1 (12 oz.) pkg. puff pastry', '1 beaten egg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(278323, ' Mix all ingredients together. Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on each slice of bread. Place on cookie sheet. Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes. Serve warm.', '1 stick Cheddar cheese (6 to 8 oz.) shredded', '1/2 lb. bacon , cooked and crushed , slice in small pieces before cooking', '1 medium onion , minced', ' mayonnaise , enough to hold mixture together', '1 pkg. small dark party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(278325, ' Cook and drain bacon , then cool and crumble bacon. Add grated Swiss cheese , mushrooms and mayonnaise. Mix together well. Spread on bread (cut into fourths if using whole slices). Broil until brown , about 5 to 10 minutes.', '1 lb. bacon', '1 c. grated Swiss cheese', '1 c. mayonnaise', '4 oz. chopped mushrooms', '8 slices of dark or rye bread or 1 pkg. party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
