(293514, ' Prepare and bake cake mix. Bake and cool. Stir pudding into crushed pineapple. Prepare dessert topping mix. Fold into mixture. Spread on cake.', '1 pkg. Duncan Hines cake mix (2 layers)', '1 (3 3/4 or 3 5/8 oz.) pkg. instant vanilla pudding', '1 (13 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(293795, ' Pour boiling water over tea bags; steep 3 minutes. Remove tea bags. Blend in juices; sweeten with honey. Cut peel from lemon and oranges; section fruit. Remove all membranes; add to tea. Wash and hull strawberries; cut in half. Add to tea; cover. Refrigerate punch at least 6 hours to blend flavors. Just before serving , add bottle of soda water. Yields about 10 cups.', '2 c. boiling water', '4 tea bags black tea', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '2 c. orange juice', '1 Tbsp. honey', '1 lemon', '2 oranges', '2 c. fresh strawberries', '1 bottle soda water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(296139, ' Mix; pour into pie crust. Refrigerate.', '1 graham cracker pie shell', '1 large container dessert topping', '1 can condensed milk', '1 small can lemonade', ' food coloring , if desired', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(296199, ' Brown meats together and drain. Melt Velveeta cheese into meats. Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Place a heaping amount on each slice of party rye. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 minutes.', '1 lb. ground meat', '1 lb. hot sausage', '1 lb. Velveeta cheese', '2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 tsp. garlic powder', '1 loaf party rye bread', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(296524, ' In large bowl , mix cereal and oyster crackers together. Measure 1/3 cup popcorn oil. Pour over top of dry cereal and crackers , gently mixing well to coat all. Sprinkle dry party dip mix over cereal mixture. Mix well to coat. Gets better as it sits a while. Store in airtight container.', '1 (12 oz.) box Kellogg''s Crispix cereal', '1 (12 oz.) pkg. oyster crackers', '1 pkg. Hidden Valley original Ranch party dip mix (dry)', '1/3 c. Orville Redenbacher''s butter flavor popcorn oil', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(296528, ' Boil water and sugar; cool. Add next 4 ingredients; mix well. Freeze in a covered flat container. When needed for serving , let set until slightly softened , 1 to 2 hours. Scrape frozen mixture into punch bowl to form slush. Add 7-Up and lemon juice; serve.', '4 c. water', '2 c. sugar', '1 (No. 2) can pineapple juice', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen orange juice', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen lemonade', '3 bananas , mashed', '4 qt. 7-Up', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
