(300876, ' Clean and dehead shrimp. Slice bacon in half. Combine Worcestershire sauce , lemon juice and butter in a small saucepan. Bring to a simmer over low heat. Wrap 1 bacon slice around 1 shrimp and secure with a toothpick and place on skewer. Season with Nature''s Seasons and place on grill. Baste with sauce several times. Turn skewers over and continue to baste with sauce until shrimp are done.', '3 lb. jumbo shrimp , cleaned', '2 lb. bacon', ' toothpicks', ' skewers for grill', '1/2 c. Worcestershire sauce', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '1 Tbsp. butter', ' Nature''s Seasons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(301030, ' Melt chocolate in microwave or double boiler. Meanwhile , prepare mousse according to package directions , adding Espresso powder before beating. Scrape chocolate into a medium-size bowl. Stir in about 1/3 mousse mixture and nuts. Spread over bottom of pie crust. Spread remaining mousse on top , mounding slightly in center. Chill at least 1 hour. Before serving , spread Cool Whip over top in swirls. Garnish with chocolate shavings or cookies or sprinkle extra chips and nuts.', '1 c. (6 oz.) semi-sweet chocolate chips', '3 (2 to 3 oz.) pkg. chocolate mousse dessert mix', '1 Tbsp. instant Espresso powder', '3/4 c. chopped pecans', '1 (8-inch) ready to fill graham cracker pie crust', '1 (8 oz.) container Cool Whip', ' chocolate shavings , leaf shaped cookies (for garnish , optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(301070, ' Defrost dessert topping. Combine all ingredients including juices from pineapple and cherries. Refrigerate. Yields 11 cups , about 14 servings. Can be made one day in advance to blend flavors , but if made two days in advance , does not hold up well.', '1 large (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '5 to 6 medium bananas , quartered and sliced', '1 (10 oz.) bottle red cherries , chopped', '1 (6 oz.) pkg. miniature marshmallows', '1 (9 oz.) container frozen dessert topping (Cool Whip , etc.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(301203, ' Mix first 4 ingredients together and freeze in a wide mouth container. Let thaw 6 hours before serving. Use plastic wide mouth jugs. Tint with food coloring. Pour ginger ale over slush before serving (128 ounces equals 1 gallon).', '3 (6 oz.) frozen lemonade', '3 (6 oz.) frozen limeade', '46 oz. pineapple juice', '46 oz. water', '2 1/2 bottles ginger ale (28 oz. bottles)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(301204, ' Mix Jell-O (flavor of Jell-O for color of punch) with boiling water in large container. Cool. Bring 4 cups of water and 4 cups of sugar to a boil in a saucepan. Cool and add to Jell-O mixture. Pour in pineapple juice and lemon juice and stir well. Pour into 2 gallon plastic milk containers and freeze. Thaw for 4 hours. Cut top off plastic milk containers and pour into large punch bowl. Slush and add 2 bottles of ginger ale to each gallon of punch.', '3 (6 oz.) pkg. Jell-O (any flavor)', '9 c. boiling water', '4 c. water', '4 c. sugar', '2 (46 oz.) cans pineapple juice', '1 (16 oz.) bottle lemon juice', '4 bottles ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(301222, ' Mix together well. Pour into well and over remainder. Cook on 80% power 10 minutes. Rotate after 5 minutes , if no turntable. Cook on High , 5 to 7 minutes. Check center for doneness. Let sit for 10 minutes.', '1 lb. lean ground meat', '1 lb. ground turkey', '1 small onion , chopped and cooked on High 4 minutes', '1 egg', '1 (8 oz.) can Spanish tomato sauce', '1 c. stale or dried in microwave bread crumbs (rye or wheat gives good flavor)', '1/2 c. water', '3 Tbsp. sweet pickle juice', '2 Tbsp. brown sugar', '2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1 Tbsp. dry mustard (2 Tbsp. regular)', ' pinch of powdered cloves', '1/4 c. catsup', '1/4 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
