(307569, ' Combine cookies and margarine (reserve 1/4 cup for topping). Press mixture onto bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 375&deg; for 5 minutes. Cool completely.', '30 chocolate cream filled cookies , crushed', '1/3 c. margarine , melted', '1 small instant vanilla pudding mix', '1 3/4 c. milk', '1 c. peanut butter', '1 (4 oz.) pkg. German sweet chocolate , chopped', '1 (12 oz.) whipped dessert topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(307614, ' Combine sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan. Add butter , lemon rind , lemon juice and egg yolks. Mix in milk and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened. Cool. Fold in sour cream and fill crust. Refrigerate at least one hour.', '1 (9-inch) pie crust , baked and cooled', '1 c. sugar', '3 Tbsp. cornstarch', '1/2 c. butter or oleo', '1 Tbsp. grated lemon rind', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '3 unbeaten egg yolks', '1 c. milk', '1 c. sour cream', ' whipped dessert topping', ' chopped walnuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(307763, ' Mix sifted , measured flour and salt. Pour oil and milk into one measuring cup. Do not stir. Add oil and milk at once to flour. Stir until mixed. Press into a smooth ball. Cut in two and flatten each half slightly. Place one half between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Roll out gently to edges of paper. Peel off top paper. Ease and fit pastry into pan. Trim and add filling. Roll top crust the same way and place over filling. Fold edges under bottom crust. Seal with fork , pressing gently. Make slits in center. Bake as directed for pie.', '2 c. all-purpose flour , sifted', '1 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. vegetable oil', '1/4 c. cold milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(307797, ' Beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar , beating to stiff peaks. Spread meringue on top and sides of each sponge cake. Place on baking sheet. Bake in very hot oven (450&deg;) for 5 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven; fill center of each cup with a scoop of ice cream. Spoon berries over ice cream. Makes 4 servings.', '2 egg whites', '1 1/2 tsp. vanilla', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '4 sponge cake dessert cups', '1 pt. strawberry ice cream', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen strawberries , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(308495, ' Reserve all juice but orange juice and mix it with pudding , then mix with other ingredients and chill.', '2 cans lite fruit cocktail', '1 can mandarin oranges', '1 can pineapple chunks', '2 bananas , chopped', '3 tsp. Tang', '1 box sugar-free vanilla jello instant pudding', '2 pkg. Equal or Sweet ''N Low', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(308725, ' Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in bowl. Drain fruit well; reserve syrups. Combine 1 cup reserved syrup and jello. Chill , stirring twice , until slightly thickened. Fold in peaches and pineapple. Fold in marshmallows. Turn into rinsed 9 x 13-inch salad pan. Chill until firm. Spread with Cheese Topping.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. lime Jell-O', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. lemon Jell-O', '2 c. boiling water', '2 (No. 303) cans sliced peaches , diced', '1 (1 lb.) can pineapple tidbits', '3/4 c. miniature marshmallows', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(309606, ' Note: This salad takes time to prepare since each layer must set until firm before the next layer is added.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. strawberry gelatin dessert', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. raspberry or black cherry gelatin dessert', '1 envelope unflavored gelatin', '1 c. sugar', '1 c. whipping cream', '2 c. dairy sour cream', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1 (15 oz.) can canned blueberries , packed in syrup or water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(309912, ' Wash the chicken wings and pat dry. In skillet , saute chicken wings in melted butter until lightly browned. Arrange in oiled baking dish. Add tomatoes with liquid and celery. In separate bowl , mix together soy sauce , vinegar and salt. Pour over chicken. Bake at 375&deg; for about 30 minutes or until tender. Serves 4. May be doubled to serve 8.', '16 chicken wings', '1 Tbsp. butter or oleo', '1/2 c. canned chopped tomatoes with liquid', '1/2 c. finely chopped celery', '1/2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1/2 Tbsp. cider vinegar', '1/2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(310498, ' Cut off tips of chicken wings , if desired. Place wings , soy sauce , sugar , five spices powder , water and garlic powder in a saucepan. Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until wings are almost done. If not using immediately , refrigerate right in the cooking liquid.', '15 chicken wings', '1/4 c. soy sauce', '1 Tbsp. sugar', '1/2 tsp. five fragrant spices powder', '1 c. water', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '1/2 tsp. seasoning salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(311526, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter , pepper sauce and vinegar; put in baking pan. Sprinkle with dry dressing mix. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with celery and Ranch dressing as dip.', '24 chicken wings/drummettes', '1/2 c. melted butter', '1/2 c. hot pepper sauce', '3 Tbsp. vinegar', '1 pkg. Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix', '1/2 tsp. paprika', ' celery sticks', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(311795, ' Place drums on rack on a foil lined baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Brush marinade generously on drums. Place in 350&deg; oven for about 1 hour or until drums are golden brown and tender , brushing frequently with the marinade.', '30 wing drums (drum portion of chicken wing)', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/4 c. soy sauce', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. sugar', '1/2 tsp. ground ginger', '5 drops Tabasco sauce', '1/4 c. spiced peach syrup', '1 tsp. garlic salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
