(346856, ' Chop the onion and saute it in the margarine until the onion is clear. Add the vinegar , lemon juice and the remains of half a squeezed lemon. Pour in the Worcestershire sauce and 2 or 3 drops of Tabasco. Sprinkle in the peppers and cumin to taste. (Start with very little , then add more as needed.) Simmer for about half an hour , then add more of the peppers , if necessary. Place the chicken on a hot grill and spoon or mop some sauce on each piece. Cook slowly , putting more sauce on the chicken each time it is turned. Remove cooked chicken from the grill and serve.', ' up to 25 pieces chicken suitable for grilling', '1/4 lb. butter or margarine', '1 medium onion', '1 small bottle Worcestershire sauce', ' juice from 6 to 8 lemons', '1/4 c. vinegar', ' red pepper', ' crushed red pepper', ' white pepper', ' black pepper', ' Tabasco sauce', ' ground cumin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
