(355852, ' Mix brown sugar , gelatin , salt and spices together in saucepan. Add eggs , milk and pumpkin; blend well. Bring to a boil over medium heat , stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Cool thoroughly. Prepare topping mix according to package directions. Fold into pumpkin mix. Spoon into pie shell. Chill until firm , 2 to 3 hours.', '1/2 c. brown sugar', '1 envelope unflavored gelatin', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 1/4 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 tsp. ginger', '1/2 tsp. nutmeg', '1/4 tsp. cloves', '2 eggs , slightly beaten', '1/2 c. milk', '1 c. cooked , mashed pumpkin', '1 envelope dessert topping mix', '1 (9-inch) graham cracker crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(356451, ' Put together in order given , beat until smooth. Let set until light and foamy. Work in enough flour so it can be handled and kneaded. Let rise , work down , pinch off what you need. (Keep the rest in refrigerator until needed.) Shape into any shape of roll you want. Put in a greased pan , let rise until double in size (about 1 hour). Bake at 400&deg;. Can be frozen.', '1 c. mashed potatoes', '1 c. shortening (Crisco)', '1 c. sugar', '1 Tbsp. salt', '1 pkg. yeast', '1 tsp. baking powder', '3 c. flour (total 7 to 8 c.)', '3 c. lukewarm potato water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(356874, ' Combine oil , sugar , yeast and warm water in large bowl. Mix well. Add 4 cups flour , eggs and salt. Mix well. Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Shape into rolls. Place in greased baking pan. Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk. Bake at 375&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.', '2 c. warm water (110~ to 115~)', '2 pkg. dry yeast', '1/2 c. oil', '3/4 c. sugar', '7 to 8 c. flour', '2 eggs', '1 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
