(396277, ' Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust. Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate. Stir pudding mixes into milk in medium saucepan. Stirring constantly , cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil. Remove from heat. Cool 5 minutes , stirring twice. Pour into crust. Place plastic wrap on surface of filling. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Garnish with Cool Whip. Store leftover pie in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.', '1/4 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 Keebler Ready-Crust chocolate flavor or graham cracker pie crust (6 oz.)', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', '2 pkg. (4 serving size) Jell-O chocolate flavor cook and serve pudding and pie filling', '3 c. milk', ' thawed Cool Whip whipped topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(396741, ' Mix all of the above well. If too thick , add 1 tablespoon milk until creamy. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.', '2 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened at room temperature', '2 small cans shrimp , drained and minced', '2 Tbsp. grated onion juice (found in spices section of market)', '1/4 c. chopped parsley', '1 tsp. m.s.g. (optional)', ' dash of salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(398596, ' Cream Crisco with sugar. Add eggs and beat until light. Add flour and salt; mix well. Add vanilla. Drop by spoonful onto an ungreased baking sheet. Put a nut or cherry half in the center. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 to 12 minutes.', '1 c. Crisco', '1 c. white sugar', '1 1/2 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '2 eggs', '1 1/2 tsp. vanilla', ' nut halves or cherry halves to decorate (I use any of these: walnuts , almonds , pecans , red and green cherries for Christmas cookies)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(399478, ' Mix jello and add sugar , juice and pineapple juice. Freeze in ice cube trays. When ready , add frozen cubes and &quot;cold&quot; ginger ale in punch bowl. Mix or stir to slush.', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. jello (strawberry , banana or orange)', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 large can pineapple juice', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '2 qt. ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(399496, ' Mix jello according to directions. To this add sugar , lemon juice and pineapple juice. Put into containers such as margarine tubs and freeze. Put in the punch bowl. Add ginger ale or 7-Up. We prefer strawberry over cherry jello.', '1 (3 oz.) box jello (cherry or strawberry)', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '1 to 2 qt. ginger ale or 7-Up', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 tall can pineapple juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
