(399965, ' Spread dessert topping on the bottom of crust. Pour milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with a wire whisk for 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or until set. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily. Store leftover pie in freezer. Makes 8 servings.', '1/3 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 1/2 c. cold milk', '1 pkg. Jell-O vanilla flavor instant pudding and pie filling', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip', '6 bars (1/4 oz. each) chocolate-covered English toffee , chopped', '1 Keebler Ready-Crust graham cracker pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(400090, ' Mix water and sugar in large container until sugar dissolves (overnight if need be). Add frozen lemonade and orange juice. Add pineapple juice. Put bananas through blender. Mix all these ingredients together and freeze. Remove from freezer; mash with potato masher to slush up. Add cold 7-Up (or Bubble-Up) , 1 bottle , or up to 5 bottles if needed.', '5 c. water', '2 c. sugar', '2 small cans lemonade (frozen)', '2 small cans orange juice (frozen)', '1 large can pineapple juice', '7 bananas', '1 bottle 7-Up or up to 5 bottles if more is needed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(400983, ' Thaw bread dough and let rise until doubled. Roll out on unfloured board into a thin rectangle. Layer with cheese and salami slices. Roll up into a long roll , pinch seams together and fold under at the ends. Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes , then at 300&deg; for 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Slice and serve. May be reheated in microwave.', '1 loaf frozen bread dough', '1 (12 oz.) pkg. beef cotti salami', '2 (6 oz.) pkg. sliced Provolone cheese', '1 egg , beaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(402382, ' Dissolve yeast in water. Let stand 5 minutes. Add 2 1/2 cups flour , oil , sugar , salt and egg. Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes. Let rest 15 minutes. Add remaining flour and knead until elastic and smooth (10 minutes). Let rise until doubled in bulk and shape into 2 large loaves or 4 dozen rolls. Bake at 350&deg; to 375&deg;. I make cinnamon rolls.', '2 pkg. dry yeast', '2 c. warm water', '1/3 c. sugar', '1/3 c. oil', '1 Tbsp. salt', '1 egg (optional)', '6 1/2 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(402391, ' ', '1 pkg. yeast', '1/4 c. melted butter', '1/2 c. warm water', '2/3 c. warm milk', '2 1/2 c. Better For Bread flour', '2 eggs (room temperature)', '3 Tbsp. sugar', '1 c. whole wheat flour', ' salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(403219, ' About 2 hours before serving , prepare lasagna noodles as label directs; drain. In medium bowl , with fork , mash tofu; stir in Romano cheese , parsley , salt , egg and cottage cheese. Preheat oven to 375&deg;. In 3-quart shallow casserole , arrange half of noodles. Spread half of tofu mixture over noodles. Arrange half zucchini. Sprinkle with half Mozzarella. Top with half spaghetti sauce. Repeat. Bake 40 minutes or until heated through. Remove from oven. Let stand 10 minutes for easier serving. Makes 8 servings.', '1/2 lb. lasagna noodles', '1/2 c. low-fat cottage cheese', '2 Tbsp. minced parsley', '1 egg', '3/4 (8 oz.) part skim Mozzarella cheese , diced', '1 (16 oz.) soft tofu , drained', '1/4 c. grated Romano cheese', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 medium zucchini , sliced thin', '1 (28 oz.) jar spaghetti sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(403452, ' Prepare cake mix according to directions on package. Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350&deg;. Cool cake. Cook pudding according to package until thickened. Cut cream cheese into hot pudding; mix until well blended. Add well drained pineapple; spread over cake. Cool thoroughly. Spread with whipped topping. Garnish with cherries and nuts. Keep refrigerated.', '1 pkg. yellow cake mix', '1 (3 1/2 oz.) pkg. vanilla pudding (not instant)', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '1 (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 pkg. dessert topping mix or 1 large Cool Whip', '1 small jar maraschino cherries', '1/2 c. chopped walnuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(404757, ' Drain pineapple well and put juice in a large bowl. Heat juice 1 to 2 minutes on high (juice should be hot but not boiling). Add and dissolve jello. Let cool. Add buttermilk and pineapple. Refrigerate until mixture starts to thicken. Fold in dessert topping and nuts. Pour into a large Pyrex dish or several small molds.', '1 (20 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '1 (6 oz.) box strawberry jello', '2 c. buttermilk', '1 (8 oz.) container dessert whipped topping', '1/2 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(405867, ' Mix all together and serve with fresh vegetables.', '1 c. mayonnaise', '1/4 tsp. curry powder', '1 tsp. tarragon vinegar', '1 tsp. horseradish', '1 tsp. grated onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(406608, ' Combine and heat ingredients; cool. Pour over wings; marinate 3 hours in refrigerator , turning wings frequently. Bake at 350&deg; for 1 1/2 hours , turning and basting. Drain. Serve hot or cold.', '3 lb. chicken wings', '1 c. soy sauce', '1 tsp. dry mustard', '1 c. brown sugar', '3/4 c. water', '1/2 c. butter', '1 dash Tabasco', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(407174, ' Add shortening to milk while milk is still warm. When milk has cooled , dissolve yeast in water and add to milk. Add sugar and salt , eggs and flour , beat well. Let rise in bowl for 20 minutes. Knead dough for 2 minutes.', '1/2 c. shortening', '2 c. milk , scalded and cooled', '5 c. sifted flour (plain)', '2 pkg. yeast', '2 eggs , well beaten', '1/2 c. lukewarm water', '1/2 c. sugar', '2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(407259, ' ', '1 (8 oz.) lemon yogurt (nonfat , Aspartame sweetened)', '2 Tbsp. lite cream cheese , softened', '1 tsp. lemon juice', '2 Tbsp. lite Cool Whip', '1 packet Equal', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(408020, ' Mix hamburger , Teri burger mix , onion and egg. Mix well. Place about two to three tablespoons of mixture to center of sheet of nori. Spread evenly in middle. Fold ends of nori. Place in pan with folds downward so nori will stick together. Place in refrigerator for about three to four hours. Coat with flour and fry in oil. Slice in several pieces.', '1 lb. hamburger', '1 pkg. Teri burger mix', '1/2 round onion , chopped', '1 egg', ' sushi nori', ' water chestnuts , chopped (optional)', ' flour (for coating)', ' oil (for frying)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(408271, ' In a blender , mix 5 bananas and lemon juice. Add orange juice and pineapple juice. Last add water and sugar. Freeze in a plastic container. Add grapefruit soda when ready to serve.', '12 oz. frozen orange juice , diluted as directed', '12 oz. frozen pineapple juice , diluted as directed', '5 bananas', '1 c. lemon juice', '6 c. water', '4 c. sugar', ' grapefruit soda', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(408272, ' Mix and dissolve jello , sugar and hot water. Add pineapple juice , lemon and cold water. Mix well. Freeze in 3 portions in plastic containers. Allow at least 2 days to freeze. When ready to serve , take 1 portion of frozen mixture and put in punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture , then use an ice pick to make a slush mixture. Repeat with another frozen mixture and ginger ale as needed.', '2 (3 oz.) boxes lime jello', '3 c. granulated sugar', '2 qt. hot water', '1 large can pineapple juice', '9 to 10 Tbsp. lemon juice', '2 qt. cold water', '4 bottles ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(408285, ' Cook 4 cups rice. Soak Kurome in water; drain when soft. Cook grated carrot , Aburage , kamaboko , Takemoto , Kurome and ajisukekogai together with Wesson oil , shoyu , sugar and sake. Set aside until rice is done. Add 1 package Tamanoi sushi rice mix to hot rice; mix all together with the cooked ingredients. Garnish with thinly sliced eggs and red and green shrimp flakes. Delicious hot or cold.', '1 carrot , grated', '2 pieces Aburage', '1 pkg. Hilo brand kamaboko (tempura round one)', '1/2 can Takemoto', '1/4 c. Wesson oil', '1/4 c. shoyu', '1/2 c. sugar', ' dash of sake', '1/2 pkg. Kurome (Marukai brand is the best)', '1 can ajisukekogai or 2 cans seasoned clams', '4 c. rice', ' fried eggs , sliced thin (for garnish)', '1 pkg. Tamanoi sushi rice mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(409013, ' In a small bowl , beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk , beat until smooth and creamy.', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '3/4 c. sifted powdered sugar', '1/2 c. peanut butter', '2 Tbsp. milk', '1 envelope dessert topping mix', '1 (8-inch) graham cracker pie shell', ' coarsely chopped peanuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(410537, ' Boil sugar and water until clear and sugar is dissolved; set aside. In blender , blend watermelon , salt , lemon juice , food coloring and lime juice. Add sugar syrup. Freeze at least 24 hours. Break into chunks and place in glasses. Pour 7-Up over chunks , blending in slush.', '3/4 c. sugar', '1/2 c. water', '2 c. seedless watermelon', '1/4 tsp. salt or less', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1 Tbsp. lime juice', '2 drops red food coloring', ' 7-Up', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(411232, ' Saute garlic , red pepper , jalapenos and green onions in the butter. Add spices , then slowly add milk and lemon juice , simmer until thickened. Add Parmesan cheese , stir until blended. Add noodles (cooked according to package instructions) and chicken breasts , serve immediately. Have the fire extinguisher near, Just kidding. It is hot and spicy though.', '1 Tbsp. butter', '1 Tbsp. chopped garlic', '1 medium red pepper , chopped', '2 jalapenos , sliced', ' egg and spinach noodles', ' grilled chicken breasts', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', '1/2 Tbsp. cajun spice', '1/2 Tbsp. ground cumin', ' juice of 1 lime', '1 c. milk', '1/4 c. chopped green onions', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(411506, ' Cream together margarine , cream cheese and sugar. Sift in flour and salt. Chill several hours or overnight. On floured board , roll dough very thin and cut with biscuit cutter. Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves on each round. Fold over and seal with fork. Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375&deg; until firm , but not browned , about 12 minutes. Sift confectioners sugar over pastries and remove from pan while warm. Store in tightly covered container.', '8 oz. cream cheese', '1 c. margarine', '1/2 c. confectioners sugar', '2 c. plain flour', '1/4 tsp. salt', ' apricot preserves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(412195, ' Fold together mayonnaise and Cool Whip. Stir in fruit juice to make consistency desired. Good on fresh fruit or jello salad. Keeps several days in the refrigerator.', '1/2 c. low-fat mayonnaise', '1/2 c. thawed Cool Whip', ' lemon juice or other fruit juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(412803, ' Mix and freeze items. Add ginger ale , Sprite or 7-Up to partially thawed mixture when ready to serve.', '1 large frozen orange juice', '1 large frozen lemonade', '1 can unsweetened pineapple juice', '1 c. sugar , dissolved in warm water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(413801, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese , pizza sauce , additional 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and green and red pepper. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted. Serve with bread sticks.', '1 (3 oz.) Philadelphia cream cheese (softened)', '1 tsp. Italian seasoning', '2 c. shredded low-moisture part-skim Mozzarella cheese', '1/2 c. pizza sauce', '2 Tbsp. each green and red pepper', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(414137, ' Dissolve cornstarch in one cup milk. In two-quart saucepan , combine the remaining milk and sugar and bring to boil over high heat , stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat , add starch , milk mixture , stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat , add starch , milk mixture , stirring constantly. Simmer 10 minutes or until mixture is thick enough to coat spoon. Pour in rosewater , stir and pour into large platter. Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate for 2 hours.', '1/2 c. cornstarch', '1 qt. cold milk', '1 c. sugar', '2 Tbsp. rosewater', ' Christmas cherry and mint leaves', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(414425, ' Spread caramel dessert topping on bottom of crust. Pour milk in a large mixing bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and Heath bars. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or until set. Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving. Garnish as desired. Store leftovers in freezer.', '1/3 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 1/2 c. cold milk', '1 pkg. (4 serving size) Jell-O vanilla instant pudding mix', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip , thawed', '6 Heath candy bars , chopped', '1 graham cracker crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(415507, ' Preheat the oven to 325&deg;. Remove the wing tips and break each wing into two pieces. Place in a shallow baking dish. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the wings. Bake for 1 hour and serve in the baking dish.', '12 chicken wings', '1/2 c. honey', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/3 c. soy sauce', ' juice of 2 fresh lemons', '1 clove garlic , minced', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(415666, ' Drain cherries; reserve juice and chop cherries. There should be 1/4 cup juice and 1/3 cup cherries. Prepare pudding mix according to package directions , using cherry juice and milk to make amount of liquid called for. Cool. Pour into cooled pastry shell. Chill.', '1 (4 oz.) jar maraschino cherries', '1 (4 oz.) pkg. regular chocolate', '1 baked 9-inch pastry shell', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping', '1/4 c. chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(416572, ' Freeze. Stir several times during freezing.', '4 or 5 oranges , juiced', '3 lemons , juiced', '1 large can pineapple juice', '5 large bananas , mashed', '1 pkg. Kool-Aid (whatever color)', '4 c. sugar', '3 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(416636, ' Drain pineapple , reserving syrup. Add water to make 1 cup and heat to a boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool. Gently stir in ginger ale and chill until partially set. Blend fruits. Fold into gelatin. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill firm. Prepare topping mix according to package. Blend in cheese and spread over gelatin. Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon of butter at 350&deg; for 10 minutes. Sprinkle on top and chill. Serves 9.', '1 (13 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. lemon jello', '1 (7 oz.) bottle ginger ale', '1 (1 lb.) can (2 c.) jellied cranberry sauce', '1 (20 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(417711, ' Crush cookies. Cream oleo , confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Mix milk , pudding mix and whipped topping dessert. Combine. Layer mixture and crushed Oreos (dirt). Make sure the last layer is the crumbled Oreo to look like dirt. Use the gummi worms as you layer mixtures. Put this in the flower pot with fake flowers in the center. Use trowel for serving. Presto. Dirt cake.', '1 large pkg. Oreo cookies', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese', '1 whipped dessert topping', '1 large instant vanilla pudding', '3/4 c. powdered sugar', '3 c. milk', '3/4 c. oleo', ' medium flower pot', ' fake flowers', ' gummi worms', ' clean trowel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(418046, ' *Choose Kool-Aid and Jell-O color according to color theme.', '2 pkg. Kool-Aid *', '3 small pkg. Jell-O *', '8 c. boiling water', '6 c. sugar', '16 oz. bottle ReaLemon', '1 large can pineapple juice', '1 gal. cold water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(419678, ' Spread dessert topping on bottom of pie crust. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars and spoon into crust. Freeze for 4 hours or until set. Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily. Garnish as desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.', '1/3 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 1/2 c. cold milk', '1 small pkg. instant vanilla pudding', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip , thawed', '6 bars (1.4 oz. each) chocolate covered English toffee , chopped', '1 prepared graham cracker pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(422105, ' Combine horseradish sauce , tomato and bacon. Place a grilled burger on each muffin half. Spoon an equal amount of horseradish sauce mixture over each patty. Cover with remaining muffin half. Makes 4 servings.', '4 grilled burgers', '1/4 c. each horseradish sauce and chopped tomato', '2 Tbsp. crumbled crisply cooked bacon', '4 English muffins , split and lightly toasted', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(423163, ' Mix Jell-O and sugar in hot water until dissolved; add pineapple juice. Stir constantly. Add water to make 1 gallon. Freeze overnight. Take out of freezer and clip with pick or knife. Add ginger ale.', '2 c. hot water', '1 large pkg. Jell-O', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '1 large can pineapple juice', '1 (2 liter) bottle ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(423531, ' Combine all ingredients and place in freezer. Stir after 8 to 12 hours. Stir occasionally. When ready to serve , add one 2 liter bottle diet 7-Up.', '1 (46 oz.) can unsweetened pineapple juice', '1 (12 oz.) can unsweetened apple juice plus 3 cans water', '1 Tbsp. almond flavoring', '1 (2 liter) 7-Up', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(423725, ' ', '2 1/2 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1 c. plus 2 Tbsp. margarine', '1 egg yolk', '2/3 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(424019, ' Mix box of jello with hot water. Add cold water and pineapple juice. Freeze. Take out 1 hour before party. Add 1 liter ginger ale when thawed enough to stir. Stir again 15 minutes before served. Makes a slush.', '1 small box jello of choice', '1 c. hot water', '3 c. cold water', '1 can pineapple juice (46 oz.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(424276, ' Cut wings in 3 pieces. Discard tips. Fry or bake until done. Melt butter. Add sauce. May add Tabasco sauce if desired. Coat wings and enjoy.', '2 1/2 lb. chicken wings', '1/2 c. butter , melted', '1/4 c. red hot sauce or more to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(425512, ' Heat oven to 350&deg;. Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle water into mixture and mix with fork. Round into a ball and divide in half. On ungreased baking sheet , pat each half into a 12 x 3-inch strip. Strips should be 3-inches apart. In medium saucepan , heat margarine and water to rolling boil. Remove from heat and quickly stir in extract and flour. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute). Remove from heat. Beat eggs and add to mixture until smooth. Spread mixture evenly over strips , covering completely.', '1/2 c. margarine , softened', '1 c. Gold Medal flour', '2 Tbsp. water', '1/2 c. margarine', '1 c. water', '1 tsp. almond extract', '1 c. flour', '3 eggs', ' Confectioners Sugar Glaze', ' chopped nuts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(425616, ' Dissolve Kool-Aid , jello and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water and pineapple juice. Freeze 4 to 6 hours until it becomes slush. Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale. Serves 20.', '1 large can pineapple juice', '1 large (46 oz.) strawberry Jell-O', '1 pkg. strawberry Kool-Aid', '2 c. boiling water', '2 c. sugar', '6 c. cold water', '2 liter ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(426098, ' Remove crusts from bread and roll out flat with rolling pin. Mix together cheese , egg yolk , 1/8 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread 1 teaspoon on each slice and roll up. Melt butter and roll breads in it , then a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place seam side down on cookie sheet. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Bake at 350&deg; for 20 minutes. Cut in half. Serve warm or cold.', '16 slices white bread', '8 oz. pkg. cream cheese', '1 egg yolk', '1/8 c. sugar', '1 tsp. vanilla', '1/4 lb. butter', '2 tsp. cinnamon', '1 c. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(426442, ' Boil 3 minutes. Cool thoroughly and add 1 large can pineapple juice and 1 large frozen orange juice (undiluted). Freeze in gallon jugs filling below the neck to allow for expansion. Remove from freezer 2 to 3 hours before using. Add 1 liter 7-Up to each recipe. Makes 40 (15 ounce) servings.', '2 small apricot Jell-O', '9 c. water', '3 c. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
