(434994, ' In small saucepan , combine skim milk and gelatin; let stand until gelatin is softened , about 1 minute. Stir over low heat about 5 minutes until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat; add cocoa , Sweet ''N Low , stirring until dissolved; stir in 1 cup evaporated skim milk and vanilla. Pour into a large bowl; refrigerate 2 hours until mixture is syrup-like consistency. In a large bowl with an electric mixer , beat remaining 1/2 cup chilled evaporated skim milk on high speed about 4 minutes until stiff peaks form. Fold into gelatin mixture. Spoon into 4 individual dessert glasses. Chill until firm , about 30 minutes.', '1 c. skim milk', '1 envelope unflavored gelatin', '1/4 c. unsweetened cocoa powder', '3 packs Sweet ''N Low sweetener', '1 c. (12 oz.) evaporated skim milk , chilled', '1 tsp. vanilla extract', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(435473, ' Stir together the soup , onion , hot sauce , nutmeg and dash of black pepper. In another bowl , put 1/2 soup mix with broccoli (thawed and drained) , seafood (example: small shrimp , scallops , crabmeat , your choice) and 1 cup cheese. Mix. Soften tortillas , covered with a damp paper towel , in microwave for 30 to 60 seconds. Place 1/3 cup of mixture in each tortilla. Roll , seam side down , in 12 x 7-inch oil sprayed pan. Stir milk into rest of soup mix. Pour over enchiladas. Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes , covered. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Let sit 10 minutes and serve.', '1 can Campbell''s Healthy Request cream of chicken soup', '1/2 c. chopped onion', ' several dashes of hot sauce', ' dash of nutmeg', '1 (10 oz.) frozen , chopped broccoli', '8 oz. (total) seafood', '1 3/4 c. low-fat shredded Monterey Jack', '8 (6-inch) corn tortillas', '1 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(436205, ' Mix together rhubarb , orange juice , sugar and honey. Simmer about 10 minutes until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in strawberries. Cover and chill. To serve , spoon fruit mixture over shells and add topping.', '4 stalks rhubarb , chopped', '1/2 c. orange juice', '2 tsp. brown sugar', '1 tsp. honey', '1/2 c. strawberries , quartered', '1 pkg. sponge cake dessert shells or 4 puff pastry shells', ' whipped topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
