(441452, ' Cut bean cake squares in half and gently pull open the center of each , making little bags. Simmer in water to cover , 20 minutes. Drain. Place chicken stock , soy sauce , sugar and a dash of monosodium glutamate in a saucepan. Bring to a boil; add the bags and simmer 15 minutes. Carefully spoon out bags; drain. Cook chicken breasts in remaining liquid for about 5 minutes. Remove. Add mushrooms to pan and cook for 15 minutes. If most of the liquid is gone , add 1/3 cup chicken stock , 1 teaspoon each of soy sauce and sugar , and a dash of monosodium glutamate. Drain mushrooms when tender. Snap ends off peas; pull side strings. Cut into small pieces. Parboil in salted water for 1 minute. Drain and rinse with cold water. Gently combine chicken , vegetables , omelet and sushi rice. Fill bags; fold over top to close. Makes 12 bags.', '6 pieces aburage (fried soybean cake)', '1 c. chicken stock', '1 Tbsp. soy sauce', '2 Tbsp. sugar', ' monosodium glutamate', '1/2 chicken breast , skinned , boned and cut into 1/4-inch squares', '2 dried mushrooms , presoaked and diced', '6 edible pod peas', '1/4 c. diced omelet', '3 c. prepared sushi rice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
