(447463, ' Let bread dough thaw completely. (Thawing in the microwave is not recommended). Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear 1 loaf into pieces and put in pan. Melt margarine. Add rest of ingredients. Mix until smooth. Pour mixture over bread dough in pan. Tear second loaf into pieces and put in pan. Let rise until doubled (about 2 hours). Bake at 350&deg; for 30 to 40 minutes until bread in center is done.', '2 loaves frozen bread dough', '1 c. brown sugar', '1/4 c. milk', '1/2 tsp. cinnamon', '1/2 c. margarine', '1 large cook vanilla pudding', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(448055, ' Mix crumbs and butter , reserving 2 tablespoons. Press on bottom of 8-inch round or square cake pan. Chill. Whip cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy. Stir in pineapple. Prepare topping acccording to package directions; fold into pineapple mixture. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Chill well. Makes 6 to 8 servings.', '1/2 c. graham cracker crumbs', '2 Tbsp. melted butter or margarine', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese , softened', '1/2 c. sifted powdered sugar', '1 (1 lb. 4 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple , well drained (2 1/2 c.)', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix (Dream Whip)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(448078, ' Combine the ingredients (bananas , lemon and orange juice) in blender. The rest , put in a large container , then mix well. Pour into Tupperware container or 1/2 gallon milk carton. Freeze. When ready to serve , set out of freezer until thawed to slush (3 hours or so , depending on weather). Add 4 quarts of ginger ale. Makes 50 servings. Can be colored with food coloring to match color scheme. Can be frozen in 4-pint container , if you choose.', '2 c. sugar', '3 c. water', '2 c. orange juice', '1/4 c. lemon juice', '5 ripe bananas', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(448611, ' Combine egg , mayonnaise , seasoning , onions and pepper; stir in bread crumbs and tuna (undrained). Put this in a pie plate; take a spoon and shape the mixture to fit like a pie shell.', '1 can lite tuna in water', '1 egg , slightly beaten', '1/2 c. mayonnaise', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. lite cheese , shredded', '1/2 tsp. dry mustard', '3 Tbsp. onions , chopped', '3 Tbsp. bell peppers , chopped', '1/2 c. dry bread crumbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(449430, ' Mash bananas , adding lemon juice. Dissolve sugar in water. Add bananas and juices to sugar water. Freeze. Two hours before serving , remove from freezer. To 2 quarts of frozen mixture , add 16 ounces ginger ale. Stir until punch is slushy. Serves 12.', '24 oz. pineapple juice', '24 oz. Hawaiian Punch', '1 (6 oz.) can frozen lemonade', '1 (6 oz.) can frozen orange juice', '4 bananas', '3 c. water', '1 1/2 c. sugar', '1 Tbsp. lemon juice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(449872, ' Pour strawberries into gelatin mold. Line Lite Twinkies around mold on top of strawberries. Place Cool Whip between and around Lite Twinkies. Cover gelatin mold and place in freezer. Thirty minutes before serving , thaw out to serve.', '1 box Lite Twinkies', '1 small container Cool Whip Lite', '1 box frozen strawberries in syrup , slightly thawed *', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(450617, ' Break chicken wings into drumettes and discard wing tips. Dip chicken into milk and roll in dry Ranch mix. Pour extra mix over pieces. Put on cookie tray and bake 15 to 20 minutes until done at 350&deg;. Serve with celery sticks and Ranch dressing.', '2 lb. chicken wings', '2 packets Hidden Valley Ranch (dry)', '1/4 c. milk', ' Ranch salad dressing (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(450758, ' Spread an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle bottom and side with graham cracker crumbs. Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container. Add cottage cheese and cream cheese; cover. Blend at medium speed about 2 minutes. Pour into a large bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan. Smooth top. Chill until set , about 4 hours. When ready to serve , remove side of pan. Top cheesecake with pie filling. Makes 8 servings.', '1 whole graham cracker , crushed or 2 Tbsp. graham cracker crumbs', '1 (4 serving size) pkg. Jell-O sugar-free lemon flavored gelatin', '2/3 c. boiling water', '1 c. low-fat cottage cheese', '8 oz. light cream cheese', '2 c. light whipped topping , thawed', '1 c. light cherry pie filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(450809, ' Mix well until sugar is dissolved. Add pineapple juice and stir. Pour into 2 clean 1/2 gallon cardboard milk containers. Close with paper clips and freeze solid. One hour before serving , remove frozen slush from freezer and place in punch bowl. Let sit until serving time. With fork , chop and scrape until well broken up. Add ginger ale. Mix and serve.', '2 pkg. unsweetened cherry Kool-Aid', '2 qt. water', '2 c. sugar', '46 oz. can pineapple juice', '4 liters ginger ale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
