(458319, ' Drain pineapple , reserving syrup. Add water to make 1 cup; heat to boil. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool. Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set. Blend fruits; fold into gelatin. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish; chill firm. Prepare topping according to package. Blend in cheese; spread over gelatin. Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon butter at 350&deg; for 10 minutes; sprinkle atop. Chill. Serves 9.', '1 (13 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 (3 oz.) pkg. lemon flavored gelatin', '1 (7 oz.) bottle ginger ale', '1 (1 lb.) can jellied cranberry sauce (2 c.)', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix', '1 (8 oz.) pkg. soft cream cheese', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
