(461666, ' Put tofu and ingredients in covered bowl or plastic bag and shake well to coat tofu thoroughly. Deep fry in olive oil. Drain and put aside.', '2 to 3 c. cooked bulgur wheat , cracked wheat , rice , spaghetti or Ramen noodles', '1 sq. tofu , diced into 1/2-inch squares', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1/8 tsp. cayenne pepper', '1 clove garlic , very finely chopped', '2 dessert spoons flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(461702, ' Blend to smooth the tofu , garlic , onion , olive oil , salt , cayenne pepper , flax seed and water.', ' tofu', ' garlic', ' onion', '1 dessert spoon olive oil', ' salt to taste', ' dash of cayenne pepper', '1/2 tsp. flax seed', '1 Tbsp. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(462467, ' Heat sugar , milk , oleo and salt together on stove to just a boil. Take off stove and cool to lukewarm. Add eggs , beaten in yeast cup (yeast dissolved in warm water). While milk mixture cools. Add together and add flour (small amounts at a time). Let raise on stove in warm place until doubled in size. Knead down; let raise again and then knead and make into shapes (bread or rolls). Let raise and bake until golden brown at 400&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes. Butter when hot.', '1/2 c. sugar', '2 c. milk', '1 stick oleo', '3 tsp. salt', '2 eggs , beaten', '2 pkg. Red Star yeast dissolved in 1/2 c. warm water', '5 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(463617, ' In small bowl , combine graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons chocolate syrup. Using a fork , mix well. Using the back of a spoon , press crumb mixture over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate; set aside. Using mixer on medium speed , beat frozen dessert until smooth. Using a spatula , spread over prepared crust. Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm , about 2 hours.', '12 graham crackers (2 1/2-inch squares) , made into crumbs', '1/4 c. plus 2 tsp. chocolate syrup , divided', '16 fluid oz. chocolate nonfat frozen dietary dessert or nonfat frozen yogurt', '2 medium bananas , peeled', '3/4 c. thawed whipped topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(464255, ' Boil water and syrup for 5 minutes. Cool slightly. Add pineapple , lemons , orange juice and bananas. Mix , freeze overnight. Take out and mash with a potato masher. Pour 3 liters ginger ale over it. Serve.', '8 c. water', '4 c. sugar', '46 oz. pineapple juice', '4 fresh lemons (juice)', '2 small frozen orange juice', '5 ripe bananas , mashed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(464466, ' Cook broccoli pieces for 7 minutes in microwave. Cook pepper pieces and onions for 5 minutes in microwave. Mix other ingredients into vegetables. Cook all (broccoli and vegetables) and other ingredients another 5 to 10 minutes to taste tenderness. Or , may bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes to taste tenderness and with rest of oven-dinner main meat dish.', '1 large bag frozen broccoli pieces', '1 red pepper , chopped', '1 yellow pepper (or green at Christmas time)', '3 stalks celery , chopped', '6 to 8 green onions , chopped', '1 can cream of celery or chicken soup', '1 c. sour cream', '1/4 tsp. Bon Monet', '1/8 tsp. dried red pepper seed', '1/2 can sliced black olives (optional)', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(465301, ' Cook macaroni , rinse and drain. In large bowl , combine all ingredients , except cheese and lettuce. Mix well. Cover , chill to blend flavors. Just before serving , cut 8 slices of cheese into small pieces. Cut 4 slices diagonally into quarters. Fold cheese pieces into salad. Serve on lettuce and top with cheese quarters. Cover and refrigerate leftovers. Serves 8.', '1 (7 oz.) pkg. or 2 c. uncooked elbow macaroni', '1 (7 oz.) can tuna fish , drained and flaked', '2 c. chopped fresh tomato (2 medium)', '1/2 c. chopped green pepper', '6 Tbsp. bottled Italian dressing', '2 Tbsp. lemon juice', '1/2 tsp. garlic salt', '12 slices cheese', '1/2 Tbsp. horseradish', '2 Tbsp. chopped parsley', ' lettuce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(465655, ' Mix well warm water , yeast and honey and set aside. Cook milk and flour and stir over low to medium heat until begins to stiffen. Mix salt , butter , honey , eggs and flour well. Add milk and flour mixture. Stir hard or beat , adding yeast mixture. Mix well. Cover and let set for 1 hour. Punch down and let rest for 15 minutes. Knife the dough and shape into loaves or rolls. Just add enough flour to the pastry sheet for shaping. No need to knead too much. Grease loaf pans. Brush loaves with butter and bake at 350&deg; for 30 to 40 minutes until browned well on top.', '1/2 c. very warm water', '2 pkg. yeast', '1 tsp. honey', '1 c. milk', '1 c. flour', '1 tsp. salt', '1 stick butter', '1/4 c. honey', '3 eggs', '2 1/2 c. flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(466597, ' Let bread rise. Roll both loaves into a rectangle about 1/2-inch thick. Brown ground meat , sausage and onions. Drain. Add other ingredients and mix well. Spread meat evenly on the dough. Roll dough starting on long side , like a jelly roll. Put roll on cookie sheet. Curve dough into a horseshoe shape. Brush with cooking oil. Cover with foil. Bake at 350&deg; for about 45 minutes. Remove foil at the end of cooking time so it will brown.', '2 loaves frozen bread', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. sausage', '1 large onion , chopped', '2 c. grated cheese', ' jalapeno pepper , chopped (to taste)', ' salt and pepper', ' mushrooms , chopped (optional)', ' green pepper , chopped (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
