(469700, ' Preheat oven to 400&deg;. Spray 12-inch square of foil with nonstick cooking spray. Place fillet in center and all other ingredients on top. Fold edges to seal.', '5 oz. fish fillet (flounder , sole , etc.)', '1/4 c. julienned carrots', '1/4 c. julienned celery', '2 Tbsp. chopped tomato', '2 Tbsp. chopped onion', '1 tsp. dry white wine', ' salt and pepper to taste', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(469792, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Mix eggs and milk and set aside. Cook broccoli with 1/8 teaspoon salt until tender; discard stalks. Cut into flowerets. Alternate broccoli and cheese in pie crust.', '4 eggs , well beaten with 1/8 tsp. salt', '1 1/2 c. milk', '10 oz. broccoli spears', '1/8 tsp. salt', '1 1/4 c. shredded sharp Cheddar cheese', '1 deep dish pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(469986, ' Line the bottom of a glass bowl with ladyfingers , then pour sherry over them. Drain fruit and place on top of ladyfingers. Make red Jell-O and pour over fruit. Refrigerate until set.', '1 packet ladyfingers', '1 c. sherry', '1 large can diced fruit', '1 packet red Jell-O', '1 packet lime Jell-O', '2 (3/4 oz.) envelopes Birds Eye dessert powder or vanilla pudding', ' whipped cream', ' maraschino cherries', ' sliced bananas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(470304, ' Mix all ingredients in ice cream bucket or large container. Store in freezer for 24 hours before serving. Scoop out about 3/4 serving per glass , filling the remainder of the glass with white soda. Garnish with a stem cherry.', '8 to 9 c. boiling water', '4 tea bags , steeped in water 5 to 10 minutes', '2 c. sugar , dissolved in tea', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen orange juice', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen lemonade', '2 c. brandy', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(470335, ' Add boiling water to gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Add juice from pineapple and beverage. Chill until medium-stiff. Whip with mixer until foamy. Gradually whip into whipped topping. Fold in pineapple. Pour into mold and chill until set. Makes approximately 8 servings. Calories: 58.', '1 pkg. lemon or lime low calorie gelatin dessert', '1 c. boiling water', '1 (8 oz.) can crushed pineapple in unsweetened pineapple juice', '1/2 (12 oz.) can citrus or lemon-lime sugar-free carbonated beverage', '4 oz. lite whipped topping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(472260, ' Mix cake mix and yeast together and set aside. Mix water and salt together in large bowl. Stir in yeast mixture and 3 cups flour. Knead about 6 minutes. Cover and let rise 1 hour. Punch down and make into 24 rolls or 2 loaves bread. Let rise and bake at 350&deg; to 375&deg; for 30 minutes or until brown.', '1 box white cake mix (Jiffy)', '1 pkg. dry yeast', '1 1/2 c. warm water', '1/2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(472348, ' Drain pineapple (save syrup). Add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling; dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid. Cool. Gently stir in ginger ale. Chill until partially set. Blend fruits; fold into gelatin and chill. Blend cheese with topping. Put on top. Toast pecans in 1 tablespoon butter. Spread on top. Chill.', '1 (13 1/2 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '2 (3 oz.) lemon Jell-O', '1 (7 oz.) ginger ale', '2 c. jellied cranberry sauce', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping or Cool Whip', '1 (8 oz.) cream cheese', '1/2 c. pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(472915, ' Drain pineapple , reserving syrup. Add water to syrup to make 2 cups; bring to boil. Add gelatin to boiling syrup and stir to dissolve. Add drained pineapple; pour into 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch dish. Cover immediately with a layer of marshmallows. Chill until gelatin is firm.', '1 (8 3/4 oz.) can crushed pineapple', '1 (3 oz.) pkg. lime-flavored gelatin', '2 c. miniature marshmallows', '1 (2 oz.) pkg. dessert topping mix', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(472986, ' Combine coconut and butter or margarine; press into 8-inch pie plate. Bake at 325&deg; until coconut is golden , about 10 minutes. Cool thoroughly. In small saucepan , dissolve coffee powder in 2 tablespoons water; add chocolate bar. Stir chocolate mixture over low heat until melted; cool. Fold in whipped dessert topping; pile into coconut crust. Chill in freezer several hours or overnight. (It will not freeze solid.)', '1 1/3 c. grated coconut', '2 Tbsp. butter or margarine , melted', '1 tsp. instant coffee powder', '1 (7 1/2 oz.) milk chocolate candy bar with almonds , broken', '4 c. frozen whipped dessert topping , thawed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(473291, ' Wash the chicken wings and pat dry. In skillet , saute chicken wings in melted butter until lightly browned. Arrange in oiled baking dish. Add tomatoes with liquid and celery. In separate bowl , mix together soy sauce , vinegar and salt. Pour over chicken. Bake at 375&deg; for about 30 minutes or until tender.', '16 chicken wings', '1 Tbsp. butter', '1/2 c. canned chopped tomatoes with liquid', '1/2 c. finely chopped celery', '1/2 Tbsp. soy sauce', '1/2 Tbsp. cider vinegar', '1/2 tsp. salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
