(477066, ' Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or until set. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be easily cut. Garnish as desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.', '1/3 c. caramel dessert topping', '1 1/2 c. cold milk', '1 (4 oz.) pkg. Jell-O vanilla instant pudding and pie filling', '1 (8 oz.) tub Cool Whip', '6 (1.4 oz.) bars chocolate-covered English toffee , chopped', '1 graham cracker ready pie crust', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(477247, ' Prepare hot roll mix per directions on box. Knead 5 minutes; let rise. Knead again and let rise 30 minutes. While bread is rising , brown sausage. Grate the cheese. Separate dough in half. Roll out 1/2; sprinkle with seasoning salt , then 1/2 sausage and 1/2 cheeses. Roll like jelly roll. Put on to greased baking sheet. Repeat with other half. Bake at 350&deg; until brown. Top with butter. Can freeze.', '1 box Pillsbury hot roll mix', '1 lb. regular sausage', '1 lb. hot sausage', ' seasoning salt', ' Cheddar cheese', ' Mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(478442, ' For crust , combine cracker crumbs and margarine. Press onto bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Place pan in the freezer while preparing sherbet mixture.', '1 c. graham cracker crumbs', '1/4 c. margarine or butter , melted', '1 (4 oz.) container frozen whipped dessert topping , thawed', '1 qt. raspberry sherbet or pineapple', '1 c. raspberries', '1 banana , finely chopped (about 1 c.)', '1/2 c. chopped pecans', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
