(539545, ' In a large cooker or pot , on medium-high heat , pour in 6 cups water. Add the peeled diced potatoes. Cook while preparing the chicken in the microwave as directed on package. Also while chicken is cooking , blend in the blender the tomatoes and picante sauce. When chicken is done , cut into cubes. Add the Ramen noodles and the sauce packages to the pot. After noodles soften , stir in chicken and tomato mix. Lower heat to simmer; heat until the potatoes are tender.', '4 pkg. Ramen noodle chicken soup', '4 Tyson grilled chicken breasts', '1/4 c. Pace chunky picante sauce', '6 potatoes , diced', '1 can tomatoes', '6 c. water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(539997, ' Drain and reserve juice from both fruits. Mix together fruit juices , Tang and pudding mix. Mix until smooth; add fruit and chill. Add bananas just before serving. If too thick , thin with orange juice.', '2 cans chunky lite mixed fruit', '1 can chunky lite pineapple chunks', '2 Tbsp. sugar-free Tang', '1 small pkg. sugar-free vanilla pudding mix', '2 bananas , sliced', ' orange juice (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(540359, ' Melt sugar in boiling water (to make syrup) and let cool. In large bowl , combine syrup and all ingredients except soda pop. Mix well and freeze. (Ziploc freezer bags work well.) When ready to serve , place frozen mixture in punch bowl and pour strawberry soda pop over to break it up. Will be ready to serve in 20 to 30 minutes. Drowns 25 , serves 30 to 50.', '2 c. sugar', '6 c. water', '2 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen strawberries', '1 large can frozen lemonade', '1 large can frozen orange juice', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '5 mashed bananas', '2 (2 liter) bottles strawberry soda pop', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
