(547497, ' Bring 1 1/2 cups of the cranberry juice to boil in small saucepan. Stir into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups juice and milk. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze 1 1/2 hours or until frozen edges. Spoon mixture into food processor container; cover. Process until smooth. Pour into bowl; cover. Freeze for 3 hours or until firm. Spoon or scoop into dessert dishes. Store leftover sorbet in freezer. Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 8 servings.', '3 c. low calorie cranberry juice cocktail , divided', '1 (4 serving size) pkg. Jell-O brand grape flavored sugar-free , low calorie gelatin dessert', '1 c. cold evaporated skim milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(547862, ' Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Trim crusts from bread and cut each slice in half. Lay strip of bacon and place 2 slices of bread vertically , covering almost all the strip. Sprinkle with cheese. Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Bake in broiler pan for 20 minutes , turning once. Remove toothpicks and cut in half. Makes approximately 100 hors d''oeuvres.', '1 large loaf thin sliced sandwich bread', '1 lb. thin sliced ham', ' grated American cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
