(688064, ' In a large bowl , mix together all ingredients except flour. Let stand until yeast begins to work. Stir in thoroughly , a little at a time , the flour. Cover and allow dough to rise until double. After second rising , turn dough onto floured board or counter top and knead until all air bubbles are gone. Form dough into bread or rolls. Cover with a cloth and let rise until almost double. Bake rolls at 425&deg; , loaves of bread at 400&deg;. Brush tops of rolls with melted margarine as they come from the oven. Cover either bread or rolls with a cloth until cool. Makes 3 to 4 dozen rolls or 2 loaves of bread.', '1 c. milk , room temperature', '1 1/2 c. hot water (about 140~)', '3/4 c. shortening', '1/2 c. sugar', '1 tsp. salt', ' pinch of soda', '2 envelopes dry yeast', '6 to 7 c. all-purpose flour', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
