(922023, ' Cook pasta as directed and set aside. Slice/chop zucchini , carrots and broccoli. Chop artichoke hearts if whole. Cut cheese into bite size pieces or crumble. Blanch zucchini , carrots and broccoli. Put into boiling water for 5 seconds; remove and rinse with cold water until cool. Put everything into a large bowl with the pasta and add pesto; mix well to coat everything. Best when served cold. Enjoy,', '12 oz. bag pasta &quot;garden swirls&quot; or other shapes (trees for Christmas , hearts , etc.)', '1 large zucchini', '2 medium carrots', ' approximately 3 1/2 c. broccoli', ' Feta cheese', '1 small jar artichoke hearts (marinated or not , depending on your taste)', '1 small jar capers', ' Contadina pesto with sundried tomatoes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(922101, ' Mix all ingredients together in medium bowl. Barbecue chicken wings until crispy and well done. Place chicken wings in bowl with sauce and mix until chicken is coated. Place back on grill for 5 minutes , then serve.', '1 c. barbecue sauce', '3 cloves garlic , minced', '4 dashes of hot sauce', '1/2 c. honey', '1 Tbsp. dill', '1/2 c. hot bean paste or 1/4 c. hot red pepper', '2 to 3 lb. chicken wings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(922476, ' Dissolve all ingredients in hot water; add to 1 large unsweetened pineapple juice in a gallon container; finish with water. Freeze to slush and serve with vanilla ice milk.', '2 small pkg. Kool-Aid', '1 small box Jell-O', '2 c. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(922527, ' Drain the fruit and combine with the cottage cheese and Cool Whip in a medium mixing bowl. Sprinkle the jello over the top and stir to mix well. Add pecans , if desired. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.', '1 (17 oz.) can lite fruit cocktail , drained', '1 (8 oz.) can lite crushed pineapple , drained', '1 (12 oz.) carton cottage cheese', '1 c. lite Cool Whip', '1 small box sugar-free jello (any flavor)', '1/3 c. chopped pecans (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(922547, ' Heat oven to 400&deg;. Combine bread crumbs , flour , onion salt , paprika , poultry seasoning , garlic powder , thyme and pepper. Stir with fork to distribute. Stir until well blended. Moisten chicken with water. Roll in coating mixture. Place in single layer in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan or other large pan. Sprinkle any remaining crumb mixture over chicken. Bake at 400&deg; until no longer pink in center. Makes 8 servings.', '3/4 c. fine dry bread crumbs', '1/4 c. all-purpose flour', '1 tsp. paprika', '1 tsp. poultry seasoning', '1/2 tsp. garlic powder', '4 whole chicken breasts , skinned and split', '1/2 tsp. dried thyme leaves', '1/4 tsp. pepper', '1 Tbsp. + 1 1/2 tsp. oil', '1 tsp. onion salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(922790, ' Bring to boil water and sugar to make a simple syrup. Cool. Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze in 3 half gallon milk cartons. When ready to serve , mix with ginger ale in punch bowl (1 milk carton of punch mixture to 2 or 3 tall bottles ginger ale). Can be made ahead and used as needed.', '5 ripe bananas', '1 (12 oz.) can frozen lemonade', '2 (12 oz.) cans frozen orange juice', '1 (46 oz.) can pineapple juice', '6 c. water', ' ginger ale', '4 c. sugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(923322, ' Drain and dice crab. Chop celery and green onions. Mix in cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add salt , pepper and lemon juice. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.', '8 oz. cream cheese', '3/4 c. mayonnaise', '1/2 bunch green onions', '1 to 2 stalks chopped celery', ' dash of salt and pepper', '1 tsp. lemon juice', '1 lb. crab', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(923391, ' Combine all ingredients except chicken and mix well; allow flavors to blend 30 minutes. Serve with grilled chicken.', '2 c. Washington apples , halved , cored and chopped', '3/4 c. chopped Anaheim chili pepper', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '1/4 c. lime juice', ' salt and pepper to taste', ' Grilled Chicken (recipe follows)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(924667, ' Combine oil , soy sauce and seasoning in a large , self-closing plastic bag or glass dish. Add steak and refrigerate for 1 hour.', '1/2 c. olive oil', '1/4 c. soy sauce', '4 tsp. McCormick/Schilling Grill Mates Montreal Steak Seasoning', '1 (2 lb.) sirloin or strip steak', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(925422, ' Place seasoning mix in heavy plastic bag. Add a few chicken pieces. Shake until well coated. Repeat to coat all pieces. Place in lightly greased baking pan. Bake at 375&deg; for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Serve hot with salsa for dipping.', '1 (1 1/4 oz.) pkg. Ortega taco seasoning mix', '12 chicken wings , split with tips removed (about 2 lb.)', '1/2 c. Ortega (mild , medium or hot , thick and chunky salsa)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(926134, ' In a bowl , mix flour and salt; add oil and milk all at once. Stir until well mixed. Press into a smooth ball; flatten slightly. Place dough between 2 (12-inch) square sheets of waxed paper. (Dampen counter top slightly to prevent slipping.) Roll out pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate. Peel off top paper. Place the dough , paper-side up in the pie plate. Gently peel off the paper , easing and fitting the pastry into the plate.', '1 1/3 c. all-purpose flour', '1/2 tsp. salt (optional)', '1/3 c. oil', '1/4 c. cold milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(927665, ' Cut wing in half at joint. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. In deep fryer , place oil and heat to high temperature. Add half the wings and cook (about 10 minutes). Stir occasionally. When brown and crisp , remove and drain. Repeat until all wings are cooked. Melt butter in saucepan. Add hot sauce and vinegar. Pour over cooked wings. Serve with Bleu cheese dressing and celery.', '24 broiler-fryer chicken wings', '1 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper', '4 c. vegetable oil', '4 Tbsp. butter', '1 tsp. white vinegar', '4 Tbsp. bottled red hot sauce', ' celery', ' Bleu cheese dressing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(929774, ' Stir all ingredients together in mixing bowl until mixed thoroughly. Roll balls of dough (the size of walnuts) until smooth. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten tops of balls with the bottom of a glass. Decorate with pecans , sprinkles , colored sugar , Hershey''s Kisses , etc. Bake at 350&deg; for 10 to 12 minutes , until lightly browned on bottom. Cookies should be soft. Place on wax paper to cool. Yield: 12 to 20 cookies.', '1 small (4 oz.) box instant pudding mix (any flavor for color or taste; pistachio is great for Christmas)', '1 c. Bisquick', '1/4 c. vegetable oil', '1 egg , beaten', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(930144, ' In small saucepan over low heat , melt margarine. Remove from heat; stir in sugar , cocoa and corn syrup. Add evaporated skim milk. Cook over low heat , stirring constantly , just until mixture begins to boil and is smooth. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Cool slightly. Spoon 1 tablespoon warm sauce over 1/2 cup vanilla ice milk for each serving. Makes 3/4 cup sauce.', '2 Tbsp. regular margarine', '1/4 c. plus 2 Tbsp. sugar', '2 Tbsp. Hershey''s cocoa', '2 Tbsp. light corn syrup', '1/4 c. evaporated skim milk', '1 tsp. vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(930769, ' Mix first 7 ingredients. Pour over chicken wings. Refrigerate overnight , covered. Drain well. Sprinkle with lemon pepper. Bake at 325&deg; for 1 1/2 hours , until dark and chewy.', '1 c. Kikkoman soy sauce', '3 tsp. sugar', '1/4 c. dry vermouth', '2 cloves garlic', '1/4 c. vegetable oil', '1 tsp. powdered ginger', ' lemon pepper', '5 lb. chicken wings', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(930885, ' In a glass or ceramic bowl , mix together vinegar , oil , garlic , parsley , oregano , sage , salt , pepper flakes and onion slices. Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel. Toss mushrooms with marinade. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours , tossing mushrooms occasionally.', '1/2 c. cider vinegar', '1 c. olive oil', '3 cloves garlic , minced', '2 Tbsp. fresh minced parsley', '1/2 tsp. dried oregano', '1/4 tsp. dried sage', '1/4 tsp. salt', '1/4 tsp. dried hot pepper flakes', '1 medium-sized red onion , sliced', '2 lb. large mushrooms , stems trimmed', ' canola oil for brushing grill rack', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(932438, ' Season steak to taste with garlic powder , pepper and seasoned salt. Grill to desired doneness. Chill in fridge and trim. Slice thinly across grain into strips. Combine salad dressing mix , mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well. Chill. Toss steak with enough dressing to coat. Add tomatoes and mushrooms.', '1 1/2 lb. grilled sirloin', ' garlic powder', ' pepper', ' seasoned salt', '1 pkg. Ranch salad dressing mix', '1 c. mayonnaise', '1 c. sour cream', '1 pt. cherry tomatoes', '4 oz. fresh mushrooms', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(933318, ' Mix Cool Whip and yogurt. Put in pie crusts and top with fresh strawberries.', '2 graham cracker pie crusts', '1 (12 oz.) Cool Whip', '3 (8 oz.) strawberry fat-free yogurt', '1 pt. fresh strawberries', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(933779, ' Combine ham , beef , pork , bread crumbs , egg and tomato puree. Form into a loaf pan. Steam for 1 hour and bake in a 350&deg; oven for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with tomato sauce or grilled pineapple slices. Makes 16 portions.', '1 lb. ground smoked ham', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 lb. ground pork', '1 c. bread crumbs', '1 egg', '1 (8 oz.) can tomato puree or juice', ' tomato sauce or grilled pineapple slices (for garnish)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(936281, ' Mix ingredients. Chill dough 3 hours or overnight. Roll out very thin. Cut into 1-inch strips 3 to 5 inches long. Cut slit in center. Pull one end of dough through slit. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350&deg;. Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.', '2 sticks oleo', '2 Tbsp. sour cream', '1 pkg. (8 oz.) cream cheese', '2 1/2 c. flour', '1/2 tsp. vanilla', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
