(940889, ' Preheat oven to 325&deg;. Remove wing tips and break each wing into 2 pieces. Place in a shallow baking dish. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the wings. Bake for 1 hour.', '12 chicken wings', '1/2 c. honey', '2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce', '1/3 c. soy sauce', '1 clove garlic , minced', ' juice of 2 lemons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(941326, ' Combine yeast and water. Let stand until yeast is dissolved. Add sugar , salt and shortening and blend. Stir in flour and mix. Make into a round ball and put in greased large pan or bowl. Let raise three times , kneading each time. Divide dough; shape into rolls or loaves. Let rise double , about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake bread at 400&deg; for 30 to 35 minutes. Bake rolls at 350&deg; for 15 to 20 minutes.', '6 c. lukewarm water', '2 yeast cakes or pkg.', '4 Tbsp. sugar', '1 Tbsp. salt', '1/4 c. shortening', '12 c. sifted flour (approximately)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
