(992632, ' Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl. Pour oil and milk into measuring cup , but do not stir. Then pour this all at once into flour. Stir lightly until mixed. Divide dough in half. Place one half between 2 sheets of waxed paper , 12-inches square and roll out gently until circle reaches edges of paper. Peel off top paper and place pastry , paper side up , in pie pan. Peel off top paper. If you wet the counter you are rolling the pastry on , the paper will not slip. Makes enough for 2 pie shells or one 2-crust pie.', '2 c. flour', '1 1/2 tsp. salt', '1/2 c. oil', '1/4 c. milk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
